<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="MAT" stage="Rev" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:38:51Z" when="2009-10-02 03:38:51Z" stage="Draft">Initial draft by Pdt. Drs. Max Jacob &amp; Bob Jacob, Team check (June Jacob, Mus Zacharias, Hans Ndoen) August 2003, exegetical check in Darwin (June, Mus, Hans, Barbara) Sept 2003, UNS check by Mus begun 19 Sept 03 in Kupang. 24 Sept: UNS check changes entered through 5:42. Consultant checked by Marge Crofts in Kupang with June, Mus and Hans, October 2003; Corrections reviewed and entered by Chuck, Nov 2003, questions arising discussed with Marge and Barbara 25 Nov 2003; read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:36:41Z" when="2014-02-24 10:36:41Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 6-14 October 2003 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved, (A+). Report: CnRepKMmatthew.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-06 06:56:13Z" when="2015-01-06 06:56:13Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read through for mini-Bible with Chuck, Helena Aplugi (Lena), and Rina 6 Jan 2015. BT cleaned up significantly.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Mateos</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae<bt>Lord Yesus' Good Story</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">iko<bt>according to</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Mateos<bt>Mateos</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung daftar nene-moyang<bt>The Lord Yesus' ancestor list</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 3:23-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-2" />Ini buku carita so'al Yesus Kristus, itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang. Dia tu, raja Daud pung turunan deng ba'i Abraham pung turunan.<bt>This book narrates about Yesus Kristus, that Person whom *God promised beforehand from long ago to send. He is king Daud's descendant and grandfather/forefather Abraham's descendant.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Mulai dari ba'i Abraham sampe raja Daud ada 14 turunan. Dia pung daftar nene-moyang dong, bagini:<bt>Beginning from forefather Abraham until king Daud there are 14 descendants. It's list of ancestors are like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Abraham barana sang Isak,<bt>Abraham gave birth [as males can] to Isak,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Isak barana sang Yakob,<bt>Isak gave birth to Yakob,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yakob barana sang Yahuda deng dia pung adi-kaka dong,<bt>Yakob gave birth to Yahuda and his younger-elder siblings, [NOTE: natural RL order.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Yahuda barana sang Peres deng Sera (dong pung mama, nama Tamar),<bt>Yahuda gave birth to Peres and Sera (their mother, was named Tamar),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Peres barana sang Herson,<bt>Peres gave birth to Herson,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Herson barana sang Ram,<bt>Herson gave birth to Ram,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Ram barana sang Aminadab,<bt>Ram gave birth to Aminadab,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Aminadab barana sang Nahason,<bt>Aminadab gave birth to Nahason,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nahason barana sang Salmon,<bt>Nahason gave birth to Salmon,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />Salmon barana sang Boas (dia pung mama, nama Rahab),<bt>Salmon gave birth to Boas (his mother, was named Rahab),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Boas barana sang Obet (dia pung mama, nama Rut),<bt>Boas gave birth to Obet (his mother, was named Rut),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Obet barana sang Isai,<bt>Obet gave birth to Isai,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6a" />Isai barana sang Daud.<bt>Isai gave birth to Daud.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6b-11" />Dari Daud sampe itu waktu yang bangsa Isra'el kaná buang pi Babel, ada 14 turunan lai, andia:<bt>From Daud until that time when the Israel people/nation was thrown out/exiled to Babel, there were 14 more descendants, that is:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) combined verses, structured like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** (2009) combined verses, structured like CEV</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Daud barana sang Soleman (dia pung mama tu, dolu Uria pung bini).<bt>Daud gave birth to Soleman (his mother, was previously/formerly Uria's wife).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Soleman barana sang Rehabeam,<bt>Soleman gave birth to Rehabeam,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Rehabeam barana sang Abia,<bt>Rehabeam gave birth to Abia,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Abia barana sang Asaf,<bt>Abia gave birth to Asaf,</bt><note reference="1:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng paling bae, tulis <span class="Italic">Asaf</span>. Ada tulisan saparu lai yang tulis bilang, <span class="Italic">Asa.</span> Ini orang, sama deng orang yang muncul di <span class="Italic">1 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda</span> 3:10.<bt>The oldest and the best Yunani language writings write <span class="Italic">Asaf</span>. There are some other writings that write, <span class="Italic">Asa.</span> This person is the same as the one who appears in 1 <span class="Italic">Chron. </span>3:10. [NOTE: on Asaf vs. Asa, see Carson, AGNT, NRSV, NLT. But TB writes Asa.]</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Asaf barana sang Yosafat,<bt>Asaf gave birth to Yosafat,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** structure and ftn location fixed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** structure and ftn location fixed (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yosafat barana sang Yoram,<bt>Yosafat gave birth to Yoram,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yoram barana sang Usia,<bt>Yoram gave birth to Usia,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Usia barana sang Yotam,<bt>Usia gave birth to Yotam,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yotam barana sang Ahas,<bt>Yotam gave birth to Ahas,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ahas barana sang Heskia,<bt>Ahas gave birth to Heskia,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Heskia barana sang Manase,<bt>Heskia gave birth to Manase,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Manase barana sang Amos,<bt>Manase gave birth to Amos,</bt><note reference="1:10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu tulis <span class="Italic">Amos,</span> deng saparu lai tulis <span class="Italic">Amon</span>.<bt>Some Yunani language writings write <span class="Italic">Amos,</span> and some others write <span class="Italic">Amon.</span> [NOTE: on Amos vs. Amon, see Carson, AGNT, NRSV, NLT. But TB writes Amon.]</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Amos barana sang Yosias,<bt>Amos gave birth to Yosias,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yosias barana sang Yekonya deng dia pung adi dong waktu dong kaná buang pi Babel.<bt>Yosias gave birth to Yekonya and his younger siblings when they were thrown/exiled to Babel.</bt><note reference="1:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 24:14-15, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 36:10, Yeremia 27:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12-16" />Waktu dong kaná buang pi Babel sampe di Yesus, ada 14 turunan lai, andia:<bt>When they were thown/exiled to Babel until Yesus, there were again 14 descendants, that is:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** verses bridged like CEV (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** verses bridged like CEV (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yekonya barana sang Saltiel,<bt>Yekonya gave birth to Saltiel, [EXEG: TH, TN and TRT note this follows the LXX here, not the Hebrew; if one follows the Heb, Zerubbabel is actually the grandson of Shealtiel (Pedaiah was the father); although CONNOT says he was probably the nephew of Shealtiel. AGNT, NRSV, TB, TH, TN use ‘Jechoniah’ here. NLT, CEV and Morris use ‘Jehoiachin’ without comment. CONNOT says Jechoniah = Jehoiachin without additional discussion. We follow TB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) this link restored, note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** (2009) this link restored, note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Saltiel barana sang Serubabel,<bt>Saltiel gave birth to Serubabel,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Serubabel barana sang Abihut,<bt>Serubabel gave birth to Abihut,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Abihut barana sang Elyakim,<bt>Abihut gave birth to Elyakim,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Elyakim barana sang Asor,<bt>Elyakim gave birth to Asor,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Asor barana sang Sadok,<bt>Asor gave birth to Sadok,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sadok barana sang Akim,<bt>Sadok gave birth to Akim,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Akim barana sang Eliut,<bt>Akim gave birth to Eliut,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Eliut barana sang Eliasar,<bt>Eliut gave birth to Elieser,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Eliasar barana sang Matan,<bt>Eliasar gave birth to Matan,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Matan barana sang Yakob,<bt>Matan gave birth to Jakob,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">ais Yakob barana sang Yusuf.<bt>then Yakob gave birth to Yusuf.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yusuf tu, kawin deng Maria. Maria tu, yang barana sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>That Yusuf, married Maria who gave birth to Yesus Kristus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Jadi mulai dari Abraham sampe Daud ada 14 turunan; dari Daud sampe dong kaná buang pi Babel ada 14 turunan; deng dari waktu kaná buang pi Babel sampe barana sang Kristus, ada 14 turunan.<bt>So (consequently), from Abraham until Daud there were 14 descendants; from Daud until they were thrown out/exiled to Babel there were 14 descendants, and from when they were thrown out to Babel until giving birth to Kristus, there were 14 descendants.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** paragraph added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** paragraph added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Maria barana sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Maria gives birth to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 2:1-7)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Maria barana sang Yesus tu, dia pung carita bagini:<bt>Maria giving birth to Yesus, its/the story is like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Maria su batunangan deng Yusuf. Dong dua balóm parná tidor bakumpul sama ke laki-bini, ma tau-tau te, Maria su dudu parú dari Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi.<bt>Maria was engaged with Yusuf. The two of them had not yet slept together as husband-wife, but it became apparent that Maria was pregnant from the *Holy Spirit (God's Spirit who is Clean/Holy).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batunangan = engaged; dudu paru ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">batunangan = engaged; dudu paru = pregnant ; See NLT "while she was still a virgin, she became pregnant by the Holy Spirit. tau-tau = ternyata; te = bahwa (realis compl) ??</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 1:27</note><v n="19" />Waktu Yusuf dapa tau bagitu ju, dia mau bekin putus dong dua pung hubungan. Ma dia sonde mau bekin malu sang Maria di muka orang banya, tagal dia pung hati barisi. Andia ko dia mau bekin putus deng diam-diam sa.<bt>When Yusuf got to know like that, then he wanted to sever their relationship. But he did not want to embarass Maria in front of many people, because his liver was clean/holy [=he was righteous]. That's why he want to just sever quietly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais, waktu dia masi bapikir pi-datang, satu malam ju, dia mimpi. Dalam itu mimpi, dia dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga datang kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;We, Yusuf! Lu ni, raja Daud pung turunan. Lu jang ragu kawin ame sang Maria. Te itu Ana yang ada dalam dia pung parú tu, itu Tuhan pung Roh yang bekin.<bt>And/then one night, when he was still thinking going-coming (=pondering), then he dreamed. In that dream, he saw God's underling from heaven (*angel) come to tell him saying, &lt;&lt;We, [+get attention] Yusuf! You-sg here, are king Daud's descendant. You don't be anxious to marry with Maria. Cuz (elaboration) that Child which is in her stomach/belly there, it is God's Spirit who did/made it. [NOTE to daughter translations: Morris, TRT, TN all agree this is not fear of physical danger, but of social danger, so in these lgs, “don't be embarrassed to marry Mary...” might be an acceptable alternative (suggested by Dhao team).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pikir pi datang = all about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">pikir pi datang = all about it, in detail, over &amp; over ; ragu (BI?) ; grogi = gugup ?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais satu malam, waktu dia masi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Ais satu malam, waktu dia masi bapikir pi-datang, ju dia mimpi.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Nanti Maria barana satu ana laki-laki. Ais lu musti kasi nama sang dia, <span class="Italic">Yesus,</span> te Dia yang nanti kasi salamat sang Tuhan Allah pung orang dari dong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later Maria will give birth to a male child. Then you must name him, &lt;Yesus&gt;, cuz (elaboration) He is the one who will later *save/rescue God's people from their wrongs/*sins.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi salamat = from drowning, protect"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">kasi salamat = from drowning, protect from attack or murder</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Nama <span class="Italic">Yesus</span> pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan kasi salamat orang&gt;&gt;.<bt>The name <span class="Italic">Yesus</span> means 'The Lord saves people.'</bt></note><note reference="1:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 1:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ini hal nanti jadi bagitu, tagal Tuhan Allah su kasi tau memang dari dolu. Dia parná pake Dia pung jubir Yesaya ko tulis bilang,<bt>This thing later happened like that, because God has told it beforehand from long ago. He had used his *prophet (spokesperson) Yesaya to write saying, [EXEG: The use of the Kupang /nanti/ is ambiguous: 1) this will happen; 2) this (salvation) happened later (after the natural gap of time in the pregnancy-delivery-travel to Bethlehem-birth-crucifixion-resurrection). Without /nanti/ is also acceptable.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="23" />&lt;&lt;Bosong dengar, ó! Nanti ada satu nona yang masi parawan,<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl listen up! Later there will be a maiden who is still a virgin, [NOTE to daughter translations: parawan is mesolectal. You may have to unpack the meaning “who has never slept together with a man”.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tau-tau te dia su dudu parú.<bt>it will become apparent (contrary to expectation) that she is pregnant.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais dia barana satu Ana laki-laki.<bt>Then she will give birth to a male Child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong ju kasi nama sang Dia, <span class="Italic">Imanuel</span>.&gt;&gt;<bt>They will name Him, <span class="Italic">Imanuel</span>.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">(Dalam bahasa Ibrani, &lt;Imanuel&gt; pung arti:<bt>(In the Hebrew language, ‘Imanuel’ means:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan Allah ada sama-sama deng kotong.)<bt>God is together with us-inc.)</bt><note reference="1:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 7:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Yusuf mimpi abis, ju dia bangun. Tarús dia iko memang Tuhan Allah pung pasán tu. Dia ame sang Maria jadi dia pung bini,<bt>[When] Yusuf finished dreaming, then he got/woke up. Next he immediately followed that message/instructions of God's. He took Maria to become his wife,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mimpi abis bagitu, Yusuf..."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Mimpi abis bagitu, Yusuf...</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />ma dia sonde tidor bakumpul sama ke laki-bini sampe Maria su barana abis itu Ana. Barana abis ju, Yusuf kasi nama itu Ana, <span class="Italic">Yesus.</span><bt>but he did not sleep together with her as husband-wife until Maria had given birth to that Child. After giving birth, Yusuf named that Child, <span class="Italic">Yesus.</span> [NOTE to daughter translations: TB uses /bersetubuh/ Avoid problem of saying in 24 he took her as wife, then in 25 only they were not together as husband-wife until the birth, which ambiguously can mean they didn't live in the same house, at odds with 24. So “sleep together” is important here, and more refined than the TB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 2:21</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang pintar lia bintang, datang lia sang Yesus<bt>People who are skilled in looking at stars come to see Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yesus lahir di kampong Betlehem di propinsi Yudea, raja Herodes ada pegang parenta. Itu waktu, ada barapa orang datang di kota Yerusalem dari tampa jao di sablá matahari nae. Dong tu, orang yang pintar lia bintang.<bt>When Yesus was born in Betlehem village in Yudea province, king Herodes was holding rule/authority. At that time, several people came to Yerusalem city from a far place on the east side. They were people who are skilled in looking at stars.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Raja H ada pegang parenta,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Waktu Raja H ada pegang parenta, Y lahir di satu kampong nama B di prop Y. Itu waktu ada barapa orang pintar lia bintang yang jalan dari dong pung tampa jao di sabla timur. Dong datang pi Yerusalem ais</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Waktu dong sampe di Yerusalem, dong batanya pi-datang bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang Yahudi pung raja yang baru lahir tu, ada di mana, é? Botong su dapa lia satu bintang di sablá matahari nae, yang kasi tanda bilang, Dia su lahir. Andia ko botong datang ko mau sémba sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>When they arrived in Yerusalem, they asked all over the place saying, &lt;&lt;That king of the Jewish people who was just born, where is he, é? We-inc have seen a star on the east side, which gave a signal saying He was born. That's why we come in order to worship Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="3" />Waktu raja Herodes dengar dong pung omong bagitu, ju dia pung hati tar enak. Andia ko samua orang di Yerusalem dong ju rasa bagitu.<bt>When king Herodes hear what they were saying like that, then his liver was not pleasant (=he was upset). That is why all the Yerusalem people also felt like that. [NOTE to daughter translations: TB missed the meaning of the Gk here. Herod was stressed out, not surprised.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais ju raja Herodes kumpul ame kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng guru agama dong samua, ko dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba bosong kasi tau sang beta dolo! Itu Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang tu, Dia mau lahir di mana, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then king Herodes gathered together all the *chief priests (bosses of the Yahudi *priests) and the religious teachers (*scribes), in order that he ask them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl try and tell me [mild imperative]! That Kristus, whom God promised, He is going to be born where, é?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja. Dia lahir di kampong Betlehem, di propinsi Yudea. Te Tuhan pung jubir Mika su tulis memang dari dolu bagini:<bt>Then they answered saying, &lt;&lt;Father king. He (will) be born In the village of Betlehem, in Yudea province. Cuz (elaboration) the Lord's *spokesperson Mika has written in.advance from long ago like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />&lt;We, bosong orang Betlehem, di propinsi Yudea sana.<bt>&lt;We, [+get attention] you-pl Betlehem people, in Yudea province over.there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong jang kira, bosong pung kampong tu,<bt>You don't think, that village of yours,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">cuma satu kampong kici yang sonde ada pung arti.<bt>is merely a small village which has no meaning.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te nanti ada satu orang bésar yang datang dari sana.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later there will be a big/ important person who comes from there. [NOTE to daughter translations: some MTTs want to change 'come' to 'appear'. But be careful. 1) The Gk is 'come'. 2) 'appear' can mean 'appear miraculously' (as prophets are expected to do. But this latter is outside both the OT and the NT context and intent.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Nanti Dia jadi gambala kasi Beta pung orang Isra'el dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Later He will become a shepherd for My Israel people.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** close quotes added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** close quotes added (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mika 5:1; 2 Samuel 5:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dengar abis bagitu ju, raja Herodes pange diam-diam itu orang yang pintar lia bintang dong. Ju dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kapan bosong dapa lia itu bintang muncul di langit?&gt;&gt; Ju dong kasi tau sang dia.<bt>After hearing like that, then king Herodes silently/secretly called those people who were skilled in looking at stars. Then he asked them saying, &lt;&lt;When did you-pl see that star appear in the sky?&gt;&gt; So they told him.</bt><v n="8" />Ais Dia kirim sang dong pi Betlehem. Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pi ko cari kuliling itu Ana di sana. Kalo bosong su katumu sang Dia, na, bale datang ko kasi tau sang beta. Te beta ju mau pi sémba sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He sent them to go to Betlehem. He told saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl go look all around for that Child there. If/when you find Him, na, return back to tell me. Cuz (elaboration) I also want to go worship Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju dia kasi tau sang dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Ju dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pi cari itu Ana di satu kampung, dia pung nama B. ,,,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00295C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Orang yang pintar kasi dong pung hadia<bt>Knowledgable men give their gifts</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dengar abis raja pung omong, ju dong pi. Tau-tau te, dong dapa lia lai itu bintang yang dolu dong su parná lia di sablá matahari nae tu. Itu bintang muncul di dong pung muka, ais dia jalan sampe barenti pas di atas itu Ana pung tampa tenga.<bt>After hearing the king's speaking, then they went. It became apparent/contrary to expectation, they saw that aforementioned star which previously they had seen on the east side. That star appeared in front of them, and.then it travelled/went until stopping exactly over that Child's staying/living place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Lia bagitu ju, dong sanáng mau mati.<bt>Seeing like that, they were very happy.</bt><v n="11" />Ais dong maso pi dalam itu ruma, ju dong dapa lia itu Ana deng Dia pung mama Maria. Ju dong tikam lutut ko sémba sang Dia. Ais dong buka dong pung bungkusan hadia barang-barang mahal, ko kasi pi itu Ana. Dong kasi mas, kamanyán, deng dara kayu wangi.<bt>Then2 they entered that house, and they saw that Child with His mama Maria. Then they knelt to worship Him. Then2 they opened their bundles of expensive gifts, to give to that Child. They gave gold, and incense and fragrant sap.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Sonde lama, ju dong dapa mimpi dari Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang kambali pi raja Herodes lai.&gt;&gt; Andia ko dong pulang pi dong pung negrí iko jalan laen.<bt>Not long (=soon), then they got a dream from God saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't return to king Herodes again.&gt;&gt; That's why they returned home to their country following a different road.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yusuf dong lari pi negrí Masir<bt>Yusuf (collective) run/flee to Masir (Egypt) country</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Waktu itu orang yang pintar lia bintang dong pulang, ju Tuhan pung ana bua satu dari sorga datang kasi tau sang Yusuf dalam mimpi bilang, &lt;&lt;Usu! Bangun capát su! Angka bawa lari itu Ana deng Dia pung mama pi negrí Masir sana. Tenga tarús di situ sampe Beta kasi tau kapan bosong bole pulang, te raja Herodes ada cari ko mau bunu itu Ana!&gt;&gt;<bt>When those people who were skilled in looking at stars were returning home, then the Lord's underling from heaven (*angel) came to tell Yusuf in a dream saying, &lt;&lt;Usu [Yusuf nickname]! Get/Wake up quickly! Pick up run away with that Child and His mother to Masir country (remote). Stay there continually until I tell when you may return home, cuz (elaboration) king Herodes is looking/hunting wanting to kill that Child!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais Yusuf bangun. Ju dia bawa ame dia pung bini deng itu Ana malam-malam, ko dong lari pi negrí Masir.<bt>Then Yusuf woke/got up. And he took away his wife and that Child by night (implies secretly), in order for them to run/flee to Masir country.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yusuf mimpi abis, ju dia bangun."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Yusuf mimpi abis, ju dia bangun. Itu malam ju dia bawa ame dia pung bini deng itu Ana ko dong lari pi negrí Masir.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dong tenga di sana sampe Herodes mati. Deng bagitu Tuhan Allah pung omong jadi, sama ke Dia pung jubir Hosea su kasi tau memang dari dolu bilang,<bt>They stayed/lived there until Herodes died. With that God's speaking happened/came into being, like His *spokesperson Hosea had told beforehand from long ago saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta pange pulang Beta pung Ana, ko kaluar dari Masir.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;I call/summon home My Child to come out of Masir.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="2:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 11:1</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raja Herodes bunu bekin mati ana-ana kici di Betlehem<bt>King Herodes murders killing the small children in Betlehem</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Waktu raja Herodes dapa tau bilang, itu orang yang pintar lia bintang dong su pakane'o sang dia, ju dia jadi mara mau mati. Dia parenta dia pung tantara dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi di kampong Betlehem deng kampong-kampong yang badeka di situ. Bunu bekin mati samua ana laki-laki kici dong, yang umur dua taon pi bawa.&gt;&gt; Herodes parenta bagitu, tagal dia inga itu orang pintar dong pung carita. Dia itong mulai dari partama kali dong lia itu bintang muncul di langit.<bt>When king Herodes got to know that those star watching experts had decieved him, then he became very angry. He ordered his army guys saying, &lt;&lt;Go to Betlehem village and the villages which are near there. Murder kill all the small male children, who are two years and under.&gt;&gt; Herodes ordered like that, because he remembered those experts' story. He counted starting from the first time they saw that star appear in the sky. [NOTE: consider restructuring for foreground-background.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Raja Herodes dapa tau, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Waktu Raja Herodes dapa tau, bilang, itu orang pintar lia bintang dong su pakane'o sang dia, ju dia jadi mara mo mati. Dia parenta dia pung tantara dong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi di kampong Betlehem deng kampong-kampong yang badeka di situ. Bunu bekin mati samua ana laki-laki kici dong, yang umur dua taon pi bawa.&gt;&gt; Herodes parenta bagitu, tagal dia inga itu orang pintar dong pung carita. Dia itong mulai dari partama kali dong lia itu bintang muncul di langit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ini hal samua jadi, iko apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir Yeremia su tulis memang dari dolu bilang,<bt>All these things happened, following what God's *spokesperson Yeremia had written beforehand from long ago saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />&lt;&lt;Ada suara orang manangis maskakeduk di kota Rama.<bt>&lt;&lt;There is the sound of a person crying sobbing in Rama city.</bt><note reference="2:18" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Rama tu, satu kota deka kota Yerusalem.<bt>That Rama was a city near Yerusalem city.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Rahel ada manangis makarereu,<bt>Rahel is crying wailing [in grief],</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal dia pung ana dong su mati abis.<bt>because her children are all dead.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde mau orang datang kokoe sang dia,<bt>She doesn't want people to come comfort her,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal dia pung ana dong su sonde ada lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>because her children no longer exist [idiomatic = dead].&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="2:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 31:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yusuf dong pulang kambali dari Masir<bt>Yusuf (collective) return back from Masir</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Lama-lama ju raja Herodes mati. Itu waktu Yusuf dong masi ada di Masir. Ju Tuhan Allah pung ana bua satu dari sorga, datang kasi tunju rupa sang dia dalam mimpi.<bt>Eventually then king Herodes died. At that time Yusuf (coll) was still in Masir. Then God's underling/s from heaven (*angel), came to show himself to him in a dream.</bt><v n="20" />Itu ana bua bilang, &lt;&lt;Usu! Bangun su! Angka bawa pulang itu Ana deng dia pung mama, ko pi Isra'el su. Te orang yang mau bunu itu Ana su mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>That underling said, &lt;&lt;Usu! Get/Wake up! Pick up take home that Child and his mother, to go to Isra'el. Cuz (elaboration) the person who wanted to murder that Child has died.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="21" />Dengar bagitu ju Yusuf bangun. Ais dia bawa pulang sang dong pi negrí Isra'el.<bt>Hearing like that then Yusuf got/woke up. Then he took them home to Isra'el country.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma waktu dia dapa dengar bilang, raja Herodes pung ana Arkalaus sakarang ada pegang parenta di propinsi Yudea, ju dia taku pulang pi situ. Ais Tuhan Allah parenta sang dia dalam satu mimpi lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Yusuf, lu jang tenga di Yudea.&gt;&gt; Andia ko dia pi tenga di propinsi Galilea,<bt>But when he heard that king Herodes' child Arkalaus now was holding rule/government in Yudea province, then he was afraid to return home there. Then God ordered him in a dream again saying, &lt;&lt;Yusuf, you-sg don't stay/live in Yudea.&gt;&gt; That's why he went to live/stay in Galilea province,</bt><v n="23" />di satu kampong nama Nasaret. Deng bagitu, Tuhan Allah pung omong tu, su jadi parsís, iko apa yang Dia pung jubir su tulis memang bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti dong pange sang Dia, Orang Nasaret.&gt;&gt;<bt>in a village called Nasaret. With that [happening] that speaking of God's happened exactly according to that which His *spokesperson had written beforehand saying, &lt;&lt;Later they will call Him, a Nasaret Person.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 1:24, Lukas 2:39, Yohanis 1:45</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tukang sarani ajar orang dong<bt>Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer teaches people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:1-8; Lukas 3:1-18; Yohanis 1:19-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yesus su bésar, ju Yohanis tukang sarani mulai ajar orang di tampa sunyi, di propinsi Yudea.<bt>When Yesus was big/grown, then Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer began to teach people in a lonely place, in Yudea province. [NOTE to daughter translations: some of our lgs distinguish between /besar datang/ ‘adolescence, around 13-15’ vs. /su besar/ ‘already adult’. Make sure it's the latter. The gospels tell us he was around 30 when he began his ministry.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Sodara sayang dong! Bosong musti mangaku deng kasi tenga bosong pung sala-sala, ko kambali pi Tuhan Allah su. Te sakarang, samua orang su bisa maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>He told saying, &lt;&lt;Dear siblings [=same generation/status as speaker]! You-pl must acknowledge/confess and leave behind your-pl wrongs, in order to turn/return to God. Cuz (elaboration) now all people can enter to become God's people.&gt;&gt; [EXEG (Key Term) Kingdom of God. A: Carson's commentary does a beautiful job of showing how Matthew ties his book together around the high level themes of ‘kingdom of heaven’, ‘son of David’ and a few others. Our tension. A literal ‘kingdom of God’ or ‘kingdom of heaven’ doesn't work in these languages for a number of reasons, so a lexical concordance of this very important key term is highly problematic. Beekman n Callow (1974) and a couple TBT articles point out there are many aspects/functions of the ‘kingdom of heaven’. Sometimes it is focusing on the notion of something which will happen in heaven, something now available on earth, God's rule or governing, the network of God's people, God's power, the collective influence of God's people and God's power, etc. We don't blow it out to 36 or so aspects like some of these articles do. We try and keep it to 4-5 simple phrases that we use consistently to highlight common aspects of ‘the kingdom’. This is a compromise that we have worked out with the guidance of several consultants. Many parables and teachings DO make sense if we say “God's people are like…” “God's rule/governing is like…” “when people accept God as their King…”, but NONE of these work for all occurrences.] [EXEG: (Aspect) The kingdom "is near/has come near/is upon you/has come/is coming soon". We take Dallas Willard's point that it means “is now available/accessible” (like your house is wired, electricity is available, but it does you no good if you don't turn on the switch).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="initial Dia = Yesus or Yohanis"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">initial Dia = Yesus or Yohanis</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 4:17, Markus 1:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dolu Tuhan Allah pung jubir satu, nama Yesaya su tulis so'al Yohanis bilang,<bt>Previously one of God's *spokespersons named Yesaya had written about Yohanis saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nanti ada orang yang batarea di tampa sunyi bilang,<bt>&lt;&lt;Later there will be a person that shouts out in a lonely place saying, [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure word for ‘shout’ can have message, not just sound.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Samua orang siap-siap bekin bae jalan,<bt>&lt;All people get ready to fix the road,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko sambut Tuhan Allah pung datang!<bt>to greet/welcome God's coming!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bekin lurus jalan kasi sang Dia!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Make straight the road for Him!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="3:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Yohanis ni pung cara idop sama ke Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu dong. Dia pung pakean, bekin dari binatang onta pung bulu. Dia pung ika pinggang, bekin dari binatang pung kulit. Dia pung makanan, kalamak deng madu utan.<bt>This Yohanis' way of living was like the Lord's *spokespersons from long ago. His clothing, was made from camel's hair. His belt, was made from animal skin. His food, was grasshoppers and jungle [=wild] honey.</bt><note reference="3:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 1:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Itu waktu orang banya datang ko mau katumu deng Yohanis. Dong datang dari kota Yerusalem, deng dari anteru propinsi Yudea. Dong ju datang dari kampong-kampong yang badeka deng kali Yarden.<bt>At that time many people came to meet Yohanis. They came from Yerusalem, and from all over Yudea province. They also come from villages which were close to the Yordan river.</bt><v n="6" />Dong buka hati deng mangaku dong pung sala-sala samua, ais ju Yohanis sarani sang dong di kali Yarden.<bt>They opened their livers and confessed all their wrongs, afterwards then, Yohanis *baptised them in the Yordan river. [NOTE: *baptise is method neutral term, entrenched in the region for several hundred years; probably via the eastern church, not Rome].</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Itu waktu, orang-orang dari partei agama Farisi deng partei agama Saduki ju datang ko minta Yohanis sarani sang dong. Ma waktu dia lia sang dong, ju dia masparak bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bosong ni sama ke ular yang tukang putar-balek! Tuhan Allah nanti hukum sang bosong tagal bosong pung bekin-bekin yang jahat dong. Weh! Jang kira bosong bisa lari kaluar dari Dia pung hukuman.<bt>At that time, people from the Farisi religious party and the Saduki religious party also came to request Yohanis to baptise them. But when he saw them, then he got angry saying, &lt;&lt;Heh! [+angry, objection] You-pl here are like snakes who are habitual twisters-turners (=decievers)! God will later judge/punish you, because of your evil doings. Weh! [+negative] Don't think that you can run away from His judgement.</bt><note reference="3:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:34, 23:33</note><v n="8" />Jadi lebe bae bosong kambali pi Tuhan Allah, deng kasi tenga bosong pung sala-sala dong samua. Ais itu, bekin hal-hal yang bae, sama ke pohon yang kasi kaluar bua yang bae.<bt>So it's better that you return to God, and leave behind all your wrongs. After that then, do good things, like trees which produce fruit that is good.</bt><v n="9" />Jang kira kata bosong su aman, tagal bosong ni ba'i Abraham pung turunan. Parcaya sang beta! Te Tuhan Allah bisa bekin ini batu dong jadi ba'i Abraham pung turunan.<bt>Don't think you are safe because you here, are Gf/Ff Abraham's descendants. Believe Me! Cuz (elaboration) God can made there rocks to become Gf/Ff Abraham's descendants. [EXEG: NLT ‘we're safe’; TRT ‘we escape punishment’ (vs.7)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** bae &gt; aman; Beta &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** bae &gt; aman; Beta &gt; beta (it's John, not Jesus); note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 8:33</note><v n="10" />Awas, é! Te ada Orang yang pegang kapak ko siap-siap mau potong samua pohon yang pung bua sonde bae. Potong ais, Dia lempar buang pi dalam api.<bt>Watch out! Cuz (elaboration) there is a Person who holds the axe in preparation for wanting to cut down all the trees whose fruit is not good. After cutting [them], He will throw them away into the fire.</bt><note reference="3:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sakarang beta sarani sang bosong pake aer, ko jadi tanda bilang, bosong su bale balakang kasi tenga bosong pung sala-sala dong. Ma nanti satu Orang yang lebe hebat dari beta mau datang. Biar cuma jadi Dia pung tukang suru-suru sa ju, beta sonde pantas. Nanti Dia bekin ponu bosong pung hati deng Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi. Dia ju bekin bosong jadi barisi, sama ke orang pake api ko bakar buang kotoran.<bt>Now I baptise you-pl using water, to be a sign saying you have turned their backs leaving behind your wrongs. But later there will be a Person who is more amazing that me who will come. Even just to be his servant (person who gets bossed around all the time), I am not appropriate/worthy. Later He will fill your livers with God2's Holy Spirit. He will also make you clean/holy, like a person uses fir to burn off rubbish. [EXEG: TRT, TN] [NOTE to daughter translations: phrase as in Mark 1:8.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***fixed grammar of last sentence, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">***fixed grammar of last sentence, and added “and with fire”, framed as in Luke, which flows into vs.12 below. Rewrote ftn to make it more accurate (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti Dia po'a kasi sang bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Nanti Dia po'a kasi sang bosong pake Tuhan Allah pung Roh ko bekin bosong jadi barisi.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dia pung kata bahasa Yunani asli bilang: &lt;&lt;baptis deng Tuhan pung Roh Barisi, deng api.&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;Baptis deng Dia pung Roh&gt;&gt; ada pung arti, andia, &lt;&lt;bekin ponu bosong pung hati deng Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi.&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;Baptis... deng api&gt;&gt; ada pung arti, andia, &lt;&lt;bekin bosong jadi barisi, sama ke orang pake api ko bakar buang kotoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>The original Yunani words say: &lt;&lt;baptis with God's Holy Spirit, and fire.&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;Baptis with His Spirit&gt;&gt; has the meaning of, &lt;&lt;fill your livers with God's Holy Spirit.&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;Baptis... with fire&gt;&gt; has the meaning of, &lt;&lt;make you become clean/pure/holy like a person who uses fire to burn off rubbish.&gt;&gt;</bt></note><v n="12" />Te Dia su pegang nyiru yang ada isi barás, ko mau tapis buang dia pung uuk. Ais Dia kasi maso itu barás pi dalam sokal. Ma itu uuk dong, Dia lempar buang pi dalam api yang manyala sonde tau abis-abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He already holds a winnowing basket that is filled with rice, in order to winnow throw away the husks. He puts that rice into a rice.storage.basket. But those husks, he throws them away into the fire which burns without ever ending.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="uuk ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">uuk =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis sarani sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis *baptizes the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:9-11; Lukas 3:21-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Itu waktu, Yesus turun datang dari Galilea pi kali Yarden. Dia datang minta Yohanis sarani sang Dia,<bt>At that time Yesus came down from Galilea to go to Yordan river. He came requesting Yohanis to *baptise Him,</bt><v n="14" />ma Yohanis sonde mau. Dia protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana ko beta musti sarani sang Bos? Sonde tabale ni, ko? Bos ni yang musti sarani sang beta. Te itu yang beta parlú na!&gt;&gt;<bt>but Yohanis did not want [to]. He protested saying, &lt;&lt;How can it be that I must baptise Bos (=you, term recognising someone's superior/boss/respected position to speaker)? Isn't this backwards, [+tag question]? It's Bos (=You) who must baptise me. Cuz (elaboration) that's what I need [obviously]!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: if ‘Bos’ causes problems, just use pronouns ‘me’ and ‘you’ like the Gk. (remember, they were cousins). Terms like ‘father’ are socially inappropriate here for ‘you’, since they were cousins. But many speakers object to using 2s ‘lu’, seeing it as rude when applied to Jesus.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Aman sa. Ma buat sakarang, biar bu yang sarani sang Beta sa. Deng bagitu kotong iko Tuhan Allah pung mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;It's ok/don't worry. But for now, let it be that elder.brother  (=you) just baptises me. With that we-inc follow God's will.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar bagitu ju Yohanis manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dari-dari sa.&gt;&gt; Ju dia sarani sang Yesus.<bt>Hearing like that then Yohanis answered saying, &lt;&lt;Whatever/OK (idiomatic = mildly reluctant agreement).&gt;&gt; Then he baptised Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Sarani abis, ju Yesus kaluar dari kali. Ma takuju sa, ju langit tabuka. Ais Dia dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung Roh turun datang pi sang Dia, sama ke burung pompa datang hinggap di Dia.<bt>After baptising [him], then Yesus came out from the river. But suddenly/unexpectedly, then the sky was opened (agentless; resulting state). Then He saw God's Spirit come down to Him, like a dove/pidgin came alighting on Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: slightly diff than Mrk. In the Gk here it alights (NRSV, NLT). CEV and TB both undertranslated here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hinggap *** note added; hinggap added."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">hinggap *** note added; hinggap added.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ais dong dapa dengar Tuhan Allah pung suara dari langit bilang,<bt>Then they could hear God's voice from the sky saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ini Dia, Beta pung Ana sayang.<bt>&lt;&lt;He is My beloved Child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia salalu bekin sanáng sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>He always makes Me happy/pleases Me.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="3:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 22:2, Lagu Puji dong 2:7, Yesaya 42:1, Mateos 12:18, 17:5, Markus 1:11, Lukas 9:35</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Setan dong pung bos goda sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Evil spirits' boss (*Satan) tempts/seduces/bothers the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 4:1-13; Markus 1:12-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Tuhan Allah pung Roh antar bawa sang Yesus pi tampa sunyi, ko biar setan dong pung bos goda sang Dia.<bt>After that, the Lord's Spirit took/led/escorted Yesus to a lonely place, so that the evil spirit's big boss could tempt/seduce/bother Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: also consider using /coba/ “test mettle, character”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added note (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added note (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ibrani 2:18, 4:15</note><v n="2" />Ju Dia puasa 40 siang 40 malam di situ. Ais itu ju, Dia lapar mati pung.<bt>And He fasted 40 days and 40 nights there. After that, then He was very hungry.</bt><v n="3" />Waktu Dia su lapar bagitu, ju setan dong pung bos datang goda sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana, ko? Kalo batúl, na, parenta ini batu dong ko jadi makanan su.&gt;&gt;<bt>When He was hungry like that, then the evil spirit's big boss came tempting/seducing/bothering Him saying, &lt;&lt;Are You here, really God's Child, right? If that's true, na, command these stones to become food [+imperative].&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada tatulis dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang:<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;It is written in God's Holy Writings (= *Scriptures) saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Manusia sonde idop dari makanan sa.<bt>&lt;Humans don't live from just food.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma dong ju musti dengar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata,<bt>But they must also hear/obey God's Words/Sayings,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng bekin iko Dia pung mau.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>and do/act according to His will.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added \cf (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added \cf (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 8:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Tarús, itu setan bawa sang Yesus pi kota Yerusalem, andia Tuhan pung kota barisi. Ais dia bawa nae sang Yesus pi atas Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung tampa yang paling tinggi.<bt>Next that evil spirit brought Yesus to Yerusalem city, that is the clean/holy city of the Lord's. Then he took Yesus up on top of the Central/Main Worship House's (*Temple's) highest place.</bt><v n="6" />Ju itu setan bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Lu memang batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana, na, coba Lu malompa turun pi bawa su. Te ada tatulis di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Then that evil spirit said, &lt;&lt;If You are really God's Child, then You try and jump down to the bottom [+imperative]. Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Scriptures saying, [EXEG: Q: Is this an “If” or a “since”? Does the RL match the Greek? (1) Since you are God’s Son, feed yourself by working a miracle (Tasker, Hill, Hendriksen). This implies that Satan knew that Jesus was the Son of God and that he wanted Jesus to use his own power to feed himself. (2) If you are God’s Son, prove it by working a miracle (Plummer, Lenski). This implies that Satan wanted Jesus to show whether he was the Son of God. When John baptized Jesus (3:17), God said that Jesus was his Son. And since Satan’s demons knew Jesus was God’s Son (Mark 1:24), Satan surely did. Jesus knew that Satan knew this. So it was clear to both Jesus and Satan that Satan meant “since” here, even though he said “if.” A: either interpretation is possible, and the RL can also be read either way from the phrasing of the whole sentence. But note that the commentaries favouring ‘since’ are actually basing their interpretation not on the basis of the meaning/functions of the Gk connector /ei/, but rather on the context in comparison with related/supporting passages to build a larger case. All lexicons give conditional ‘if’ as the primary sense of Gk /ei/, and some (like LN) don't even list ‘since’ as one of its senses. So I would say the strong and safe interpretation from the Gk here is ‘if’, and a possible interpretation given the context with support from other passages could be ‘since’. Most RL languages in this region don't have a way to distinguish ‘if’ from ‘since’. Changing to use the local connectors for asserted reason ‘because’, would be going beyond the Greek text. Both the Gk and the RL default reading would be ‘if’, and a ‘since’ interpretation is not excluded.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Nanti Tuhan Allah parenta Dia pung ana bua dari sorga dong,<bt>&lt;Later God will order His underling/s from heaven,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko jaga sang Lu.&gt;<bt>to protect/guard You.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi ju ada tulis bilang,<bt>In the Scriptures it is also written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Nanti dong tada ame Lu deng dong pung tangan,<bt>&lt;Later they will collect/undergird/catch from below You with their hand/s, [NOTE to daughter translations: the TB completely missed s.t. in the Gk, all the commentaries, and most English translations here. There are actually two different OT quotes here, not one as in TB, which we've made explicit in the KM with an intervening quote margin. So the punctuation starting the second quote after the quote margin with a capital is correct.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar Lu pung badan sonde saki, deng Lu sonde sonto batu ju.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>so that Your foot/feet does not trip on stones.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko biar Lu pung kaki jang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">ko biar Lu pung kaki jang tatumbu di batu.&gt;&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 91:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada tatulis ju dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;It is written also in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah tu, yang hak parenta sang lu.<bt>&lt;God is the one who has the say-so/ordering rights over you-sg. [NOTE: restructured to reflect meaning of Gk /kurios/, while minimizing the uses of ‘Bos’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko lu jang coba sang Dia.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why you should not test Him (mettle, character, power, ability, see what He's made of).&gt;&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: If UNSs can't answer test what? then fuller form has been worked through with several consultants. ALT: Andia ko lu jang suru Dia pake Dia pung kuasa ko kasi bukti bilang, Dia tu, batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah.]</bt><note reference="4:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Tarús, itu setan bawa sang Yesus pi atas satu gunung yang talalu tinggi. Ju dia kasi tunju samua negrí di dunya, deng dong pung hebat samua.<bt>Next that evil spirit took Yesus to the top of a very tall mountain. Then he showed him all the nations/countries in the world and all their amazingness. [EXEG: Gk ‘glory, spelndour’here.]</bt><v n="9" />Kasi tunju abis itu samua, ju itu setan kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal Lu tikam lutut ko sémba sang beta, nanti beta kasi itu samua-samua pi di Lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>After showing all that, then that evil spirit told saying, &lt;&lt;As long as You-sg bend your knee to worship me, I will give all of that to You-sg.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ma Yesus masparak bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh, setan! Lu iskarobis dari sini su! Te Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi ada bilang,<bt>But Yesus spoke angrily saying, &lt;&lt;Heh, evil spirit! You get.out of here! Cuz (elaboration) God's Holy Writings say,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Lu musti sémba sang Tuhan Allah,<bt>&lt;You must worship God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng lu musti karjá kasi sang Dia sa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>and you must work only for Him.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="4:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu setan angka kaki kasi tenga sang Yesus. Ju Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga dong datang ko urus sang Dia.<bt>Hearing like that, then that evil.sprit picked up his feet leaving Yesus [NOTE: sense of left in a bit of a huff]. And/then God's *angels (underlings) from heaven came and took care of Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus mulai ajar di Galilea<bt>The Lord Yesus begins to teach at Galilea</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:14-15; Lukas 4:14-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Itu waktu, raja Herodes kasi maso Yohanis tukang sarani dalam bui. Waktu Yesus dapa dengar bagitu, ju Dia pulang pi Galilea.<bt>At that time, king Herodes put Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer into jail. When Yesus heard that, then He returned to Galilea.</bt><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 14:3, Markus 6:17, Lukas 3:19-20</note><v n="13" />Dia pi Dia pung kampong Nasaret, ais Dia jalan tarús ko pi tenga di kampong Kapernaum. Itu kampong ada di dano Galilea pung pinggir, di Sebulon deng Naftali pung tana.<bt>He went to His village Nasaret, and then He continued on to go stay in Kapernaum village. That village is at Galilea lake's edge in Sebulon and Naftali's land.</bt><note reference="4:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 2:12</note><v n="14" />Deng bagitu, Dia bekin iko apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir Yesaya su tulis memang bilang,<bt>In that way, He did according to what God's *spokesperson Yesaya had written beforehand saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />&lt;&lt;Di Sebulon pung tana, deng Naftali pung tana,<bt>&lt;&lt;In Sebulon's land, and Naftali's land</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang deka di dano Galilea, di kali Yarden pung sablá,<bt>which are close to Galilea lake, on Yordan river's other side,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">orang yang bukan orang Yahudi ada tenga di situ ju.<bt>people who are not Yahudi people are also living there. [EXEG: both Jews and non-Jews live in these regions. TN, NLT, TH, TRT. NOTE Gk is vocative, personifying land. We follow NLT as location to avoid personification.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di situ ada tenga orang yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Di situ ada tenga orang yang bukan orang Yahudi.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Dong ada idop dalam galáp,<bt>They are living in darkness, [EXEG: CONNOT: “shadow of death” is a doublet with “living in darkness” and means “fearing death” (M. Crofts); Both parts of this doublet mean exactly the same. Be sure that this is understood as such, or if a doublet here is unnatural, you may combine the parts. (Willis Ott). But there is also something more fundamental that these are not picking up on. I was just drafting Ps.23 with its well know phrase (23:4) valley of “the shadow of death”. All sources there say it is a Hebrew idiom meaning ‘darkness’ (TH, NRSV, NLT, NCV, NET, BART, BDB, TWOT)]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma sakarang dong su dapa lia Taráng.<bt>but now they have seen Light.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Taráng su basinar<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Light has shone</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi samua orang yang balóm kanál sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>for all people who do not yet know God.</bt><note reference="4:15-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 9:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Mulai dari itu waktu, ju Yesus mulai ajar orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti bale balakang deng kasi tenga bosong pung sala-sala dong, ko idop barisi su! Te sakarang samua orang su bisa maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Starting from that time, then Yesus began to teach people saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl must turn your backs and leave behind your wrongs, to live clean/holy/pure [imperative]! Cuz (elaboration) now all people can enter to become God's person/people.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="4:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pange nalayan ampa orang ko iko sang Dia<bt>The Lord Yesus calls four fishermen to follow Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:16-20; Lukas 5:1-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Satu hari, Yesus ada jalan iko dano Galilea pung pinggir. Dia nae katumu dua orang adi-kaka. Yang satu nama Simon, ma orang biasa pange sang dia, Petrus. Deng dia pung adi nama Anderias. Dong ada jala ikan di dano, tagal dong dua tu, nalayan.<bt>One day, Yesus was walking along Galilea lake's edge/shore. He happened to meet two people who were younger-elder siblings. [NOTE: RL order] One was named Simon, but people often/usually called him, Petrus. And his younger sibling named Anderias. They were cast-netting fish in the lake, because the two of them were fishermen. [NOTE to daughter translations: Q: It appears using ‘Peter’ here clashes with John's account. A: It's in the Gk. TN says “this was the name Jesus later gave to Simon, but Matthew probably uses it from the beginning of his Gospel because it was the name by which his readers knew Simon.”]</bt><v n="19" />Ju Yesus pange sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;We, mari ko iko sang Beta su! Bosong biasa cari ikan, ma sakarang Beta mau ajar sang bosong, ko bosong jadi tukang cari jiwa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus called them saying, &lt;&lt;We, [+attention] come to follow Me [+imperative]! You usually hunt fish, but now I will teach you-pl, so that you become habitual soul hunters.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: avoid wording that makes Jesus training them to be sorcerers (people hunters). Make them more like recruiters to a political party. Careful that equiv of /jiwa/ isn't only in relation to dead people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dengar abis bagitu, ju dong dua kasi tenga dong pung jala, ko iko memang sang Yesus.<bt>After hearing like that, then they two left behind their castnet, to straight away follow Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais itu, Yesus dong jalan tarús sadiki lai, ju Dia dapa lia Sabadeus pung ana. Yang kaka pung nama Yakobis, deng dia pung adi nama Yohanis. Dong dua ada ator bekin bae pukat dalam parahu sama-sama deng dong pung bapa. Ju Yesus pange sang dong dua ko iko sang Dia.<bt>After that, Yesus (and those associated with Him) walked on a bit more, then He saw Sabadius' child/ren. The elder sibling's name was Yakobis, and his younger sibling's name was Yohanis. They two were arranging/readying their dragnet in a boat together with their father. Then Yesus call them two to follow Him.</bt><v n="22" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong jalan kasi tenga dong pung bapa deng dong pung parahu, ko dong iko memang sang Dia.<bt>Hearing like that, then they walked leaving behind their father and their boat, to straight away follow Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang, deng bekin bae orang saki dong<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people and heals sick people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:17-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais itu, Yesus dong bajalan kuliling propinsi Galilea, ko Dia ajar di orang Yahudi pung ruma sambayang dong. Dia ajar so'al Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae, deng kasi tau cara karmana ko orang bisa iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta. Dia ju bekin bae samua orang dari dong pung panyaki macam-macam.<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) walked all around Galilea province, in order for Him to teach in the *Jewish people's worship houses. He taught about God's *Good News, and told/explained how people can follow/obey God's commands / participate in God's rule. He also healed all the people from all of their different kinds of sicknesses.</bt><note reference="4:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:35, Markus 1:39</note><v n="24" />Sonde lama, ju kabar so'al Yesus tu, tasiar kuliling sampe di anteru propinsi Siria. Ais ju orang bawa datang dong pung orang saki macam-macam pi sang Dia. Dong ju bawa orang yang takaná setan, yang gila kambing, deng yang lumpu. Ju Dia bekin bae dong samua.<bt>Not long (=soon), then news about Yesus, spread around to the point of the entire Siria province. After then, people brought their all kinds of sick people to Him. They also brought people who were afflicted with evil spirit/s, who were crazy goat (=epileptic), and those who were lame. Then He healed all of them.</bt><v n="25" />Itu waktu, orang bam-banya datang iko sang Dia. Dong datang dari propinsi Galilea, deng dari da'era Sapulu Kota, yang dong subu bilang, <span class="Italic">Dekapolis.</span> Ada laen lai yang datang dari kota Yerusalem, dari propinsi Yudea, deng dari kali Yarden pung sablá.<bt>At that time very many people came following Him. They came from Galilea province, and from the area of Ten Cities, which they call saying, <span class="Italic">Dekapolis.</span> There were still others who came from Yerusalem city, from Yudea province, and from the other side of the Yarden river.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang di atas gunung<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches on the mountain</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yesus dapa lia orang bam-banya datang iko sang Dia, ju Dia nae pi satu gunung kici, ko dudu di situ. Dia pung ana bua dong yang Dia su pili tu, datang deka-deka ko dengar sang Dia.<bt>When Yesus saw many-many people coming following Him, then He went up a small mountain, to sit there. Those aforementioned underlings (*disciples) of His whom He had chosen, came close to hear Him.</bt><v n="2" />Ais Dia mulai ajar sang dong bilang,<bt>Then He began to teach them saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang dapa ontong batúl [\s2]<bt>The people who truly fortunate/benefit/profit [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:20-23)</p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />&lt;&lt;Orang kasian yang rasa parlú sang Tuhan dong ontong,<bt>&lt;&lt;Poor/pitiful people who feel the need for God2 are fortunate/benefit, [EXEG: see CEG PPT word study on Gk. /makarios/ as “how fortunate you are” or “what a good state of affairs you're in in God's eyes”; “happy” may be a secondary effect, but is not really part of the primary meaning of the Gk. Compare discusssion in parallel passage in Luke 6. See also discussion in Ex.Summ.] [EXEG-2: this verse has nothing to do with poor people who live in material poverty. It is about an attitude and state of mind. See Ex.Summ.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Tuhan Allah sandiri, dong pung Raja yang bae.<bt>because the Lord God himself, is their good King.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Orang yang rasa dukacita dong ontong,<bt>People who feel sorrow/grief [from a death] are fortunate/benefit,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Tuhan Allah sandiri yang kokoe sang dong.<bt>because God himself comforts/persuades [to do s.t. positive] them.</bt><note reference="5:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 61:2</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />Orang kici dong ontong,<bt>Little people (=low status people) are fortunate/benefit,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal nanti dong tarima samua berkat yang Tuhan Allah su janji.<bt>because they will receive all the blessing/s which God has promised.</bt><note reference="5:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 37:11</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Orang yang talalu rindu sang Tuhan Allah pung jalan lurus dong, ontong,<bt>People who intensely long for God's straight/right/just path/way are fortunate/benefit, [NOTE to daughter translations: OV “Intensely long for God” is probably too broad/vague; but TB “for God's will” and CEV “to obey God” are probably too narrow, not to mention that Greek has other vocabulary to say those things that is does not use here. Changed to /TA pung jalan lurus/ to get it in the right range and give lexical ties to how we render this Gk term elsewhere.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal nanti Dia bekin puas sang dong.<bt>because He will make them satisfied.</bt><note reference="5:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />Orang yang kasi tunju rasa kasian dong ontong,<bt>People who show mercy/pity are fortunate/benefit,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang pung hati mas tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Orang yang pung hati mas tu, dong ontong,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal nanti Tuhan Allah ju jato kasian sang dong.<bt>because God will also feel compassion/pity for them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Orang yang pung hati barisi dong ontong,<bt>People who have clean livers (=honest, pure, having integrity) are fortunate/benefit,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal nanti dong sandiri dapa lia Tuhan Allah.<bt>because they will see God for themselves.</bt><note reference="5:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 24:3-4</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />Orang yang tukang bekin dame dong ontong,<bt>People who habitually make (relational) peace are fortunate/benefit,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal nanti Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;Dong tu, Beta pung ana.&gt;<bt>because God will say, &lt;They are My child/ren.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Orang yang kaná siksa tagal iko sang Tuhan Allah dong ontong,<bt>People who experience persecution/torture/abuse because they follow God are fortunate/benefit,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Tuhan sandiri tu, dong pung Raja yang bae.<bt>because the Lord himself, is their good King.</bt><note reference="5:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Petrus 3:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Kalo orang laen bekin sangsara sang bosong tagal bosong iko sang Beta, bosong ju ontong. Kalo dong omong jahat sang bosong, deng bacarita putar-balek bekin busuk bosong pung nama, bosong ju ontong.<bt>If other people cause you-pl suffering because you follow Me, you also are fortunate/benefit. If they speak evil to/about you, and tell decietful things making your name rotten, you also are fortunate/benefit.</bt><note reference="5:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Petrus 4:14</note><v n="12" />Biar bagitu, ma bosong musti bekin diri sanáng deng hati babunga sa, tagal Tuhan Allah su sadia balas kasi bosong pung bagian, satu mal'unuk di sorga. Ma inga, é! Bukan cuma bosong sa yang dapa sangsara bagitu, te dolu-dolu orang dong ju bekin jahat bagitu sang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even if it's like that, nevertheless you-pl must just make yourselves happy and your livers flowered (=be joyful), because God is ready to reciprocate your share, one huge heap in heaven. But remember! It is not only you who obtain suffering like that, cuz (elaboration) long ago people also did evil like that to God's spokespersons.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="5:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 36:16, Utusan dong pung Carita 7:52</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang iko Tuhan Yesus, sama ke garam deng taráng [\s2]<bt>The people who follow the Lord Yesus are like salt and light [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:50; Lukas 14:34-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />&lt;&lt;Kalo kotong mau bekin enak makanan, na, kotong parlú taro garam dolo. Bagitu ju orang yang idop di ini dunya, dong parlú sang bosong. Ma kalo garam su jadi tawar, na, dia pung guna apa? Cuma angka buang di jalan ko kaná inja sa.<bt>&lt;&lt;If we-inc want to make food tasty, then we need to put salt first. Like that also people who live in this world, they need you-pl. But if that salt has become fresh/neutralised, na, what is it's use? Just pick it up throw it on the road/path to be stepped on.</bt><note reference="5:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 9:50, Lukas 14:34-35</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Bosong ju musti idop sama ke lampu, ko biar orang banya dapa lia deng bae-bae. Bosong musti manyala taráng-taráng, sama ke kota yang ada di atas gunung, yang samua orang dapa lia.<bt>You-pl also must live like a lamp, so that many people can see well. You must shine clearly/brightly, the same as a city which is on top of a mountain, which all people can see.</bt><note reference="5:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 8:12, 9:5</note><v n="15" />Orang yang kasi manyala lampu te'oek, sonde kasi maso itu lampu pi dalam pareu tana. Ma dong taro itu lampu di tampa tinggi, ko bisa bekin taráng ruma pung isi samua.<bt>People who light <span class="Italic">te'oek</span> lamps (= small wick lamps), don't put that lamp inside a clay pot. But they put that lamp in a high place, so it can may make.clear/light all the contents of the house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added ‘but’ (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added ‘but’ (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 4:21, Lukas 8:16, 11:33</note><v n="16" />Bosong ju musti idop bagitu. Bosong musti bacaya, ko biar orang laen dong dapa lia bosong pung idop yang bae. Deng lia bagitu nanti dong puji sang Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;Awii! Bosong pung Bapa di sorga tu, talalu hebat, ó!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl also must live like that. You must shine, so that other people can see your life which is good. And seeing like that then later they will praise God saying, &lt;Awii! [+amazement] That Father of Yours in heaven, is really amazing huh!&gt;&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk: give glory here] [DISCOURSE: made direct speech following RL patterns.]</bt><note reference="5:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Petrus 2:12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus datang ko bekin ganáp Tuhan Allah pung atoran [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus came to make complete God's *regulations/law [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />&lt;&lt;Bosong jang pikir kata, Beta datang di ini dunya, ko mau hapus buang Tuhan Allah pung atoran yang Dia kasi sang ba'i Musa. Deng jang kira Beta sonde toe deng apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong su omong memang dari dolu. Te Beta datang ni, mau bekin samua jadi parsís sama ke samua hal yang dong su omong memang.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl shouldn't think that, I come to this world, in order to wipe away God's regulations which He gave to Gf/Ff Musa. And don't think I'm not concerned with what God's spokesperson have spoken beforehand from long ago. Cuz (elaboration) I have come here, wanting/intending to make everything happen exactly like all the things which they spoke about beforehand.</bt><v n="18" />Tagal itu, dengar bae-bae, é! Langit deng bumi balóm bisa ancor buang, kalo samua balóm jadi, iko Tuhan Allah pung atoran dong. Biar satu titi ko koma ju, sonde ada yang bisa tahapus buang.<bt>Because of that, listen carefully, é! Sky/heaven and earth will not yet be destroyed thrown away, if everything has not yet happened according to God's regulations. Even just one dot/period or comma, will not be erased thrown away.</bt><note reference="5:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 16:17</note><v n="19" />Dari Tuhan pung orang dong samua, kalo ada yang langgar Tuhan pung atoran, tagal dia pikir bilang, &lt;Hee! Ini atoran ni, kici sa, sonde ada pung guna apa-apa!&gt; Ais dia ajar bagitu kasi orang laen, nanti Tuhan Allah di sorga bekin dia jadi orang kici sa. Ma orang yang bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung atoran samua, ais dia ajar bagitu kasi orang laen, nanti Tuhan Allah bekin dia jadi orang yang ada pung guna.<bt>From among all of God's people, if there is someone who violates the Lord's regulation/s, because he thinks saying, &lt;Hee, this little regulation here, doesn't have any use!&gt; And.then he teaches like that to other people, God in heaven will just make him become a small/unimportant person. But people who do/act according to all God's regulations, and.then he teaches like that to other people, God will make him become a person who has use/value. [NOTE: added leading clause to restore 'kingdom of heaven' as scope of who is being talked about.]</bt><v n="20" />Parcaya sang Beta! Kalo bosong sonde idop lurus lebe bae dari itu guru agama deng orang partei Farisi dong, na, bosong sonde bisa maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Believe Me! If you don't live righteous/straight better than those religion teachers and Farisi party people, then you can not enter to become God's person.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Ex. Summ.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang dong ko jang bamara [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people to not be angry at each other [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 12:57-59)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />&lt;&lt;Bosong su tau ba'i Musa pung atoran yang dia kasi tau memang sang kotong pung nene-moyang bilang, &lt;Jang bunu orang, te sapa yang bunu orang, nanti dia kaná hukum.&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl already know Gf Musa's regulation which he explained beforehand to our-inc ancestors saying, &lt;Don't kill people, cuz (elaboration) whoever kills people, he will be afflicted with punishment/be punished.&gt;</bt><note reference="5:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:13, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:17</note><v n="22" />Ma Beta mau kasi tau bagini: jang bamara, te sapa yang mara sang dia pung sodara, nanti dia kaná hukum. Orang yang maruak sang dia pung sodara bilang, &lt;Lu otak kea!&gt; nanti itu orang musti mangada di muka tua-tua agama dong. Deng orang yang masparak sang dia pung sodara bilang, &lt;Bodo, é!&gt;, nanti dia kaná hukum di api naraka.<bt>But I want to explain like this: don't get reciprocally mad at each other, cuz (elaboration) whoever gets mad at his sibling, he will be afflicted with punishment. A person who is fed up with/ furious at his sibling saying, &lt;You turtle-brain (slow-witted)!&gt; later that person must front up before the religious elders. And person who snarls angrily at his sibling saying, &lt;(You) stupid/idiot, é!&gt;, he will be afflicted with punishment in hell fire. [NOTE to daughter translation: Translate the meaning, not the words. Find local metaphors for “stupid fool”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** bamara deng &gt; mara sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** bamara deng &gt; mara sang (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Jadi, kalo lu ada bawa persembahan kasi sang Tuhan Allah, ma lu inga bilang, ada sodara yang masi mara sang lu,<bt>So (consequently), if you are bringing an offering to God, but you remember that there is a sibling that is angry with you, [EXEG: not reciprocal anger here, but a brother offended at you (regardless of whether you have issues with him/her or not). All sources.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** fixed exegesis (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** fixed exegesis (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma lu inga, bilang, lu ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">ma lu inga, bilang, lu ada bamara deng lu pung sodara,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />na, jang taro itu persembahan dolo. Lu pi badame deng lu pung sodara dolo, ais itu baru lu pi taro itu persembahan kasi sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>na, don't place that *offering down first. You go be reciprocally at relational peace with your sibling first, after that only then you go place that offering to God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Kalo ada orang yang mau bekin parkara deng lu, na, lebe bae lu pi urus dame capát-capát deng dia dolo. Kalo sonde, nanti itu orang hela bawa sang lu pi mangada di hakim. Ais hakim sarakan sang lu pi di polisi, ju dong sese maso sang lu pi dalam bui.<bt>If there is a person who wants to make a dispute/litigation with you-sg, na, it's better you go quickly to arrange relational peace first. If not, that person will drag bring you to front up before the judge. Then the judge will hand you over to the police, and they will stuff you into jail.</bt><v n="26" />Beta omong batúl ni! Nanti lu tenga tarús dalam bui sampe bayar abis lu pung utang samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>What I say here is true! You will remain continually in jail until you have completely paid off all of your debts.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang ko jang maen serong [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people to not play around sexually [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />&lt;&lt;Bosong su tau ba'i Musa pung atoran yang bilang, &lt;Jang maen serong.&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl already know Gf Musa's regulation which says, &lt;Don't commit adultery.&gt;</bt><note reference="5:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:14, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:18</note><v n="28" />Ma Beta mau kasi tau bagini: orang yang angka mata ko lia satu parampuan, ais dia pung hati kapingin tidor bakumpul deng dia, na, itu laki-laki su maen serong deng itu parampuan dalam dia pung hati.<bt>But I want to tell like this: a person who lifts his eyes to look at a woman, and.then his liver/heart desires to sleep together (euphemism for sex) with her, na, that man has already committed adultery with that woman in his liver/heart.</bt><v n="29" />Kalo lu bekin sala pake lu pung mata kanan, na, do'i buang sang dia sa. Te lebe bae lu maso pi dalam sorga deng lu pung mata satu sa, ko biar dong jang lempar buang sang lu pi api naraka deng lu pung mata biji dua-dua.<bt>If you do wrong using your right eye, na, just gouge it out throw it away. Cuz (elaboration) it's better you enter heaven with just your one eye, so that they don't throw away dispose of you in hell fire with both your eyeballs.</bt><note reference="5:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:9, Markus 9:47</note><v n="30" />Deng kalo lu bekin sala pake lu pung tangan kanan, na, potong buang itu tangan sa. Te lebe bae lu maso pi dalam sorga deng lu pung tangan sablá sa, ko biar dong jang lempar buang sang lu pi api naraka deng lu pung tangan dua-dua.&gt;&gt;<bt>And if you do wrong using your right hand, na, just cut off throw away that hand. Cuz (elaboration) it's better you enter heaven with just your one hand, so that they don't throw away dispose of you in hell fire with both your hands.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="5:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:8, Markus 9:43</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang ko jang bacere [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches to not divorce [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:9; Markus 10:11-12; Lukas 16:18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />&lt;&lt;Bosong su tau ba'i Musa pung atoran bilang, &lt;Orang yang cere buang dia pung bini, na, dia musti kasi surat cere sang itu parampuan.&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl know Gf Musa's regulation saying, &lt;A person who divorces throws away his wife, na, he must give a divorce letter to that woman.&gt;</bt><note reference="5:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 24:1-4, Mateos 19:7, Markus 10:4</note><v n="32" />Ma Beta kasi tau bagini: kalo ada orang yang cere buang dia pung bini, padahal dia pung bini sonde parná maen serong, ais, itu parampuan kawin ulang, na, itu sama deng dia pung laki partama bekin dia barsina. Deng kalo ada laki-laki yang kawin ame sang satu parampuan yang parná kaná cere buang, na, dong dua su barsina ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>But I tell like this: a person who divorces throws away his wife, when actually his wife has never deviated (sexually), then, that woman remarries, that is that same as her first husband has made/caused her to commit adultery. And if there is a man who marries a woman who has been divorced, na, the two of them have committed adultery.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: ellipsed proposition “and she remarries” See Ex. Summ. TN, TRT (unanimous).] [EXEG: Gk uses both “porneia” and “moicheuw”, so try to reflect that difference as in KM.] [NOTE to daughter translations: this is complicated. It only works if you get the connectors right.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV overstates it here ; ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">CEV overstates it here ; *** fixed ellipsed proposition, added notes, and other things. (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu su sama deng dia cap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">itu su sama deng dia cap dia pung bini, parampuan barsina. Deng kalo ada laki-laki laen kawin ame sang itu parampuan, na, dong dua su maen serong tu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 19:9, Markus 10:11-12, Lukas 16:18, 1 Korintus 7:10-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang so'al angka janji [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about taking up promises [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />&lt;&lt;Bosong su tau ba'i Musa pung atoran yang dia kasi tau sang kotong pung nene-moyang dong bilang, &lt;Kalo lu angka janji pake sumpa deng Tuhan Allah pung nama, na, lu su ta'ika deng itu janji.&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl know Gf Musa's regulation which he told to our-inc ancestors saying, &lt;If you take up a promise using an oath with God's name, na, you are tied/bound to that promise.&gt;</bt><note reference="5:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:12, Daftar Sensus 30:2, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 23:21</note><v n="34" />Ma Beta kasi tau bagini: kalo lu angka janji, na, jang pake sumpa. Jang sumpa pake sorga pung nama, tagal sorga tu, Tuhan Allah pung tampa tenga.<bt>But I tell (you) like this: if/when you take up/establish a promise, na, don't do it by swearing an oath. Don't oath using heaven's name, because heaven, is God's residing place.</bt><note reference="5:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yakobis 5:12, Yesaya 66:1, Mateos 23:22</note><v n="35" />Jang sumpa pake bumi pung nama, tagal bumi tu Tuhan Allah pung alas kaki. Deng jang sumpa pake Yerusalem pung nama, tagal Yerusalem tu, Raja Bésar pung kota.<bt>Don't oath using the earth's name, because earth is God's footpad. And don't oath using Yerusalem name, because Yerusalem is the Big/Important King's city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** name added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** name added (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 66:1, Lagu Puji dong 48:3</note><v n="36" />Jang sumpa deng bosong pung kapala. Te bosong sonde ada pung kuasa ko parenta rambu satu daon ko jadi itam ko puti.<bt>Don't oath with your-pl head/s. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl do not have power/authority to command one strand of hair to become black or white. [NOTE to daughter translations: Make sure that /kapala/ here is linked to body, not head of social group (which could be implied by context above).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Jadi kalo bosong mau angka janji bilang, &lt;hoo&gt;, na, kasi tau bilang, &lt;hoo&gt; sa. Ma kalo sonde, na, bilang &lt;sonde&gt; sa. Kalo bosong bilang lebe dari itu, na, itu su ba'akar dari setan.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), if you want to take up a promise saying &lt;hoo&gt;, then tell saying, &lt;hoo&gt;. But if not, then say &lt;sonde&gt;. If you say more than that, na, that is rooted/sourced in evil spirit/s.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** other than &gt; more than"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** other than &gt; more than (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang ko jang babalas jahat deng jahat, ma musti layani deng lebe bae lai [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches to not reciprocate evil with evil, but (one) must serve even better instead [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:29-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />&lt;&lt;Bosong su tau ba'i Musa pung atoran bilang, &lt;Kalo ada orang bekin rusak lu pung mata, na, balas bekin rusak dia pung mata. Deng kalo ada orang bekin rubu lu pung gigi, na, balas bekin rubu dia pung gigi ju.&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl know Gf Musa's regulation saying, &lt;If a person ruins/destroys your eyes, then reciprocate ruining his eye. And if a person knocks out your tooth/teeth, na, reciprocate knocking out his tooth/teeth also.&gt;</bt><note reference="5:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 21:24, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 24:20, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 19:21</note><v n="39" />Ma Beta kasi tau bagini: jang balas jahat deng jahat. Kalo orang tampeleng lu pung pipi sablá, na, kasi tenga ko dia tampeleng pipi yang laen lai.<bt>But I tell (you) like this: don't reciprocate evil with evil. If a person slaps your one side check, na, permit it so he slaps your other cheek as well.</bt><v n="40" />Kalo ada orang yang mau bekin parkara deng lu, ko mau ame lu pung baju, na, kasi pi lu pung baju panas lai.<bt>If there is a person who wants to have a litigation/ argument with you, in order to take your shirt, then give away your jacket (for warmth) as well. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure /ko/ here is understood as “purpose”, and not “or”.]</bt><v n="41" />Kalo ada tantara satu paksa sang lu, ko jalan pikol bawa dia pung barang satu kilometer, na, pikol bawa tarús sampe dua kilometer.<bt>If there is an army person forcing you to walk carrying his thing/s one kilometre, na, carry take it on until two kilometres. [EXEG: Gk lexeme implies compelled by a soldier, as in NLT &amp; CEV.]</bt><v n="42" />Kalo ada orang minta lu pung barang apa, na, kasi pi sa. Deng kalo ada orang yang mau pinjam lu pung barang apa, na, kasi pi sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>If there is a person requesting anything you might have, na, just give it. And if there is a person who wants to borrow anything you might have, na, just give it.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang ko sayang orang yang binci sang kotong [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people to love people who hate us-inc [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:27-28, 32-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />&lt;&lt;Bosong su dengar orang bilang, &lt;Sayang sang lu pung sodara, deng binci orang yang binci sang lu.&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl have heard people say, &lt;Love your sibling, and hate people who hate you.&gt;</bt><note reference="5:43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18</note><v n="44" />Ma Beta kasi tau bagini: lu musti sayang sang orang yang binci sang lu. Deng minta ko Tuhan kasi berkat sang orang yang bekin sangsara sang lu.<bt>But I tell like this: you must love people who hate you. And request so that the Lord gives blessing to people who cause suffering to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** remove “want to”"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** remove “want to”</Message></Annotation><v n="45" />Kalo lu bekin bagitu, na, lu kasi tunju bilang, lu ni Bapa di sorga pung ana. Tagal Dia bekin matahari basinar kasi orang bae, deng Dia ju bekin matahari basinar kasi orang jahat. Dia ju kasi turun ujan kasi orang yang bekin iko Dia pung parenta sama-sama deng orang yang malawan Dia pung parenta.<bt>If you do like that, na, you show that, you are Father in heaven's child. Because He made/makes the sun shine for good people, and He also makes the sun shine for evil people. He also sends down rain for people who do according to his command/s together with people who oppose his command/s.</bt><v n="46" />Jadi, kalo lu cuma sayang sang orang yang sayang sang lu, na, lu kira Tuhan Allah musti balas deng berkat kasi sang lu, ko? Sonde! Te orang jahat ju sayang dong pung tamán yang sayang sang dong.<bt>So (consequently), if you only love people who love you, then you think God has to reciprocate with blessing to you, ko [+tag question]? No! Cuz (elaboration) evil people also love their friends who love them.</bt><v n="47" />Jadi, kalo lu cuma kasi saloom sang lu pung tamán, na, dia pung lebe apa? Te orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan Allah ju bekin bagitu.<bt>So (consequently), if you only give peace.greeting to your friend, na, what is the specialness of that? Cuz (elaboration) people who do not believe God also act like that.</bt><v n="48" />Jadi inga, é! Lu pung Bapa di sorga sayang samua orang. Jadi lu ju musti bekin iko bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) remember! Your Father in heaven loves all people. So you must also do/act like that!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="5:48" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:2, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 18:13</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar ko tolong orang susa dong [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches to help people in difficulty [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Yesus ajar tarús bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga, é! Jang iko-iko agama pung atoran ko biar orang puji-puji sang bosong. Te kalo bosong bekin bagitu, na, bosong pung Bapa di sorga sonde akan kasi bosong pung upa apa-apa.<bt>Yesus continued to teach saying, &lt;&lt;Remember! Don't just keep [blindly] following religion's regulations, so that people praise and praise you-pl. Cuz (elaboration) if you do like that, na, your Father in heaven will not give you any reward (whatsoever).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bosong pung Bapa di sorga sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">bosong pung Bapa di sorga sonde akan balas apa-apa kasi sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Kalo bosong mau tolong orang kasian dong, na, jang pi badodol di mana-mana. Te kalo bosong bekin bagitu, na, bosong su sama ke orang yang omong laen bekin laen. Dong suka pasiar pi ruma sambayang ko biar orang puji sang dong bilang, &lt;Awii, ini orang ni, hebat mati, ó!&gt; Beta omong yang batúl! Deng makan puji bagitu, dong su tarima abis dong pung upa.<bt>If you-pl want to help poor/pitiful people, na, don't go talking about it all over the place. Cuz (elaboration) if you do like that, well you are like people who speak one thing and do another. They like to go out to the worship houses so that people will praise them saying, &lt;Awii [+impressed] these people here, are really amazing!&gt; I'm telling the truth! By eating praise like that [=idiom], they have completely received their reward/compensation.</bt><v n="3" />Jadi, kalo bosong mau tolong orang kasian dong, na, jang kasi tau sapa-sapa, é!<bt>So (consequently), if you-pl want to help poor people, then don't tell anyone, é!</bt><v n="4" />Deng bagitu, orang di ini dunya sonde tau. Ma bosong pung Bapa di sorga yang tau apa yang bosong bekin diam-diam tu. Nanti Dia balas sang bosong deng berkat bam-banya.&gt;&gt;<bt>By doing like that, people in this world do not know. But your Father in heaven is the one who knows that which you are doing in secret there. Later He will reciprocate you with many-many blessings.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang sambayang [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people to praying [\s2] [NOTE to daughter translations: because local languages often don't distinguish directionality between learning/teaching, make sure “people” is object to avoid reading of “Jesus learns to pray” :-) ]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 11:2-4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />&lt;&lt;Waktu bosong sambayang, na, jang bekin diri sama ke orang yang omong laen bekin laen. Dong suka pi pasiar di jalan rame, deng badiri di dalam ruma sambayang, ko biar orang banya lia deng puji-puji sang dong bilang, &lt;Awii! Dong ni, orang barisi, ó!&gt; Ma dengar, é! Deng makan puji bagitu, dong su tarima abis dong pung upa.<bt>&lt;&lt;When you-pl pray, na, don't make yourself like the people who say one thing and do another. They like to stroll about on the busy street/s, and stand in the worship house/s, so that many people see and praise and praise them saying, &lt;Awii! [+impressed] They are clean/holy/pure people!&gt; But listen up! By eating praise like that, they have completely received their reward/compensation.</bt><note reference="6:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 18:10-14</note><v n="6" />Ma bosong sonde bole bagitu. Kalo bosong sambayang, na, maso pi dalam kamar ko tutu pintu. Ais sambayang diam-diam pi sang bosong pung Bapa. Biar orang laen sonde lia, ma bosong pung Bapa yang lia. Nanti Dia balas kasi sang bosong deng berkat bam-banya.<bt>But you-pl may not do/be like that. If/when you pray, na, enter into a/the room to shut the door. And.then pray quietly/secretly to your Father. Even though other people do not see, nevertheless your Father sees. Later He will reciprocate giving to you many-many blessings.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00271C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Orang Yahudi sambayang<bt>A Yahudi person prays [NOTE to daughter translations: check if this works, or if /Cara orang Yahudi sambayang/ works better for your langauge.]</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Kalo bosong sambayang, na, jang omong bataputar pi-datang. Te orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah ju bisa sambayang bagitu. Dong pikir kata, Tuhan Allah suka dengar dong pung sambayang yang panjang lalolak tu.<bt>If/when you-pl pray, na, don't use flowery indirect words (lit: twisting here and there). Cuz (elaboration) people who do not know God also can pray like that. They think that God likes to hear those prayers of theirs which are really long (=roughly equivalent to ‘mile long prayers’)</bt><v n="8" />Jang bekin iko sama ke dong, é! Te biar bosong balóm minta apa-apa sang Bapa di sorga, ma Dia su tau memang apa yang bosong parlú.<bt>Don't act doing the same as them! Cuz (elaboration) even if/though you still have not requested anything from Father in heaven, nevertheless He already knows beforehand that which you need.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added biar (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added biar (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Jadi, kalo sambayang, na, pake conto bagini:<bt>So (consequently), if/when praying, na, use an example like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Bapa di sorga! Bapa pung nama paling barisi.<bt>&lt;Father in heaven! Father's name is most clean/holy/pure.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Biar samua orang angka nae tinggi-tinggi Bapa pung nama yang hebat.<bt>May all people lift up high the name/reputation of Father's which is amazing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Biar Bapa jadi Raja kasi samua orang!<bt>May Father be/become King for all people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Biar samua orang bekin iko Bapa pung parenta di ini dunya,<bt>May all people do according to Father's commands here on earth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke Bapa pung ana bua dong bekin iko Bapa pung parenta di sorga.<bt>like Father's underlings do according to Father's commands in heaven.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Bapa tolong kasi sang botong makanan yang cukup tiap hari.<bt>Father help/please give us food which is enough every day. [EXEG: TB and Indonesian liturgical Lord's Prayer misses Gk /epiousios/ “daily”. Q: where did the element of ‘today’ go? A: Kedua istilah Yunani memungkinkan makna ganda. Catatan kaki pada: bhs Indonesia: BIS; bhs Inggris: NRSV, NLT1/2, CEV, NET, NASB, ESV, REB, TEV; bhs Spanyol: NVI, VP masing-masing mengaku paling sedikit 2-3 susunan yg berbeda yg dapat diterima. Ex.Summ. terima lebih dari itu. Jadi bukan satu benar dan yang lain salah. Tantangan bagi kita adalah kita menonjolkan unsur-unsur yang mana? NLT2 mencerminkan beberapa hal yg baik. “Give us today the food for today.” 1) ‘bread’ = food (metonymy); 2) dari kedua istilah Yunani, ‘today … today’ atau ‘today … every day’ mempunyai dasar yg lebih kuat daripada ‘today … tomorrow’; Ex. Summ. mencatat juga: ‘daily food’ = the food we need. Kupang versi lama (yang dibahas dengan Om Max dan Om Mus dong): Bapa tolong kasi sang botong ini hari makanan yang cukup tiap hari. Menurut UNS dong, itu kaku, dengan sedikit kurang masuk akal atau paksa bahasa Kupang, karena setiap hari termasuk hari ini juga. Jadi dengan persetujuan 2-3 konsultan, unsur ‘ini hari’ dijadikan tersirat.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Botong minta Bapa hapus buang botong pung sala-sala dong,<bt>We request Father to wipe away/*forgive our wrongs,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke botong ju lupa buang orang pung sala yang dong bekin sang botong.<bt>the same as we-exc also completely forget people's wrongs which they do to us.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="13" />Bapa, jaga ko botong sonde bekin jahat.<bt>Father guard/take.care. so that we don't do evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng kasi salamat sang botong, dari setan pung kuasa.<bt>And *save/rescue us, from evil spirit's power.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">[Te Bapa tu, Raja yang paling kuasa deng paling hebat.<bt>[Cuz (elaboration) Father is King who is most powerful and most amazing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bapa yang pegang parenta tarús-tarús.<bt>Father is the one who holds rule/authority continually-continually/forever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Botong pung sambayang, bagitu sa Bapa. Amin.]&gt;<bt>Our prayer, is just like that Father. Amin.]&gt; [DISCOURSE: natural RL closure.]</bt><note reference="6:13b" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua sonde tulis tamba ini bagian ahir ni.<bt>The oldest Greek language writings don't write adding this last part here.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma dengar, é! Kalo bosong lupa buang orang pung sala sang bosong, nanti bosong pung Bapa di sorga ju hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>But listen up! If you completely forget people's wrongs against you-pl, your Father in heaven will also wipe away your wrongs.</bt><v n="15" />Ma kalo bosong sonde mau lupa buang orang pung sala sang bosong, nanti bosong pung Bapa ju sonde lupa bosong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But if you don't want to forget throw away people's wrongs against you, your Father also will not forget your wrongs.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="6:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 11:25-26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang so'al puasa [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people about fasting [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />&lt;&lt;Kalo bosong sambayang deng puasa, na, jang bekin muka masnana'ok sama ke orang yang omong laen bekin laen. Te dong bekin bagitu ko biar orang puji sang dong bilang, &lt;Awii! Dong ni, orang barisi, ó!&gt; Ma dengar, é! Deng makan puji bagitu, dong su tarima abis dong pung upa.<bt>&lt;&lt;If/when you-pl pray and fast, na, don't make your face sour like the people who say one thing and do another. [NOTE: Q: When do people "not eat"? A: When they are angry at their wives. :-) So Arabic loan used to carry sense of fasting as a religious activity--the whole country is effected by Muslim fasting month.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if /masnana'ok/ is not known by your team, we're looking for the range of the Greek word “sad, gloomy, miserable, dismal, somber, sullen”. Note NLT goes to “do not make it obvious”, but you'd have to check what UNSs think that means.] Cuz (elaboration) they do like that for people to praise them saying, &lt;Awii! [+impressed] They are holy/clean/pure people!&gt; But listen up! By eating praise like that, they have completely received their reward/compensation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="masnana'ok ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">masnana'ok =</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ma kalo bosong puasa, na, cuci bosong pung muka barisi-barisi, deng sisir rambu bae-bae!<bt>But if/when you-pl fast, na, wash your faces clean, and comb your hair well!</bt><v n="18" />Jadi nanti orang lia sang bosong, dong sonde tau bilang, bosong ada puasa. Ma bosong pung Bapa yang tau. Nanti Dia balas kasi sang bosong deng berkat bam-banya.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) later people see you, they will not know that you are fasting. But your Father is the one who knows. Later He will reciprocate/reward you with many-many blessings.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang so'al kumpul harta di sorga [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people about gathering wealth in heaven [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 12:33-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />&lt;&lt;Jang karjá karás ko kumpul harta bam-banya di ini dunya. Te fufuk deng karat nanti bekin rusak sang dong. Deng pancuri ju datang bongkar ko angka bawa.<bt>&lt;&lt;Don't work hard in order to gather lots of wealth here on earth. Cuz (elaboration) moths/ wood.boring.insects and rust will later destroy them. And thieves will also come dismantle and pick it up take it away.</bt><note reference="6:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yakobis 5:2-3</note><v n="20" />Ma lebe bae bosong karjá karás ko kumpul harta bam-banya di sorga. Te di sana fufuk deng karat sonde bisa bekin rusak. Deng pancuri ju sonde bisa datang bongkar ko angka bawa.<bt>But it's better you-pl work hard to gather lots of wealth in heaven. Cuz (elaboration) there moths and rust cannot destroy. And thieves also cannot come dismantle and pick it up take it away.</bt><v n="21" />Bosong simpan bosong pung harta di mana, pasti bosong pung hati ju makaditi di sana.&gt;&gt;<bt>Where you-pl store your wealth, surely your liver/s also sticks/glues there.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang so'al idop dalam taráng [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people about living in the light [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 11:34-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />&lt;&lt;Orang pung mata, sama ke lampu yang bekin taráng dia pung dalam hati. Kalo dia pung mata taráng, na, dia iko jalan idop yang bae, sama ke orang yang jalan dalam taráng.<bt>&lt;&lt;A person's eye, is like a lamp which lights up his liver (=heart). If/when his eye is clear/light, na, he follows the good life path, like a person who walks in the light. [EXEG: Just a note to alert you all to an emerging exegesis that we're not following yet, but is gaining discussion and support. “with a good/clear eye” is a Hebrew idiom meaning “generous”. These days the Red Cross goes around Israel saying, “Give with a good eye.”]</bt><v n="23" />Ma kalo dia pung mata kabur, na, dia sonde iko jalan yang bae, sama ke orang yang jalan raba-raba dalam galáp. Jadi, kalo itu taráng yang ada di bosong pung hati su jadi galáp, na, bosong ju idop dalam galáp.&gt;&gt;<bt>But if/when his eye is hazy/blurred, na, he does not follow the good path, like a person who walks groping around in the dark. So (consequently), if/when that light which is in your-pl livers has become dark, na, you-pl also live in the dark.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: ‘dark’ tends to symbolise ‘ignorance’, and can extend into the ‘invisible spiritual realm’, sometimes being extended to ‘evil’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang ko jang bapikir-pikir mau idop karmana [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches people to not keep thinking (worry about) how you're going to live [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 16:13, 12:22-31)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />&lt;&lt;Orang sonde bisa karjá batúl-batúl kasi dua bos, tagal dia nanti suka sang bos yang satu, lebe dari bos yang laen. Bisa ju dia iko bos yang satu, ma dia sonde toe deng bos yang laen. Tagal itu, lu sonde bisa bilang, &lt;Tuhan tu, yang hak parenta sang beta,&gt; kalo lu su bekin doi jadi lu pung bos.<bt>&lt;&lt;A person cannot really/successfully work for two bosses, because he will later like one boss, more than the other boss. It can also be that he follows/obeys the one boss, but he doesn't care.about/pay.attention to the other boss. Because of that, you-sg may not say, &lt;The Lord is the one with say-so/command rights over me,&gt; if you have made money be your-sg boss. [NOTE: adjusted to “the one with say-so/command rights” to reduce occurrences of ‘Bos’, which is problematic for some older speakers.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Andia ko Beta kasi tau bagini: jang repot deng bapikir, beta mau idop karmana, beta mau makan apa, minum apa, pake apa? Bosong kira idop tu, cuma buat makan sa? Deng badan tu, cuma buat pake baju sa? Bukan bagitu.<bt>That's why I tell like this: don't be all pre-occupied/fussed.over.details and think/worry, how am I going to live, what will I eat, what [will I] drink? Do you think that life is only just for eating? And the body is only just for wearing clothes? It's not like that.</bt><v n="26" />Coba lia itu burung yang tarbáng di udara dong. Dong sonde repot batanam deng bakoru ko simpan makanan dalam gudang. Ma bosong pung Bapa di sorga piara sang dong tarús. Dia ju tantu bisa piara sang bosong lebe dari ini lai. Jadi pikir bae-bae dolo. Te Dia nilei bosong lebe dari itu burung dong.<bt>Have a look at the birds which fly in the air. [Note to MTTs: should this be air or sky?] They don't get all fussed/pre-occupied planting and picking in order to store food in the storage.house. But your-pl Father in heaven takes care of them continually. Because of that, He also can surely take care of you-pl more than that. So (consequently) think carefully about this (=imperative). Cuz (elaboration) He values you-pl, more than those birds.</bt><v n="27" />Kalo orang badiri di muka carmín, ais dia repot deng dia pung diri, dia bisa bekin tamba tinggi dia pung badan, ko? Sonde bisa!<bt>If/when a person stands in front of a mirror, then he fusses/gets pre-occupied with himself/his body, can he make taller his body, [+tag question]? He can't! [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK collocations. Taller? or longer?] [EXEG: Q: gambaran tentang “badiri di muka cermin” tidak ada di teks Yunani dan teks2 bahasa Inggeris, TB, BIS. Hanya ada di teks Kupang. Ini gambaran dari mana? A: Benar. Tidak ada dlm teks Yunani atau Inggeris. Masalah yang kami temukan dalam beberapa bahasa ialah ayat 26 bicarakan makanan, dan ayat 28 bicarakan pakaian. Kedua-duanya konkret. Ayat 27 bicarakan hal abstrak, yaitu memperpanjang umur tanpa gambaran seperti burung atau bunga. UNS dong bingung karena tidak ada tanda dlm discourse untuk “shift/change topic”, sehingga ada yang pikir ayat 27 masih bicarakan makanan. Padahal connector bhs Yunani membawa tanda “shift topic”. Satu konsultan tanya UNS dong, “Dalam konteks/kegiatan yang bagaimana orang Kupang/Timor/Rote sering pikirkan status hidup?” Yang dapat kesepakatan ialah “waktu berdiri di muka cermin”. Itu juga diterima oleh beberapa konsultan lain. Kalau UNS pikir ayat itu jelas tanpa frase tsb, boleh dicabut. Tetapi hati-hati, karena mereka tidak lagi “fresh”. Jangan diputus MTT.]</bt><v n="28" />Kalo sonde, na, akurang ko bosong barepot ko pikir-pikir so'al pakean lai? Pi lia coba itu bunga bakung di padang. Dong sonde putar banáng, deng sonde tanún kaen.<bt>If not, na, why do you-pl get.all.fussed/preoccupied thinking about clothes again? Go have a look at the <span class="Italic">bakung</span> flowers in the field. They don't spin thread, and don't weave cloth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma dengar bae-bae, ó! Raja Soleman pung pakean yang paling mewa ju, sonde bisa lawan itu bunga dong pung bagus.<bt>But listen carefully! Even King Soleman's fanciest clothes, cannot oppose/compete with those flower's beauty. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><note reference="6:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 10:4-7, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 9:3-6</note><v n="30" />Te Tuhan Allah taro hati di bunga yang cuma idop ini hari, ais beso mati ko orang buang pi dalam api. Kalo Dia bekin bagitu, Dia ju pasti kasi pake sang bosong lebe dari itu bunga dong. Jadi, akurang ko bosong sonde parcaya batúl-batúl sang Dia?<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God pays attentions to flowers which live only today, then tomorrow die so people throw them into the fire. If/when He does like that, He will also certainly clothe you-pl better than those flowers. So (consequently), why don't you-pl truly believe/trust in Him?</bt><v n="31" />Jadi sonde usa repot bapikir bilang, &lt;Botong mau makan apa?&gt; ko, &lt;Botong mau minum apa?&gt; ko, &lt;Botong mau pake apa?&gt;<bt>So (consequently) [you] don't need to get.all.fussed thinking/worrying, &lt;What will we eat?&gt; or, &lt;What will we drink?&gt; or, &lt;What will we wear?&gt;</bt><v n="32" />Orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, dong banting tulang ko mau coba dapa itu hal samua. Ma bosong jang bagitu, te bosong pung Bapa di sorga su tau samua yang bosong parlú.<bt>People who do not believe in God, they work throwing down bones (=work really hard) to try to get all those things. But you shouldn't do like that, cuz (elaboration) your-pl Father in heaven already knows everything that you need.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dong banting tulang ko cari ame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">dong banting tulang ko cari ame itu hal samua.</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ma bosong musti kasi jalan Dia pung karjá dolo, deng musti iko Dia pung parenta dolo, ais nanti Dia kasi tamba samua hal yang bosong parlú.<bt>But you-pl must carry.out His work first/primarily, and must follow His commands first/primarily, and then He will add all the things which you need.</bt><v n="34" />Jadi jang repot bapikir deng apa yang bosong parlú beso. Te beso ada dia pung repot laen lai. Ini hari pung susa su cukup.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), don't get all fussed/pre-occupied thinking/worrying about what you-pl need tomorrow. Cuz (elaboration) tomorrow has it's own pre-occupations yet again. Today's difficulties are already enough/sufficient.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar ko jang maen tudu orang [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches to not criticize people [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:37-38, 41-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />&lt;&lt;Bosong jang tudu orang, ko biar Tuhan jang tudu sang bosong.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl don't criticize/accuse people, so that the Lord doesn't criticize/accuse you.</bt><v n="2" />Bosong nilei orang karmana, na, nanti Tuhan Allah nilei sang bosong bagitu ju. Bosong ukur orang laen pung sala karmana, nanti Tuhan Allah ukur sang bosong bagitu ju.<bt>However you value/evaluate people, na, God will evaluate you like that also. However you measure other people's wrongs, God will measure you like that also.</bt><note reference="7:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 4:24</note><v n="3" />Te lu suka tanda orang pung sala kici ana sa, ma lu pung sala yang bésar, lu anggap ke sonde ada sa. Itu sama ke lu lia abu satu titik di lu pung tamán pung mata. Padahal ada balok bésar pele lu pung mata, ma lu sonde rasa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you-sg like to note/make.a.big.deal.about a person's teeny-tiny little wrong, but your-sg wrong which is big, you-sg consider it as if it doesn't even exist. That's the same as if you see/saw a dot of dust in your friend's eye. However there is a big block obstructing your eye, but you don't feel it.</bt><v n="4" />Karmana ko lu barani omong bilang, &lt;Konco! Mari ko beta tolong lap kasi kaluar itu abu dari lu pung mata biji dolo.&gt; Padahal lu sandiri sonde bisa lia apa-apa, te ada balok pele lu pung mata na.<bt>How is it that you dare to speak saying, ‘Friend/Mate! Come so that I can help wipe out that dust from your eyeball (=polite imperative).’ However you-sg yourself can't see anything, cuz (elaboration) there is a block/wood beam which is obstructing your eye (obviously = you should know that).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="konco = some see as fully"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">konco = some see as fully Kupang, some see as Jawa</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Woi! Dasar lu tu, orang muka-balakang batúl! Tolong doo! Angka buang itu balok dari lu pung mata sandiri dolo, baru lu bisa lia, ko tolong lap buang abu sapo'ong ana dari lu pung kawan pung mata.<bt>Woi! [+challenge] The basis/foundation of you-sg is a person who truly front to back. Please/Help [yourself] (=imperative)! Pick up throw away that block/beam from your own eye first, only then you can see in order to help wipe away that tiny piece of dust from that eye of your friend.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Jang ajar hal barisi so'al Tuhan, kasi tukang ba'olok. Tagal dong tu, sama ke anjing jahat yang nanti bale datang ko saráng sang bosong. Dong ju bodo sama ke babi. Kalo orang kasi kalong mutiara yang mahal, na, dia sonde toe! Te dia cuma tau inja-inja sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Don't teach clean/holy thing/s about God2 to habitual mockers. Because they are like evil dog/s who later come back to attack you. They are also stupid like a pig. If a person gives an expensive pearl necklace, na, he doesn't care! Cuz (elaboration) he only knows to just step all over it.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk chiasmus here unravelled. Use pearls if it works. NOTE also still implicit the double whammy that pigs and dogs are not kosher for Jews.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang ko sambayang sonde putus-putus [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches to pray without stopping [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 11:9-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />&lt;&lt;Kalo bosong sambayang,<bt>&lt;&lt;If/when you-pl pray,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">minta tarús sang Tuhan;<bt>keep requesting to the Lord:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nanti Dia kasi.<bt>later He will give [what you ask].</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo cari tarús;<bt>If/when [you] look for/search continually;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti Dia kasi tunju jalan.<bt>later He will show the path.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo eki tarús;<bt>If [you] call.out continually; [NOTE to daughter translations: in many local cultures, knocking is done by thieves checking to see if anyone is home. Even in the cities, calling out is the norm, especially if the person is known to the household.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti Dia buka pintu.<bt>later He will open the door.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Te samua orang yang minta tarús sang Tuhan,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) everyone who requests continually from the Lord,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti tarima.<bt>later [they] receive.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yang cari tarús,<bt>Those who look for/search continually,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dapa.<bt>later [they] obtain.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yang eki tarús,<bt>Those who call.out continually,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti Dia buka pintu.<bt>later He opens the door.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Bosong pikir coba! Kalo ada ana yang minta roti, tantu dia pung bapa sonde kasi batu, aa?<bt>You-pl have a think (=mild imperative)! If there is a child who requests bread, surely his father won't give a rock, right?</bt><v n="10" />Ko, kalo ana minta ikan, bapa sonde kasi ular!<bt>Or if the child requests fish, the father doesn't give a snake!</bt><v n="11" />Bosong pung Bapa di sorga tu, memang bae batúl. Jadi kalo manusia yang jahat macam bosong sa, suka kasi barang yang bae sang bosong pung ana dong, apalai bosong pung Bapa! Dia tantu kasi apa yang bosong minta.<bt>Your-pl Father in heaven is truly very good. So if people who are evil just like you, like to give things which are good to their children, even more so your Father! He certainly will give what you request.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jadi, apa yang lu mau orang laen bekin kasi sang lu, na, lu musti bekin bagitu kasi sang dia ju. Tagal ini ni, dasar dari samua yang ba'i Musa deng Tuhan Allah pung jubir laen dong su ajar memang dari dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), what you-sg want another person to do for you, na, you must do like that for him also. Because this here is the foundation of all that which Gf Musa and God's spokespersons have taught beforehand from long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="7:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 6:31</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang so'al pintu yang sampít [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about the door/gate which is narrow [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 13:24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />&lt;&lt;Kalo orang mau maso sorga, na, dia musti jalan lewat pintu yang sampít. Te ada jalan yang gampang deng pintu yang lebar ju, yang orang banya dong suka lewat. Ma awas, ó! Te jalan bagitu yang bawa orang pi naraka, ko dong tapisa buang dari Tuhan.<bt>&lt;&lt;If/when a person wants to enter heaven, then he must go/walk passing through the door which is narrow. Cuz (elaboration) there is also a way/path which is easy and a door which is wide, which many people like to pass by on. But be careful! Cuz (elaboration) it is path like that which brings/leads people to hell, so they are separated off/cut off from God2. [EXEG: Gk is word for ‘perish’, see note at John 3:16.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">***</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Orang yang mau maso sorga musti iko itu jalan yang susa, deng maso itu pintu yang sampít. Te biar cuma sadiki orang sa yang jalan di situ, ma jalan sampít bagitu yang bawa orang pi Tuhan.&gt;&gt;<bt>People who want to enter heaven must follow that way/path which is difficult and enter that door which is narrow. Cuz (elaboration) even though it's only a few people who go/walk there, nevertheless it is the narrow path like that which brings/leads people to God.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar orang ko jang iko sang tukang putar-balek [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches to not follow the habitual twisters-turners (=deceivers) [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:43-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />&lt;&lt;Ati-ati deng tukang tipu yang angka diri bilang, dong tu Tuhan pung jubir. Te dong bekin diri pura-pura bae sama ke domba. Padahal dong tu jahat, sama ke anjing utan yang datang makan domba.<bt>&lt;&lt;Be careful of the con.artists who elevate/promote themselves saying, they are God's *spokesperson. Cuz (elaboration) they make themselves pretending to be good as sheep. However they are evil, the same as a forest/wild dog who comes to eat sheep. [EXEG: Adding /mau/ would make it narrower than the Greek present middle passive “who come to you in sheep's clothing”. In that sense it is an on-going state of affairs, so our languages reflect this best by NOT marking it for aspect. The Greek implies they are already in your midst and doing this, as a general ongoing state of affairs.]</bt><v n="16" />Karmana bosong bisa kanál orang yang pura-pura? Lia sa dari apa yang dong bekin. Sama ke orang lia bua, ko kanál itu bua pung pohon. Bua yang bae, sonde kaluar dari pohon yang sonde bae.<bt>How can you-pl know/recognize those pretending people? Just look at what they do. The same as a person looks at fruit, in order to know/identify that fruit's tree. Fruit that is good, does not come out of a tree which is not good.</bt><v n="17" />Te pohon yang bae kasi kaluar bua yang bae. Ma pohon yang sonde bae, kasi kaluar bua yang sonde bae.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) a tree which is good produces fruit which is good. But a tree which is not good produces fruit which is not good.</bt><v n="18" />Sonde ada pohon yang bae yang kasi kaluar bua yang sonde bae. Deng sonde ada pohon yang sonde bae yang kasi kaluar bua yang bae.<bt>There are no good trees which produce fruit that is bad. And there are no trees which are not good which produce fruit that is good.</bt><v n="19" />Pohon yang kasi kaluar bua yang sonde bae, tantu dong datang potong ko lempar buang maso pi dalam api.<bt>A tree which produces fruit that is not good, certainly they come cut it in order to. throw it out into the fire. [NOTE to daughter translations: /Orang/ works too, but isn't quite as good. Check it stylistically. In linguistics this non-referential 3p (doesn't refer to anybody in the story), is one strategy that many languages in eastern Indonesia (and other parts of the world) use to demote the actor, and have something kind of like an English agentless passive “then that tree is cut down and thrown into the fire…”]</bt><note reference="7:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:10, Lukas 3:9</note><v n="20" />Bagitu ju deng itu jubir pura-pura dong. Bosong bisa kanál sang dong dari dong pung bekin-bekin.&gt;&gt;<bt>Like that also with those pretending spokespersons. You-pl can recognise them from their deeds.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: RL lexeme implies negative value/connotations associated with their ‘deeds’.]</bt><note reference="7:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:33</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau so'al orang yang cuma subu Tuhan Allah di bibir sa [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus tells about people who just mention God with their lips only [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 13:25-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />&lt;&lt;Nanti ada orang yang sapa sang Beta bilang, &lt;Bos!&gt;, andia yang hak parenta sang dong. Ma dong cuma subu di bibir sa. Nanti Tuhan Allah di sorga tola buang sang dong. Te cuma orang yang iko batúl-batúl Dia pung mau sa, yang Dia tarima ame jadi Dia pung orang.<bt>&lt;&lt;Later there will be people who address Me saying, &lt;Bos!&gt;, that is the one with say-so/ordering rights over them. But they only mention/say just with (their) lips. God in heaven will reject throw them away. Cuz (elaboration), only just people who truly follow His will, whom He receives/accepts to become His people. [NOTE to daughter translations: Repetition of vocative is not natural in these lgs.]</bt><v n="22" />Nanti waktu hari kiamat, banya orang mangaku bilang, Beta ni yang hak parenta sang dong. Dong kokoe sang Beta bilang, &lt;Bos, é! Botong su pi kasi tasiar Bos pung ajaran. Botong ju usir setan dong pake Bos pung nama. Deng botong bekin tanda heran macam-macam pake Bos pung kuasa.&gt;<bt>Later when at end of the world, many people will acknowledge saying, I here am the one with say-so/command rights over them. They will plead with Me saying, &lt;Boss, é! We-exc have gone to spread around Boss's (=your) teaching. We also expelled evil spirits using Boss's name. And we have done all sorts of amazing things (*miracles) using Boss's power.&gt; [NOTE: adjusted to “the one with say-so/command rights” to reduce occurrences of ‘Bos’, which is problematic for some older speakers.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Biar dong maen kokoe sang Beta bagitu ju, ma nanti Beta kasi tau dong bilang, &lt;Bosong ni, sapa? Beta sonde kanál sang bosong, te bosong sonde idop iko Tuhan pung mau. Jadi iskarobis dari sini su!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Even if/though they keep trying to persuade Me like that, nevertheless I will tell them saying, &lt;Who are you-pl? I don't know you, cuz (elaboration) you don't live according to the Lord's will. So (consequently) get out of here (imperative)!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="7:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 6:9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar so'al orang yang pintar deng orang yang bodo [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about wise/smart people and stupid people [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:47-49)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />&lt;&lt;Orang yang datang dengar sang Beta, ais bekin iko Beta pung omong, dia sama ke orang yang pintar, yang kasi badiri dia pung ruma di atas fanderen batu.<bt>&lt;&lt;A person who comes to listen to Me, then does according to My speaking, he is like a smart/clever/wise person who erected/built his house on a rock foundation.</bt><v n="25" />Lama-lama ju ujan bésar turun sampe banjer datang. Angin kincang ju datang hantam itu ruma. Ma itu ruma sonde rubu, tagal dia badiri di atas fanderen batu yang kuat.<bt>Eventually big rain comes down until floods come. Strong winds also come and bash that house. But that house does not fall.down, because it stands on top of the stone foundation which was strong.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Orang yang datang dengar sang Beta, ma dia sonde bekin iko Beta pung omong, dia sama ke orang bodo yang kasi badiri dia pung ruma di atas pasir.<bt>A person who comes to listen to Me, then he does not do according to My speaking, he is like a stupid/ignorant person who erects/builds his house on top of sand.</bt><v n="27" />Lama-lama ju ujan bésar turun sampe banjer datang. Angin kincang ju datang hantam itu ruma. Ju itu ruma rubu buang sampe ancor-ancor.&gt;&gt;<bt>Eventually big rain comes down until floods come. Strong winds also come bash that house. Then that house falls apart until it completely destroyed.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang dong taheran-heran dengar Tuhan Yesus pung ajaran yang hebat<bt>People are amazed hearing the impressive teaching of the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus omong abis bagitu, ju samua orang dong taheran-heran dengar Dia pung ajaran,<bt>Yesus finished speaking like that, then all the people were amazed hearing his teaching,</bt><v n="29" />te Dia tau batúl-batúl itu ajaran pung isi. Dia pung cara ajar tu, sonde sama deng dong pung guru agama dong.<bt>cuz (elaboration) He really knew/understood that teaching's contents. That way of teaching of His, was not the same as their religion teachers (*scribes).</bt><note reference="7:28-29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 1:22, Lukas 4:32</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang panyaki kusta<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a person with leprosy disease</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:40-45; Lukas 5:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Yesus turun datang dari gunung, ju orang banya dong rame-rame pi iko sang Dia.<bt>Yesus came down from the mountain, then many people crowdedly/bustlingly followed Him.</bt><v n="2" />Takuju sa, ada satu orang panyaki kusta datang mangada sang Dia. Dia tikam lutut ko minta tolong sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Tolong sang beta dolo! Kalo mau, na, Bos bisa kasi ilang beta pung panyaki ni, ko biar orang jang noju sang beta lai, ju beta bisa sambayang lai dalam ruma ibadat.&gt;&gt;<bt>Suddenly/unexpectedly, a person sick with leprosy came facing Him. He knelt to request Yesus to help him saying, &lt;&lt;Boss! Help me! If (=you) want, Bos can make this sickness disappear, so that people are not repulsed at me anymore, and I can worship again in the house of prayer/worship.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: ‘clean’ from leprosy (from Leviticus) seems to have 3 facets: 1) health, 2) social, 3) spiritual/religious (God and worship). Here focus on social and religious, so as to not imply that lepers can't worship God in their hearts. CR]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus sorong tangan, ais sonto itu orang kusta, deng omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau sa! Lu bae su!&gt;&gt; Takuju sa, itu orang pung panyaki ilang memang.<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus extended his hand, then touched that person and spoke saying, &lt;&lt;I do want to! You be well (=imperative)!&gt;&gt; Unexpectedly/suddenly that person's illness disappeared right away.</bt><v n="4" />Ais Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga, é! Lu su bae, ma sonde bole kasi tau sapa-sapa. Lu musti iko ba'i Musa pung atoran dolo. Jadi pi di kapala agama, ko dia pareksa lu pung badan, biar dia tau lu pung panyaki su ilang batúl, ko sonde. Ais lu musti kasi persembahan tanda tarima kasi, ko orang samua tau bilang, lu su bae batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told him saying, &lt;&lt;Remember, é! You are well, but [you] may not tell anyone. You must follow Gf Musa's regulation first. So (consequently) go to the head of religion (*priest), in order for him to examine your body, so that he can know if your sickness has truly disapppeared, or not. Then you must give a thank-you offering, so that all people know that you are really healed/well.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** parenta &gt; atoran"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** parenta &gt; atoran</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 14:1-32</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu komandán tantara Roma pung ana karjá<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a Roma army commander's worker</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 7:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais itu, ju Yesus maso pi kampong Kapernaum. Di situ ada satu komandán tantara Roma yang datang ko mau minta tolong bilang,<bt>After that, then Yesus entered into Kapernaum village. There, there was a Roma army commander who came to request help saying,</bt><v n="6" />&lt;&lt;Bos, é! Beta pung ana karjá satu ada saki barát di ruma. Dia sonde bisa bangun dari koi, te dia ada sangsara mau mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Boss! One of my workers is very sick at home. He cannot get up from his bed, cuz (elaboration) he is suffering greatly.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae! Nanti Beta pi ko bekin bae sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Good/OK! Later I will go heal him.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma itu komandán bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Sonde usa cape-cape pi lai, te beta sonde pantas tarima sang Bos di beta pung ruma. Asal Bos omong sa dari sini, beta pung ana karjá tu, pasti bae memang.<bt>But that commander said, &lt;&lt;Boss! You don't need to get all tired going anymore, cuz (elaboration) I am not worthy to receive Boss in my house. As long as Boss/You just speaks it from here, that worker of mine, will surely be healed right away. [EXEG: TN points out that “not worthy” could be from 1) spiritual awareness (he is a sinner); 2) social sensitivity (he is a gentile, and doesn't want to ask a Jew to violate religious norms by coming into his house; of 3) both. So don't force the first reading. The “don't trouble yourself” is from Luke, not Matthew, but is left here for softening the social interaction.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Beta mangarti ini hal, tagal beta pung bos dong ada pung kuasa ko parenta sang beta. Deng beta ju ada pung kuasa ko parenta beta pung tantara dong. Kalo beta kasi parenta beta pung ana bua bilang, &lt;Pi sana!&gt; pasti dia pi. Kalo beta bilang, &lt;Datang sini!&gt; pasti dia datang. Deng kalo beta suru beta pung orang karjá bilang, &lt;Karjá ini!&gt; pasti dia bekin bagitu. Jadi asal Bos omong sa, pasti beta pung ana karjá tu, bae memang.&gt;&gt;<bt>I understand this matter, because my bosses have power/authority to order me. And I also have power to order my soldiers. If I order my underling saying, &lt;Go there!&gt; surely he goes. If I say, &lt;Come here!&gt; surely he comes. And if I order my worker saying, &lt;Do this!&gt; surely he does that. So (consequently), as long Boss just speaks, surely that worker of mine, will be healed straight away.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus heran. Dia omong sang itu orang banya yang ada iko deng Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heran, é! Su bagini lama, ma Beta balóm parná katumu satu orang Yahudi ju yang parcaya sama kuat ke ini orang Roma!<bt>Hearing like that, Yesus was amazed. He spoke to those many people who were following Him saying, &lt;&lt;Amazing, é! All this time, but [+contrary to expectation] I have not yet ever met even one Jewish person who believes equally as strong as this Roma person!</bt><v n="11" />Dengar, é! Te nanti ada banya orang luar sama ke ini orang Roma ni yang datang dari sablá matahari nae deng dari sablá matahari turun, ko dudu makan pesta sama-sama deng ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak deng ba'i Yakob dalam Tuhan Allah pung ruma di sorga.<bt>Listen! Cuz (elaboration) later there will be many outsiders (*gentiles) like this Roma person here who come from the east and from the west to sit eat a feast with Gf Abraham, Gf Isak, and Gf Yakob in God's house in heaven.</bt><note reference="8:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 13:29</note><v n="12" />Biar Tuhan su pili orang Yahudi ko jadi Dia pung orang, ma ada banya yang sonde toe sang Dia. Nanti Dia tola buang sang dong pi tampa galáp buta. Di situ dong manangis makarereu deng sangsara mati pung.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even though God has chosen Jewish people to become His people, nevertheless there are many who don't pay attention to/aren't concerned with/ignore Him. Later He will reject throw them away to a very dark place. There they will cry wailing with very great suffering.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Padahal &gt; Biar ; added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** Padahal &gt; Biar ; added banya (NLT) (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 22:13, 25:30, Lukas 13:28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Omong ais bagitu, ju Yesus kasi tau sang itu komandán bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak pulang su. Te itu ana karjá su bae, sama ke pak pung parcaya.&gt;&gt; Pas itu waktu ju, itu ana bae memang.<bt>Finishing speaking like that, then Yesus told that commander saying, &lt;&lt;Pak (=you, sir) go home (=imperative). Cuz (elaboration) that worker is healed, the same as what Pak believe.&gt;&gt; Exactly at that time then, that worker was healed straight away. [EXEG: TN “at that very hour: This does not refer to an hour of sixty minutes. It means that he was healed at the very same time that Jesus said these words.”] [NOTE to daughter translations: if this guy is high rank should Yesus address him as Lu or Pak? Be natural, don't force Malay etiquette.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang saki bam-banya<bt>The Lord Yesus heals many sick people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 1:29-34; Lukas 4:38-41)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais satu kali, Yesus pi di Petrus pung ruma. Dia lia Petrus pung mama mantu ada tidor di koi, te dia ada damám.<bt>Then one time Yesus went to Petrus' house. He saw Petrus' mother in law was sleeping on a bed, cuz (elaboration) she had a fever.</bt><v n="15" />Yesus pegang dia pung tangan, ju itu mamatua pung damám ilang memang. Ais dia bangun ko pi urus sang Yesus dong.<bt>Yesus held her hand, then that elder.woman's fever disappeared straight away. Then she got up to go take care of/serve Yesus them (collective).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Waktu matahari mulai turun, ju orang dong datang bawa dong pung orang yang takaná setan dong. Ais Yesus parenta itu setan dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh, setan! Iskarobis dari ini orang dong!&gt;&gt; Ju itu setan dong kaluar memang. Dia ju bekin bae samua orang saki.<bt>When the sun began to go down, then people brought their people who were afflicted by evil spirits. Then Yesus ordered those evil spirits saying, &lt;&lt;Heh, [+rebuke] evil spirits! Get out of these people!&gt;&gt; Then those evil spirits came out right away. He also healed all the sick people. [EXEG: changed from &lt;&lt;get out of here&gt;&gt; (location) to &lt;&lt;get out of these people&gt;&gt; to better reflect the focus of the Gk.]</bt><v n="17" />Dia bekin ini samua, ko bekin iko apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir Yesaya su tulis memang bilang,<bt>He did all this, to fulfill what God's spokesperson Yesaya had written ahead of time saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** tagal &gt; ko bekin iko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** tagal &gt; ko bekin iko apa (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dia bekin bae kotong pung panyaki.<bt>&lt;&lt;He heals our sicknesses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia tanggong kotong pung sangsara.&gt;&gt;<bt>And He carries/bears our suffering.&gt;&gt; [LEX: tanggong = takes the burden off us onto himself; can be physical or financial or in this case, spiritual.]</bt><note reference="8:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang mau iko sang Tuhan Yesus musti iko deng batúl-batúl<bt>People who want to follow the Lord Yesus must follow truly</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 9:57-62)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais itu, Yesus dapa lia orang bam-banya datang kuliling sang Dia. Ju Dia suru Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko kotong balayar pi dano pung sablá.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus saw many people come gather around Him. Then He ordered his underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Come let's go sail to the lake's other side.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ju ada satu guru agama datang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Bapa pi mana sa, na, beta mau iko tarús deng Bapa!&gt;&gt;<bt>And a religion teacher came speaking saying, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! Where ever Father goes, na, I want to go continually with Father!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae ju! Ma inga bagini. Samua orang deng binatang ada dong pung tampa tenga sandiri. Anjing utan kambali pi dia pung lobang. Burung kambali pi dia pung sarang. Ma Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, sonde ada pung ruma sandiri ko pulang pi situ. Tampa alas kapala ju sonde ada.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus responded saying, &lt;&lt;Good/ok, then! But remember like this. All people and animals have their own living/staying places. A forest/wild dog returns to his hole. A bird returns to his nest. But I, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, do not have my own home to return to there. A place to pad/undergird my head, also does not exist.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: (key term) ‘Son of Man’. A: First issue: As you know, Heb frame ‘son of…’ has two basic patterns. 1) son of (person's name) [e.g. Zebedee, Joseph], and 2) son of (x, not a person's name), which evokes the character or quality most prominently associated with x [e.g. brood of vipers, sons of thunder, etc.] Second issue: Heb worldview paradigm is “Son of Man vs. Son of God (humans contrasting with God), whereas in the greater Timor worldview in this region, with group after group, when we ask what situation might someone use the words “I am the son of man/humans”, the answer comes back very consistently “when someone is cursing me and calling me an animal, I would protest and say “I am the son of man/humans (too, just like you)”. so the dyad here is not humans-God, but rather humans-animals. Third issue: To the Jews, “Son of Man” was understood to be a messianic title (as can be seen in the reaction of various groups when Jesus applies the title to Himself). Fourth issue: Almost every occurrence of Jesus applying the title to Himself in the gospels is in the context of divine power or authority (e.g. the right to heal the sick, the right to forgive sins, seated at the right hand of the Father, returning in glory from heaven with angels, etc.) so in one sense it is kind of like ‘kingdom of heaven’ being a circumlocution for ‘kingdom of God’. So putting these all together, we try to find something that falls in the range of “Ideal/Prototypical/Genuinely Human”, in a way that can function as a title.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais satu orang laen lai, yang ada iko-iko sang Dia, datang minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Beta mau iko sang Bos, ma biar beta pulang ko urus orang tua dong dolo. Kalo beta pung bapa su mati, na, baru beta iko.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then yet another person, who was following Him, came requesting saying, &lt;&lt;Bos! I want to follow Bos, but allow me to return home to take care of my parents first. If/when my father has died, only then I will follow.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: see discussion in TN. Favours father not dead and managing things over a period of time.] [NOTE to daughter translations: try to reflect this on-going business in the lexical choice in next to last sentence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Kasi tenga ko orang yang sonde ada pung parcaya sang Tuhan dong, urus dong pung orang mati. Te kalo lu mau iko sang Beta, na, lu musti iko batúl-batúl!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus spoke saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this! Just let people who don't believe in God2, take care of (burying) their dead people. Cuz (elaboration) if you want to follow Me, na, you must truly follow!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: phrase as in Luke 9:60]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin tadó angin ribut<bt>The Lord Yesus makes a noisy wind calm</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 4:35-41; Lukas 8:22-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais itu, ju Yesus nae pi atas parahu sama-sama deng Dia pung ana bua dong.<bt>After that, then Yesus got on a/the boat, together with his *underlings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***dalam &gt; atas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">***dalam &gt; atas</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Waktu dong ada balayar pi dano pung sablá, ju Dia tidor. Sonde lama ju, angin ribut datang. Galombang puku pi-datang, ju aer maso pi dalam parahu.<bt>When they were sailing/going by boat to the other side of the lake, He slept. Not long then, a noisy wind came. Waves came beating, and water entered into the boat. [NOTE to daughter translations: Read entry for ‘Galilea’ in electronic version of Kamus Alkitab to discuss this. CHECK: some lgs distinguish between ‘ombak’ “normal waves” and ‘gelombang’ “big waves (dangerous)”. One lg in the region also has different words for lake waves vs. sea waves. This is a freshwater lake.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu dong ada balayar, te Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Waktu dong ada balayar, te Dia tidor.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-08 00:27:14Z">This is a</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Lia bagitu, ju ana bua dong kasi bangun sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Bos, é! Bangun ko tolong kasi salamat sang botong dolo! Te kotong su mau mati tanggalám ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, then the underlings woke up Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Boss! Boss, é! Wake up and help save/rescue us (=imperative)! Cuz (elaboration) we-inc are about to die drowning here!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh, akurang ko bosong taku!? Bosong sonde parcaya sang Beta, ko?&gt;&gt; Ju Dia bangun. Ais Dia togor itu angin deng galombang bilang, &lt;&lt;Barenti su!&gt;&gt; Ju galombang deng angin jadi tadó memang.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Weh, [+rebuke, frustration] how come you-pl are afraid here? Don't you believe in Me [+tag question]?&gt;&gt; Then He got up. Then He scolded/rebuked that wind and waves saying, &lt;&lt;Stop!&gt;&gt; Then the waves and wind became calm straight away.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju Yesus pung ana bua dong heran. Dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Dia ni, sapa, é? Karmana ko Dia bisa parenta angin deng galombang ko dong iko Dia pung mau?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus' underlings were amazed. They said, &lt;&lt;Awii [+amazement]! Who is this guy? How can it be that He can command the wind and waves so that they follow His will?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae dua orang yang takaná setan<bt>The Lord Yesus heals two people who are affected by evil spirits</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 5:1-20; Lukas 8:26-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Sonde lama lai, ju dong sampe di dano pung sablá, di orang Gadara<bt>Not much longer (=soon), then they arrived at that lake's other side, in the Gadara</bt><note reference="8:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling bae tulis <span class="Italic">Gadara</span> di Injil Mateos. Ada tulisan saparu lai tulis <span class="Italic">Gergesa</span>, deng saparu laen lai, tulis <span class="Italic">Gerasa</span>.<bt>The best Yunani language writings write <span class="Italic">Gadara</span> in the Gospel of Mateos. There are some other writings which write <span class="Italic">Gergesa</span>, and some others which write <span class="Italic">Gerasa</span>. [NOTE: see Morris, Carson, CEV, NRSV, NLT.]</bt></note>pung da'era. Di situ ada dua orang takaná setan yang tenga di goa batu tampa orang mati. Dong tu, jahat mau mati, sampe sonde ada satu orang ju yang barani jalan iko situ. Dong lia Yesus datang ju,<bt>people's area. There, there were two people who were afflicted with evil spirits who lived in rock hole in the place of dead people. They were very evil, to the point that there was not a single person who dared walk along there. They saw Yesus come then,</bt><v n="29" />dong batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Woi, Tuhan Allah pung Ana! Akurang ko Lu datang ganggu sang botong? Biar dia pung waktu ko mau hukum sang botong balóm sampe, ma Lu su mau siksa sang botong.&gt;&gt;<bt>they yelled saying, &lt;&lt;Woi, [+challenge] God's Child! Why have You come to bother us-ex? Even though the time to punish us has not yet arrived, nevertheless You already want to torment/torture/persecute us-ex.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lu mau siksa sang botong, padahal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Lu mau siksa sang botong, padahal dia pung waktu ko hukum sang botong balóm sampe!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Sonde jao dari situ, ada babi bam-banya do'i-do'i tana ko cari makan.<bt>Not far from there, many pigs were nozzling through the dirt hunting for food.</bt><v n="31" />Ju itu setan dong minta sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo mau usir sang botong, na, suru sang botong ko maso pi dalam itu babi dong sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those evil spirits requested Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;If you're going to evict us-exc, na, order us-ex to enter into those pigs!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ju Yesus parenta sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi su!&gt;&gt; Ais, itu setan dong kaluar kasi tenga itu dua orang, ju dong maso pi dalam itu babi dong. Tarús itu babi dong lari harba-biruk turun iko pinggir gunung ko maso pi dalam dano. Ju dong samua mati tanggalám.<bt>Then Yesus ordered them saying, &lt;&lt;Go!&gt;&gt; Then, those evil spirits came out leaving those two people, then they entered into those pigs. Next those pigs ran helter-skelter down the edge of the mountain into the lake. Then they all died drowning. [EXEG: avoid the word “cliff”, since there are none.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Lia bagitu ju, tukang jaga babi dong lari pulang pi kampong, ju dong carita samua-samua.<bt>Seeing like that then, the guards of the pigs ran home to the village, and they told everything.</bt><v n="34" />Dengar dong pung carita bagitu, ju orang banya dong kaluar pi itu tampa. Dong katumu sang Yesus, ju dong noki-noki ko Dia jalan kasi tenga dong pung tampa.<bt>Hearing their story like that, then many people came out to that place. They met Yesus, and they begged him to leave that place of theirs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang lumpu<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a lame person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 2:1-12; Lukas 5:17-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus dong nae kambali pi dalam parahu, ko balayar pi dano pung sablá, sampe di Dia pung kota sandiri.<bt>After that, Yesus (coll) got back in the boat, to sail to the lake's other side, arriving at His own city. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk uses /polis/ ‘city’ here. In Mrk we also used city for Capernaum and other larger population centres.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** kampung &gt; kota, note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** kampung &gt; kota, note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Di situ ada orang yang dorok bawa dong pung kawan yang lumpu ko pi di Dia. Lia bagitu ju, Yesus tau dong ada parcaya sang Dia bilang, Dia bisa bekin bae dong pung kawan tu. Ju Dia omong sang itu orang lumpu bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana, é! Kasi kuat lu pung hati dolo! Te Beta su hapus buang lu pung sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>There people who carried [s.t. bulky] brought their friend who was lame in order to go to Yesus. Seeing like that, then Yesus knew they were believing in Him, saying He could heal that friend of theirs. The He spoke with that lame person saying, &lt;&lt;Child! Be encouraged! Cuz (elaboration) (elaboration) I have have wiped away your wrongs.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: “child” here focuses on social status/relation, not age.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***undertranslated added “cheer up!” (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">***undertranslated added “cheer up!” (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ma ada barapa orang guru agama Yahudi di situ, yang dengar Yesus pung omong tu. Ju dong pung hati panas memang. Ais dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang talalu barani omong bagitu, ó! Cuma Tuhan Allah sa yang bisa kasi ampon orang pung sala. Ma ini orang pung omong tu, bekin diri sama ke dia Tuhan Allah sa. Dia su hojat tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were several Jewish religion teachers there, who heard that speaking of Yesus'. Then their livers were hot (=anger) straight away. Then they spoke to each other saying, &lt;&lt;This person is too bold speaking like that! Only God alone is the one who can forgive people's wrongs. But that speaking of this person, makes himself the same as God. With that he has *slandered/blasphemed!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati panas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">hati panas</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma Yesus tau dong pung dalam hati. Ais Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong pikir kata, Beta ni, ada omong hojat?<bt>But Yesus knew the insides of their livers. Then He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Why do you think that, I here, have spoken slandering/blaspheming?</bt><v n="5" />Mana yang lebe gampang? Kalo Beta kasi tau sang ini orang lumpu ni bilang, &lt;Lu pung sala su dapa ampon,&gt; ko, Beta bilang, &lt;Bangun suda, ko pulang.&gt;<bt>Which is easier? If I tell this lame person here saying, &lt;Your wrongs have been forgiven,&gt; or I say, &lt;Get up, and go home.&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Compare with Mark 2:9-10, in case you've come up with a clearer structure for your local audience, but retain the differences in the two gospels.]</bt><v n="6" />Kalo dia bangun memang, bosong baru lia bukti bilang, Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Te Beta ada hak ko kasi ampon orang pung sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>If he gets up straight away, then you-pl will see evidence that I here, am the Ideal/Prototypical Human. Cuz (elaboration) I have the right/authority to forgive people's wrongs.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus parenta sang itu orang lumpu bilang, &lt;&lt;Bangun su! Angka lu pung tandu ko jalan pulang!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus ordered that lame person saying, &lt;&lt;Get up! Pick up your stretcher and walk home!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Tarús, itu orang lumpu bangun, ju dia jalan pulang.<bt>Next, that lame person got.up, and he walked home.</bt><v n="8" />Lia bagitu ju, samua orang heran. Ais dong angka nae tinggi-tinggi Tuhan Allah pung nama bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah tu, talalu hebat, ó! Dia su kasi kuasa bésar bagini sang manusia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that then, all people were amazed. Then they lifted up high God's name (=glorified God) saying, &lt;&lt;God is really awesome, ó! He has given big/great/awesome power like this to humans.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: made direct speech for natural RL patterns.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pange sang Mateos ko iko sang Dia<bt>The Lord Yesus calls Mateos to follow Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 2:13-17; Lukas 5:27-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais itu, Yesus jalan dari situ, ju Dia dapa lia satu orang tukang tagi bea yang ada karjá di kantor pajak. Dia pung nama, Mateos. Ais Yesus ajak sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari iko sang Beta!&gt;&gt; Dengar bagitu, ju Mateos bangun ko iko memang sang Dia.<bt>After that, Yesus walked from there, and He saw a habitual tax collector who was working at the tax office. His name was Mateos. Then Yesus invited him saying, &lt;&lt;Come follow Me!&gt;&gt; Hearing like that, then Mateos got up to straight away follow Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: this is a kios or pos, not a full kantor. See if you can reflect that.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais itu, Mateos undang sang Yesus dong datang makan di dia pung ruma. Dia ju undang dia pung kawan-kawan tukang tagi bea, deng tamu-tamu laen dong, ko datang makan sama-sama deng dong.<bt>After that, Mateos invited Yesus (coll) to come eat at his house. He also invited his tax collector friends, and other guests, to come eat together with them. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk has ‘and sinners’ in both vs. 10 &amp; 11. But to force it here skews the focus and implies this reflects Jesus' attitude, whereas in the story it is those in vs.11 that have the issue with them. So we've undertranslated it here to not skew the focus.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ma ada barapa orang dari partei Farisi yang datang mangomek di Yesus pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong pung guru dudu makan sama-sama deng orang tar laku-laku dong, sama ke itu tukang tagi bea dong, deng dong pung kawan orang jahat dong?&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were several people from the Farisi party, who came complaining to Yesus' underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Why does your-pl teacher sit eating together with useless/unacceptable people, like those tax collectors and their evil friends?&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="9:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 15:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ma Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang saki memang parlú dokter. Ma orang yang su bae, sonde parlú.<bt>But Yesus told them saying, &lt;&lt;People who are sick really need a doctor. But people who are healed/well, don't need one.</bt><v n="13" />Lebe bae bosong pulang ko pareksa bae-bae Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, yang dolu Dia suru Dia pung jubir Hosea tulis bilang,<bt>It's better if you-pl go home to carefully examine God's Words, which previously He ordered His spokesperson Hosea to write saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Beta pung mau, andia,<bt>&lt;My desire is for,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta pung orang dong basayang satu deng satu deng kasi tunju rasa kasian.<bt>My people to love each other by showing mercy/pity.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo dong sonde bekin bagitu, na,<bt>If they don't do that, na,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong pung korban binatang yang dong bawa kasi Beta tu,<bt>those animal *sacrifices of theirs which they bring to give to Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sonde ada pung arti apa-apa.&gt;<bt>don't have any meaning at all.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu yang Tuhan Allah su bilang. Tagal itu, Beta sonde datang ko urus orang yang anggap diri su bae, ma Beta datang ko urus orang tar bae-bae dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is what God has said. Because of that, I did not come to sort out/take care of people who consider themselves good/well, but I came to sort out/take care of the people who are not good/well.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk “call”; TRT “call/exhort”; LN “call to a task”; TN “tell them to repent (get straightened out)”; we go to “sort out” which resonates with LN, TN, with parallel passages, and carries the implication that these are people you have taken on a connection with and rights and responsibilities over. so we've skewed the focus from slightly PROCESS to RESULTING relationship, but we see that as the focus of the whole verse. In RL lgs, “call” by itself is quite weak.]</bt><note reference="9:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:7, Hosea 6:6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang tanya, akurang ko Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua dong sonde puasa<bt>People ask why the Lord Yesus' underlings do not fast</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 2:18-22; Lukas 5:33-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais itu, Yohanis tukang sarani pung ana bua dong datang sang Yesus. Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong yang iko sang Yohanis, biasa puasa. Orang Farisi dong ju puasa. Ma akurang ko Bapa pung ana bua dong maen makan-minum tarús? Dong sonde tau puasa, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yohanis that Habitual Baptizer's *disciples (underlings) came to Yesus. They asked saying, &lt;&lt;We-exc who follow that Yohanis, usually *fast. Farisi people also fast. But why do Father's underlings repeatedly eat-drink all the time? They don't know how to fast, right?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma Yesus manyao sang dong pake umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini: kalo ada pesta kawin, tamu dong sonde puasa, ma dong makan kinyang. Kalo baroit laki-laki masi ada di situ, tantu dong samua makan rame-rame. Ma nanti satu kali, kalo orang laen tangkap bawa itu baroit laki-laki, ju dia pung tamán dong rasa susa dolo, baru itu sa'at dong puasa.<bt>But Yesus responded to them, using an example/allegory saying, &lt;&lt;It's like.like: if/when there is a wedding feast, the guests don't fast, but they eat until satisfied. If/when the bridegroom is still there, surely they all eat festively. But later one time, if/when other people capture taking that bridegroom, then his friends feel difficulty fundamentally, only.then at that moment they fast. [NOTE to daughter translations: don't for /itu sa'at/ if it is heavy. /baru dong puasa/ is fine.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Orang sonde ame kaen baru sapo'ong, ko tempel pi di baju tua yang su tarobe. Te nanti kalo cuci itu baju, kaen tempel yang baru tu batakundur. Deng bagitu, itu baju tua tamba tarobe.<bt>People/person do not take a piece of new cloth, in order to patch it onto a old shirt which is already ripped. Cuz (elaboration) later if they wash that shirt, that cloth patch which is new will shrink. And with that, that old shirt will rip even more.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Check sapo'ong, if it works with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Check sapo'ong, if it works with cloth too, or just land</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Bagitu ju, orang sonde isi tuak baru, pi dalam haik yang su lapuk. Te nanti itu haik pica, ju itu tuak malele buang. Jadi tuak baru, musti po'a pi dalam haik yang baru ko dong dua bisa batahan!&gt;&gt;<bt>Like that also, people do not fill new palmwine into palmwine containers <span class="Italic">(haik)</span> which are already decaying. Cuz (elaboration) later that palmwine container will crack, and the palmwine will trickle all out. So (consequently) new palmwine must be poured into palmwine containers which are new in order that the two of them both endure/last!</bt><note reference="9:17" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli bilang, &lt;&lt;jang isi aer anggor yang baru pi dalam tas kulit yang lama, ko jang sampe dia pica ko tarobe.&gt;&gt;<bt>The original Greek language writings say, “don't fill grape.wine which is new into skin bags which are old, in order that it doesn't crack and tear.”</bt></note>[Deng bagitu Yesus ajar sang dong bilang Dia pung ajaran tu, baru. Jadi jang kasi bacampor deng ajaran lama.]<bt>[With that Yesus taught them saying that teaching of His, was new. So don't mix it with old teaching.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu mama yang saki dara loos, deng kasi idop kambali satu ana nona<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a woman who is sick with unlimited blood/bleeding, and makes a young girl live again</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 5:21-43; Lukas 8:40-56)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Waktu Yesus masi ba'omong deng Yohanis pung ana bua dong, ju ada satu kapala ruma sambayang datang katumu deng Dia. Itu orang tikam lutut di Yesus pung muka, ko minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, é! Tolong dolo! Te beta pung ana nona baru mati. Bapa tolong pi ko taro tangan pi di dia dolo, ko dia bisa idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>While Yesus was still talking with Yohanis' underlings, then a head of a worship house (*synagogue) came to meet Him. That person knelt before Yesus, in order to request saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Please help! Cuz (elaboration) my young girl just died. Father please go in order to place hand/s on her, so she can live again.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Matt version is "just died"; Mark version is "about to die".]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong iko memang sang itu orang.<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus and his underlings went straight away with that person.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20-21" />Di tenga jalan, ada satu mama yang jalan iko deng dong. Dia pung datang bulan sonde tau-tau barenti batúl, su 12 taon. Dia ada pikir di dia pung hati bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal beta bisa raba Yesus pung baju sa, tantu beta jadi bae.&gt;&gt; Andia ko dia pi raba Yesus pung ujung baju.<bt>In the middle of the traveling, there was a mama who walked following them. Her monthly had not stopped correctly for already 12 years. She was thinking in her liver saying, &lt;&lt;As long as I can just touch Yesus' robe/shirt, surely I will become well.&gt;&gt; That's why she went to touch the edge of Yesus' robe/shirt. [NOTE to daughter translations: “think in her liver” can work for KM, but check that it's natural in your lg. “Think” could be enough.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Yesus ada barasa, ju Dia bale muka ko lia itu mama. Tarús Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana, é! Kasi kuat lu pung hati. Te, tagal lu parcaya batúl-batúl sang Beta, andia ko lu jadi bae.&gt;&gt; Itu waktu ju, itu mama bae memang.<bt>Yesus felt it then He turned his face, to see that mama. Then2 He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Child! Strengthen your liver. Cuz (elaboration), because you really believe in Me, that's why you become well.&gt;&gt; At that time then, that mama became well/healed straight away. [NOTE: “child” is vocative reflecting social relationship plus affection, not age.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais itu, Yesus dong jalan tarús pi di itu kapala ruma sambayang pung ruma. Sampe di sana ju Dia maso deng lia tukang maen musik duka, deng orang banya manangis makarereu.<bt>After that, Yesus them walked on to that head of worship house's house. Arriving there then He entered and saw the sorrow/grief (=from a death) music performers, and many people crying wailing.</bt><v n="24" />Ma Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Barenti manangis, ko bosong pulang su! Te ini ana sonde mati. Dia cuma tidor sa.&gt;&gt; Ma dong katawa kasi bengko mulu sang Dia.<bt>But Yesus told them saying, &lt;&lt;Stop crying, so you-pl go home (=imperative)! Cuz (elaboration) this child is not dead. She is only just sleeping.&gt;&gt; But they laughed with bent mouths (=ridicule) at Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** omong deng dong &gt; kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** omong deng dong &gt; kasi tau sang dong (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, ju itu orang dong kaluar samua. Ju Yesus maso pi dalam itu ana pung kamar, deng pegang dia pung tangan. Ju itu ana idop kambali memang.<bt>After that, then those people all left. Then Yesus entered into that child's room, and held her hand. Then that child lived again straight away.</bt><v n="26" />Lia bagitu, ju orang mulai bacarita rame kuliling dong pung da'era, so'al apa yang Yesus su bekin.<bt>Seeing like that, then people began to enthusiastically tell all around their area, that which Yesus had done there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae dua orang buta<bt>The Lord Yesus heals two blind people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais ju Yesus jalan tarús. Di tenga jalan, ada dua orang buta iko-iko sang Dia. Dong ba'eki pange bilang, &lt;&lt;Raja Daud pung turunan, é! Kasian sang botong dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Afterwards then Yesus walked on. In the middle of the traveling/journey, there were two blind people following along after Him. They were yelling out saying, &lt;&lt;King Daud's descendant! Pity us!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus maso pi dalam ruma, ju itu dua orang buta tu datang sang Dia. Ais Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong parcaya batúl-batúl bilang, Beta ada pung kuasa ko bekin bosong bisa dapa lia?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus entered into a house, then those two blind people came to Him, Then He asked them saying, &lt;&lt;Do you-pl really believe that I have the power to make you able to see?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Bapa jang tanya lai, te botong su parcaya sang Bapa isi-isi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they answered saying, &lt;&lt;Of course! Father don't ask anymore (=idiomatic way to say of course, you don't even need to ask), cuz (elaboration) we totally-totally believe in Father.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus raba dong pung mata, deng omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, biar jadi iko bosong pung parcaya!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus touched their eyes and spoke saying, &lt;&lt;If it's like that, then may it happen according to that belief of yours!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="30" />Yesus omong ais bagitu, ju dong dapa lia memang. Ma Yesus kasi inga karás sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga, é! Jang kasi tau satu orang ju deng apa yang su jadi ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus finished speaking like that, then they were able to see straight away. But Yesus reminded/warned them strongly saying, &lt;&lt;Remember! Don't tell even one person about what has happened here!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma dong sonde bisa tahan diri. Ais dong jalan kuliling itu da'era ko kasi tasiar so'al apa yang Yesus su bekin.<bt>But they couldn't restrain/control themselves. Then they went all around that area to spread around all about that which Yesus had done. [EXEG: Q: Is first sentence an addition? A: Implicit to explicit under consultant supervision, when UNSs agreed that without it, it indicated wilful disobedience. Support from Morris, TRT.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang yang sonde bisa omong<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a person who cannot speak</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Itu dua orang buta kaluar abis ju, orang bawa datang satu orang laen pi Yesus. Itu orang sonde bisa ba'omong, tagal dia takaná setan.<bt>Those two blind people left then, people brought another person to Yesus. That person could not talk, because he was afflicted by evil spirit/s. [EXEG: Gk is not clear if it is 1) can't make a sound with voice, or 2) can make a sound but can't speak. Some local lgs distinguish. 2nd is safe choice. (Most don't address this explicitly, but implied by all sources).]</bt><v n="33" />Lia bagitu ju, Yesus parenta itu setan kaluar dari itu orang. Itu setan kaluar ju, itu orang bisa ba'omong memang. Ais orang banya di situ taheran-heran. Dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Kotong orang Yahudi balóm parná lia yang bagini ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that then, Yesus ordered that evil spirit/s to come out of that person. That evil spirit came out then, that person could speak/converse straight away. Then many people there were very amazed. They said, &lt;&lt;Awii! [+amazement] We-inc Jewish people have never seen anything like this before!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma orang Farisi dong sonde sanáng. Dong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Setan dong pung bos yang kasi Dia kuasa ko Dia bisa usir kaluar setan dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the Farisi people were not happy. They spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! [+negative] It's the evil spirits' boss who gives Him power so He can expel evil spirit/s.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="9:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:25, 12:24, Markus 3:22, Lukas 11:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jato kasian lia orang banya dong<bt>Lord Yesus feels pity seeing many people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais Yesus pi kuliling banya kota deng kampong, ko ajar orang di ruma sambayang dong. Dia ajar orang so'al Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae, deng karmana dong bisa maso jadi Dia pung orang. Dia ju bekin bae samua macam panyaki, deng samua orang yang badan sonde batúl dong.<bt>Then Yesus went all around many cities and villages, to teach in the worship houses. He taught people about God's Good News, and how they can enter becoming His person/people. He also healed all kinds of diseases, and all the people who bodies were not correct (=had deformities). [EXEG: TN notes: Gk disease: The literal Greek means “those who were sick.” sickness: The Greek here literally means “those who were weak.” This refers to those who were weak because they were sick. Unfortunately TB translate second literally, leading teams who look at it to think they are emotionally or socially weak. It's just a doublet saying the same thing na! Translate as various sorts of diseases.] [NOTE to daughter translation: omit last clause if it skews the focus. The meaning of the Gk is already covered in the previous clause.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 4:23, Markus 1:39, Lukas 4:44</note><v n="36" />Lia itu orang banya, ju Yesus jato kasian sang dong, tagal dong sonde tau mau bekin karmana. Te dong samua tu, sama ke domba yang sonde ada pung gambala.<bt>Seeing those many people, then Yesus felt pity on them, because they did not know what to do. Cuz (elaboration) all of them there, were like sheep who do not have a shepherd. [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, CEV, etc. TB unfortunately says “lelah” which throws some teams off. The English gloss “helpless” is much better, reflecting the Gk sense of being oppressed and without guidance. The TN display is disappointing in going in the same direction as the TB. Follow the KM here.]</bt><note reference="9:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 27:17, 1 Raja-raja dong 22:17, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 18:16, Yeskial 34:5, Sakaria 10:2, Markus 6:34</note><v n="37" />Ais Yesus omong deng Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang banya ni, sama ke kabón pung hasil. Biar hasil banya, ma orang karjá sonde cukup ko koru ame itu hasil, deng simpan pi dalam gudang.<bt>Then Yesus spoke with His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;This many people here, are the same as garden harvest. Even though the harvest is much/alot, nevertheless the workers are not sufficient to pick that harvest and store it in the store house. [EXEG: Gk is ambiguous if the harvest is in one field, or in many fields. Err on the side of the latter, with the picture of a wealthy landowner who has to manage the challenging task of harvesting from many fields in scattered locations.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added biar, deleted su in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added biar, deleted su in 2nd sentence of quote (2009) note added ; verse 38 restored</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Hasil su banya, ma orang karjá"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Hasil su banya, ma orang karjá sonde cukup ko...</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Tagal itu, bosong musti minta sang Tuan kabón, ko Dia kirim orang karjá, ko biar dong pi kumpul ame Dia pung hasil dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, you-pl must request that garden Master/Lord, so He sends workers, so they can go collect His harvest.</bt><note reference="9:37-38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pili Dia pung ana bua 12 orang<bt>The Lord Yesus choses His underlings 12 people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 3:13-19; Lukas 6:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus pange Dia pung ana bua dong ko datang bakumpul. Ju Dia kasi dong kuasa ko usir setan deng bekin bae orang dari dong pung panyaki macam-macam.<bt>After that, Yesus called his underlings to come gather together. Then He gave them power to expel evil spirit/s and to heal people from all kinds of sicknesses.</bt><v n="2" />Itu 12 ana bua yang Dia utus dong pung nama, andia:<bt>Those 12 disciples whom He commissioned, their names are: [EXEG: Gk uses ‘disciple’ in vs.1, but ‘apostle’ in vs.2; we keep disciple for referent tracking, but use verbal form ‘commission’ to resonate with utusan ‘apostle’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yang partama, nama Simon (yang biasa orang pange bilang, &lt;Petrus&gt;),<bt>The first is named Simon (whom usually people refer.to/call saying, &lt;Petrus&gt;),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais dia pung adi, nama Anderias,<bt>then his younger sibling Anderias, [NOTE to daughter translations: if the prose form of this list is not natural, then just strip off the extras and get down to the essentials.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added for whole list"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added for whole list (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais itu, Yakobis,<bt>after that, Yakobis,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng dia pung adi, nama Yohanis (dong dua tu, Sabadeus pung ana).<bt>and his younger sibling named Yohanis (these two are Sabadius' children).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="3" />Ada ju Filipus,<bt>There is also Filipus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Bartolomeos.<bt>and Bartolomeos.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais Tomas,<bt>Then Tomas,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Mateos (tukang tagi bea).<bt>and Mateos (tax collector).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais Yakobis (Alpius pung ana),<bt>Then Yakobis (Alpius' child),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Tadius.<bt>and Tadius.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="4" />Ais Simon (yang iko partei politik Selot),<bt>Then Simon (who follows the Selot political party),</bt><note reference="10:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Partei Selot ni, ada cari jalan ko dong mardeka dari Roma pung pamarenta. Ju dong kasi nama ini partei bilang &lt;Patriot&gt;.<bt>This Selot party, was looking for a way for them to be independent from Roma's government. And they named this party saying ‘Patriot’.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Yudas Iskariot (yang nanti jual buang sang Yesus).<bt>and Yudas Iskariot (who later sold threw away (=betray) Yesus).</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus utus Dia pung ana bua dong<bt>The Lord Yesus commissions/sends.on.a. mission His *underlings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 6:7-13; Lukas 9:1-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Ais itu, Yesus utus Dia pung ana bua 12 orang, deng Dia kasi parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta utus sang bosong pi di kotong pung orang Yahudi, tagal ada banya dari kotong pung orang yang sonde iko batúl Tuhan pung jalan. Dong tu, sama ke domba kasasar. Tagal itu, bosong sonde usa pi di orang bukan Yahudi, conto ke orang Samaria dong.<bt>After that, Yesus commissioned his 12 underlings and He commanded them saying, &lt;&lt;I'm commissioning you-pl to go to our-inc Jewish people, because there are many of our-inc people who do not truly follow the Lord's path. They are like lost sheep. Because of that, you do not need (=polite negative command - don't) to go to non-Yahudi people, such as the Samaria people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added batúl in middle (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added batúl in middle (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Pi kasi tau sang kotong pung orang Isra'el dong bilang, &lt;Dia pung waktu su sampe ko samua orang bisa maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.&gt;<bt>Go tell our-inc Isra'el people saying, &lt;The time has arrived so that all people can enter becoming God's people.&gt;</bt><v n="8" />Pi bekin bae orang saki, kasi idop kambali orang mati, bekin bae orang kusta, deng usir kasi kaluar setan. Tuhan su kasi bam-banya sang bosong, ma Dia sonde minta kambali apa-apa. Jadi sakarang bosong musti pi ko kasi bam-banya sang orang laen, ma bosong sonde usa minta kambali apa-apa ju dari dong.<bt>Go heal the sick people, make the dead people live again, heal the leprosy people, and expel making exit evil spirit/s. The Lord has given much to you-pl, and He doesn't ask anything in return. So (consequently) now you must go give much to other people, and you don't need to ask anything in return from them either. [EXEG: Gk here has no object so seems to leave open the possibility that demons could be cast out of places as well as people. If your lg requires an object, use people; otherwise leave it vague as Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** removed Deng at beginning ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** removed Deng at beginning ; note added</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Jalan deng kosong-kosong sa, é. Sonde usa bawa doi,<bt>Leave just empty-empty (=don't take anything). It's not necessary to take money,</bt><v n="10" />bakál, pakean ganti, sapatu, ko tongkat. Te orang musti kasi sang orang karjá, apa yang pantas ko dong bisa idop.<bt>travel food, clothes to change (= extra clothes), shoes, or walking stick. Cuz (elaboration) people must give workers, what is appropriate for them to be able to live.</bt><note reference="10:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 9:14, 1 Timotius 5:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Kalo bosong maso dalam satu kota, ko, satu kampong, na, bosong cari orang yang mau tarima sang bosong. Ais tenga di situ, sampe bosong barangkat kasi tenga itu tampa.<bt>If/when you enter into a city, or, a village, na, you-pl look for people/person who wants to receive you. Then stay there until you depart leaving that place.</bt><v n="12" />Kalo bosong maso pi orang pung ruma, na, omong bilang, &lt;Saloom! Tuhan kasi berkat sang bosong.&gt;<bt>If/when you enter into someone's house, then speak saying, &lt;Peace <span class="Italic">(Saloom),</span> the Lord give blessing to you-pl.&gt;</bt><v n="13" />Kalo orang di itu ruma tarima sang bosong deng bae, bosong minta ko Tuhan kasi berkat sang dong. Ma kalo dong sonde tarima sang bosong, Tuhan ju sonde kasi berkat sang dong.<bt>If people/person in that house receive you well, you ask the Lord to give blessing to them. But if they don't receive you, the Lord also does/will not give blessing to them.</bt><v n="14" />Kalo orang sonde mau dengar sang bosong, na, kaluar dari itu ruma, ko itu kota, ais kabás buang abu dari bosong pung kaki, ko jadi tanda bilang, dong sonde mau dengar, na, dong pikol tanggong-jawab sandiri.<bt>If people/person does not want to listen to you, na, go out from that house, or, that city, then brush off throw away the dust from your feet/leg as a sign saying, they don't want to listen, na, they bear their own responsibility. [EXEG: See Acts, Morris.]</bt><note reference="10:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 13:51</note><v n="15" />Nanti kalo Tuhan Allah kasi jato hukum sang manusia di ini dunya, tantu Dia kasi jato hukum yang barát sang itu orang Sodom deng Gomora yang dolu paling jahat. Ma inga! Te nanti Dia kasi jato hukum yang lebe barát lai kasi orang yang sonde mau tarima sang bosong!&gt;&gt;<bt>Later when/if God sends down judgement to humans on this world, surely He will send down judgement which is heavy to those prior time Sodom and Gomora people who were very evil. But remember this! Cuz (elaboration) later He will send down judgement which is even heavier to people who do not want to accept/receive you!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:7-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:4-12, Mateos 11:24, Carita Mula-mula 19:24-28</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, nanti dong dapa sangsara [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus tells His underlings saying, later they will obtain suffering [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 13:9-13; Lukas 21:12-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />&lt;&lt;Inga, te Beta utus sang bosong ni sama ke Beta kirim domba pi teng-tenga anjing utan yang jahat. Tagal itu, bosong musti pake otak sama ke ular yang pintar. Deng bosong pung hati ju musti lurus sama ke burung pompa yang sonde tau cari hal.<bt>&lt;&lt;Remember, é! Cuz (elaboration) I commission you-pl here as if I was sending sheep to the middle of evil wild dogs. Because of that, you must use your brains the same as snakes who are clever. And your livers also must be straight (=honest) the same as dove/pidgin birds who don't know how to create issues/deceptions. [NOTE to daughter translations: “ular yang pintar” may have several sorts of problems. 1) Jesus is talking here about a quality that is positively valued-a good thing to have; 2) Kupang ‘pintar’ may be slightly too broad. In English ‘[NRSV] wise, clever, [NLT, TN] shrewd’ tend to be more positive, but ‘cunning, slick, tricky, crafty’ can be negative; TB ‘cerdik’ can be positive, but ‘licik’ tends to be more negative; 3) the positive quality for snakes here must not clash with the comment at the end of vs.16 about ‘hati lurus … yang sonde tau cari hal’; 4) to the Jews, a snake is evil and scheming, but also can be admired for its craftiness for evaluating a situation and finding clever (outside the box) ways around the obstacles, and that is what Jesus seems to be talking about here. But in many cultures that quality is not associated with snakes, and so a confusing clash arises. Snakes are ‘dangerous’, and in this context Jesus is clearly not teaching us to be dangerous. 5) For “brood of vipers”, that is meant to be negative. “sly as a fox” (Kupang ‘musang yg licik’) in Lk 13:32-33, that is also slightly negative. But in Matt. 10:16, “wise/clever as serpents” is meant to be positive-something we are to admire and emulate-while at the same time being innocent/pure-hearted/harmless (like doves). 6) If there is no clear way around the clash, then TH suggests dropping the image of the snake. So ALT /bosong musti pake otak yang pintar/cerdik/. TN suggests substituting another animal that is associated with being shrewd. In some cultures in this region this might be a ‘monkey’. My preference (CEG) I think would be to drop the image of the snake, because substituting the image of a monkey introduces many other problems.]</bt><note reference="10:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:3</note><v n="17" />Ma ati-ati, ó! Te nanti orang siksa sang bosong sama ke anjing jahat gigi bekin mati domba. Nanti dong hela bawa bosong maso pi tampa urus parkara agama. Deng nanti dong firuk sang bosong di dong pung ruma sambayang.<bt>But becareful! Cuz (elaboration) later people will mistreat you-pl like evil dogs bite to death sheep. Later they will drag take you into the place for handling religious litigations. And later they will whip/hit/swing.at you in their worship house/s.</bt><v n="18" />Nanti dong hela bawa sang bosong pi mangada di gubernor deng raja, tagal bosong iko sang Beta. Ma bosong musti pake itu kasampatan kasi tau Beta pung Kabar Bae sang dong. Deng bagitu, orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan ju dapa dengar so'al Beta.<bt>Later they will drag take you to face/report.to governor/s and king/s, because you follow Me. But you must use that opportunity to tell My Good News to them. In doing like that, people who do not know the Lord also will be able to hear about Me.</bt><v n="19" />Ma kalo dong hela bawa sang bosong bagitu, na, bosong sonde usa taku bilang, &lt;Nanti beta mau ba'omong bilang, apa?&gt; Ko, &lt;Nanti beta manyao bilang, apa?&gt; Sonde usa pikir-pikir bagitu, te sampe dia pung waktu, nanti bosong pung Bapa di sorga kasi tau so'al apa yang bosong musti omong.<bt>But if/when they drag take you like that, you don't need to be worried/thinking saying, &lt;Later I will converse saying what?&gt; Or, &lt;I respond saying what?&gt; It's not necessary (=don't, in polite way) to be worried like that), cuz (elaboration) when the time comes, later your Father in heaven will tell what you must speak.</bt><v n="20" />Itu waktu, apa yang bosong omong sonde ba'akar di bosong sandiri, te Dia pung Roh Barisi yang ajar ko bosong omong apa.<bt>At that time,. what you say is not rooted/sourced in you-pl yourselves, cuz (elaboration) His Holy Spirit is the one who teaches/instructs you what to say.</bt><note reference="10:17-20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 13:9-11, Lukas 12:11-12, 21:12-15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Bosong lia sa, te nanti dalam satu ruma, kalo ada orang yang parcaya sang Beta, nanti dia pung sodara sandiri yang cari jalan ko orang bunu sang dia. Ais kalo ana yang parcaya, nanti dia pung bapa yang bunu sang dia. Kalo bapa deng mama yang parcaya, nanti dong pung ana sandiri yang bunu sang dong.<bt>You-pl just watch, cuz (elaboration) within one house, if there is a person who believes in Me, later [it will be] his/her own sibling/s who look for a way for people to murder him/her. And if a child believes, later [it will be] his/her father who murders him/her. If father and mother believe, later [it will be] their own child/ren who murder them. [EXEG: Gk. ‘deliver’ in the 1st part of the verse implies indirect causation “have someone else kill them”. However, in the last bit the Gk “children ... put to death ... parents” is active (LN), so several English versions that render it as passive are reading into the lexicon. See options in TRT. RL phrasing can be read as direct or indirect action.]</bt><note reference="10:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 13:12, Lukas 21:16</note><v n="22" />Lia te nanti samua orang binci mati sang bosong, tagal bosong iko sang Beta. Ma orang yang batahan tarús sampe abis, Tuhan Allah nanti kasi salamat sang dia.<bt>Watch cuz (elaboration), later all people will extremely hate you-pl, because you follow Me. But the person who endures continually until the end/finish, God later will save him/her.</bt><note reference="10:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:9, 13, Markus 13:13, Lukas 21:17</note><v n="23" />Kalo orang siksa sang bosong di satu kota, na, bangun lari pi kota laen. Batúl tu! Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Nanti bosong masi balóm jalan kuliling abis samua kota di Isra'el, ma Beta su kambali.<bt>If people mistreat you-pl in one city, then get up run to another city. That true! I here am The Ideal/Prototypical Human. Later you=p still will not have finished travelling around to all the Isra'el cities, but I will already have returned/come back.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti Beta kambali te bosong balóm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Nanti Beta kambali te bosong balóm jalan kuliling abis samua kota Isra'el ni.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Orang dong biasa taro hormat sang satu guru, lebe dari dia pung ana bua dong. Deng orang taro hormat sang satu bos, lebe dari dia pung ana karjá dong.<bt>People normally respect a teacher more than his pupils/followers/disciples. And people respect a bos more than his workers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** I (CEG) couldn't find any"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** I (CEG) couldn't find any support for old exeg. (skewed focus) Complete change (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo orang sonde suka satu guru,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Kalo orang sonde suka satu guru, na, dong ju sonde suka deng dia pung ana bua dong. Kalo orang sonde suka satu bos, na, dong ju sonde suka deng dia pung ana karjá dong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 6:40, Yohanis 13:16, 15:20</note><v n="25" />Kalo ana bua su balajar sama pintar deng dia pung guru, dia su rasa cukup. Deng kalo ana karjá su balajar sama pintar deng dia pung bos, na, dia ju rasa cukup.<bt>If an underling has studied to the same skill as his/her teacher, s/he feels enough/satisfied. And if a worker has studied to the same skill as his/her boss, then s/he also feels enough/satisfied.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Jadi inga, é! Kalo orang su pange tuan ruma bilang, &lt;Lu ni, Balsebul, andia setan dong pung bos!&gt; na, tantu dia pung isi ruma ju dapa nama lebe tar bae lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>So remember! If people have called a house owner/master saying, &lt;You here, are Balsebul, that is the boss of the evil spirits!&gt; na, certainly his household will also get an even worse name yet.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:34, 12:24, Markus 3:22, Lukas 11:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang taku sang manusia, te Tuhan Allah ada jaga sang bosong [\s2]<bt>Don't fear humans, cuz (elaboration) God is guarding/taking.care.of you [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 12:2-7)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />&lt;&lt;Jadi bosong sonde usa taku deng orang yang lawan sang bosong. Te apa yang orang bekin sambunyi-sambunyi, nanti samua orang dapa lia.<bt>&lt;&lt;So (consequently) you-pl don't need to be afraid of people who oppose you. Cuz (elaboration) what people do in secret, later all people will get to see [it].</bt><note reference="10:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 4:22, Lukas 8:17</note><v n="27" />Apa yang Beta su ajar sang bosong sandiri-sandiri, nanti bosong musti pi kasi tau samua orang. Deng apa yang Beta kasi tau diam-diam, nanti bosong musti pi kasi tau kuliling di samua tampa.<bt>That which I have taught you alone/by.yourselves, later you must go tell all people. And that which I have told quietly, later you must go tell [it] all around in all places.</bt><v n="28" />Jang taku manusia, te dong cuma bisa kasi mati orang sa, ma dong sonde bisa bekin rusak orang pung jiwa. Tagal itu, bosong musti taku sang Tuhan Allah, te Dia sa yang ada pung kuasa ko lempar buang orang pung badan deng dia pung jiwa pi dalam laut api yang manyala tarús-tarús.<bt>Don't be afraid of humans, cuz (elaboration) they can only just kill a person, but they cannot destroy a person's soul. Because of that, you-pl must be afraid of God, cuz (elaboration) He alone [is the one] who has the power/authority to throw out/cast a person's body and his soul in the sea/ocean of fire which burn on and on (=forever).</bt><v n="29" />Jadi kasi kuat bosong pung hati. Orang jual burung pipit di pasar deng harga paling mura sa. Ma sonde ada satu ju yang jato mati, kalo bosong pung Bapa di sorga sonde kasi isin.<bt>So strengthen/encourage your livers. People sell sparrow <span class="Italic">(pipit</span>) birds in the market for only the very cheapest price. But there is not even one who falls down dead, if your-pl Father in heaven does not give permission.</bt><v n="30" />Bosong pung Bapa di sorga ju ada taro mata sang bosong sampe hal yang paling kici. Bosong pung urat rambu pung banya di kapala ju, Dia su tau na.<bt>Your-pl Father in heaven also is attending/watching over (lit. placing eyes on) you-pl down to the smallest matter. Even your hair strands number on [your] head, He knows, [+certainly/obviously].</bt><v n="31" />Jadi bosong jang taku! Tagal Tuhan Allah nilei sang bosong lebe mahal dari itu burung pipit dong samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) you don't be afraid. Because God values you more expensive/precious than all those <span class="Italic">pipit</span> birds.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang malu mangaku sang Tuhan Yesus [\s2]<bt>Don't be embarrassed to acknowledge the Lord Yesus [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 12:8-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang barani mangaku kanál sang Beta di muka orang banya di ini dunya, nanti Beta ju mangaku kanál sang dia di muka Beta pung Bapa di sorga bilang, &lt;Dia ni, Beta pung orang.&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke again saying like this, &lt;&lt;The person who dares acknowledge knowing Me in front of many people on earth here, later I also will acknowlege knowing him in front of My Father in heaven saying, &lt;He here is My person.&gt;</bt><v n="33" />Ma orang yang manyangkal sang Beta di muka orang banya bilang, dia sonde kanál sang Beta, nanti Beta ju kasi tau sang Beta pung Bapa di sorga bilang, &lt;Beta sonde kanál sang ini orang.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But the person who deny.knowing Me in front of many people, saying he/she doesn't know Me, later I also will tell My Father in heaven saying, &lt;I don't know this person.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** last word dia &gt; ini"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** last word dia &gt; ini orang to fit the direct quote better and set social distance (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Timotius 2:12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus datang bekin orang dong bamalawan, bukan badame [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus comes to make people oppose each other, not to be a peace with each other [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 12:51-53, 14:26-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />&lt;&lt;Bosong jang sangka bilang, Beta datang bawa dame di ini dunya. Te Beta datang ko bekin manusia bamalawan satu deng satu.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl don't/shouldn't think that, I came to bring peace to this world. Cuz (elaboration) I came to make humans oppose each other.</bt><v n="35" />Beta datang di ini dunya, iko apa yang Tuhan pung jubir su tulis memang bilang,<bt>I came to this world following that which the Lord's spokeperson/s had said ahead of time saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Nanti ana laki-laki malawan dia pung bapa,<bt>&lt;Later male child will oppose his father,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ana parampuan malawan dia pung mama,<bt>female child will oppose her mother,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng ana mantu parampuan malawan dia pung mama mantu,<bt>and female child-in-law will oppose her mother-in-law,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="36" />te isi ruma sandiri yang bamusu satu deng satu.&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) a household itself is who is enemies one with another.&gt;</bt><note reference="10:35-36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mika 7:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Jadi orang yang batúl-batúl mau iko sang Beta, dia musti sayang sang Beta <span class="Italic">lebe</span> dari samua; lebe dari dia pung mama-bapa, deng lebe dari dia pung ana dong. Te kalo sonde, na, itu orang sonde pantas jadi Beta pung orang.<bt>So (consequently) the person who really/truly wants to follow Me, he must love Me <span class="Italic">more</span> than all; more than his mother-father (= class of parents), and more than his children. Cuz (elaboration) if not, na, that person is not worthy of being My person.</bt><v n="38" />Te orang yang mau iko sang Beta, ma sonde mau pikol sangsara, dia sonde pantas jadi Beta pung orang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who wants to follow Me, but doesn't want to shoulder.carry suffering, s/he is not appropriate to be/become My person.</bt><note reference="10:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:24, Markus 8:34, Lukas 9:23</note><v n="39" />Orang yang sadia mati tagal dia iko sang Beta, nanti dia dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan. Ma orang yang cuma mau idop buat dia pung diri sandiri sa, nanti dia pung idop tu, ilang buang bagitu sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>The perosn who is ready/prepared to die because s/he follows Me, later s/he will get to live continually with the Lord. But the person who only wants to live just for him/her.self, later that life of his/hers, [will] disappear/be lost completely just like that!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:25, Markus 8:35, Lukas 9:24, 17:33, Yohanis 12:25</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah nanti balas apa yang orang bekin [\s2]<bt>God later will reciprocate that which people do [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:41)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />&lt;&lt;Orang yang tarima sang bosong deng bae, dia ju tarima sang Beta. Deng orang yang tarima sang Beta, dia ju tarima sang Tuhan Allah yang utus sang Beta.<bt>&lt;&lt;The person who receives you well, s/he also receives Me. And the person who receives Me, s/he also receives God who commissioned Me.</bt><note reference="10:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 9:37, Lukas 9:48, 10:16, Yohanis 13:20</note><v n="41" />Orang yang tarima Tuhan Allah pung jubir tagal itu jubir ada omong so'al Tuhan, nanti Tuhan balas sang dia sama ke Tuhan balas sang satu jubir. Deng orang yang tarima satu orang hati lurus tagal itu orang ada iko batúl-batúl Tuhan pung mau, nanti Tuhan balas sang dia sama ke Tuhan balas sang satu orang hati lurus.<bt>The person who receives God's spokesperson, because that spokesperson is talking about God, later God will reciprocate him/her the same as God reciprocates a spokesperson. And the person who receives a straight/righteous person, because that person is truly following God's will, later God will reciprocate him/her the same as God reciprocates a straight/ righteous person. [EXEG: “in the name of” = because he has the rank of, because he belongs to me; see word study for “name” (CEG-PPT)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** itu &gt; satu (x2) (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** itu &gt; satu (x2) (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Orang yang tarima sang satu orang yang paling kici tagal dia iko sang Beta, pasti Tuhan balas sang dia. Biar orang cuma kasi aer puti satu galás sa, tantu Tuhan Allah sonde lupa sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>The person who receives the most insignificant person because s/he follows Me, surely God will reciprocate him/her. Even if it is only just one glass of white water (=plain water not tea or anything in it), certainly God will not forget him/her.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tukang sarani kirim utusan pi Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer sends envoys/commisioned.ones to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 7:18-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yesus kasi pasán abis sang Dia pung ana bua 12 orang tu, ju Dia pi kuliling di kampong-kampong di itu da'era, ko ajar orang deng kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae.<bt>When Yesus finished giving instructions to those 12 underlings of his, then He went all around the villages in that area, to teach people and tell God's Good News.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Itu waktu, Yohanis su ada dalam bui. Waktu dia dengar samua hal yang Yesus su bekin, ju dia suru dia pung ana bua dong pi tanya sang Yesus bilang,<bt>At that time, Yohanis was already in jail. When he heard all the things which Yesus had done, then the ordered his underlings to go ask Yesus saying,</bt><v n="3" />&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu bilang, Dia mau kirim datang Kristus ko kasi salamat sang kotong orang Yahudi. Bapa ni, andia Kristus, ko? Ko, botong musti tunggu sang orang laen lai?&gt;&gt; Ju dong pi tanya sang Yesus.<bt>&lt;&lt;God has promised beforehand from long ago saying, He will send Kristus to save us-inc Jewish people. Father (=You, having John call Yesus Father is showing greater respect than their kinship relationship calls for) here is Kristus, [+tag question]? Or, must we-inc wait for yet another person?&gt;&gt; So they went and asked Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong su dengar deng su lia sandiri. Jadi pulang ko lapor sang Bu Anis bilang, samua su jadi, iko apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir Yesaya su tulis memang bilang:<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl have heard and have seen yourselves. So go home to report to Elder.Brother (=real kinship relationship but also respectful) Anis (=nickname for John) saying, everything has happened following that which God's spokesperson Yesaya has written ahead of time saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="5" />Orang buta, dapa lia.<bt>Blind people/person, can see. [NOTE to daughter translations: If possible, get a rhythm going here in vs.5. No translations seem to put this in quotes.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang kaki lumpu, bangun bajalan.<bt>Lame leg people/person, get up and walk.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang panyaki kusta, jadi barisi.<bt>Leprosy sickness people/person, become clean.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang tuli, dapa dengar.<bt>Deaf people/person, can hear.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang mati, idop kambali.<bt>Dead people/person, live again.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang kasian, dengar Kabar Bae.<bt>Poor/Pitiful people/person, hear Good News.</bt><note reference="11:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 35:5-6, 61:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Jadi bagini: pi kasi tau Bu Anis, nanti dia ontong kalo dia parcaya tarús sang Beta. Tagal nanti Tuhan Allah kasi berkat sang orang yang dia pung parcaya sang Beta sonde tagoyang!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), it's like this: go tell Elder.Brother Anis, later he will be fortunate if he believes continually in Me. Because later God will give blessing to the person whose faith in Me does not sway/shake!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: LN] [NOTE: TB missed the meaning of the two key Gk words in this verse.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Waktu Yohanis pung ana bua dong su pulang, ju Yesus omong deng orang banya dong so'al Yohanis bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu bosong pi cari Yohanis di tampa sunyi sana tu, bosong pikir mau katumu deng manusia model ke apa? Sonde mungkin bosong pi sana ko katumu orang yang noe-noe, sama ke bambu yang tagoyang-goyang iko angin sa!<bt>When Yohanis' underlings had returned home/ had left for home, then Yesus spoke with many people about Yohanis saying, &lt;&lt;When you-pl went to seek Yohanis in that lonely place over there, what kind of human did you think you would meet? It's not possible you would go there to meet a person who is soft/pliable, like bamboo which sways back and forth just following the wind!</bt><v n="8" />Deng sonde mungkin bosong pi ko lia orang yang pake pakean mahal-mahal, te orang macam bagitu cuma tenga di istana sa!<bt>And it's not possible you would go there to see a person who wears/wore expensive clothing, cuz (elaboration) people like that only just live in palaces!</bt><v n="9" />Jadi bosong pi lia orang macam karmana di sana? Bosong pikir bosong pi cari Tuhan Allah pung jubir? Batúl! Ma dia tu, jubir yang paling hebat.<bt>So (consequently) what kind of person did you go see there? Did you think you were going to find God's spokeperson? Correct! But he there, is the spokesperson who is the greatest. [EXEG: Q: Is the phrase “I tell you” undertranslated? A: NO. It is an emphatic handled by “Correct!”, as in NLT, CEV, and TH discussion.]</bt><v n="10" />Te Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis memang so'al Yohanis bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the Scriptures have written beforehand about Yohanis saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dengar! Beta utus Beta pung orang,<bt>'Listen! I am commissioning My person,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko pi buka jalan kasi sang Lu.&gt;<bt>to go open the path/road for You .&gt;</bt><note reference="11:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dengar bae-bae, ó! Di ini dunya, sonde ada satu orang ju, yang lebe hebat dari Yohanis. Ma dari samua manusia yang parná mangaku Tuhan Allah jadi dong pung Raja, orang yang paling kakorek sa su lebe hebat dari Yohanis.<bt>Listen well! In this world, there is not a single person, who is greater than Yohanis. But among all humans who have ever acknowledged God as their King, the person who is the absolute worthless/last.in.line is already more great than Yohanis. [EXEG: Two overlapping problems here. “among those born of women” is in contrast to supernatural beings [TH], so something like, “any human who has ever lived, living or dead”. The second problem is how to talk about the first and still retain the “kingdom of heaven” figure which is a Jewish circumlocution for “kingdom of God”. No matter how you cut it, this verse is inherently puzzling. “No human has ever been born who is greater than John; but everyone in the kingdom (including the lowest in status/significance) is greater than John”-which seems to imply that John is not part of the kingdom. (implied by all versions, even though most commentators take great care to say he IS part of the kingdom). TRT note explains it this way, “Jesus is not saying that John is unimportant, but in an idiomatic way He is emphasizing that His followers are also very great. Most Bible scholars think Jesus is referring to the great privileges/blessings His followers have, not how important they are. For example, John did not live long enough to see or hear that Jesus died and rose from the dead, but Jesus' followers did. However, many scholars think “the Kingdom of Heaven/God” refers to the new covenant which Christ established, so that the text means John is the greatest under the old covenant, which was preparatory for Christ, but John is not as great as anyone under the new covenant.” Morris expresses a similar view-John was part of the BC era, and the kingdom starts with Christ. Carson discusses this problem at length. The difficulties of this passage were recognized as far back as Augustine and Chrysostom. We must not translate away the puzzle.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma di Tuhan Allah pung pegang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Ma di Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta, orang yang paling kakorek sa su lebe hebat dari Yohanis.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Mulai dari Yohanis angka dia pung karjá sampe sakarang, banya orang su maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung milik. Ma ada orang saparu yang pikir sala, ais dong baparáng ko paksa orang maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang. Deng ada yang baparáng malawan sang Tuhan pung orang ju.<bt>Starting from Yohanis picking up/beginning his work until now, many people have entered becoming God-owned. But there are some people who think wrongly, so (result) they war/fight to force people to enter becoming God's people. And there are also those who war/fight opposing God's people. [EXEG: see discussion in TH for the complexities of the inverted clauses that has violence going in two directions. See also M Crofts Consultant Notes (in many branch libraries). Earlier version was undertranslated.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Following M. Croft, CONNOT"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Following M. Croft, CONNOT</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Sampe deng Yohanis tukang sarani pung datang, kotong orang Yahudi biasa idop iko ba'i Musa deng Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong pung atoran.<bt>Until Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer's arrival, we-inc Jewish people usually lived following Gf/Ff Musa and God's spokespersons' regulations.</bt><note reference="11:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 16:16</note><v n="14" />Jadi parcaya sang Beta sa! Yohanis tu, andia Elia yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong su kasi tau memang so'al dia pung datang.<bt>So (consequently) just believe Me! Yohanis, is like Elia whom God's spokespersons have told about his arrival ahead of time.</bt><note reference="11:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 4:5, Mateos 17:10-13, Markus 9:11-13</note><v n="15" />Jadi, yang kapingin mangarti musti dengar bae-bae, ó!<bt>So (consequently), those who desire to understand must listen carefully!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Beta mau kasi umpama ko bosong dapa tau, orang sakarang ni, manusia macam apa. Te dong tu, sama ke ana-ana yang ada dudu-dudu di pasar. Dong ada maen babatarea deng dong pung tamán bilang,<bt>I want to give an example/comparison so that you-pl know, what kind of humans people nowadays are. Cuz (elaboration) they, are like children who are sitting around at the market. They are yelling back and forth at their friends saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />&lt;We! Botong tiop suling rame-rame,<bt>&lt;We! [+get attention] We-exc blow flutes really lively,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">teng</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bosong sonde manari sanáng-sanáng.<bt>but you-pl don't dance happily.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais botong manyanyi lagu duka,<bt>And we sing mourning song/s,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lagu mete = dirge, funeral song"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">lagu mete = dirge, funeral song</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bosong sonde manangis.&gt;<bt>but you don't cry.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Bosong ni sama ke ana kici dong yang sonde tau puas. Waktu Yohanis datang, dia suka puasa, deng sonde minum anggor. Ma orang cap sang dia bilang, &lt;Dia ada takaná setan!&gt;<bt>You(pl) here are like small children who can't be pleased. When Yohanis came, he regularly fasted and didn't drink wine. But people labeled him saying, &lt;His is affected by evil spirit/s!&gt;</bt><v n="19" />Ma sakarang Beta, Manusia Tulen, su datang. Beta sonde puasa, deng Beta minum anggor. Ma orang cap sang Beta bilang, &lt;Dia tu, dasar manusia balalas! Pamabok barát lai! Dia pi bakawan deng tukang tagi bea dong! Satu partei deng orang tar laku-laku dong! Sonde tau diri lai!&gt; Ma bosong tanda sa, Beta pung omong, é! Tuhan pung pintar jadi kantara di Dia pung orang dong pung idop.&gt;&gt;<bt>But now I, Ideal/Prototypical Human, have come. I do not fast and I drink wine. But people have labeled Me saying, &lt;He is fundamentally a gluttonous person! And even more a heavy drunkard! He goes and makes friends with tax collectors! [He is ] one party (=associates) with the worthless nobodies. He really gone off his rocker! [<span class="Italic">Sonde tau diri lai</span> - could get MTTs to explain meaning of this idiom which is literally 'he doesn't know himself anymore' - which carries the idea of lost his sense of his social position/responsibility and thrown away social norms]&gt; But you just note My words! God's cleverness/intelligence/wisdom is made visible/obvious in the lives of His people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang sonde mau tarima sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>People who do not want to accept the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 10:13-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais itu, Tuhan Yesus mulai togor orang yang ada tenga di barapa kampong. Dia su bekin tanda heran paling banya di sana, ma dong sonde mau kasi tenga dong pung sala-sala dong ko iko Tuhan pung jalan idop yang batúl.<bt>After that, the Lord Yesus began to scold people who were living in several villages. He had already done very many miracles there, but they did leave their wrongs to follow the Lord's life path which is true.</bt><v n="21" />Yesus togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong orang Korasin deng orang Betsaida dong! Awas, é! Nanti bosong calaka! Beta su bekin tanda heran macam-macam di bosong pung batang idong, ma bosong sonde mau parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Padahal bosong ni orang Yahudi, yang mangaku kanál sang Tuhan. Ma andekata itu tanda-tanda heran yang Beta bekin di bosong pung kampong, su jadi lebe dolo di kota Tirus deng kota Sidon, tantu bagini lama orang di situ dong su tobat memang, deng su kasi tenga dong pung sala-sala ko iko sang Tuhan. Deng dong ju tantu pake pakean duka, deng taro abu di atas kapala ko jadi tanda bilang, dong ada manyasal deng dong pung sala-sala. Padahal orang Tirus deng orang Sidon ni, bukan orang Yahudi yang mangaku kanál sang Tuhan.<bt>Yesus scolded saying, &lt;&lt;You Korasin people and Betsaida people! Watch.out! Later you-pl will meet disaster/misfortune! I have done all.sorts of miracles at you nose stalk (idiom=right in front of your face), but you-pl do not want to believe in God. However in actual fact, you-pl here are Jewish people, who acknowledge knowing the Lord. But if perchance those miracles which I have done in your village, had happened before in Tirus city and Sidon city, certainly after all this time people there would have repented straight away already and have left their wrongs to follow the Lord. And they also would surely wear grieving clothes, and put dust on top of their heads to make a sign saying they regretted their wrongs. However these Tirus people and Sidon people are not Jewish people who acknowledge knowing the Lord.</bt><note reference="11:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 23:1-18, Yeskial 26:1--28:26, Yoel 3:4-8, Amos 1:9-10, Sakaria 9:2-4</note><v n="22" />Batúl! Nanti bosong lia sa! Kalo Tuhan putus samua orang dong pung parkara, orang Tirus deng orang Sidon pung hukuman masi jao lebe ringan dari bosong pung hukuman.<bt>True! Later you-pl will see! If/when the Lord decides all people's cases/litigations, Tirus people and Sidon people's judgement will still be far more light/lenient than your judgement/punishment.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Bosong orang Kapernaum! Awas, é! Bosong jang pikir bilang, nanti Tuhan angka nae sang bosong maso pi sorga. Sonde! Nanti Tuhan lempar buang sang bosong maso pi naraka! Andekata itu tanda-tanda heran yang Beta bekin di bosong pung kampong su jadi lebe dolo di kota Sodom, tantu Tuhan Allah sonde parlú kasi ancor itu kota jahat. Te kalo orang Sodom lia itu tanda heran dong, su tantu dong kasi tenga dong pung jahat.<bt>You Kapernaum people! Watch out! You-pl don't think that later the Lord will lift you up to enter into heaven. No! Later the Lord will throw you away into hell! If perchance those miracles which I did in your village, had happened before in Sodom city, God would certainly not have needed to have destroyed that city there. Cuz (elaboration) if Sodom people had see those miracles, certainly they would have left behind their evil.</bt><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 14:13-15, Carita Mula-mula 19:24-28</note><v n="24" />Batúl! Nanti bosong lia sa! Kalo Tuhan putus samua orang dong pung parkara, orang Sodom pung hukuman masi jao lebe ringan dari bosong pung hukuman!&gt;&gt;<bt>True! Later you will see! If/when the Lord decides all people's cases/litigations, Sodom people's judgement will still be far more light/lenient than your judgement!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="11:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:15, Lukas 10:12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus undang orang ko iko sang Dia, ko biar dong jadi kuat kambali<bt>The Lord Yesus invites people to follow Him, so they can become strong again</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 10:21-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Omong abis bagitu, ju Yesus sambayang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Bapa yang pegang hak parenta samua di langit deng bumi. Beta minta tarima kasi bam-banya, tagal Bapa tutu ame itu hukuman dari orang yang anggap diri pintar, deng yang tinggi hati dong. Ma Bapa buka itu hal samua kasi orang kici dong, deng orang yang randá hati dong.<bt>After finishing speaking like that, then Yesus prayed saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Father is the one who holds the right to rule everything on earth and in heaven. I give many thanks, because Father has covered over/closed/hidden that punishment from people who consider themselves smart, and who are high livered (=proud). But Father has revealed all those things to the small (=simple) people, and the people who are low livered (=humble). [EXEG: the problem in "hid these things", is what does "these things" refer to? Because of untamed UNS responses, one consultant urged us to put in this OV explication "tutu ame so'al Tuhan kasi jato hukum dari orang-orang yang…", which grammatically makes for a fairly heavy information load. We take this as the Judgment or Punishment theme of the previous verses (20-24), following the urging of our consultant. TRT goes broad and vague "your kingdom rule", which is safe, but doesn't really link well to the immediate context. Morris accepts either, and Carson also sees room for both. TH and TN want to avoid the issue, but acknowledge it could be about what He just said in the previous verses.]</bt><v n="26" />Batúl, Bapa! Te itu yang bekin Bapa pung hati sanáng!&gt;&gt;<bt>It's true, Father! Cuz (elaboration) that is what makes Father's liver happy!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Sambayang abis bagitu, ju Yesus kasi tau sang orang di situ dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae, ó! Beta pung Bapa di sorga su kasi samua kuasa sang Beta. Yang kanál bae sang Beta tu, andia cuma Bapa sa. Deng yang kanál bae sang Bapa, cuma Bapa pung Ana sa, andia Beta ni. Deng Beta pili orang laen dong, ko kasi tau sang dong, ko biar dong ju kanál bae sang Dia.<bt>After finishing praying like that, then Yesus told the people there saying, &lt;&lt;Listen carefully! My Father in heaven has given all power/authority to Me. The one who knows Me well, is only just Father. And the one who knows Father well, is only just the Father Child, which is Me here. And I choose other people, in order to tell them, so that they can also know Him well.</bt><note reference="11:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 3:35, 1:18, 10:15</note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00019C.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Sapi luku<bt>Yoked cows pulling plow</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Bosong samua yang cape karjá karás, mari iko sang Beta! Bosong samua yang ada pikol masala barát, mari datang sang Beta! Te nanti Beta kasi bosong barenti cape yang batúl.<bt>You all who are tierd of working hard, come follow Me! You all who shoulder.carrying heavy problems, come here to Me! Cuz (elaboration) I will give/cause you real rest (lit: stop tiredness) at/in Me. [EXEG: Last sentence missing from OV.]</bt><v n="29" />Kalo bosong tarima Beta pung ajaran ko jalan sama-sama deng Beta, na, kotong ni sama ke sapi luku dua ekor yang ada hela sama-sama satu luku. Te Beta ni, pung hati bae, deng Beta ni, randá hati. Kalo bosong iko sang Beta, na, bosong bisa barenti cape ais jadi kuat kambali.<bt>If you receive My teaching in order to walk together with Me, na, we-inc here are like two tails (=counter for animals) of plow cows who are pulling together one plow. Cuz (elaboration) I here am good livered (=kindhearted), and I here am low livered (=humble). If you follow Me, na, you can rest and (result) become strong again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="luku = bajak, plow"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">luku = bajak, plow</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 6:16</note><v n="30" />Tagal Beta pung ajaran sonde susa. Deng Beta pung parenta sonde barát.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because that teaching of mine, is not difficult. And those commands of mine are not heavy/difficult.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang karitik sang Tuhan Yesus so'al hari barenti karjá<bt>People criticize the Lord Yesus about the day of stopping work (*Sabbath)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 2:23-28; Lukas 6:1-5)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, kaná deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari barenti karjá, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong ada jalan iko orang pung kabón. Dia pung ana bua dong lapar, andia ko dong ketu ame padi-gandum pung puler ko dong makan jalan-jalan.<bt>One time, occuring on the Jewish people's day of stopping work, Yesus and His underlings were walking following someone's garden. His underlings were hungry, that's why they picked rice(generic type)-wheat grainheads in order to eat as they walked along.</bt><note reference="12:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 23:25</note><v n="2" />Di situ, ada barapa orang dari partei agama Farisi yang pegang karás dong pung adat Yahudi. Lia Yesus pung ana bua dong bekin bagitu, ju dong togor sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung ana bua dong ada ketu padi-gandum kaná deng hari barenti karjá! Sonde bole bagitu! Te itu su langgar kotong pung atoran.&gt;&gt;<bt>There, there were several people from the Farisi religious party who held strongly their Jewish customs. Seeing Yesus' underlings do like that, then they scolded Him saying, &lt;&lt;Your [somewhat disrepectful-- but appropriate to this context] underlings are picking rice-wheat on the day of stopping work! They can't do like that! Cuz (elaboration) that violates our-inc regulations.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3-4" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana, ó? Bosong sonde inga ba'i Daud pung carita tu? Ba'i Daud deng dia pung ana bua dong pung parú su karoncong tagal lapar mau mati. Ju dia maso pi dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tenda Sambayang, ko ame itu roti yang kapala agama dong su kasi sang Tuhan, ko dong makan. Padahal cuma kapala agama dong sa yang bole makan itu roti. Orang laen sonde bole. Ais ba'i Daud dong makan, ma sonde ada orang kasi sala sang dong. Bosong tingka ke sonde tau baca Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi sa!<bt>But Yesus responded saying, &lt;&lt;How is it? Don't you-pl remember that story of grandfather Daud's? Gf/Ff Daud and his underlings' stomaches were strumming because they were very hungry. Then he entered into God's Worship Tent (*Tabernacle), to take that bread which the religion heads had already given to the Lord, in order for them to eat. However in actual fact [it was] only just the religion heads who could eat that bread. Other people weren't allowed. Then grandfather Daud (collective) ate [it], but no one accused them. You are as if you just do not know how to read the Scriptures! [EXEG: Gk is sg-pl: he entered, he took, they ate.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** dia &gt; dong (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** dia &gt; dong (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:3-4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 21:1-6, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 24:9</note><v n="5" />Te di situ ju ada tulis so'al kapala agama dong yang karjá layani di ruma sambayang, kaná deng hari barenti karjá. Ma dong sonde dapa sala apa-apa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there it is also written about the *priests (religion heads) who are working serving/ministering in the worship house, on the day/s of stopping work. But they did not obtain any fault.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added karjá (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added karjá (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 28:9-10</note><v n="6" />Dengar, ó! Dolu Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang pantíng, ma sakarang ada yang lebe pantíng lai. Andia, Beta, Manusia Tulen ni.<bt>Listen! Previously [it was] the *temple that was important, but now there is something even more important. That is, Me, this Ideal/Prototypical Human here.</bt><v n="7" />Dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi, Tuhan Allah ada bilang, &lt;Beta pung mau bagini: Beta pung orang dong musti kasi tunju rasa kasian satu deng satu. Kalo dong sonde bekin bagitu, na, dong pung korban binatang yang dong bawa kasi Beta tu, sonde ada pung arti apa-apa.&gt; Naa, kalo bosong mangarti bae-bae Tuhan pung omong tu, tantu bosong sonde tudu Beta pung ana bua dong sala. Ko dong sonde bekin sala apa-apa na!<bt>In the Scriptures, God says, &lt;My will is like this: My people must show mercy/pity to each other. If they don't do like that then, those animal offerings of theirs which they bring to Me, do not have any meaning at all.&gt; Naa [+shift], if you truly understand that speaking of the Lord's, surely you will not accuse my underlings of wrong. Cuz (elaboration) they have not done anything wrong! [+emphatic]</bt><note reference="12:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:13, Hosea 6:6</note><v n="8" />Te Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Beta yang ada pung hak ko putus bilang, orang bole bekin apa kaná deng hari barenti karjá.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I here am the Ideal/Prototypical Human. I am the One who has authority to decide what people may do on the day of stopping work.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang, kaná deng hari barenti karjá<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a person, on the day of stopping work</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 3:1-6; Lukas 6:6-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais itu ju Yesus jalan kasi tenga itu tampa, ko pi di dong pung ruma sambayang.<bt>After that then Yesus walked/traveled leaving that place, to go to their worship house.</bt><v n="10" />Di situ, ada satu laki-laki yang dia pung tangan mati sablá. Itu orang Farisi dong ada mau cari-cari jalan ko kasi sala sang Yesus, andekata Dia bekin bae itu orang yang tangan mati sablá, kaná deng hari barenti karjá. Ais dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko kotong pung atoran agama, orang bole bekin bae orang kaná deng hari barenti karjá, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>At there, there was a man whose arm was dead on one side. Those Farisi people were wanting to find a way to accuse Yesus, if perchance He healed that person whose arm was dead on one side, on the day of stopping work. Then they asked Him saying, &lt;&lt;According to our religious regulations, can people heal people on the day of stopping work, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo orang pung domba satu jato dalam lobang, kaná deng hari barenti karjá, tantu itu domba pung tuan pi angka kasi kaluar itu domba, aa?<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;If someone's sheep (singular) fell into a hole, on the day of stopping work, surely that sheep's owner/master would go lift up take out that sheep, [+tag; I expect you to agree with me]?</bt><note reference="12:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 14:5</note><v n="12" />Naa! Tuhan sayang sang manusia, lebe dari itu tuan sayang sang dia pung domba. Tagal itu, orang bole bekin hal bae kaná deng hari barenti karjá.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa! God loves humans, more than that owner/master loves his sheep. Because of that, people can do good things on the day of stopping work.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tarús Dia omong deng itu orang yang tangan mati sablá bilang, &lt;&lt;Bu, é! Sorong datang lu pung tangan!&gt;&gt; Ais dia sorong dia pung tangan mati sablá tu, ju itu tangan jadi bae memang, sama ke dia pung tangan sablá lai.<bt>Next Yesus spoke with that person whose arm was dead on one side, side, &lt;&lt;Elder.brother (=in this context a term of some respect and compassion)! Extend your arm here!&gt;&gt; Then he extended that dead arm of his, and that arm was good straight away, the same as his arm on the other side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Lia bagitu, ju itu orang Farisi dong maruak. Ais dong bangun jalan kasi tenga itu ruma sambayang, ju dong pi ba'akór bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong musti cari jalan ko bunu sang Dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, then those Farisi people got furious. Then they got up and walked leaving that worship house, then they went to seek mutual agreement [with each other] saying, &lt;&lt;We-inc must find a way to kill Him!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah yang pili Yesus ko karjá kasi sang Dia<bt>[It is ] God who chose Yesus to work for Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma Yesus tau dong pung rancana jahat tu, andia ko Dia jalan pi tampa laen. Banya orang iko sang Dia, ju Dia bekin bae samua orang saki.<bt>But Yesus knew that evil plan of theirs, that's why He walked to another place. Many people followed Him, then He healed all the sick people.</bt><v n="16" />Ma Dia larang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang kasi tau orang laen so'al Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>But He forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl may not tell other people about Me.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk does not use the &lt;who&gt; word here, but rather something close to the NRSV &lt;make Him known&gt;. Matthew is careful to focus on what He DOES in the first parts of the book, and only in the later chapters does he start getting into the question of WHO Jesus is. High level.]</bt><v n="17" />Dia bekin bagitu iko apa yang Tuhan Allah su kasi tau sang Dia pung jubir Yesaya bilang,<bt>He did like that following that which God had already told His spokesperson Yesaya saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />&lt;&lt;Coba lia! Ini Dia, Beta pung Orang suru-suru yang Beta su pili.<bt>&lt;&lt;Look! Here he is, My ordering around person (=low level worker/slave) whom I have chosen. [NOTE: don't capitalise needlessly in OT quotes, unless there is clear evidence that the original OT writer saw it as messianic, which is actually quite rare - MC]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta sayang sang Dia,<bt>I love Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng Beta pung hati sanáng tarús deng Dia.<bt>and My liver is continually happy with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Beta kasi Beta pung Roh sang Dia,<bt>Later I will give My Spirit to Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Dia pi ajar orang di samua suku-bangsa<bt>so that He goes teach people in all ethnic groups</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">so'al Beta pung jalan idop yang lurus.<bt>about My life path which is straight/just.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="19" />Dia sonde tau puku-puku dada.<bt>He does not beat his chest (=be arrogant) [NOTE to daughter translations: Lit. "he does not quarrel or shout". This KM rendering is idiomatic, being described by UNSs as “a good person; kind, gentle; not fight or argue; anassuming ; not arrogant; not unreasonably assertive”. If the symbolic action doesn't convey the desired meaning in your language, then do something close to literal.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia sonde tau angka-angka diri.<bt>He does not lift himself up.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="20" />Dia pung hati bae.<bt>He has a good liver (=kindhearted).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde bekin susa orang.<bt>He doesn't cause difficulty/trouble to people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kayu yang amper pata, Dia sonde pata buang.<bt>Wood/stick which is almost broken, He doesn't break it all the way.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lampu te'oek yang amper mati, Dia sonde fuu bekin mati.<bt>A <span class="Italic">(te'oek)</span> wick lantern which is almost dead, He doesn't blow it out.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia ajar orang tarús, sampe lama-lama samua suku-bangsa tau ko iko Tuhan pung jalan idop yang lurus.<bt>He continually teaches people, until eventually all the ethnic groups know to follow the Lord's life path which is straight/just.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="21" />Orang dari samua suku-bangsa nanti parcaya sang Dia, tagal dong tau Dia tu, sapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>People from all tribes/races will believe in Him, because they know who He is.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:18-21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 42:1-4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Guru agama dong tudu sang Tuhan Yesus bilang, setan dong pung bos yang kasi kuasa sang Dia<bt>The religion teachers accuse the Lord Yesus saying, evil spirits boss is the one who give power to Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 3:20-30; Lukas 11:14-23)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais satu kali, orang dong bawa pi Yesus satu orang yang takaná setan sampe dia buta deng sonde bisa ba'omong. Ju Yesus usir kasi kaluar itu setan ko bekin bae sang dia. Ais, itu orang bisa lia deng bisa ba'omong memang.<bt>Then one time, people brought to Yesus a person who was afflicted by evil spirit/s until he was blind and could not speak. Then Yesus expelled making leave that evil spirit to heal him. Then, that person could see and could speak straight away.</bt><v n="23" />Lia bagitu, ju samua orang taheran-heran. Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mangkali Dia ni, Daud pung turunan, yang Tuhan pung jubir dong su tulis memang dari dolu-dolu. Dia ni, tantu Orang yang kotong su tunggu-tunggu tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that then all the people were amazed. They conversed (w/each other) saying, &lt;&lt;Probably He here is Daud's descendant whom the Lord's spokespersons have written all about from long ago. He here is surely that Person whom we-inc have been waiting and waiting for!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ma waktu orang Farisi dengar bagitu, ju dong sonde tarima. Ais dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Woeh! Ini orang bisa usir kasi kaluar setan, tagal setan dong pung bos Balsebul, yang kasi kuasa sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>But when the Farisi people heard like that, then they did not accept [it]. Then they spoke to each other saying, &lt;&lt;Woe [+NEG]! This person can expel make leave evil spirit/s because evil spirits' boss Balsebul, is the one who gives that power to Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:34, 10:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma Yesus tau orang Farisi dong pung omong tu. Ju Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pung omong tu, sonde maso di akal! Kalo dalam satu negrí, dia pung rakyat dong baku hantam, karmana ko itu negrí masi bisa batahan! Bagitu ju kalo orang dalam satu kota, ko, dalam satu ruma, satu bara'u deng satu, tantu dong tu tapica-pica sampe ancor-ancor, ó!<bt>But Yesus knew that speaking of the Farisi people. And He told them saying, &lt;&lt;That speaking of yours, doesn't make any sense! If inside one political.unit, the masses/people attack each other, how can it be that that political.unit still can endure! Like that also if people in one city, or in one house, are at odds with each other, surely they will be broken into pieces until they are completely destroyed!</bt><v n="26" />Jadi, kalo setan dong maen bamusu deng maen ba'usir satu deng satu, na, dong pung bos su sonde bisa pegang parenta lama-lama lai!<bt>So (consequently), if evil spirits keep being enemies with each other, and keep expelling each other, na, their boss can not hold power much longer anymore.</bt><v n="27" />Inga, é! Bosong pung orang dong ju tau usir setan. Dong pake kuasa dari setan, ko? Sonde! Jadi bosong jang omong sambarang bilang, Beta ada pake setan pung kuasa ko usir setan. Nanti bosong pung orang sandiri yang putus bilang, apa yang bosong tudu tu, sala.<bt>Remember! Your-p people also know how to expel evil spirits. Do they use power from evil spirits? No! So you don't talk haphazardly/aimlessly saying, I am using evil spirits' power to expel evil spirits. Later [it will be] your very own people who decide that that which you accuse there, is wrong.</bt><v n="28" />Ma kalo Beta batúl-batúl usir setan pake kuasa dari Tuhan pung Roh, itu kasi tunju bilang, Tuhan tu memang Raja yang su ada di bosong pung muka idong.<bt>But if I truly expel evil spirits using power/authority from God2's Spirit, that proves that it is the Lord who is the King that is right in front of your noses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Kalo orang mau datang rampok barang di satu orang kuat pung ruma, dia musti ika mati itu orang dolo. Abis, baru dia bisa rampok ame itu orang pung barang dong.<bt>If someone wants to come steal things in a strong person's house, he must completely tie up that person first. After that, only then he can steal away that person's thing/s.</bt><note reference="12:29" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Deng bagitu, Yesus kasi tau bilang, Dia lebe kuat dari setan dong pung bos, yang dong biasa pange &lt;Balsebul&gt;.<bt>With that, Yesus told saying He was stronger than the evil.sprit's boss, whom they usually called 'Balsebul'.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Inga bae-bae! Te orang yang sonde bapartei deng Beta, dia tu bamusu deng Beta. Deng orang yang sonde babantu deng Beta pung karjá, dia tu bekin kaco sa.<bt>Remember well! Cuz (elaboration) the person who is not one party with Me, he there is enemies with Me. And the person who does not help out with My work, he there is only just making chaos.</bt><note reference="12:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 9:40</note><v n="31" />Jadi dengar bae-bae Beta pung omong ni! Tuhan Allah su sadia hapus buang sang orang dong pung sala. Deng kalo orang omong tar bae-bae kaná orang laen, Tuhan Allah masi sadia kasi ampon sang dia. Ma kalo ada orang barani omong tar bae-bae kasi Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi, Tuhan Allah sonde hapus buang dia pung sala tu.<bt>So (consequently) listen carefully to this speaking of Mine! God is ready to wipe away people's wrongs. And if people speak not well about other people, God is still prepared to forgive them. But if there is someone who dares speak not good about the Clean/Holy Spirit of God's, God will not wipe away that sin of his.</bt><v n="32" />Kalo orang omong jahat sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, Tuhan sadia kasi ampon sang dia. Ma kalo orang omong bekin hina lawan Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi, ma Tuhan Allah sonde hapus buang dia pung sala tu, biar dari sakarang sampe salamanya ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>If someone speaks evil about Me, the Ideal/Prototypical Human here, the Lord is prepared to forgive him/her. But if someone speaks opposing making dispicable the Lord's Spirit which is Clean/Holy, nevertheless [+contrary to expectation] God will not wipe away that wrong of his, neither from now (or) until forever!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pohon, deng dia pung bua<bt>Tree and its fruit</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 6:43-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais Yesus omong tarús sang itu orang Farisi dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pikir bae-bae! Pohon yang bae kasi kaluar bua yang bae. Ma pohon yang sonde bae kasi kaluar bua yang sonde bae. Tagal dari pohon pung bua, orang bisa tau bilang, itu pohon tu, bae ko sonde.<bt>Then Yesus continued talking with those Farisi people saying, &lt;&lt;Think carefully! A tree which is good produces fruit which is good. But a tree which is not good produces fruit which is not good. Because from a tree's fruit, people can know whether that that tree there is good or not.</bt><note reference="12:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:20, Lukas 6:44</note><v n="34" />Ma bosong ni sama ke ular tukang putar-balek! Bosong sonde bisa omong hal-hal yang bae. Tagal apa yang tasimpan dalam orang pung hati, itu yang nanti kaluar dari dia pung mulu.<bt>But you here are like snakes who are habitual twisters-turners (=deceivers)! You cannot speak of things which are good. Because whatever is stored.away in a person's liver, that is what later comes out of his/her mouth.</bt><note reference="12:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:7, 23:33, 15:18, Lukas 3:7, 6:45</note><v n="35" />Orang bae, tantu omong yang bae, tagal ada hal-hal yang bae tasimpan dalam dia pung hati. Ma orang jahat, pasti omong yang jahat, tagal ada hal-hal yang jahat tasimpan dalam dia pung hati.<bt>A good person, surely says what is good, because there are various good things stored in his liver. But an evil person, surely says what is evil, because there are various evil things stored away in his liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang bae, tantu dia pung omong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Orang bae, tantu dia pung omong bae, tagal dia pung dalam hati ada tasimpan hal-hal yang bae. Ma orang jahat, pasti dia pung omong jahat, tagal dia pung dalam hati ada tasimpan hal-hal yang jahat.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Parcaya sang Beta! Te nanti hari kiamat datang, Tuhan Allah pareksa samua orang pung parkara. Itu waktu, tiap orang musti tanggong-jawab dia pung kata-kata yang sonde ada pung guna.<bt>Believe Me! Cuz (elaboration) later the end.of.the.world comes, God will examine all people's cases/litigations. At that time every person must bear responsibility for his/her words which do not have any use.</bt><v n="37" />Jadi ati-ati, ó! Te nanti Tuhan Allah timbang bosong pung kata-kata, deng putus bilang, bosong kaná hukum, ko sonde.&gt;&gt;<bt>So be careful, ó! Cuz (elaboration) later God will weigh/consider your words, and decide whether, you will be punished, or not.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang minta Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju bukti<bt>People request the Lord Yesus to show evidence</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 8:11-12; Lukas 11:29-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Dengar Yesus pung omong bagitu, ada barapa guru agama deng orang Farisi yang minta sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Botong kapingin lia Pak bekin tanda heran, ko jadi bukti bilang, Pak pung kuasa tu batúl-batúl dari Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus' speaking like that, there were several religion teachers and Farisi people who requested Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! We-exc want to see Father  (=you) do miracle/s, to be evidence that, that power of Fathers really does come from God.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:1, Markus 8:11, Lukas 11:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ma Yesus masparak sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bosong orang sakarang ni, sonde mau dengar-dengar sang Tuhan! Bosong cuma tau bekin jahat sa! Biar bosong minta tanda heran, ma Beta sonde kasi. Tagal dolu Tuhan su kasi tanda heran pake Dia pung jubir Yunus. Itu su cukup!<bt>But Yesus rebuked/spoke.angrily.at them saying, &lt;&lt;Heh! [+rebuke] You people nowadays, don't want to listen to/obey the Lord! You want only to do just do evil! Even if you request miracles, but I won't give [them]. Because previously the Lord already gave miracle/s using his spokesperson Yunus. That is enough!</bt><note reference="12:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:4, Markus 8:12</note><v n="40" />Yunus tenga tiga siang, tiga malam dalam ikan bésar pung parú. Bagitu ju Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Nanti Beta tenga tiga siang, tiga malam dalam goa batu tampa orang mati.<bt>Yunus stayed three days, three nights inside the big fish's stomach. That's similar to Me, this Ideal/Prototypical Human. Later I will stay three days, three nights in the rock cave in the place of the dead people. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /tenga/ means 'live', rather than just 'be-at', then find another way to say this like /ada di/, since we don't want to communicate the impression that Jesus didn't die.]</bt><note reference="12:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yunus 1:17</note><v n="41" />Nanti di hari kiamat, kalo Tuhan jadi hakim, orang Niniwe dong badiri jadi saksi ko tudu sang bosong bilang, &lt;Bosong samua ni, ngali!&gt; Dolu, itu orang Niniwe dong dengar sang Tuhan pung jubir Yunus, ju dong tobat deng kasi tenga dong pung sala-sala. Ma bosong sonde. Padahal sakarang ada Orang di bosong pung teng-tenga yang lebe hebat dari Yunus, andia Beta ni. Ma bosong sonde mau toe sang Beta sadiki ju.<bt>Later at the end.of.the.world, if/when the Lord is judge, the Niniwe people will stand to be witness accusing you saying, &lt;You all here are idiots!&gt; Previously, those Niniwe people heard the Lord's spokesperson Yunus, and they repented and left behind their sins. But you don't/won't. But in actual fact, now there is a Person in your midst who is more amazing/impressive/ terrific than Yunus, that's Me here. But you don't want to care. about/pay.attention.to Me even a little bit.</bt><note reference="12:41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yunus 3:5</note><v n="42" />Nanti di hari kiamat, kalo Tuhan jadi hakim, ratu Seba dari salatan sana ju badiri jadi saksi. Dia tunju jari ko tudu sang bosong samua yang idop sakarang ni bilang, &lt;Bosong samua ni, bodo, é!&gt; Dolu, itu ratu datang dari jao-jao ko lia deng mata kapala sandiri raja Soleman pung pintar. Padahal sakarang ada Orang di bosong pung teng-tenga yang lebe hebat dari Raja Soleman, andia Beta ni. Ma bosong sonde mau toe sang Beta sadiki ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later at the end of the world, if/when the Lord is judge, queen Seba (Sheba's queen) from the south over.there will also stand to be a witness. She will point her finger and accuse all of you who live nowadays saying, &lt;You all here are stupid!&gt; Previously, that queen came from far away to see with her very own eyes king Soleman's skill/cleverness. But in actual fact, now there is a Person in your midst who is more amazing/impressive/terrific that King Soleman. That's Me here. But you don't want to care. about/pay.attention.to Me even a little bit.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: if people in your area are likely to think of Seba on Sabu island, rather than Sheba, then use the Indonesian spelling Syeba.]</bt><note reference="12:42" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 10:1-10, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 9:1-12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Setan yang kambali lai pi di orang yang dolu dia parná tenga<bt>The evil spirit who returns again to the person where he had lived</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 11:24-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />&lt;&lt;Kalo setan kaná usir kaluar dari satu orang, itu setan pi tampa sunyi ko cari tampa barenti cape. Ma dia sonde dapa tampa yang cocok.<bt>&lt;&lt;If an evil spirit is expeled out of a person, that evil spirit goes to a lonely place to look for a stopping/resting place. But he doesn't find a place that fits/is.appropriate.</bt><v n="44" />Ju dia pikir bilang, &lt;Ee! Sonde dapa tampa bagini, lebe bae beta pulang pi tenga kambali di itu orang yang dolu tu.&gt; Ais dia kambali, ju dia lia itu tampa su barisi deng ta'ator bae-bae.<bt>Then he thinks saying, &lt;&lt;Ee! [+hmmm] [I'm] not finding a place like this, [so] it's better I return to stay again in that previous person.&gt; Then he returns, and he sees that place there, already clean and well-arranged.</bt><v n="45" />Ais ju itu setan pi pange dia pung kawan tuju, yang lebe jahat lai dari dia. Tarús dong samua pi tenga di itu orang, ju dong karoyok rame-rame sang dia. Jadi sakarang, itu orang pung idop su lebe calaka lai. Bagitu ju kaná deng orang jaman sakarang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then that evil spirit go to call his seven friends, who are more evil that him. Next they all go to stay in that person, and they gang.up enthusiastically on him. So now that person's live is even more misfortunate. It's the same way also effecting people of this age.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Last clause was ommitted from earlier versions. Nov 2009. FTN added Apr 2013 to explicate meaning of last sentence. TN, Crofts, CR.]</bt><note reference="12:45" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Te dolu, dong ada bekin jahat deng tunggu-tunggu Mesias pung datang ju. Ma sakarang dong su katumu deng Mesias, ju tola buang sang Dia. Jadi sakarang dong lebe rusak.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) peviously, they were doing evil and awaiting the coming of the Mesias also. But now they have met the Mesias, and have rejected Him. So now they are more ruined/worse off.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung kelu yang batúl dong<bt>The Lord Yesus' real family</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 3:31-35; Lukas 8:19-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Itu waktu, Yesus masi ba'omong deng orang banya. Ju Dia pung mama deng Dia pung adi dong datang ko mau katumu deng Dia. Dong badiri sa di luar ruma ko suru orang pange sang Dia.<bt>At that time, Yesus was still conversing with many people. Then his mama and His younger siblings came wanting to met Him. They just stood outside the house and told someone to go call Him.</bt><v n="47" />Ju orang datang kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Bapa pung mama deng adi dong ada di luar. Dong mau katumu deng Bapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the person came told saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Father's mama and younger siblings are outside. They want to meet Father.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:47" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu yang sonde muat ini ayat 47.<bt>There are some Yunani language writings which do not carry this verse 47. [TEXT: see TH and TRT. Majority accepts this verse.]</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung mama yang batúl tu, sapa? Deng Beta pung sodara-sodara yang batúl tu, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Who is my real mama? And who are my real siblings?&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="49" />Ju Dia tunju pi di orang-orang yang iko sang Dia, deng kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Lia, te dong ni Beta pung mama deng Beta pung sodara dong.<bt>Then He pointed at the people who were following Him, and told saying, &lt;&lt;Look, cuz (elaboration) they here are My mama and My siblings.</bt><v n="50" />Te orang yang bekin iko Beta pung Bapa di sorga pung mau, dong tu Beta pung kelu yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) people who do according to My Father in heaven's will, they there are My real family.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al orang yang tanam bibit di tana macam-macam<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about a person who plants seed in all sorts of soil/dirt</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 4:1-9; Lukas 8:4-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Itu hari ju Yesus kaluar dari itu ruma, ko pi dudu di dano Galilea pung pinggir.<bt>That day then Yesus went out of that house, to go sit at lake Galilea's edge.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added several paragraphs in this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added several paragraphs in this pericope (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ju orang bam-banya datang makarubu sang Dia. Ais Dia nae pi dudu di atas satu parahu yang ada balabu di situ, ko mangajar. Itu orang di darat dong samua dengar sang Dia.<bt>Then very many people came crowding around Him. Then He got up and went to sit in a boat which was docked there, in order to teach. All those people on the land could hear Him.</bt><note reference="13:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 5:1-3</note><v n="3" />Ju Dia ajar bam-banya sang dong, pake umpama. Dia angka carita bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang tani pi dia pung kabón ko siram bibit.<bt>Then He taught alot [of things] to them using examples. He picked.up (=started) a story saying, &lt;&lt;There was farmer person who went to his/her garden to scatter/sprinkle seed.</bt><v n="4" />Waktu dia siram itu bibit dong, ada yang jato di jalan. Ju burung dong datang ko toto bekin abis itu bibit dong samua.<bt>When he/she scattered those seeds, there some who/that fall on the path/road. Then birds came and completely pecked up all those seeds.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma ada bibit saparu jato kaná di tana babatu. Itu bibit banupuk capát, tagal itu tana isi tipis.<bt>But there some seeds which fell on the stony land. Those seeds sprouted quickly, because that land/soil was thin. [EXEG: Gk. conjunction here is /dia/ interpreted as a causal “because”, or “since”. If we were writing it ourselves, we probably wouldn't connect it that way, but here we're trying to reflect the Gk. Apparently the thought is that thin soil over rocks heats more quickly and triggers the growth process more quickly.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** tana &gt; tana isi +"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** tana &gt; tana isi + note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma waktu matahari nae, ju itu nupuk dong mamalek, ko mati karíng. Te dong pung akar sonde maso sampe dalam tana na.<bt>But when the sun rose, then those sprouts withered, and died dry. Cuz (elaboration) their roots could not enter down deep in the soil obviously.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ada bibit saparu lai jato di tenga rumput baduri. Ju itu rumput baduri dong gepe bekin mati itu nupuk.<bt>There were some other seeds which fell in the middle of thorny grass. Then that thorny grass pinched/grabbed killing those sprouts.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma ada bibit saparu lai jato kaná di tana isi. Itu bibit dong banupuk, abis ju dong jadi bésar sampe babua. Ada yang kasi bale hasil tiga pulu kali, ada yang anam pulu kali, deng ada yang sampe saratus kali.<bt>But there were some other seeds which fell on the well.formed/fertile land/soil. Those seeds sprouted, and then they grew until they fruited. There were some who returned a yield thirty times, there were some sixty times, and there where some even up to a hundred times.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Sapa yang ada talinga, na, dengar bae-bae, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>Whoever has ears, na, listen carefully!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau kanapa Dia suka ajar pake umpama<bt>The Lord Yesus explains why He like to teach using examples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 4:10-12; Lukas 8:9-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais ju Yesus pung ana bua dong datang ko tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko Bapa ajar sang itu orang banya dong pake umpama?&gt;&gt;<bt>Afterwards then Yesus' underlings came to ask Him saying, &lt;&lt;Why does Father teach those many people using examples?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal bosong mau mangarti batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung parenta, andia ko Beta kasi tau memang itu umpama pung arti. Ma kalo orang laen, na, Beta ajar pake umpama sa.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Because you really want to understand God's commands, that's why I tell you straight way the meaning of those examples. But as for other people, na, I just teach with examples.</bt><v n="12" />Te orang yang mau cari tau batúl-batúl Tuhan pung mau, nanti Tuhan kasi dia tamba mangarti lai. Ma orang yang sonde toe deng Tuhan pung mau, nanti Tuhan bekin dia tabodo-bodo.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who really wants to know the Lord's will, later the Lord will enable him/her to understand even more. But the person who doesn't have a concern for the Lord's will, later the Lord will make him/her stupid. [NOTE to daughter translations: try to reflect “increasingly wise... increasingly stupid”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 25:29, Markus 4:25, Lukas 8:18, 19:26</note><v n="13" />Beta ajar sang dong pake umpama sa, tagal:<bt>I teach them using only examples, because:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dong su lia,<bt>&lt;They have seen,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma sonde mau mangarti.<bt>but don't want to understand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong su dengar,<bt>They have heard,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma sonde mau tau.&gt;<bt>but don't want to know.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Dong tu sama ke orang yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir Yesaya su tulis bilang,<bt>They there are the same as people whom God's spokesperson Yesaya wrote about saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Bosong nanti dengar,<bt>&lt;Later you-pl will hear,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bosong sonde mau mangarti.<bt>but you will not understand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bosong nanti lia,<bt>Later you will see,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma bosong sonde mau tau apa yang su jadi.<bt>but you will not know what happened.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Tagal ini orang dong pung hati karás,<bt>Because these people's livers are hard,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong bekin tuli dong pung talinga,<bt>they make their ears deaf,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong bekin buta dong pung mata.<bt>they make their eyes blind.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi kasi tenga pi sa, ko dong pung talinga jadi tuli bagitu sa,<bt>So (consequently), just leave/allow it so their ears become deaf just like that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kasi tenga pi sa, ko dong pung mata jadi buta bagitu sa.<bt>and just leave/allow it so their eyes become blind just like that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Biar ko Beta sonde usa bekin bae sang dong,<bt>So that I don't need to heal them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dong sonde mau toe sang Beta.&gt;<bt>because they don't care/have.concern for Me.&gt; [EXEG: There is debate on what how the Gk ‘lest’ should be handled here, noting that the ‘so, so that…not’ purpose fails to fully capture the sense of the modality satisfactorily. MC argues that the run of the whole verse to her is clearly sarcastic, and she's worked with us in the Mark, Luke and Matthew versions to try to capture this. The KM phrasing helps convey the speaker attitude that there is a bit of frustration/ disappointment happening here.]</bt><note reference="13:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 6:9-10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma bosong ni, barontong, ó! Te bosong su dapa lia deng bosong pung mata sandiri, deng bosong su dapa dengar deng bosong pung talinga sandiri.<bt>But you here, are fortunate! Cuz (elaboration) you have seen with your very own eyes, and you have heard with your own ears.</bt><v n="17" />Parcaya sang Beta! Dolu-dolu Tuhan pung jubir deng orang yang pung hati lurus dong ada rindu mau lia apa yang bosong su dapa lia, ma dong sonde bisa. Dong ju rindu mau dengar apa yang bosong su dapa dengar, ma dong sonde bisa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Believe Me! Previously the Lord's spokesperson/s and people who had straight livers (=righteous people) were yearning/longing to see what you have seen, but they could not. They also yearned/longed to hear what you have heard, but they could not.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="13:16-17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:23-24</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau itu umpama bibit pung arti<bt>The Lord Yesus tells the meaning of that example about seeds</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 4:13-20; Lukas 8:11-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Omong abis bagitu, ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi sakarang bosong dengar itu umpama pung arti.<bt>After finishing speaking like that, then Yesus told them saying, &lt;&lt;So now you-pl hear that example's meaning.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added paragraphs to whole pericope"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added paragraphs to whole pericope (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Bibit yang jato di jalan tu, andia orang yang dengar Kata-kata so'al Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta, ma dia sonde mangarti batúl-batúl. Ais ju setan dong pung bos datang rampas bawa itu Kata-kata dari itu orang pung hati.<bt>The seed which fell on that road, they are a person who hears Words/Message/Instructions about God's ruling, but he doesn't really understand [it]. Afterwards then the evil spirit's boss comes and steals away those Words from that person's liver.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Bibit yang jato di tana babatu tu, andia orang yang dengar Tuhan pung Kata-kata, ju dia tarima deng hati sanáng.<bt>The seed which fell on that stony land, is a person who hears the Lord's Words, then he accepts them with a happy liver.</bt><v n="21" />Ma itu Kata-kata sonde ba'akar. Andia ko dia sonde tasimpan lama di itu orang pung hati. Bagitu orang laen bekin susa tagal dia tarima itu Kata-kata, dia langsung lapás buang sang dong.<bt>But those Words/Saying doesn't take.root. That's why it isn't stored away for long in that person's liver. When other people cause trouble [for him], because he accepted those Words, he immediately lets go throws them away. [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT for last clause: itu orang sonde pegang kuat itu Kata-kata lai.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Deng bibit yang jato di tenga rumput baduri tu, sama ke orang yang su dengar itu Kata-kata. Ma dia talalu barepot deng macam-macam urusan ko bisa idop ena-ena sa. Ju itu urusan dong samua, seti buang itu Kata-kata dari dia pung hati, sampe sonde ada guna lai.<bt>And the seed which fell in the middle of that thorny grass, is the same as the person who has heard those Words. But he/she is too preoccupied with all kinds of arrangements in order to just live luxuriously. Then all those arrangements, shove out those Words from his/her liver, to the point that it doesn't have anymore use.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ma bibit yang jato kaná di tana isi, sama ke orang yang pasang talinga ko tarima itu Kata-kata, deng iko Tuhan pung mau. Ais dia bekin hal-hal yang bae sa, sama ke bibit yang babua tu. Ada yang babua tiga pulu kali lipat, ada ju yang anam pulu, deng ada yang sampe saratus kali.&gt;&gt;<bt>But the seed which fell on that fertile land, is the same as the person who fastens his/her ears (=pays attention) in order to receive that news, and to follow the Lord's will. Afterwards he does just good things, like that seed which fruited. There are some who fruit thirty times, and also some forty times, and some even up to a hundred times.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al rumput di kabón pung teng-tenga<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about grass in the middle of the garden</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Yesus kasi tau lai satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta sama ke ada satu orang yang siram bibit yang bae di dia pung kabón.<bt>Yesus told another example saying, &lt;&lt;That ruling of God's, is like a person who scatters seeds which are good in his garden.</bt><v n="25" />Waktu malam, samua orang ada tidor sonu. Ju orang jahat datang, ko siram bibit rumput liar di itu kabón.<bt>When it's night, everyone is sleeping soundly. Then evil people come, to scatter seeds of wild grass in that garden.</bt><v n="26" />Waktu itu kabón mulai kasi kaluar hasil, ju dia pung orang karjá dong dapa lia rumput liar ada tumbu sama-sama deng gandum di situ.<bt>When that garden begins to produce crop, then his workers see wild grass is growing together with the wheat crops there. [EXEG: Gk wheat is explicit in vs. 25, but fits better in local discourse here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** gandum added, note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** gandum added, note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ais ju dong pi kasi tau sang itu kabón pung tuan bilang, &lt;Bos! Tempo hari botong tanam bibit yang bae di bos pung kabón, aa? Akurang ko sakarang su ada banya rumput?&gt;<bt>Afterwards then they go tell that garden's master saying, &lt;Bos! Earlier we-exc planted seeds which are good in bos' garden, right? So why now is there alot of grass?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Itu bos manyao bilang, &lt;Itu tu, orang jahat pung karjá.&gt;<bt>That bos replied saying, &lt;That, is evil person/s' work.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia pung orang karjá dong usul bilang, &lt;Bos, botong pi tofa buang itu rumput, ko?&gt;<bt>Then his workers suggested saying, &lt;Bos, should we go dig.up throw away that grass?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma dia manyao bilang, &lt;Jang! Te waktu bosong tofa itu rumput, nanti kotong pung tanaman bae dong ju iko tacabu buang.<bt>But he replied saying, &lt;No! Cuz (elaboration) when you dig.up that grass, later our-inc good plants will also get pulled up.</bt><v n="30" />Tenga pi ko dong tumbu sama-sama sampe musim koru. Nanti itu waktu, baru beta kasi tau orang karjá dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong kumpul dolo itu rumput liar dong. Ais ika satu-satu kabuak, ko bakar buang. Ais baru kumpul hasil yang bae dong, ko kasi maso dalam gudang.&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Just leave it so they grow together until the season for taking the harvest. Later at that tiime then I will tell workers saying, &lt;&lt;You gather first that wild grass. Then tie it in into individual wads, and burn it up. After that then gather the good harvest, and put it in the store.house.&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al biji yang kici ana<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about seed which is very small</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 4:30-32; Lukas 13:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais itu, Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta tamba satu umpama lai, ko bosong bisa mangarti karmana Tuhan Allah jadi Raja kasi banya orang. Dia pung orang dong, mulai sama ke biji kici ana yang orang tanam di dia pung kabón.<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again saying, &lt;&lt;I add one more example, so you can understand God becoming King to many people. His people, start out like very small seed which a person plants in his/her garden.</bt><v n="32" />Biar itu biji tu, paling kici ana, ma kalo dia su idop datang, na, dia jadi pohon yang paling bésar di kabón. Sampe burung dong datang basarang di dia pung cabang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even though that seed, is the smallest/tiniest, nevertheless when it has lived, then it becomes a tree which is the largest in the garden. To the point that birds come make nests in its branches.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** biar... ma (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** biar... ma (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al bibit roti<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about bread seed (*yeast)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 13:20-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Yesus tamba satu umpama lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung orang dong, sama ke bibit roti yang satu parampuan ame ko campor deng tarigu satu sak.<bt>Yesus added one more example saying, &lt;&lt;God's people are also like yeast which a woman takes and mixes with a sack of flour.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added Gk font in ftn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added Gk font in ftn (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:33" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani bilang, &lt;&lt;tarigu tiga σάτα (<span class="Italic">sata</span>)&gt;&gt;. Satu <span class="Italic">sata</span>, andia kira-kira 12 liter. Tiga <span class="Italic">sata</span>, andia kira-kira 36 liter, ko, satu sak.<bt>Yunani language writings say, “three <span class="Italic">sata</span> of flour”. One <span class="Italic">sata,</span> is approximately 12 litres. Three <span class="Italic">sata,</span> are approximately 36 litres, or, one sack.</bt></note>Ju itu roti reis sampe bésar, tagal itu bibit roti yang sadiki ana tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that bread raises until big, because of that very little bit of yeast.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pake umpama, ko ajar hal-hal baru yang orang balóm parná dengar<bt>The Lord Yesus uses an example to teach new things which people have never yet heard</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 4:33-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Yesus ajar orang banya deng pake carita banya macam bagitu. Dia pung omong samua cuma pake umpama sa.<bt>Yesus taught many people by using many stories like that. All of that speaking of his, just only used examples.</bt><v n="35" />Dia ajar bagitu ko iko apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir su tulis memang bilang,<bt>He taught like that in order to follow that which God's spokesperson had written beforehand saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nanti Beta ajar pake umpama.<bt>&lt;&lt;Later I will teach using examples.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti Beta kasi tau hal-hal yang orang balóm parná dengar,<bt>Later I will tell things which people have not yet ever heard,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">mulai dari Tuhan bekin ini dunya sampe deng sakarang.&gt;&gt;<bt>beginning from when the Lord made this world until now.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="13:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 78:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau arti dari itu umpama so'al rumput liar di kabón pung teng-tenga<bt>The Lord Yeus tells the meaning of that example about wild grass in the middle of the garden</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais Yesus jalan kasi tenga itu orang banya dong, ko pulang pi ruma. Ju Dia pung ana bua dong datang, ko minta tolong sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Tolong kasi tau sang botong itu umpama so'al rumput liar pung arti dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus walked leaving those many people, and went home. Then His underlings came, and asked help from Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Please explain to us-exc that example about wild grass's meaning (imperative)!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang siram bibit yang bae tu, andia Beta, Manusia Tulen ni.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;The person who scattered that seed which is good, that is Me, this Ideal/Prototypical Human here.</bt><v n="38" />Deng kabón tu, andia ini dunya ni. Bibit yang bae tu, andia orang-orang yang su maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung kelu. Deng rumput liar tu, andia setan dong pung bos pung orang dong.<bt>And that garden, that is this world here. That good seed there, is people who have entered becoming God's family. And that wild grass there, is evil spirit's boss's people.</bt><v n="39" />Ais, itu orang jahat yang datang ko siram itu bibit rumput tu, andia setan dong pung bos sandiri. Deng musim koru tu, andia hari kiamat. Orang karjá yang ame hasil tu, andia Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga dong.<bt>Then, that evil person comes to scatter those grass seeds, that is the evil spirit's own big boss. And that season for gathering harvest, that is the end.of.the.world. The workers who take that harvest, they are are God's underlings from heaven (*angels).</bt><v n="40" />Waktu hari kiamat, dong kumpul ame itu rumput dong ko bakar buang.<bt>At the end of the world, they gather up that grass to burn it up.</bt><v n="41" />Te Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, nanti kirim datang ana bua dari sorga dong. Nanti dong pi kumpul ame sang samua orang yang sonde iko Tuhan pung parenta. Deng dong ju kumpul ame sang samua orang yang goda sang orang laen, ko dong jang iko Tuhan pung parenta.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, later will sent underlings from heaven. Later they will go gather all the people who do not follow the Lord's commands. And they also will gather all the people who tempt other people, to not follow the Lord's commands.</bt><v n="42" />Nanti dong lempar buang itu orang jahat samua pi dalam api naraka, sama ke rumput yang kaná bakar. Di situ, baru dong rasa sangsara mau mati, deng manangis makarereu tar pake barenti.<bt>Later they will throw away all those evil people into hell fire, the same as that grass that was burned up. There then they will feel great suffering and cry wailing without stopping.</bt><v n="43" />Ma orang yang idop lurus iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, nanti dong tenga tarús deng dong pung Bapa Raja di sorga. Di situ, dong basinar taráng sama ke matahari. Naa! Orang yang mau mangarti sang Beta, pasang talinga bae-bae, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>But people who live straight/righteous according to God's will, later they stay/live continually with their Father King in heaven. There they shine clearly like the sun. So! People who want to understand Me, attach your ears!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al barang yang mahal mau mati<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about a thing which is very expensive</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Yesus tamba satu umpama lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang mau mangarti Tuhan pung pegang parenta, sama ke orang yang kapingin mau dapa barang yang mahal mati pung, yang orang parná sambunyi dalam tana sapo'ong. Itu orang datang gali, ju dia dapa katumu itu barang di situ, andia ko dia sanáng mau mati. Ais dia kubur bale itu barang. Ju dia pulang capát-capát, ko pi jual abis dia pung harta samua-samua. Tarús dia pi béli ame itu tana, ko biar dia bisa soa memang itu barang mahal tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus added an example again saying, &lt;&lt;Those people who want to understand God2's rule/government, are like a person who wants to get/obtain an incredibly expensive thing which someone has hidden in a piece of land. That person comes digging, and s/he finds that thing there, and that's why s/he is very happy. Then s/he burys again that thing. And s/he goes home quickly, to completely sell all of his/her wealth. Next, s/he goes to buy that land, so that s/he can actually posses that expensive thing.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapingin ~ kapengen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">kapingin ~ kapengen</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al mutiara yang mahal<bt>The Lord Yesus give an example about a pearl which is very expensive</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Yesus tamba lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang mau mangarti Tuhan pung pegang parenta, sama ke orang dagang satu yang kapingin mau dapa mutiara yang mahal mati pung. Ais dia cari-cari mutiara ko mau béli.<bt>Yesus added again saying, &lt;&lt;Those people who want to understand God2's rule/government, are like a merchant who wants to obtain pearls which is/are very expensive. So he keeps hunting for pearl to buy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed to pearl [EXEG]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">***changed to pearl [EXEG]</Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Waktu dia katumu satu mutiara yang talalu bagus, ju dia pulang capát-capát, ko pi jual abis dia pung harta samua-samua. Tarús dia pi béli itu mutiara, ko biar dia bisa soa memang.&gt;&gt;<bt>When he found a pearl that was very good, then he went home quickly, to completely sell all of his wealth. Next he went and bought that pearl, so that he/she could actually own it.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al ma'isi pukat<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about sorting a [fish]net</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Yesus tamba lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta tu, sama ke satu pukat yang nalayan dong pi lapás di dano. Ais itu pukat dapa ikan macam-macam.<bt>Yesus added again saying, &lt;&lt;God's rule/government is the same as a dragnet which fishermen go release/spread.out in the lake. Then that net gets all.kinds of fish. [EXEG: Gk “large body of water”. NRSV goes to “sea”; CEV and TN Display go to “lake”; CONTEXT: Jesus (collective) are still hanging around Galilee, so we go with lake.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Waktu itu pukat su ponu deng ikan, ju nalayan dong datang angka ame, ko bawa pi pante. Ais dong dudu ko ma'isi ikan dari pukat. Ikan yang bae, dong kasi maso pi karanjang. Ma ikan yang sonde bae, dong lempar buang.<bt>When that net is full of fish, then the fishermen come and take it up, to bring it to the beach. Then they sit and sort the fish from the net. The fish which are good, they put into basket/s. But the fish which are not good, they throw away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma'isi = sort out from a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">ma'isi = sort out from a bunch</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Bagitu ju deng hari kiamat. Nanti Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dong datang dari sorga, ko pi kasi pisa orang yang jahat dari orang yang hati lurus.<bt>It will be like that also, at the end of the world. Later God's underlings will come from heaven, and separate the people who are evil from the people who have straight livers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added paragraph (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added paragraph (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="50" />Nanti dong lempar buang itu orang jahat samua pi dalam api naraka. Di situ, baru dong rasa sangsara mau mati, deng manangis makarereu tar pake barenti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later they will throw away all those evil people into hell fire. There they will then feel great suffering and cry wailing without ever stopping.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar so'al ajaran lama, deng ajaran baru<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about old teachings, and new teachings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Omong abis bagitu, ju Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong mangarti samua yang Beta su omong tadi, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>After finishing speaking like that, then Yesus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;Do you understand everything which I have spoken just now, [+tag question]?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Mangarti, Bapa!&gt;&gt;<bt>They replied saying, &lt;&lt;[We] understand, Father/sir!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Ais ju Yesus manyao bale bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae! Te tiap guru agama yang su batúl-batúl balajar Tuhan pung Kata-kata yang tatulis memang dari dolu, ais dia ju pegang kuat Beta pung ajaran sakarang ni, na, dia sama ke satu tuan ruma yang suka buka dia pung gudang, ko kasi tunju dia pung harta yang lama, sama-sama deng dia pung harta yang baru.&gt;&gt;<bt>Afterwards then Yesus replied back saying, &lt;&lt;Good/Ok! Cuz (elaboration) each religious teacher who truly studies/learns the Lord's Words which have been written beforehand from long ago, then he also holds firmly to My teachings now, na, /she like a house owner/master who likes to open up his storehouse to show/display his old wealth/possessions, together with his new wealth/possessions.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***undertranslated, reworked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">***undertranslated, reworked</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And he said to them,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z" status="Information">NRSV: And he said to them, “Therefore every scribe who has been trained (lit. having become a disciple) for the kingdom of heaven is like the master of a household who brings out of his treasure what is new and what is old.”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais ju Yesus manyao bale, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Ais ju Yesus manyao bale, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae! Te orang yang mangarti Tuhan pung Kata-kata yang tatulis memang dari dolu, ais dong tarima lai Beta pung ajaran sakarang ni, na, dong tu sama ke satu tuan ruma yang sanáng pake dia pung harta yang lama, sama-sama deng dia pung harta yang baru.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Nasaret tola buang sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Nasaret people reject the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 6:1-6; Lukas 4:16-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Waktu Yesus su ajar abis orang banya dong pake umpama, ju Dia jalan kasi tenga itu tampa,<bt>When Yesus had finished teaching many people using examples, then He walked/traveled leaving that place,</bt><v n="54" />ko pulang pi Dia pung kampong. Di situ, Dia maso pi ruma sambayang ko ajar orang. Samua orang yang dengar sang Dia, heran mau mati. Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ini Orang pung pintar ame lai! Dia balajar di mana ni? Karmana ko sampe Dia bisa bekin itu tanda heran dong?<bt>to go home to His village. There, He entered into the worship house to teach people. All the people who heard Him, were very amazed. They conversed with each other saying, &lt;&lt;Awii! [+impressed] This person's skill is great! Where did he study/learn? How is it that He can do those miracles?</bt><v n="55" />Padahal Dia ni cuma tukang kayu pung Ana sa. Kotong kanál bae Dia pung mama Maria; deng Dia pung adi-adi dong, andia Yakobis, Yusuf, Yudas deng Simon.<bt>In actual fact He here is only just a carpenter's child. We-inc know well His mama Maria; and His younger siblings, who are Yakobis, Yusuf, Yudas and Simon.</bt><v n="56" />Kotong ju kanál sang Dia pung adi parampuan dong, te kotong samua tenga satu kampong na! Jadi Dia dapa Dia pung pintar tu, dari mana lai? Deng Dia dapa Dia pung kuasa hebat tu, dari sapa lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>We-inc also know His female younger siblings, cuz (elaboration) we-inc all live in one village obviously! So (consequently), where else did He that great skill/knowledge of His from? And He got that amazing power of His, from who else?&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="57" />Andia ko dong kakodok, sampe dong su sonde mau dengar sang Dia lai.<bt>That's why they were jealous/irritated, to the point that they did not want to listen to Him anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl! Di tampa laen, orang dong suka kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah pung jubir. Ma di dia pung kampong deng isi ruma sandiri, orang sonde mau hormat sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus told saying, &lt;&lt;It's really true! In other places, people like to give respect to God's spokespeople. But in his own village and household, people don't want to respect him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** new structure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** new structure</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te orang lebe suka kasi hormat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Te orang lebe suka kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah pung utusan dari tampa laen, daripada di kampong sandiri.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:57" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 4:44</note><v n="58" />Tagal dong pung hati karás sampe dong sonde mau parcaya sang Yesus, andia ko Dia sonde bekin tanda heran bam-banya di situ.<bt>Because their livers were hard to the point that they did not want to believe Yesus, that why He did not do many miracles there. [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: “He did only a few...”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong potong bekin mati sang Yohanis tukang sarani<bt>They cut killing Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 6:14-29; Lukas 9:7-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, raja Herodes pegang parenta di propinsi Galilea. Dia ju dengar kabar macam-macam so'al Yesus.<bt>At that time, king Herodes held authority in Galilea province. He also heard various kinds of news about Yesus.</bt><v n="2" />Dia kasi tau dia pung pagawe dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Yesus ni, tantu Yohanis tukang sarani yang tempo hari beta suru potong ame dia pung kapala. Sakarang dia su idop kambali, ó! Andia ko dia ada pung kuasa ko bekin itu tanda heran dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>He told his officials saying, &lt;&lt;This Yesus here, is surely Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer who previously I ordered to cut off his head. Now he lives again! That's why he has power to do those miracles.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Raja Herodes omong bagitu, te dolu dia ada baparkara deng Yohanis, sampe dia tangkap deng buang sang Yohanis pi bui. Itu parkara pung carita bagini: raja Herodes su kawin ame sang dia pung adi Filipus pung maitua, nama Herodias. Padahal Filipus deng Herodias balóm bacere.<bt>King Herodes spoke like that, cuz (elaboration) previously he was having an on.going.argument/litigation with Yohanis, to the point that he captured and threw Yohanis into jail. That litigation's story is like this: king Herodes had married his younger sibling Filipus' wife, named Herodias. However in actual fact, Filipus and Herodias had not yet divorced. [EXEG 1: CEV is overtranslating here by making ‘chains’ explicit. ‘Chains’ is not inherently part of the meaning of the Gk word. NLT reads the Greek as I do, and streamlines a fairly literal “had John arrested and restricted/ restrained/ imprisoned/ him (to be put) away in prison…[middle voice]” to read more smoothly “H had arrested and imprisoned John…” Note also LN assigns the meaning of this Gk word in this context to the sense of ‘imprison’, not to the sense of ‘bind’.] [EXEG 2: (not yet divorced): This is very complex, and has involved the commentary discussion of all three synoptic gospels, not just Matthew because of the slim background info available. It is complicated by RL cultures, in which you CAN marry your brother's wife IF he is already dead, or more problematically if he is divorced. So without filling in an ellipted proposition, the perkara doesn't make any sense in the RL cultures. Note the Gk in the synoptics uses ‘take’, or ‘have’ (his brother's wife), but not the normal Gk words for ‘marry’. This is complicated by commentaries sloppily using the English word ‘marry’ in this discussion. So the questions are: 1) did Herod divorce his own wife first? (IVP Dict. says “he divorced her in order to marry Herodias, the wife of his half-brother Herod Philip.”) and 2) did Philip divorce Herodias before Antipas ‘took’ her? There doesn't seem to be any evidence that he did. What was it that was unlawful? Apparently it wasn't divorce. In relation to question #1, Carson (p.338) says “John probably did not denounce Antipas for divorcing his former wife, an action probably judged allowable…” (going on to give sources as to why he thinks it was allowable). He points out that Herodias was both his sister-in-law and also his neice, “but for most Jews there was no bar to marrying a niece” (going on to give sources as to why he thinks it was not an issue). So we take “his brother Philip's wife” to mean his current wife, not his ex. So our solution is working within the constraints of the text, within the space provided for in the commentaries, and makes sense of it for the RL cultures.]</bt><v n="4" />Andia ko Yohanis togor ulang-ulang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa raja sonde bole ba'ame deng bapa pung adi pung bini. Te itu su langgar kotong pung adat Yahudi na!&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why Yohanis scolded over and over saying, &lt;&lt;Father king may not take father's (=your) younger sibling's wife. Cuz (elaboration) that violates our-inc Jewish custom obviously!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="14:3-4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 3:19-20; Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 18:16, 20:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma Herodes sonde mau toe sang dia, ju dia kawin deng Herodias sa. Iko yang batúl, Herodes kapingin mau bunu sang Yohanis. Ma dia eleng sang orang banya, tagal dong parcaya bilang, Yohanis tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir. Andia ko dia suru dia pung orang, ko kasi maso Yohanis pi dalam bui.<bt>But Herodes did not want to pay.attention to him, and he married Herodias anyway. According to the truth (=in actual fact), Herodes wanted to murder Yohanis, but he was fearful of the many people, because they believed that, that Yohanis, was God's spokesperson. That's why he ordered his people, to put Yohanis in jail. [EXEG: / NOTE to daughter translations: Is 1st sentence addition? Several complications. First, flashback-all this took place prior to its immediate setting. So in this region one can flash back explain the root/source/cause of a dispute to the uninformed. Local culture allows brothers to marry widows, but not to steal brother's wives (still living and not divorced). This is implied information supported by the commentaries, and discussed at length by some in relation to “the Herods”, for example in relation to sorting out the two Philips in Luke 3:1 and 3:19. The story doesn't work here without this info in vs.3. Vs. 4 is John scolding Herod. Local expectation: Of course Herod complies, because that is cultural law, and John was a prophet. In the Gk, there is a disconnect between vs. 4 and vs. 5. We fill in the ellipsed proposition (implicit to explicit) that transitions these two verses, and seems to be supported by the Mark and Luke versions. All versions (e.g. Matt. “had been telling”) seem to imply John's objections happened repeatedly over a considerable period of time, and somewhere during this process (perhaps near the beginning?) Herod went ahead anyway and married Herodias (or shacked up-the encyclopedias don't address this distinction, with all of the wife-swapping happening between the various Herods, their brothers, sons, and nephews).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma lama-lama, ju Herodes ada pesta hari jadi. Itu waktu, mama raja Herodias pung ana nona pi baronggeng mangada pi tamu dong. Dia pung ronggeng tu talalu bagus, sampe bekin Herodes pung hati sanáng mau mati.<bt>But eventually then Herodes had his birthday feast. At that time mother king (=normal term for king's wife) Herodias' daughter went to dance in front of the guests. That dancing of hers was really nice to the point that it made Herodes' liver very happy.</bt><v n="7" />Baronggeng abis, ju Herodes pange itu ana nona ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu mau minta apa sang beta, na, kasi tau sa! Te nanti beta kasi sang lu. Beta pegang batúl-batúl beta pung janji ni. Deng beta sumpa pake Tuhan Allah pung nama.&gt;&gt;<bt>The dancing finished then Herodes called that young girl and said, &lt;&lt;What ever you want to ask from me, na, just tell it! Cuz (elaboration) later I will give it to you. I hold truly this promise of mine. And I oath/swear using God's name.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: the Gk word here is not just a plain oath, but one that calls on a divine name for sanctions/punishment if the oath is not fulfilled. Pretty serious stuff. LN.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Dengar raja pung omong bagitu, ju itu nona pung mama tusu-tusu sang dia. Andia ko dia pi minta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Beta minta Yohanis tukang sarani pung kapala. Taro dalam dulang, ko bawa datang kasi sang beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing the king' speaking like that, then that girl's mother poked (=persuaded) her. That's why she went to request saying, &lt;&lt;Father! I request Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer's head. Put it on a tray, and bring it here, give it to me.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dengar itu nona minta bagitu, ju Herodes pung hati ilang memang. Ma dia sonde bisa hela kambali dia pung sumpa, te samua tamu su dengar na. Andia ko dia iko itu nona pung mau sa.<bt>Hearing that girl request like that, then Herodes liver disappeared right away (=discouraged/in.agony). But he could not pull back his oath, cuz (elaboration) all the guests had obviously heard it. That's why he just followed that girl's will.</bt><v n="10" />Tarús dia parenta ko orang pi potong ame Yohanis pung kapala di dalam bui.<bt>Next he commanded that people/person go cut off Yohanis head in jail.</bt><v n="11" />Dong potong ame Yohanis pung kapala, ju dong taro dalam dulang, ko pi kasi sang itu nona. Dia tarima ame itu dulang ju, dia koko bawa ko pi kasi sang dia pung mama.<bt>They cut off Yohanis' head, then they put it on a tray, to go give to that girl. She received that tray then, she carried took it to go give it to her mother.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Waktu Yohanis pung ana bua dong dengar dong su potong ame dia pung kapala, ju dong datang ame dia pung mayat, ko pi kubur. Ais dong pi lapor itu hal sang Yesus.<bt>When Yohanis' underlings heard they had cut off his head, then they came and took his corpse, to go bury [it]. Then they went to report that matter to Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi makan lima ribu orang lebe<bt>The Lord Yesus feeds five thousand people plus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 6:30-44; Lukas 9:10-17; Yohanis 6:1-14)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Waktu Yesus dengar itu kabar so'al Yohanis, ju Dia deng Dia pung ana bua dong mau ondor diri dari itu tampa. Ju dong nae parahu ko mau pi tampa sunyi ko bisa barenti cape. Ma orang banya dapa lia Yesus dong pung parahu ada iko-iko dano pung pinggir. Ais dong kaluar dari kampong dong, ju jalan capát-capát iko jalan darat. Andia ko dong sampe di tampa tujuan lebe dolo dari Yesus dong.<bt>When Yesus heard that news about Yohanis, then He and His underlings retreated/withdrew from that place. Then they got into a boat to go to a lonely place in order to stop from their tiredness (=rest). But many people saw Yesus them's boat going along the lake's edge. Then they came out of villages, and walked quickly along a land path/road. That's why they arrived at the destination ahead of Yesus (collective). [EXEG: Q: Is &lt;&lt;in order to rest&gt;&gt; a necessary implicit-explicit change? A: It's partly explicating the Gk word that some gloss as ‘privately’, but also added under consultant supervision in response to previous UNSs who link him going to an empty place as a response of fleeing in fear/terror (as they would do) at the news of his cousin John's beheading. Since that idea makes sense in the context, but has no support from the commentaries, it was felt we needed to force it in this direction, which is consistent with other times when he goes on retreat.]</bt><v n="14" />Waktu Dia turun dari parahu, ju Dia lia itu orang bam-banya dong ada tunggu-tunggu sang Dia. Ais Dia jato kasian sang dong. Ju Dia bekin bae dong pung orang saki dong.<bt>When He got out of the boat, then He saw those many people were waiting for Him. Then He felt pity for them. Then He healed their sick people. [EXEG: Gk “great crowd” (which later turns out to be in the thousands)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** banya &gt; bam-banya (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** banya &gt; bam-banya (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Waktu su sore, ju Dia pung ana bua dong datang kasi tau sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, é! Lebe bae Bapa suru ini orang dong samua ko dong pi béli makan di kampong-kampong badeka di sini. Te su sore ni! Di sini sonde ada makan apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>When it was late.afternoon/evening, then His underlings came told Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father! It's better that Father orders all these people so they go buy food in the villages near here. Cuz (elaboration) it's already late.afternoon/evening now! Here there is no food at all.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde usa! Bosong yang kasi makan sang dong sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;It's not necessary! It's just you-pl who gives food to them&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Aiih, Bapa, é! Botong sonde ada apa-apa ko kasi makan orang bagini banya ni. Botong mau bekin karmana? Te cuma ada roti lima bua, deng ikan dua ekor sa, ma!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they replied saying, &lt;&lt;Oh no, Father! We-exc don't have anything to feed as many people as this. What are we going to do? Cuz (elaboration) [there is] only just five bread and two fish, <span class="Italic">[ma</span> = protest particle]!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ma Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo! Su bae tu. Bawa datang su!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Yea (= agreement)! That's good. Bring it here!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="19" />Tarús Dia suru itu orang dong samua ko dudu bakumpul di atas rumput. Ais ju Yesus ame itu roti lima bua, deng itu ikan dua ekor. Ju Dia mangada pi langit ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais itu, Dia kasi pica-pica itu roti, ju sorong kasi pi di Dia pung ana bua, ko dong pi bagi-bagi kasi sang itu orang dong samua.<bt>Next He ordered all those people to sit in groups on top the grass. Afterwards then, Yesus took those five loaves of bread, and those two tails of fish. Then He faced to the sky to request thankyou to God. After that, He broke that bread, and extended it to His underlings, for them to go divide it to all those people. [NOTE to daughter translations: discuss with team merits of streamlining /ame itu roti deng itu ikan dong/ or keeping /ame itu roti lima bua, deng itu ikan dua ekor/. The Gk has it, and retaining the fuller (but reduntant) info may enhance the power of the miracle.]</bt><v n="20" />Ais ju dong samua makan sampe kinyang. Makan abis ju, dong pi kumpul ame itu makanan sisa dong, sampe ponu dua blas bakul.<bt>Afterwards then they all ate until satisfied. After eating then, they went to gather up the leftover food, until filling twelve <span class="Italic">bakul</span> baskets. [NOTE to daughter translations: Just like in Mark, the Gk here uses different terms for the baskets after feeding the 5,000, than after feeding the 4,000 (Matt. 15:37). Although LN says we can't be sure of the relative sizes, some sources way the Gk term for basket used for the 4,000 is slightly larger than the one here. Most of our lgs have lexical terms that can reflect this difference. KM doesn't. Both should be able to be picked up and carried, so avoid the gigantic baskets.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Samua orang yang iko makan tu, kira-kira ada lima ribu laki-laki. Balóm reken tamba parampuan deng ana-ana dong lai.<bt>All the people who got to eat there, were approximately five thousand men. That does not yet count adding in.addition the women and children.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bajalan di atas aer<bt>The Lord Yesus walks on top water</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 6:45-52; Yohanis 6:16-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dong samua makan abis ju, Yesus suru Dia pung ana bua dong pi nae parahu ko dong pi lebe dolo di dano pung sablá. Ma Dia masi tenga di situ, ko suru itu orang banya dong pulang.<bt>They all finished eating then, Yesus ordered His underlings to go get in the boat for them to go on ahead to the lake's [other] side. But He still stayed there, to order those many people to go.home.</bt><v n="23" />Waktu dong samua su pulang, ju Yesus nae pi atas gunung satu, ko sambayang. Sampe malam, te Dia masi sandiri di situ.<bt>When they all had gone home, then Yesus went up on top of a mountain, to pray. When it was night, He was still alone there.</bt><v n="24" />Itu waktu, Dia pung ana bua dong pung parahu su sampe jao di dano pung teng-tenga. Ma dong ada badayong satenga mati, tagal parahu balayar lawan angin muka, deng galombang bésar hantam sang dong.<bt>At that time, His underling's boat had arrived far into the middle of the lake. But they were paddling extremely hard, because the boat was sailing opposing a front wind, with big waves striking them.</bt><v n="25" />Amper siang, ju Yesus pi iko sang dong. Ma Dia ada jalan di atas aer.<bt>[When it was] almost light, then Yesus went following them. But He was walking on top of the water.</bt><v n="26" />Lia bagitu ju, itu ana bua dong takuju mati. Dong omong taku-taku bilang, &lt;&lt;He'e! Ada hantu tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that then, those underlings were very startled. They spoke fearfully saying, &lt;&lt;He'e! [+unexpected] There's a ghost there!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ma Yesus omong langsung sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Woe! Bosong jang taku, ó! Te Beta ni, Yesus! Aman-aman sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus spoke immediately to them saying, &lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Woe!</span> You-pl don't be afraid! Cuz (elaboration) I here am Yesus! Everything's safe/ok!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dengar bagitu, ju Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo situ memang Bos, na, suru beta jalan di atas aer ko pi di Bos.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then Petrus replied saying, &lt;&lt;If there (=you in this context) is truly Bos, na, order me to walk on top of the water to go to Bos.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Much discussion in the literature that Matt wants to emphasize that Peter is double-checking that this is really the LORD (not just addressing ‘sir’ with respect.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu! Mari sini su!&gt;&gt; Ju Petrus kaluar dari parahu ko pi di Yesus deng jalan di atas aer.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;OK! Come here!&gt;&gt; Then Petrus got out of the boat to go to Yesus by walking on top of the water.</bt><v n="30" />Ma waktu Petrus rasa ada angin karás, ju dia taku mau mati. Dia mulai tanggalám, ju dia batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Aduu, Bos, é! Kasi salamat sang beta doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>But when Petrus felt there was strong wind, then he was terrified. He began to sink, then he yelled, saying &lt;&lt;Oh no Bos! Save me!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Make it natural to the context. Don't force the spiritual reading of “save”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Langsung Yesus sorong Dia pung tangan capát-capát ko pegang ame sang dia. Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Aiih, Pe'u, é! Akurang ko lu pung hati bacabang? Lu sonde parcaya batúl sang Beta, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Immediately Yesus extended His hand quickly to hold him. He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Aiih, [+exasperation] Pe'u (=nickname for Peter)! Why are you doubting (branch livered)? Don't you believe in Me [+tag question]?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais itu, dong dua maso pi dalam parahu. Ju angin tadó memang.<bt>After that, they two entered into the boat. Then the wind calmed down right away.</bt><v n="33" />Lia bagitu, ju Dia pung ana bua dong angka puji-puji sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Bapa ni, memang batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, then His underlings praised Him saying, &lt;&lt;Awii [+amazement]! Father here is really truly God's Child!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang saki dong di Genesaret<bt>The Lord Yesus heals sick people in Genesaret</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 6:53-56)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Waktu dong sampe di dano pung sablá ju, dong turun di kampong Genesaret pung pante.<bt>When they arrived at the other side of the lake then, they got down/disembarked at Genasaret village's beach.</bt><v n="35" />Waktu dong turun, te orang banya dong langsung kanál sang dong. Ju dong mulai batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Yesus su datang, ó!&gt;&gt; Dong lari pi kasi tau kuliling, ju orang bawa datang samua orang saki dong.<bt>When they disembarked, many peple immediately recognised them. Then they began to yell saying, &lt;&lt;We! [+get attention] Yesus has come!&gt;&gt; They ran to tell all around, and people brought all their sick people.</bt><v n="36" />Dong minta ko dong bisa sonto ame Dia pung baju. Te dong pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal orang saki sonto ame Yesus pung ujung baju sa, tantu dong bae memang.&gt;&gt; Ju samua orang saki yang sonto Dia pung baju, bae memang.<bt>They requested that they could touch His robe/clothes. Cuz (elaboration) they thought saying, &lt;&lt;As long sick people touch just the edge of Yesus' robe/clothes, surely they will be healed straight away.&gt;&gt; And all the sick people who touch that robe of His, were healed straight away.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Manusia bekin dong pung atoran ko ganti buang Tuhan Allah pung parenta<bt>Humans make their regulations to replace throw away God's commands</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 7:1-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Satu waktu, ada rombongan orang Farisi deng guru agama datang dari Yerusalem ko katumu deng Yesus.<bt>One time, a group of Farisi people and religion teachers come from Yerusalem to meet with Yesus.</bt><v n="2" />Orang Farisi dong pegang karás dong pung adat Yahudi. Waktu dong dengar bilang, Yesus pung ana bua dong makan sonde cuci tangan iko adat pung mau, ju dong jengkel. Ais dong datang ko kasi sala sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu pung ana bua dong makan, ma sonde cuci tangan dolo? Itu su malawan kotong pung nene-moyang pung adat tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Farisi people hold/held tightly to their Jewish custom. When they heard that Yesus' underlings ate without washing their hands follow the will/rules of custom, then they got upset. Then they came and accused Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Why do your underlings eat, but not wash their hands first? That there violates our-inc ancestors' custom!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Removed /itu/ at beginning, since"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** Removed /itu/ at beginning, since this is general, not specific (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ni memang orang yang omong laen bekin laen! Bosong pintar malawan Tuhan Allah pung parenta, ko iko bosong pung nene-moyang pung adat sa.<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;You here are really people who say one thing and do another! You are skilled at opposing God's commands, in order to follow only your ancestor's custom.</bt><v n="4" />Te Tuhan Allah su parenta bilang, &lt;Kasi hormat sang bosong pung mama-bapa.&gt; Deng tamba lai bilang, &lt;Kalo satu orang maki dia pung bapa ko mama, musti hukum kasi mati sang dia.&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God has commanded saying, &lt;&lt;Honor your papa-mama.&gt;&gt; And add again saying, &lt;If a person curses his father or mama, must give him the death sentence.&gt;</bt><note reference="15:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:12, 21:17, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 20:9, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:16</note><v n="5-6" />Tuhan Allah ajar bagitu, ma bosong ajar laen lai. Te bosong bilang, &lt;Satu orang sonde parlú pake dia pung barang ko tolong dia pung mama-bapa, biar dong sangsara mati pung, kalo dia su janji mau kasi itu barang sang Tuhan.&gt; Ma deng bosong ajar bagitu, bosong su buang Tuhan Allah pung parenta, ko ganti deng bosong pung atoran sandiri.<bt>God taught like that, but you teach different again. Cuz (elaboration) you say, &lt;A person doesn't need to use his thing/possession to help his/her father-mother, even if/though they are in great difficulty, if s/he has already promised to give that thing to God2.&gt; But by teaching like that, you have thrown out God's commands, and exchanged it with your own regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo orang janji mau kasi satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Kalo orang janji mau kasi satu barang sang Tuhan Allah, biar dia pung papa-mama sangsara mo mati, ma itu barang sonde bole pake ko bantu sang dong, te dia su janji mau kasi sang Tuhan Allah na.&gt;</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Andia ko tadi Beta su bilang, bosong ni, orang yang omong laen bekin laen! Itu pas deng apa yang Tuhan pung jubir Yesaya su tulis memang so'al bosong dari dolu-dolu! Te Tuhan ada pake dia ko tulis bilang,<bt>That's why earlier I said, you here, are people who say one thing and do another! That fits with what the Lord's spokesperson Yesaya wrote ahead of time about you from long ago! Cuz (elaboration) the Lord used him to write saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />&lt;Ada orang yang puji sang Beta,<bt>'There are people who *praise Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">cuma deng mulu sa, ma sonde deng hati.<bt>only just with [their] mouth/s, but not with their livers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />Biar dong bekin bagitu ju, parcuma sa.<bt>Even if they do like that, its just fruitless/pointless.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong sonde toe deng Beta,<bt>They don't care.about/pay.attention.to Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te dong cuma toe deng manusia pung atoran sa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) they only just follow humans' regulations.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="15:8-9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 29:13</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Parkara jahat kaluar dari orang pung hati<bt>Evil matters come out of people's livers [NOTE to daughter translations: /parkara/ here = hal. Some second lg MTTs have misread it]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 7:14-23)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais itu, Yesus pange orang laen di situ ko ajar sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pasang talinga bae-bae, ko bosong bisa mangarti!<bt>After that, Yesus called other people there to teach them saying, &lt;&lt;Attach your ears well, so that you can understand!</bt><v n="11" />Apa yang maso pi dalam orang pung mulu, itu sonde bekin kamomos orang. Ma apa yang kaluar dari orang pung mulu, itu yang bekin kamomos.&gt;&gt;<bt>That which enters into a person's mouth, that doesn't make people dirty/defiled. But that which comes out of a person's mouth, that is what makes dirty/defiled.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais itu, Yesus pung ana bua dong datang ko kasi tau sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa tau, ko? Itu orang Farisi dong saki hati dengar Bapa pung omong.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus' underlings came to tell Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father knows, right? Those Farisi people were offended hearing that speaking of Father's.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung Bapa di sorga nanti cabu buang orang yang sonde ajar orang iko Tuhan pung mau. Itu sama ke orang tofa buang samua tanaman yang dia sonde tanam.<bt>But Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;My Father in heaven later will yank out people who do not teach people according/following His will. That is like a person weeds all plants which he has not planted.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added itu to beginning of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added itu to beginning of last sentence (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Jadi, jang toe deng itu orang Farisi dong! Te dong tu, sama ke orang buta yang kasi tunju jalan sang orang buta. Nanti dong jato rame-rame maso pi dalam lobang.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), you shouldn't be.concerned (=strong dismissal) with those Farisi people! Cuz (elaboration) they there are like blind people who show the way to blind people. Later they will go along enthusiastically and fall together into a hole.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="15:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 6:39</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais ju Petrus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, tolong kasi tau sang botong itu umpama tadi pung arti dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Afterwards then Petrus spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Father, please tell us that earlier example's meaning!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Bosong ju balóm mangarti?<bt>Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;What! You also still don't understand?</bt><v n="17" />Dia pung maksud bagini: apa yang kotong makan, maso di mulu, tarús pi dalam parú, abis kaluar ulang pi tampa buang aer.<bt>It's meaning is like this: that which we-inc eat, enters into the mouth, next goes into the stomach, and afterwards comes out again to the place of throwing water (=defecating). [EXEG: see Gk. ‘latrine’.]</bt><v n="18" />Ma apa yang kaluar dari mulu, itu yang bekin kamomos orang, sampe Tuhan Allah ju noju sang dia, deng sonde mau tarima sang dia.<bt>But that which comes out of the mouth, that is what makes a person dirty/defiled to the point that God is also repugnanted by him, and does not want to accept him. [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT in last clause: sonde mau badeka/bagabung/basatu deng dia.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:34</note><v n="19" />Te banya parkara yang jahat kaluar dari orang pung hati! Sama ke: pikir jahat, bunu orang, barsina, maen serong deng orang yang bukan dia pung laki ko dia pung bini, mancuri, saksi putar-balek, deng omong bekin busuk orang pung nama.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) many things which are evil come out of people's livers! Like: thinking evil, killing people, adultery, illicit sex with a person who is not his/her husband or wife, stealing, deceiving witness [EXEG: Morris], and slander someone's name/reputation.</bt><v n="20" />Hal-hal bagitu tu, yang bekin orang jadi kamomos. Ma kalo orang cuma makan deng sonde cuci tangan iko adat pung mau, na, itu sonde jadi so'al.&gt;&gt;<bt>It's matters/issues like that, which make people dirty/defiled. But if people just eat without washing their hands according to custom, that is not a problem.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bantu satu mama yang bukan orang Yahudi<bt>The Lord Yesus helps a mama who is not a Jewish person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 7:24-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais ju Yesus kasi tenga itu tampa, ko pi di da'era yang badeka deng kota Tirus deng kota Sidon.<bt>Afterwards then Yesus left that place, to go to the area close to the city of Tirus and the city of Sidon.</bt><v n="22" />Di situ ada satu mama yang asal dari itu da'era. Dia bukan orang Yahudi. Waktu dia dengar Yesus su ada, dia datang minta deng sunggu-sunggu bilang, &lt;&lt;Raja Daud pung turunan, é! Kasian sang beta doo! Te beta pung ana nona ada takaná setan. Aduu, kasian, é! Te dia su sangsara.&gt;&gt;<bt>There there was a mama who originated/came.from that area. She was not a Jewish person. When she heard Yesus was there, she came to request earnestly saying, &lt;&lt;King Daud's descendant! Have pity on me! Cuz (elaboration) my daughter is afflicted by an evil spirit. Oh please have mercy, é! Cuz (elaboration) she is already suffering.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: a native from that area, Canaanite see CONNOT M. Crofts]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asal dari itu daerah: a native"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">asal dari itu daerah: a native from that area, Canaanite see CONNOT M. Crofts</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ma Yesus diam sa, deng sonde manyao apa-apa. Ju Dia pung ana bua dong datang lapor bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, ini mama ni maen batarea bekin tasibu sa. Lebe bae Bapa suru dia iskarobis dari sini su!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus was just quiet, and didn't answer anything. Then His underlings came to report saying, &lt;&lt;Father, this mama here keeps on yelling making things chaotic. It's better Father orders her to get out of here!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah suru Beta datang ko tolong kotong pung orang Yahudi, tagal dong su jalan sala, sama ke domba yang kasasar. Dia sonde suru Beta pi tolong orang laen.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;God ordered Me to come help our-inc Jewish people, because they are travelling/walking wrongly, like sheep which are lost. He didn't order Me to come help other people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma itu mama datang lai deka-deka sang Yesus. Dia tikam lutut deng minta tolong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Tolong sang beta doo.&gt;&gt;<bt>But that mama came again close to Yesus. She knelt and request help saying, &lt;&lt;Bos! Help me.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ma Yesus buang bahasa bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde pantas ame makanan dari ana-ana dong, ais buang kasi anjing.&gt;&gt; [Dia pung maksud tasambunyi bilang, Yesus musti bantu Dia pung orang Yahudi dolo, baru bisa bantu orang laen.]<bt>But Yesus threw language out (=spoke in 'code'/ with double meaning) saying, &lt;&lt;It's not appropriate to take food from the children, then throw it to the dongs.&gt;&gt; [With hidden meaning, that Yesus must help His own Yahudi people first, only then can help other people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ana-ana dong musti makan lebe dolo,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Ana-ana dong musti makan lebe dolo, baru buang dia pung sisa kasi anjing.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ma itu mama balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, Papa, é! Ma anjing dong ada tunggu-tunggu di kolong meja. Dong ju makan apa yang jato dari ana-ana dong pung piring.&gt;&gt; [Deng maksud bilang, waktu ana dong makan, anjing ju dapa makan. Biar Yesus bantu Dia pung orang, ma Dia ju musti lia orang laen.]<bt>But that mama responded saying, &lt;&lt;True, Papa, é! But the dogs are waiting under the table. They also eat what falls from the children's dishes.&gt;&gt; [With meaning saying, when the children eat, the dogs also gets to eat. Even though Yesus helps His people, nevertheless He also must look.after other people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added tunggu-tunggu -from context (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added tunggu-tunggu -from context (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Mama parcaya batúl sang Beta, ó! Jadi mama pulang su, te apa yang mama minta tu, su jadi memang!&gt;&gt; Ais dia pulang, ju dia lia dia pung ana su bae memang.<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus told saying, &lt;&lt;Awii! [+impressed] Mama truly believes in Me, ó! So mama go home, cuz (elaboration) that which mama requests there, it has already happened!&gt;&gt; Then she went home, and she saw her child was truly healed already.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae banya orang<bt>The Lord Yesus heals many people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong kasi tenga itu tampa, ju dong jalan iko-iko dano Galilea pung pinggir. Tarús dong nae satu gunung, ais Yesus dudu ko mangajar sang dong.<bt>After that, Yesus and His underlings left that place, and they walked along Galilea lake's edge. Next they went up a mountain, and Yesus sat down to teach them.</bt><v n="30" />Ju orang bam-banya datang sang Dia. Dong bawa orang kaki hela, orang buta, orang lumpu, orang sonde bisa omong, deng orang yang saki laen ju. Dong taro itu orang saki dong deka-deka di Yesus pung kaki. Ais Dia bekin bae sang dong.<bt>Then many-many people came to Him. They brought their people with drag feet, blind people, lame people, people who could not talk, and even people with other sickness. They put those sick people near Yesus' feet. Then He healed them.</bt><v n="31" />Lia bagitu, ju itu orang banya dong heran. Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Talalu hebat, ó! Orang kaki hela, bisa bajalan bae. Orang buta, bisa dapa lia. Orang lumpu, bisa bajalan. Deng orang sonde bisa omong, su bisa ba'omong! Ini pasti Tuhan Allah yang bekin. Dia tu, andia Tuhan yang kotong pung nene-moyang dong sémba dari dolu-dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing like that, then those many people, were amazed. They spoke with each other saying, &lt;&lt;Awii! [+impressed] Incredibly amazing, ó! People with drag foot, can walk well. Blind people, can see. Lame people can walk. And people who can't talk, now can converse! This is surely God who did it. He there is that Lord whom our-inc ancestors worshiped from long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi makan ampa ribu orang<bt>The Lord Yesus feeds four thousand people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 8:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Abis barapa hari ju, Yesus pange ame Dia pung ana bua dong ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su rasa kasian sang ini orang banya dong. Ada yang su datang dari jao, baru dong bakumpul su tiga hari, sampe su sonde ada makanan lai. Lebe bae dong jang pulang dolo deng parú kosong. Te jang sampe dong samaput di tenga jalan.&gt;&gt;<bt>After several days, Yesus called His underlings to say, &lt;&lt;I feel pity on this many people here. There are those who have come from far, then they have gathered already three days, until there is no more food. It's better they don't go home with empty stomachs. Cuz (elaboration) may it not be that they faint in the middle of the road.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ma Yesus pung ana bua dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Ini tampa kosong yang jao dari kampong. Sonde mungkin kotong bisa kasi makan orang bagini banya.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus' underlings replied saying, &lt;&lt;Father! This is an empty place far from village/s. It's not possible we-inc can feed this many people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pung roti, ada barapa banya?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;How much bread do you have?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuju sa! Deng ikan sadiki!&gt;&gt;<bt>They replied saying, &lt;&lt;Just seven! With a little bit of fish!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais Yesus suru itu orang dong samua ko dudu di tana.<bt>Then Yesus ordered all those people to sit on the ground.</bt><v n="36" />Ju Dia ame itu roti tuju bua deng ikan, ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Dia bekin pica-pica, ju Dia kasi pi Dia pung ana bua dong, ko dong pi babagi kasi itu orang dong samua.<bt>Then He took those seven loaves of bread with the fish, to request thankyou of God. Then He broke it into pieces, and He gave it to His underlings, for them to go divide it out to all those people.</bt><v n="37" />Ju dong samua makan sampe puas. Ais dong kumpul ame makanan lebe, sampe ponu tuju bakul.<bt>Then they all ate until satisfied. Then they gathered up the extra food, until seven baskets full. [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with Matt. 14:20. This should be a slightly larger type of basket here than there.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Samua orang yang iko makan tu, kira-kira ada ampa ribu orang laki-laki. Balóm reken tamba parampuan deng ana-ana dong.<bt>All the people who ate there, approximately four thousand males. [That] does not yet count adding women and children.</bt><v n="39" />Ais itu, Yesus suru itu orang banya dong pulang. Ju Dia nae parahu ko dong pi di da'era Magadan.<bt>After that, Yesus ordered those many people to go home. Then He got into the boat for them to go to Magadan area.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** ftn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** ftn</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:39" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini tampa di mana, sonde jalás. Ada tulisan bahasa Yunani yang laen, yang tulis bilang, &lt;Magdala&gt;. Ada laen lai yang tulis bilang, &lt;Magdalan&gt;.<bt>Where this place is, isn't clear. There are other Yunani language writings that write saying, ‘Magdala’. There are still others which write saying, ‘Magdalan’.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Farisi deng orang Saduki mau hiki kasi jato sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Farisi People and Saduki People want to ensnare making the Lord Yesus fall (=make him make a mistake)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 8:11-13; Lukas 12:54-56)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, ada barapa orang Farisi deng orang Saduki datang sang Yesus. Dong mau baso'al-jawab deng Dia, ko mau hiki sang Dia. Tagal itu, dong minta sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak! Tolong kasi tunju tanda heran doo, ko jadi bukti bilang, Pak su dapa kuasa dari Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, several Farisi people and Saduki people came to Yesus. They wanted to debate with Him, in order to trap Him. Because of that they requested Him saying, &lt;&lt;Sir! Please show/do a miracle, for evidence that Father has obtained power from God.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="16:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:38, Lukas 11:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo matahari tanggalám deng langit pung warna mera, bosong tanda bilang, &lt;Beso sonde akan ujan.&gt;<bt>But Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;If the sun sinks and the sky's colour is red, you-pl sign it (=see it as a sign/indication) saying, &lt;Tommorow [it's] not going to rain.&gt;</bt><v n="3" />Deng kalo matahari nae deng langit ba'awan itam, bosong tanda bilang, &lt;Ini hari mau ujan.&gt; Naa, kalo bosong bisa baca tanda cuaca bagitu, akurang ko bosong sonde bisa baca tanda-tanda jaman?<bt>And if the sun rises with the sky full of black clouds, you see it a sign saying, &lt;Today [it's] going to rain.&gt; Naa, [+shift] if you can read weather signs like that, why can you not read signs of the age/times? [NOTE to daughter translations: TH suggests: "you don't know how to explain the things happening now," "you don't know what these things happening now indicate for the future," or "there are things happening now, but you don't know what they mean." ALT: “read the meaning/significance of the signs of the times”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** tanda &gt; tanda-tanda (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** tanda &gt; tanda-tanda (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Wuih! Bosong orang sakarang ni, cuma tau bekin jahat sa! Bosong sonde toe sang Tuhan! Biar bosong minta tanda heran, ma Beta sonde kasi. Tagal dolu Tuhan su kasi tanda heran pake Dia pung jubir Yunus. Jadi itu su cukup!&gt;&gt; Omong abis bagitu, ju Yesus jalan kasi tenga sang dong.<bt><span class="Italic">Wuih</span> [+Good grief!] You people nowadays, only know just how do to evil! You don't care about God! Even if you request amazing sign/s (*miracle/s), but I won't give [them]. Because previously the Lord has already given amazing signs using His spokesperson Yunus. So (consequently) that's already enough!&gt;&gt; After finishing speaking like that, then Yesus went away leaving them.</bt><note reference="16:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:39, Lukas 11:29</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar bilang, ati-ati deng orang Farisi deng orang Saduki dong pung pangaru<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches saying, be careful with the Farisi people and the Saduki people' influence</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 8:14-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Waktu Yesus dong ada pi dano pung sablá, baru Dia pung ana bua dong inga bilang, dong lupa bawa roti buat dong pung bakál.<bt>When Yesus (coll.) were going to the other side of the lake, then His underlings remembered that they had forgotten to bring bread for their travel.food.</bt><v n="6" />Dengar dong omong bagitu, ju Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga é! Bosong musti ati-ati sang orang Farisi deng orang Saduki dong pung bibit roti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing them speak like that, then He told [them] saying, &lt;&lt;Remember, é! You-pl must be careful with the Farisi people and the Saduki people's bread seed (*yeast).&gt;&gt; [EXEG: not “in middle of lake” as in OV, but “going to the other side” which is one possible interpretation of the Gk participle. TB, CEV. “His underlings remembered” following NLT.]</bt><note reference="16:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dengar bagitu, ju Dia pung ana bua dong babingung. Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapatua ada omong apa tu? Mangkali Dia omong bagitu, tagal botong sonde bawa roti, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then His underlings were confused. The spoke to each other saying, &lt;&lt;What is elder.father (=term of respect) speaking about there? Probably He speaks like that, because we didn't bring bread, [+tag question]?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Yesus tau dong pung pikiran. Ais Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong ni su talalu! Akurang ko bosong omong so'al roti! Bosong kurang parcaya sang Beta, ko?<bt>But Yesus knew their thinking. So then He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! [+rebuke] You guys here are too much! Why are you talking about bread! You less/lack believe (=don't believe sufficiently) in Me, [+tag question]?</bt><v n="9" />Bosong masi balóm mangarti Beta pung kuasa, ko? Te itu hari waktu Beta bekin pica-pica itu roti lima bua ko kasi makan lima ribu orang tu, bosong ada kumpul ame dia pung lebe barapa bakul?<bt>Do you still not understang My power, [+tag question]? Cuz (elaboration) that day when I broke up those five loaves of bread to feed those five thousand people, how many baskets did you gather of that excess/left.over?</bt><note reference="16:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 14:17-21</note><v n="10" />Ais karmana lai deng itu tuju roti yang Beta bagi kasi ampa ribu orang tu? Bosong ada kumpul ame dia pung lebe barapa bakul?<bt>Then what about again those seven breads which I divided out to those four thousand people? How many baskets did you collect of that excess/left.over? [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk uses 2 different words for basket for 2 different incedents. If possible, use normal size for 5,000 and larger size for 4,000, as in Mark.]</bt><note reference="16:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 15:34-38</note><v n="11" />Akurang ko bosong sonde mangarti Beta pung omong tadi tu? Beta sonde omong so'al roti. Te Beta mau kasi inga sang bosong, ko biar bosong ati-ati deng orang Farisi deng orang Saduki dong pung ajaran. Te dong pung ajaran bisa pangaru orang banya, sama ke bibit roti kasi reis roti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Why do you not understand those words of Mine earlier? I wasn't talking about bread. Cuz (elaboration) I want/ed to remind you, so that you are careful of the Farisi people and the Saduki people's teaching. Cuz (elaboration) their teaching can influence many people, the same as bread seed makes the bread to become big.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Yesus omong bagitu, baru dong mangarti bilang, Dia sonde omong so'al roti. Ma Dia ada omong so'al orang Farisi deng orang Saduki dong pung ajaran yang sala.<bt>Yesus spoke like that and only then did they understand that He was not talking about bread. But He was talking about the Farisi people and the Saduki people teachings which are wrong.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus mangaku bilang, Tuhan Yesus tu, Kristus<bt>Petrus acknowledges that the Lord Yesus is Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 8:27-30; Lukas 9:18-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu, ju Yesus dong jalan pi da'era yang badeka deng kota Kaisarea Filipi. Di tenga jalan, Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko orang pung omong, dong bilang, Beta, andia Manusia Tulen ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, then Yesus them walked to the region near the city of Kaisarea Filipi. In the middle of the road/travel (Mark 8:27) He aked them saying, “According to people's talk, they say, I, the Ideal Human, am who?” [EXEG: vs.13 must also have people - Son of Man, then vs. 15 you - Me. (see Morris). tenga jalan from Mark 8:27.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada yang bilang Bapa ni, Yohanis tukang sarani yang su idop kambali. Laen bilang, mangkali Bapa ni, ba'i Elia. Laen lai bilang, ba'i Yeremia. Kalo sonde, na, Tuhan Allah pung jubir dolu-dolu yang laen.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;There are those who say Father here, is Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer who has lived again. Others say, probably Father here, is grandfather Elia. Yet others say, grandfather Yeremia. If not, na, one of God's other spokespersons from long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="16:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 14:1-2, Markus 6:14-15, Lukas 9:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tarús Yesus tanya lai sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo iko bosong sandiri, na, Beta ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Next Yesus asked them again saying, &lt;&lt;If according to your ownselves, na, I here, am who?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais ju Simon Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa ni, Kristus, andia itu Orang yang dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah su janji mau kirim datang! Deng Bapa ni, Tuhan Allah yang idop tarús pung Ana!&gt;&gt;<bt>And then Simon Petrus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Father here, is Kristus, that is that Person whom long ago God promised to send here! And Father  (=you) here, are the Child of the God who lives continually!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: be careful so that living/eternal modifies God, and not the Son. (focus, scope).]</bt><note reference="16:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 6:68-69</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Simon, Yunus pung ana, é! Lu ni, barontong, ó! Te bukan manusia yang kasi tau ini hal sang lu. Ma Beta pung Bapa di sorga yang kasi tau.<bt>Then Yesus said, &lt;&lt;Simon, Yunus' child! You-sg here are fortunate! Cuz (elaboration) it is not humans who told this matter to you. But My Father in heaven who told [you]. [NOTE to daughter translations: Many MTTs and UNSs have learned an Indonesian song that says “Simon, anak Yahya” (archaic Arabic form for Yohanes/John). The Matthew version says “Simon, son of Jonah”. The John version says “Simon, son of John”. See John 1:42, 21:15-17. See NLT note, and fuller info in TRT note.]</bt><v n="18" />Dengar, é! Sakarang Beta mau kasi nama &lt;Petrus&gt; sang lu. Te itu nama pung arti andia, &lt;batu&gt;.<bt>Listen! Now I want to name you, Petrus. Cuz (elaboration) that name's meaning is, stone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added Gk font to ftn,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added Gk font to ftn, cut-and-paste into yours (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:18" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Yesus ada maen kata di sini. Te bahasa Yunani bilang, Πέτρος (<span class="Italic">Petros,</span> andia, nama orang), deng πέτρᾳ (<span class="Italic">petra,</span> andia, batu).<bt>Yesus is making a word play here. Cuz (elaboration) the Yunani language says, Πέτρος <span class="Italic">Petros</span> (that is, a person's name), and πέτρᾳ <span class="Italic">(petra</span>, that is, rock).</bt></note>Nanti lu jadi fanderen kasi Beta pung orang parcaya dong, tagal lu pung parcaya su kuat ke batu. Biar dong kaná siksa sampe mati ju, dong batahan tarús.<bt>Later you will become a foundation for My believing people (=believers = church), because your faith is strong like stone. Even if they are tortured to the point of dying, they will endure continually. [EXEG: “gates of Hades will not prevail”. CONNOT (M.Crofts note), TH, TRT, CEV, EH.]</bt><v n="19" />Beta nanti kasi hak sang lu, ko urus Beta pung orang dong, sama ke lu pegang sorga pung konci. Te apa yang lu larang di ini dunya, itu Tuhan su larang di sorga. Deng apa yang lu kasi isin di ini dunya, itu Tuhan su kasi isin di sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>I will later give authority to you, to manage/arrange My people, like as if you held heaven's key. Cuz (elaboration) that which you forbid on earth, that God has already forbade in heaven. And that which you permit on earth, that God has already permited in heaven.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="16:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:18, Yohanis 20:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Omong abis bagitu, ju Yesus larang sang dong ko jang kasi tau sapa-sapa bilang Dia tu, Kristus.<bt>After speaking like that, then Yesus forbade them to not tell any one that He was Kristus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang so'al Dia pung mati deng Dia pung idop kambali<bt>The Lord Yesus foretells about His death and His living again</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 8:31--9:1; Lukas 9:22-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Mulai dari itu waktu, ju Yesus kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta musti pi kota Yerusalem. Ma nanti di situ, Beta dapa sangsara bam-banya dari tua-tua adat, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, deng guru agama dong samua. Nanti dong bunu bekin mati sang Beta, ma dia pung lusa, Beta idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Beginning from that time, then Yesus told His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;I must go to the city of Yerusalem. But later there, I will get lots of suffering from all the traditional elders, the *chief priests, and the religion teachers. Later they murder kill Me, but on the day.after.the.next.day, I will live again.</bt><note reference="16:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam bahasa Yunani, dong mulai itong dari: ini hari (= 1), beso (= 2), lusa (= 3), tula (= 4). Jadi dalam bahasa Yunani, τῃ τρίτῃ ἡμέρᾳ <span class="Italic">(tē tritē hēmera)</span> &lt;&lt;di hari yang katiga&gt;&gt; pung maksud dalam bahasa Kupang, andia &lt;&lt;dia pung lusa&gt;&gt;. Inga te, Tuhan Yesus mati hari jum'at (itong satu). Dia pung beso, andia hari sabtu (itong dua), Tuhan Yesus ada dalam kubur. Dia pung lusa, andia hari minggu (itong tiga), Tuhan Yesus idop kambali. Jadi iko kotong pung cara itong hari, na, Dia mati dua malam, ais Dia idop kambali.<bt>In the Yunani language, they begin counting from today (= 1), tomorrow (= 2), day.after.tomorrow (=3), day three (= 4). So (consequently), in the Yunani language, τῃ τρίτῃ ἡμέρᾳ <span class="Italic">(tē tritē hēmera)</span> “on the third day” means in the Kupang language, “the day after (tomorrow, next)”. Remember that, the Lord Yesus died on Friday (count one). Tomorrow/the next day, that is Saturday (count two), the Lord Yesus was in the grave. The day after(tomorrow/next), that is Sunday (count three), the Lord Jesus lived again/came back to life. So (consequently) according to the way that we-inc count days, na, He was dead for two nights, and then He came back to life.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Yesus kasi tau bagitu ju, Petrus hela ame sang Dia pi pinggir ko biar dong dua sandiri, ais togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa jang omong bagitu! Sonde mungkin Tuhan Allah kasi biar bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus told like that, then Petrus pulled/yanked Him away to the edge so the two of them were alone, then rebuked/scolded [him] saying, &lt;&lt;Father don't speak like that! It's not possible God would let that happen!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ma Petrus pung omong tu, sonde iko Tuhan pung mau. Andia ko Yesus bale ko togor sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Iskarobis dari sini! Itu tu, setan pung bos yang omong! Lu jang palang sang Beta! Lu cuma pikir iko manusia pung mau sa, bukan iko Tuhan pung mau!&gt;&gt;<bt>But that speaking of Petrus', did not follow the Lord's will. That's why Yesus turned back to scold him saying, &lt;&lt;Heh! [+rebuke] Get out of here! That there, is the Boss of the evil spirit/s' who is talking! You don't hinder/.obstruct Me! You only think just according to human's will/desire, not according to the Lord's will/desire!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais ju Yesus ajar sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang mau iko sang Beta, dia musti batahan iko tarús tiap hari! Dia musti lupa buang dia pung mau-mau sandiri, ko iko Tuhan pung mau sa. Biar orang mau bunu sang dia, dia musti iko tarús sa, sama ke orang pikol dia pung kayu palang ko pi mati.<bt>And then Yesus taught His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Person who wants to follow Me, s/he must endure following continually every day! He must forget completely his own will, in order to follow just the Lord's will. Even if people want to murder him/her, s/he must just follow continually, like a person shoulder.carrying his/her cross to go die.</bt><note reference="16:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:38, Lukas 14:27</note><v n="25" />Te orang yang sadia mati tagal dia iko sang Beta, nanti dia dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan. Ma orang yang cuma mau idop buat dia pung diri sandiri sa, nanti dia pung idop tu, ilang bagitu sa!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who is prepared to die because s/he follows Me, later s/he will be able to live continually with the Lord. But the person who only wants to live for just his/her own self, later that life of his/hers, will disapper just like that!</bt><note reference="16:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:39, Lukas 17:33, Yohanis 12:25</note><v n="26" />Dengar, é! Kalo lu dapa dunya pung isi samua, ma Tuhan Allah tola buang sang lu, na, dia pung ontong apa? Biar lu pikol bawa dunya pung isi samua ju, lu sonde bisa tukar deng lu pung jiwa!<bt>Listen up! If you obtain all of the world's contents, but God rejects you, well what is the benefit? Even if you shoulder.carry bringing all the world's contents, you cannot exchange [it/them] for your soul!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Beta kasi tau sang bosong ini hal samua, tagal Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Nanti Beta turun datang kambali pake Beta pung Bapa pung kuasa yang hebat, sama-sama deng Dia pung ana bua dari sorga. Itu waktu, nanti Beta balas kasi tiap orang iko apa yang dia bekin.<bt>I tell you all these things, because I here, am the Ideal/Prototypical Human. Later I will come back down using My Father's power which is impressive, together with His underlings from heaven. At that time later I will reciprocate to each person according to what s/he has done. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><note reference="16:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 25:31, Lagu Puji dong 62:12, Roma 2:6</note><v n="28" />Inga bae-bae, é! Nanti ada barapa orang dari bosong ni yang sonde akan mati, sampe kapan dong dapa lia sang Beta, andia Manusia Tulen, jadi Raja yang pegang parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember [this] well! Later there will be several people from among you here who do not die, until the time/when they get to see Me, the Idela Human, as a King who rules/governs.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Tuhan Yesus pung hebat<bt>God shows/reveals the greatness/glory of the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:2-13; Lukas 9:28-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="17" />
      <v n="1" />Lewat anam hari ju, Yesus pange sang Petrus, Yakobis deng dia pung adi Yohanis, ko dong sama-sama pi nae di atas satu gunung tinggi, ko dong sandiri di situ sa.<bt>After six days then, Yesus called Petrus, Yakobis and his younger sibling Yohanis, for them all to go up on top of a tall mountain, so that they would be alone there.</bt><v n="2" />Sampe di atas, ju dong lia Yesus su jadi laen. Dia pung muka basinar sama ke matahari, deng Dia pung pakean jadi puti mangkilat.<bt>Arriving at the top, they saw Yesus had become different. His face shone like the sun, and His clothes had become blazing/lightening white.</bt><v n="3" />Takuju sa, dong dapa lia Dia ada ba'omong deng ba'i Musa deng ba'i Elia.<bt>Unexpectedly, they saw Him conversing with Gf Musa and Gf Elia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Corrected order of Moses and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** Corrected order of Moses and Elijah (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ju Petrus jadi bingung, sampe dia omong sambarang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Botong su enak di sini, ó! Jadi lebe bae botong bekin tiga lopo. Satu kasi sang Bapa, satu kasi ba'i Musa, deng satu lai kasi ba'i Elia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus became confused, to the point that he spoke recklessly/without.basis saying, &lt;&lt;Father! We-exc are enjoying it here! So it's better if (=how about if) we make three <span class="Italic">(lopo)</span> huts. One for Father, one for Gf Musa, and one more for Gf Elia.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Waktu Petrus masi omong bagitu, takuju sa, awan yang manyala taráng turun datang ko tutu ame sang dong. Ju dong taheran-heran dengar satu suara kaluar dari itu awan bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, ó! Yesus ni, Beta pung Ana sayang. Dia salalu bekin sanáng Beta pung hati. Dengar bae-bae sang Dia, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Petrus was still talking like that, suddenly/unexpectedly a bright cloud came down and covered over them. Then they were surprised hearing a voice come out of the cloud saying, &lt;&lt;Listen up! Yesus here, is My loved Child. He always/regularly makes My liver happy. Listen well to him!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk. bright/shining cloud. ‘bright’ was missing from OV.]</bt><note reference="17:1-5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Petrus 1:17-18, Carita Mula-mula 22:2, Lagu Puji dong 2:7, Yesaya 42:1, Mateos 3:17, 12:18, Markus 1:11, Lukas 3:22, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 18:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu ana bua dong taku mau mati, sampe dong jato matono.<bt>Hearing like that then that those underlings were extremely afraid, to the point that they fell flat on their faces. [EXEG: TB lexical choice is misleading here. Gk doesn't imply a posture for worshipping.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma Yesus datang korek sang dong, ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Bosong bangun su. Jang taku!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus came finger.flicking./ nudging them and He said, &lt;&lt;We! [+get attention] You-pl get up. Don't be afraid!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="8" />Ais dong angka muka, ma dong sonde lia sapa-sapa di situ. Te cuma ada Yesus sa.<bt>Then they lifted their faces, but they could not see anyone there. Cuz (elaboration) there was only just Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais itu, dong mulai turun dari itu gunung. Ju Yesus larang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Apa yang bosong baru lia tadi tu, jang kasi tau sapa-sapa, é! Te Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, musti mati dolo. Ais nanti kalo Beta su idop kambali, baru bosong bole kasi tau orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, they started to go down from that mountain. Then Yesus forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;What you saw earlier there, don't tell anyone! Cuz (elaboration) I, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, must die first. Then later if/when I already live again, then you can tell people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ju dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa ni, memang Kristus, ma ba'i Elia di mana? Te itu guru agama dong ajar bilang, ba'i Elia musti datang dolo, baru Kristus datang. Ma iko Bapa, karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they asked Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father here, is really Kristus, but where is grandfather Elia? Cuz (elaboration) those religion teachers teach saying, Gf/Ff Elia must come first, then Kristus comes. But according to Father, how.is.it?&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="17:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 4:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl. Ba'i Elia musti datang dolo, ko buka jalan kasi sang Kristus.<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;That's actually true! Gf/Ff Elia must come first to open the path for Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ba'i Elia musti datang dolo, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Ba'i Elia musti datang dolo, ko buka jalan kasi sang Kristus.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ma dengar bae-bae, é! Ba'i Elia su datang, ma orang sonde kanál sang dia. Dong bekin susa sang dia iko dong pung mau. Ais nanti dong bekin bagitu ju sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>But listen carefully! Gf/Ff Elia has already come, but people did not know/recognise him. They caused difficulty to him, according to their desires/will. And later they do like that also to Me, this Ideal/Prototypical Human.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: ‘like that also’ shifted from being fronted in OV (naturalness). It was awkward.]</bt><note reference="17:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 11:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dengar abis bagitu, baru dong tau bilang, ba'i Elia yang Yesus ada omong tu, andia Yohanis tukang sarani.<bt>After hearing like that, then they knew that that Gf/Ff Elia whom Yesus was talking about there, was Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu ana yang takaná setan<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a child who is affliceted with evil spirit/s</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:14-29; Lukas 9:37-43a)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais waktu Yesus dong su kambali, dong katumu deng orang banya yang ada tunggu sang dong. Ju ada satu bapa datang tikam lutut ko minta tolong sang Dia<bt>Then when Yesus them had returned, they met many people who waiting for them. Then a father came kneeling to request help from Him,</bt><v n="15" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Kasian beta pung ana doo! Te dia saki gila kambing, deng dia sangsara mau mati. Kalo itu panyaki su foe, na, dia suka tajato dalam aer ko dalam api. Tolong doo!<bt>saying, &lt;&lt;Bos! Have pity on my child! Cuz (elaboration) he has crazy goat sickness (=epilepsy) and he is suffering greatly. If/when that sickness flares up, na, he often falls in water or in fire. Please help!</bt><v n="16" />Beta su bawa sang dia pi Bos pung ana bua dong, ma dong sonde bisa bekin bae sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>I have already brought him to Bos' underlings, but they could not heal him.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus masparak sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bosong ni su talalu! Beta su ajar ulang-ulang sang bosong, ma bosong sonde mangarti bae-bae. Deng bosong sonde parcaya batúl-batúl sang Beta! Beta musti sabar sang bosong sampe kapan lai? Mari bawa itu ana datang sini!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then Yesus got angry at His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;What? You guys are too much! I have taught you over and over, but you don't understand well. And you don't believe truly in Me! I have to be patient with you until when?! Go bring that child here!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Who is Jesus addressing here? The literature discusses several possibilities: 1) the father, 2) the disciples, 3) the crowd, 4) general open statement about people of the day. TH says he is answering #1 (which I find a bit unlikely since the Greek is grammatically 2p), but actually addressing #2, saying it could be translated as “Jesus responded by saying (to the disciples).” CEV plays on the lack of precision between English 2s/2p and makes it appear to be #1. TRT avoids choosing between 2, 3, or 4, but says it was clearly “the disciples' unbelief” that triggered the comment. Morris says “His words are apparently directed at the crowds and the disciples; they can scarcely be aimed at the father,”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added \p (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added \p (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dong bawa itu ana, ais ju Dia usir buang setan kaluar dari itu ana. Tarús itu setan kaluar kasi tenga itu ana, ju dia bae memang.<bt>They brought that child, then He expelled that evil spirit out of that child. Then2 that evil spirit went out leaving that child, and he was healed straight away.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais itu, waktu Yesus sandiri sama-sama deng Dia pung ana bua dong, dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Akurang ko tadi botong sonde bisa usir kasi kaluar itu setan?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, when Yesus was alone together with his underlings, they asked Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Why could we not expel that evil spirit earlier?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Yesus manyao bale bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde bisa usir itu setan, tagal bosong sonde parcaya batúl na. Inga, é! Kalo bosong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Beta, biar cuma sadiki ana ju, sama ke satu biji yang kici ana,<bt>Yesus replied back saying, &lt;&lt;You couldn't expel that evil spirit, because obviously you didn't believe correctly. If you believe correctly in Me, even if only just a tiny bit, like a tiny seed [NOTE to daughter translations: MTTs pointed out that there is nothing in the text of the verse about a seed, so it's difficult to bridge a connection with the footnote. Figure of seed restored, also since this is a well-known verse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** ftn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** ftn</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tuhan Yesus banding orang pung parcaya deng satu biji yang kici ana. Di sini, itu biji pung bésar yang pantíng, bukan dia pung jenis. Alkitab bahasa Indonesia di sini bilang, &lt;biji sesawi&gt;, ma ada barapa masala deng itu tafsiran.<bt>The Lord Yesus is comparing a person's faith/belief with a very tiny seed. Here, it is the size of the seed which is important, not the kind/type. The Indonesian Bible here says, ‘seed of Chinese cabbage [in a form not found in most dictionaries]’, but there are several problems with that interpretation.</bt></note>na, bosong bisa parenta satu gunung bilang, &lt;We, gunung! Pinda pi sana!&gt; Tantu sa dia pinda. Jadi bosong bisa bekin apa sa, asal bosong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan.<bt>na, you can ordered a mountain saying &lt;We, [+get attention] mountain! Move over there!&gt; Surely it will move. So (consequently), you can do whatever, as long as you truly believe God2.</bt><note reference="17:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 21:21, Markus 11:23, 1 Korintus 13:2</note><v n="21" />[Ma dengar, é! Setan macam bagini dong memang jahat talalu. Kalo bosong sonde sambayang deng puasa ko minta tolong sang Tuhan, na, bosong sonde bisa usir setan macam bagitu dong.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[But listen! Evil.spirits of this type are really especially evil. If you-pl don't pray and fast in order to request help from God, na, you can't expel an evil.sprit like that.&gt;&gt;] [EXEG: Evil spirits of this type, = excessively evil not just evil spirits in general. We also don't want to imply some types of evil spirits are evil (and by implication: others are not). TRT, EH, Deibler.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo bosong sonde sambayang deng puasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">Kalo bosong sonde sambayang deng puasa ko minta tolong sang Tuhan, na, setan macam bagitu tu, bosong sonde bisa usir sang dia.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling bae deng yang paling tua sonde muat ini ayat 21 ni.<bt>The best and oldest Yunani language writings don't carry/load this verse 21.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong kali kadua so'al Dia pung mati<bt>The Lord Yesus talks a second time about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:30-32; Lukas 9:43b-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais satu kali, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua ada bakumpul di propinsi Galilea. Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde lama lai, te dong mau jual sang Beta pi orang laen.<bt>Then one time, Yesus and His underlings were gathered in Galilea province. He told them saying, &lt;&lt;Not much longer, they will sell (=betray) Me to other people.</bt><v n="23" />Ais dong bunu bekin mati sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Memang Beta mati, ma nanti dia pung lusa, Beta idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they will murder kill Me, this Ideal/Prototypical Human. I will truly die, but later on the day.after.the.following.day, I will live again.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar Dia pung omong bagitu, ju Dia pung ana bua dong hati susa mau mati.<bt>Hearing His talk like that, then His underlings were very distressed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong so'al ruma sambayang pung pajak<bt>The Lord Yesus talks about the worship houses' tax</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Waktu Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong datang di kampong Kapernaum, ju tukang tagi bea dong, datang sang Petrus ko tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pung Guru bayar Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung pajak, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus and his underlings arrived in Kapernaum village, then tax collectors came to Petrus and asked saying, &lt;&lt;Does your-pl Teacher pay the *Temple tax, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** connected first two sentences, dependent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** connected first two sentences, dependent clause (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 30:13, 38:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ju Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bayar!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus replied saying, &lt;&lt;[He] pays!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu dia pulang, ju Yesus langsung kasi tau sang dia lebe dolo bilang, &lt;&lt;We, Simon! Coba lu pikir. Raja-raja di ini dunya ame pajak dari sapa? Dari dong pung ana sandiri, ko, dari orang laen?&gt;&gt;<bt>When he went home, then Yesus immediately told him first saying, &lt;&lt;We, Simon! Have a think. The kings of this world take tax from who? From their own child(ren), or from other people?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dari orang laen!&gt;&gt;<bt>Petrus replied saying, &lt;&lt;From other people!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus sambung lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, raja pung ana sandiri sonde usa bayar, to?<bt>Yesus continued again saying, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, the kings own child doesn't need to pay, right? [EXEG: See Carson for cristalogical significance of this.]</bt><v n="27" />Bagitu ju deng Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung pajak. Ma kotong sonde usa bekin mara itu tukang pajak dong. Jadi lebe bae, lu pi pancing ikan di dano sa. Lu tangkap ame ikan partama, na, buka dia pung mulu. Nanti lu dapa doi perak satu di dalam itu ikan pung mulu. Ais pake itu doi, ko pi bayar kotong dua pung pajak. Te itu su pas buat kotong dua.&gt;&gt;<bt>It's the same with the Temple tax. But we-inc don't need to make those tax collectors angry. So it's better if you just go fish for fish in the lake. You catch the first fish, then you open its mouth. Later you will find a silver money in that fish's mouth. Then take that money to go pay us two's tax. Cuz (elaboration) this is the exact amount for us two.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: Why does the TB say “dirham” here?? Point out to your team how bad this is from a translation perspective. It neither transliterates the Gk, nor translates it into an Indonesian word that anybody has ever known, Nobody knows where they got it!!]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TB dirham ??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">TB dirham ??</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tiap taon, tiap laki-laki Yahudi yang su umur 20 pi atas musti bayar satu pajak ko bantu piara Ruma Sambayang Pusat (baca di <span class="Italic">Kaluar dari Masir</span> 30:12-16). Waktu Tuhan Yesus idop, dong itong itu pajak deng doi <span class="Italic">didrakma</span>. Satu <span class="Italic">didrakma</span> pung nilei tu, sama ke dua <span class="Italic">dinari</span>. Satu <span class="Italic">dinari</span> tu, sama ke satu tukang pung gaji satu hari. Di sini, Yesus kasi tau sang Petrus bilang, nanti dia dapa satu doi <span class="Italic">stater</span> di itu ikan pung mulu. Satu <span class="Italic">stater</span> pung nilei tu, andia dua <span class="Italic">didrakma</span>, ko, ampa <span class="Italic">dinari</span> -- cukup ko bayar itu pajak kasi Yesus deng Petrus.<bt>Each year, each male Yahudi who was 20 years old and older must pay a tax to help care for the *Temple (read in <span class="Italic">Exit from Masir</span> 30:12-16). While the Lord Yesus was alive, they counted that tax with the <span class="Italic">didrakma</span> money/coin. The value of one <span class="Italic">didrakma</span> was the same as two <span class="Italic">dinari</span>. One <span class="Italic">dinari</span> was equivalent to a worker/craftsman's wages for one day. Here, Yesus was telling Petrus that he would find a <span class="Italic">stater</span> money/coin in that fish's mouth. The value of one <span class="Italic">stater</span> was two <span class="Italic">didrakma s</span>, or, four <span class="Italic">dinari</span> -- enough to pay that tax for Yesus and Petrus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua dong batanya bilang, sapa yang paling bésar<bt>The Lord Yesus' underlings ask who is the biggest</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:33-37; Lukas 9:46-48)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="18" />
      <v n="1" />Itu waktu, Yesus pung ana bua dong datang sang Dia ko tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Sapa yang paling bésar dari Tuhan Allah pung orang samua?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Yesus' underlings came to Him to ask saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Who is the biggest/most important of all God's people?&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="18:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ju Yesus pange satu ana kici, ais kasi badiri di dong pung teng-tenga.<bt>Then Yesus called/summoned a small child, and stood him in their midst.</bt><v n="3" />Ais Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Orang yang mau maso jadi Tuhan pung orang, dia musti oba dia pung cara pikir, ko jadi sama ke ana kici yang sonde tau angka-angka diri.<bt>Then He said, &lt;&lt;Listen well! A person who wants to become the Lord's person, he must change his/her thinking to become the same as a small child who does not know how to elevate (=praise) him/herself.</bt><note reference="18:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 10:15, Lukas 18:17</note><v n="4" />Tagal orang yang randá hati sama ke ana kici ni, dia tu orang yang paling bésar di Tuhan pung muka.<bt>Because the person who is low livered (=humble) like this small child here, he there is the person who is the biggest before the Lord.</bt><v n="5" />Deng orang yang tarima orang kici sama ke ini ana ni, tagal dia parcaya sang Beta, na, itu orang su tarima sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>And the perosn who accepts/receives a small person (=low rank person) like this child here, because he believes in Me, na, that person has received/accepted Me.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added close quotes (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:51Z">*** added close quotes (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi inga so'al orang yang buat orang laen bekin sala<bt>The Lord Yesus reminds about people who make other people do wrong</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 9:42-48; Lukas 17:1-2)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais Yesus kasi tau lai sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo ada orang yang bekin satu ana kici iko jalan yang sala, sampe dia sonde parcaya lai sang Beta, awas, ó! Lebe bae orang ika batu bésar satu<bt>Then Yesus told them again saying, &lt;&lt;If there is a person who makes a small child/unempowered person follow a/the path that is wrong, to the point that s/he does not believe in Me anymore, watch out! It's better (if/for) people tie a big stone</bt><note reference="18:6" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;batu giling&gt; yang dong pake ko mol padi-gandum.<bt>Greek language writings write saying, &lt;grinding stone&gt; which they use to mill wheat grain.</bt></note>di dia pung batang leher, ko kasi tanggalám sang dia di tenga laut.<bt>, on his/her neck, and sink/drown him/her in the middle of the ocean.</bt><v n="7" />Ini dunya ni memang tampa calaka, tagal ada banya hal yang bekin orang jato dalam dosa. Ma orang yang paling calaka tu, andia orang yang bekin gara-gara, ko orang laen bekin sala.<bt>This world here is truly a place of misfortune, because there many things which make people fall in sin. But that people/person who is the most misfortunate, is the person who makes excuses/reasons so other people do wrong.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Kalo lu bekin sala pake lu pung tangan, ko, lu pung kaki, na, potong buang sang dia sa! Te lebe bae lu maso sorga deng tangan sablá sa, ko, kaki sablá sa, ko biar dong jang buang sang lu pi api naraka deng lu pung tangan deng kaki dua-dua.<bt>If you do wrong using your hand/arm, or your foot/let, na, just cut it off! Cuz (elaboration) it's better you enter heaven with an arm on just one side, or a foot on just one side, so that they don't throw you into hell fire with both of your hands and feet. [NOTE: better A, than B is difficult in these lgs.]</bt><note reference="18:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:30</note><v n="9" />Kalo lu bekin sala pake lu pung mata, do'i buang lu pung mata sa! Te lebe bae lu maso pi sorga deng mata sablá sa, ko biar dong jang buang sang lu pi api naraka deng lu pung mata dua-dua.&gt;&gt;<bt>If you do wrong using your eye, just gouge out your eye! Cuz (elaboration) it's better you enter heaven with an eye on just one side, so that they don't throw you into hell fire with both of your eyes.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="18:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:29</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al satu domba yang ilang<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about one sheep which disappears (=the usual way to talk to about 'losing' st)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 15:3-7)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ati-ati, ó! Jang sampe bosong pandang enteng ana kici bagini. Te dong ada Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga yang jaga sang dong. Deng itu ana bua dong bisa maso kapan-kapan sa, ko pi kasi tau ini orang dong pung hal di Tuhan Allah.<bt>Yesus spoke again saying, &lt;&lt;Be careful! May it not be that you-pl look.disparagingly/belittle a small child/unempowered person like this. Cuz (elaboration) the Lord's has their *angels (underlings) from heaven who are watching/taking.care.of them. And those underlings can enter any time they want, to go tell these small children's matters to God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11-13" />Bosong pikir bae-bae, te Beta mau kasi umpama bagini: ada satu orang pung domba saratus ekor. Ais satu hari, ada domba satu ekor yang serong, iko jalan sandiri. Naa, bosong kira itu gambala musti bekin apa? Tantu dia kasi tenga dia pung domba 99 ekor di atas gunung, ko pi cari itu domba satu ekor yang ilang tu.<bt>You think well, cuz (elaboration) I want to give an example like this. There was a person [who] had one hundred tails (counter) of sheep. Then one day, one tail of sheep wandered off-track/astray, following his own way. Naa, [+shift] what do you think that shepherd must do? Surely he/she will leave those 99 tails of sheep of his/hers on top the mountain, to go look for that one tail of sheep which disappeared.</bt><note reference="18:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 19:10</note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00001C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Gambala dapa domba yang ilang<bt>A shepherd finds (the) sheep which was lost</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Kalo dia su dapa kambali, nanti dia lebe sanáng lia dia pung domba yang satu tu, daripada dia lia dia pung domba 99 ekor yang sonde ilang. [Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, datang ju ko mau kasi salamat sang orang yang serong dari jalan lurus.]<bt>If/when s/he finds it again, later s/he will be happier seeing that one sheep there, than when s/he sees his 99 tails of sheep which didn't disappear. [I, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, also came/come to save people who have deviated from the straight/righteous path/way.]</bt><note reference="18:11-13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling bae deng yang paling tua sonde muat ini kalimat dalam kurung ni.<bt>The Yunani language writings which are the best and the oldest don't carry/load this sentence in parentheses.</bt></note><v n="14" />Te biar cuma satu ana kici sa yang ilang ju, Beta pung Bapa di sorga sonde sanáng.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) even if only just one small child/unempowered person who believes gets lost/disappears, My father in heaven is not happy.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau cara karmana kotong babae kambali deng orang yang bekin sala sang kotong<bt>The Lord Yesus tells how we-inc can be reciprocally good with people who do wrong to us</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Yesus omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo lu pung sodara orang parcaya bekin sala sang lu, na, lu yang musti pi katumu deng dia. Ais kalo bosong dua sandiri, baru kasi tau dia pung sala. Kalo dia dengar lu pung omong, na, bosong dua su babae kambali tu.<bt>Yesus spoke again saying, &lt;&lt;If your sibling/fellow believer does wrong to you, then you are the one who must go meet with him/her. Then when the two of you are alone, only then tell his/her wrong. If s/he hears (implies consent as well as hearing) your speaking, na, you two are in a reciprocally good relationship again. [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, CEV, Morris.]</bt><note reference="18:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 17:3</note><v n="16" />Ma kalo dia sonde mau dengar sang lu, na, pi ame lu pung tamán satu-dua orang ko pi sama-sama deng lu lai. Ais bosong pi katumu deng itu orang, ko omong lai deng dia. Te dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang, &lt;Dalam satu parkara, musti ada dua ko tiga saksi yang omong sama, baru bisa tarima dong pung omong tu.&gt;<bt>But if s/he doesn't want to hear you, na, go get one or two of your friends to go together with you. Then you-pl go meet that person and talk again with him/her. Cuz (elaboration) in the Bible it is written saying, &lt;In a dispute/case/litigation, there must be two or three witnesses who say the same thing, only then can (you) accept what they say.&gt;</bt><note reference="18:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 19:15</note><v n="17" />Ma kalo dia masi sonde mau dengar sang bosong, na, pi kasi tau sang jama'at. Deng kalo dia ju su sonde mau tarima bae jama'at pung omong, na, anggap dia sama ke orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan. Kalo sonde, na, anggap dia jahat sama ke tukang tagi bea dong.<bt>But if s/he still does not want to hear you-pl, then go tell the congregation. And if s/he also does not want to receive well the congregation's speaking/view, then consider him/her the same as a person who does not know the Lord. If not, na, consider him/her evil the same as tax collector/s.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Inga bae-bae Beta pung omong, é! Apa yang bosong larang di ini dunya, itu Tuhan su larang di sorga. Deng apa yang bosong kasi isin di ini dunya, itu Tuhan su kasi isin di sorga.<bt>Remember well My speaking! Whatever you-pl forbid on earth, that [matter] the Lord has already forbidden in heaven. And whatever you permit on earth, that [matter] the Lord has already permitted in heaven.</bt><note reference="18:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:19, Yohanis 20:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Deng Beta kasi tau ulang bilang, kalo ada dua orang dari bosong yang sambayang satu hati, nanti Beta pung Bapa di sorga kasi apa yang dong minta.<bt>And I tell again saying, if there are two people from you who pray with one liver, later My Father in heaven will give that which they ask.</bt><v n="20" />Te kalo ada dua-tiga orang bakumpul ko sambayang sama-sama, tagal dong tu Beta pung orang, na, Beta ju ada di dong pung teng-tenga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if there are two or three people gathered praying together because they are My people, na, I am also in their midst.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: “in my name” here means “because they belong to me”. See my PPT word study on “name”, NLT, CEV note, TRT. etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** revised &amp; note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** revised &amp; note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kalo ada dua ko tiga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">Te kalo ada dua ko tiga orang bakumpul ko sambayang sang Beta, na, Beta ju ada di dong pung teng-tenga.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al pagawe yang sonde kasi ampon sang dia pung tamán<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about an official who doesn't give forgiveness to his friend</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais itu, ju Petrus datang tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, beta mau tanya sadiki. Kalo beta pung sodara orang parcaya bekin sala ulang-ulang sang beta, na, beta musti kasi ampon sang dia sampe barapa kali? Sampe tuju kali, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Petrus came asking Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Bos, I want to ask a little something (=polite way to say I have a question). If my sibling/fellow believer wrongs me over and over, then how many times must I give forgiveness to him/her? Up to seven times, [+tag question]? [EXEG: NRSV, see also note at 8:15]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Lu musti kasi ampon sang dia 7 kali 70 kali,<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;No! You must give forgiveness to him/her 7 times 70 times,</bt><note reference="18:22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani di sini, bisa dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;7 kali 70 kali&gt;&gt;. Bisa ju, &lt;&lt;77 kali&gt;&gt;.<bt>The Yunani language here can mean, &lt;&lt;7 times 70 times&gt;&gt;. It can also (mean), &lt;&lt;77 times&gt;&gt;.</bt></note>sampe lu sonde bisa itong lai.<bt>until you can't count anymore.</bt><note reference="18:21-22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 17:3-4</note><v n="23" />Bosong musti bekin iko bagitu, tagal Tuhan Allah sama ke satu raja yang ba'itong dia pung pagawe dong pung utang.<bt>You-pl must like that, because God is like a king who counts his officials' debts.</bt><v n="24" />Waktu dia mulai ba'itong, ju dia suru dia pung orang ko pi pange datang satu pagawe yang ada ba'utang doi deng dia, sampe juta-juta.<bt>When he started to count, then he ordered his people to go call in one official who was in debt to him for money, up to millions and millions.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added Gk to ftn plus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** added Gk to ftn plus one extra sentence (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="18:24" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;10.000 τάλαντον (<span class="Italic">talanton</span>)&gt;&gt;. Satu <span class="Italic">talanton</span> pung nilei, andia, satu orang karjá pung gaji 15-20 taon. Alkitab bahasa Indonesia bilang &lt;talenta&gt; di sini.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes “10,000 τάλαντον (<span class="Italic">talanton</span>)”. The value of one <span class="Italic">talenton</span> was a worker's wages for 15-20 years. The Indonesian Bible says ‘talenta’ here.</bt></note><v n="25" />Ma itu pagawe sonde bisa bayar ganti dia pung utang. Jadi raja parenta bilang, &lt;Pi jual ini orang deng dia pung bini-ana samua, ko dong jadi budak. Deng jual abis dia pung harta dong samua, ko bayar dia pung utang dong.&gt;<bt>But that official could not repay that debt of his. Then the king ordered saying, &lt;&lt;Go sell this person and his wife and all his children so they become slaves. And sell off all his wealths in order to pay his debt.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu pagawe jato tikam lutut di raja pung muka, ko kokoe sang dia bilang, &lt;Aduu! Bapa, é! Bapa raja tolong kasi beta waktu sadiki doo! Nanti beta bayar kambali beta pung utang dong samua.&gt;<bt>Hearing like that then that official feel kneeling in front of the king and pleaded with him saying, &lt;Oh no! Oh, Father! Father king please give me a little bit of time. Later I will return/repay all of my debts.&gt;</bt><v n="27" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu raja jato kasian sang dia. Ju dia hapus memang dia pung pagawe tu pung utang samua. Ais dia kasi lapás sang itu pagawe.<bt>Hearing like that, then that king felt pity on him. Then he straight away erased away all the debts of that official of his. And he released that official.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ma waktu itu pagawe kaluar, ju dia nae katumu deng dia pung tamán satu yang ada ba'utang doi sadiki sang dia.<bt>But when that official went out, then he met one of his friends who was in debt a little money to him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added Gk to ftn (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** added Gk to ftn (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="18:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;100 δηνάριον (<span class="Italic">dēnarion</span>)&gt;&gt;. Satu <span class="Italic">dēnarion</span> pung nilei, andia, satu orang karjá pung gaji satu hari sa. Jadi, kalo banding deng 10.000 τάλαντον (<span class="Italic">talanton</span>) di atas (ayat 24), na, ini utang ni sonde ada pung arti apa-apa.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes, &lt;&lt;100 δηνάριον (<span class="Italic">deinarion</span>)&gt;&gt;. The value of one <span class="Italic">deinarion</span> is one workers wage for one day. So (consequently), when compared with the 10,000 τάλαντον (<span class="Italic">talanton</span>) above, na, this debt here has not meaning/significance whatsoever.</bt></note>Tarús dia tangkap dia pung tamán, ko ceke dia pung batang leher deng masparak bilang, &lt;Weh! Bayar lu pung utang sakarang ju!&gt;<bt>Next that official captured his friend, and strangled his neck angrily saying, &lt;Weh! Pay up your debt right now!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dengar bagitu, ju dia pung tamán jato tikam lutut ko kokoe sang dia bilang, &lt;Aduu! Tamán, é! Tolong kasi beta waktu sadiki doo! Nanti beta bayar kambali beta pung utang sang lu.&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then his friend fell kneeling and pleaded with him saying, &lt;Oh no! Friend! Please give me a little bit of time. Later I will return/repay my debt to you.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ma itu pagawe bilang, &lt;Sonde bisa! Pokonya, lu musti bayar sakarang ju!&gt; Ais dia lempar kasi maso dia pung tamán pi dalam bui, sampe dia bayar abis dia pung utang dong.<bt>But that official said, &lt;Can't do! The important thing is you must pay now!&gt; Then he threw his friend in jail, until completely paid that debt of his. [EXEG: The Gk subjunctive “until he should repay” his debts is a bit hard to nail down, and also hard to reflect in these lgs. It can actually be interpreted either as “could pay” or “did pay”, and I'm not sure there is any difference in the result. NRSV and NLT1 seem to capture both. TB is as we have it (Indonesian also not having a subjunctive).]</bt><v n="31" />Waktu raja pung pagawe yang laen dapa lia apa yang su jadi tu, ju dong pung hati susa. Ais dong pi lapor sang raja.<bt>When the kings other officials saw what happened there, then their livers were distressed. Then they went to report to the king.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu raja pange itu pagawe yang sonde tau diri tu. Dia togor bilang, &lt;Heh, orang jahat! Tagal lu minta beta kasian sang lu, andia ko beta su hapus buang lu pung utang dong samua.<bt>Hearing like that, then that king called that official who didn't know himself (=who had lost all sense of social propriety). He scolded him saying, &lt;Hee, evil person! Because you requested me to pity you, that's why I have erased away all of your debts.</bt><v n="33" />Ma akurang ko lu sonde tau kasian sang lu pung tamán, sama ke beta su kasian sang lu tu?&gt;<bt>But why could you not have pity/mercy on your friend, the same as I had pity/mercy on you?&gt;</bt><v n="34" />Itu raja maruak, sampe dia suru dong pi tola maso sang itu orang dalam bui, ko biar dong siksa sang dia, sampe dia bayar abis dia pung utang dong samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>That king was so angry, to the point that he ordered them to go push/shove that person [+contempt] into jail, so that they would torture him, until he completely pays off all those debts of his.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** dia &gt; itu orang (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** dia &gt; itu orang (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ju Yesus tutu Dia pung carita deng kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa, Beta pung Bapa di sorga ju ba'itong bagitu. Nanti Dia hukum sang bosong, kalo bosong sonde lupa buang batúl sang bosong pung sodara orang parcaya pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus closed His story by telling saying, &lt;&lt;Naa, [+shift] My father in heaven also counts like that. Later He will punsih you-pl, if you do not truly forget throw away your sibling/fellow believer's wrongs.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: see note at 18:15]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Farisi cari jalan ko hiki sang Tuhan Yesus deng so'al kawin-cere<bt>The Farisi people look for a way to trap the Lord Yesus about marriage-divorce</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 10:1-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="19" />
      <v n="1" />Yesus ajar abis itu samua, ju Dia jalan kasi tenga Galilea ko pi propinsi Yudea di kali Yarden pung sablá sana.<bt>Yesus finished teaching all of that, then He walked/travelled leaving Galilea to go to Yudea province at Yordan river's other side.</bt><v n="2" />Orang banya iko sang Dia, ju Dia bekin bae orang saki di sana.<bt>Many people followed Him, and He healed sick people there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ada ju barapa orang Farisi yang datang ko mau hiki kasi jato sang Dia. Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Iko kotong pung atoran agama, kalo laki-laki su kawin, dia bole cere buang dia pung bini deng alasan apa sa, ko karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>There were also several Farisi people who came wanting to ensnare making Him fall. They asked saying, &lt;&lt;Father! According to our-inc religious regulations, if a male has married, may he divorce away his wife with whatever reason, or what?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ni, orang yang pintar agama. Ma akurang ko bosong sonde tau Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi pung isi? Te di carita mula-mula ada tulis bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah bekin manusia, laki-laki deng parampuan.&gt;<bt>But He responded saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl here are religious experts. But why do you not know the Bible's contents? Cuz (elaboration) in the origin/beginning story, it is written saying, &lt;God made humans male and female.&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: this is intended as 'story of creation' or 'story of beginnings' not the title of the book of Genesis. That's why it's not capitalised. Some find this confusing, so find a way around it.]</bt><note reference="19:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 1:27, 5:2</note><v n="5" />Deng ada tatulis lai bilang,<bt>And it is written again saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tagal itu, laki-laki musti kasi tenga dia pung mama-bapa,<bt>&lt;Because of that, a man/male must leave his father-mother,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko pi idop satu hati deng dia pung bini,<bt>in order to go live one liver with his wife,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te dong dua su jadi satu.&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) the two of them have become one/united.&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Follow the wording you used in Gen 2:24.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tagal itu, kalo Tuhan Allah sandiri yang bekin dong dua jadi satu, na, manusia jang kasi cere lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, if God himself has made the two of them to become one/united, then humans mustn't make them separated/divorced anymore.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dengar Yesus omong bagitu, ju itu orang Farisi dong tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, akurang ko ba'i Musa bilang, orang bole bacere, asal dia kasi surat cere sang dia pung bini dolo?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus speak like that, then those Farisi people asked again saying, &lt;&lt;If it's like that, na, why did Gf/Ff Musa say, a person can divorce, as long as he gives a divorce letter to his wife first?&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="19:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 24:1-4, Mateos 5:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ju Yesus manyao lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ba'i Musa kasi biar bosong pung nene-moyang bacere deng dong pung bini, tagal dong tu, kapala batu sama ke bosong! Ma waktu Tuhan Allah bekin ini dunya, Dia pung maksud bukan bagitu.<bt>Then Yesus answered again saying, &lt;&lt;Gf/Ff Musa allowed your ancestors to divorce their wives, because they there, were stone heads (=stubborn) just like you! But when God made this world, His intent was not like that.</bt><v n="9" />Andia ko Beta kasi tau, é! Kalo bini ada maen serong lebe dolo, na, laki-laki bole bacere. Ma kalo bini sonde maen serong, laki-laki yang cere buang sang dia, ais kawin lai deng parampuan laen, na, dia su barsina tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why I'm telling [you]! If the/a wife commits.adultery prior, then a male/man may divorce. But if the wife doesn't commit adultery, the male/man who divorces her away, and marries again with another woman, then he has committed.adultery there [=in that situation].</bt><note reference="19:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:32, 1 Korintus 7:10-11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dengar Dia omong bagitu, ju Dia pung ana bua dong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, lebe bae jang kawin sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Him speak like that, then His underlings spoke saying, &lt;&lt;If it's like that, na, it's better just not to get married.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde samua orang yang bisa tarima Beta pung omong ni. Cuma orang yang Tuhan Allah tunju sa.<bt>Then Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Not all people can accept this speaking of mine. Only just people whom God designates. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that /tunju/ in your lg doesn't imply that God superimposes singleness on some people. He calls some and enables them to remain single for ministry purposes in partnership with him.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Te ada orang yang sonde kawin, tagal dari lahir su bagitu. Ada ju yang sonde kawin, tagal orang bekin bagitu sang dia. Deng ada ju, yang pili ko sonde kawin, tagal dia cuma mau kasi jalan Tuhan Allah pung karjá sa. Orang yang bisa mangarti ini ajaran, na, biar dia tarima sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there are people who don't marry, because [they] were born like that. There are also those who don't marry, because people made him like that. And there are also, those who choose to not marry, because he only wants to carry out God's work. The person who can understand this teaching, na, let him accept it.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: see discussion in Morris &amp; Carson. Both marriage and singleness are “approved” here; avoid making either one superior, or either one inferior.] [EXEG: Gk ‘eunuch’ is used here in three different senses, so don't force your RL to use the same phrasing for all 3. a) (physical) birth defect, b) (physical) castration, c) (spiritual/social) choice. NOTE: the Kupang for (b) is vague, so make it more explicit in your language if the Team or UNSs don't know what the KM is talking about. Euphemisms are better than explicit “cutting off genitals”, which perhaps could not acceptably be read in church. How do they talk about castrating pigs and dogs in polite company?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang bisa tarima ini ajaran,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">Orang yang bisa tarima ini ajaran, na, biar ko dia bekin iko.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong kasi berkat sang ana kici dong<bt>The Lord Yesus speaks gives blessing to small children</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 10:13-16; Lukas 18:15-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Itu waktu, orang dong koko bawa dong pung ana-ana pi Yesus, ko biar Dia mua tangan deng omong kasi berkat sang dong. Ma Dia pung ana bua dong togor sang itu orang dong.<bt>At that time, people carried brought their children to Yesus, so that He would put hands and speak giving blessing to them. But His underlings scolded those people.</bt><v n="14" />Ju Dia mara sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi tenga itu ana dong datang sang Beta! Sonde usa larang! Te orang yang sama ke dong ni, andia Tuhan Allah pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He got angry with His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Allow those children to come to Me! It's not necessary (=don't) forbid/prohibit! Cuz (elaboration) people like them here, they are God's people.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: Jesus is rebuking his disciples here. In Kupang this is indicated by “got angry with”. It is driven by the discourse pragmatics, and UNS responses that thought Jesus was legitimating his disciples actions and adding a nice teaching. He was not. How does your RL signal rebuke?]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais Dia mua tangan pi di itu ana kici dong, deng minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi berkat sang dong. Ais itu, ju Dia jalan kasi tenga itu tampa.<bt>Then He put hand/s on those children, and requested that God give blessing to them. After that, then He walked/travelled leaving that place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang kaya cari jalan ko idop tarús deng Tuhan Allah<bt>A rich person hunts for a way to live forever with God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 10:17-31; Lukas 18:18-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais satu kali, ada orang datang tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Beta musti bekin hal bae yang karmana, ko biar beta tau parsís bilang, beta bisa maso sorga? Te beta mau idop tarús sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then one time, a person came asking Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! What good thing must I do so that I know exactly/precisely, that I can enter heaven? Cuz (elaboration) I want to live continually together with God?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) long sentence broken up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) long sentence broken up</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu tanya sang Beta so'al apa yang bae? Cuma Tuhan Allah sa yang bae. Kalo lu mau idop deng Dia, na, idop iko Dia pung parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He replied saying, &lt;&lt;Why do you ask Me about what is good? Only God alone is good. If you want to live with Him, then live following/obeying His commands.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: “keep His com...” has durative on-going sense.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added /idop/ in last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) added /idop/ in last sentence, plus note</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Itu orang tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Parenta yang mana tu?&gt;&gt;<bt>That person asked again saying, &lt;&lt;Which command is that (from several options)?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang,<bt>Then Yesus answered saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Jang bunu orang;<bt>&lt;&lt;Don't murder people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jang maen serong;<bt>don't play.around.sexually,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jang mancuri;<bt>don't steal,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jang jadi saksi putar-balek;<bt>don't be a twisted/deceitful witness;</bt><note reference="19:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:13-16, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:17-20</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="19" />kasi hormat sang lu pung mama-bapa;<bt>give honour to your father-mother;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng sayang lu pung sodara sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;&gt;<bt>and love your sibing/equal the same as you love your own self.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="19:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:12, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:16, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa, itu parenta samua tu, beta su bekin. Apa yang masi kurang lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>That person replied saying, &lt;&lt;Naa, [+shift] I have done all those commands. What else is still lacking?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Kalo lu mau iko Tuhan pung mau samua, na, pulang ko jual lu pung harta samua. Ais pi bagi-bagi itu doi kasi orang miskin dong. Ais itu, baru lu datang ko iko sang Beta. Te nanti Tuhan Allah balas kasi lu harta bam-banya di sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that then Yesus said, &lt;&lt;Well! If you want to follow all the Lord's will/desires, then go home and sell all your wealth. Then go divide out that money to the poor people. After than, then you come and follow Me. Cuz (elaboration) later God will reciprocate to you lots of wealth in heaven.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang pulang deng hati susa, te dia kaya mau mati.<bt>Hearing like that, then that person went home with a troubled liver, cuz (elaboration) he was very rich.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais ju Yesus omong deng Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Parcaya sang Beta, te orang kaya paling susa maso sorga.<bt>And then Yesus spoke with His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Believe Me, cuz (elaboration) rich people have the greatest difficulty entering heaven.</bt><v n="24" />Dia pung susa tu, sama ke binatang onta yang bésar, maso pi dia pung kandang lewat jarom pung lobang.&gt;&gt;<bt>That difficulty, is like a camel animal which is big, entering into his corral through a needle's hole.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Dengar bagitu ju, Dia pung ana bua dong jadi taheran-heran. Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, sapa yang bisa maso sorga?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then His underlings were amazed/surprised. And they replied saying, &lt;&lt;If it's like that, na, who is it who can enter heaven?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dia lia bae-bae sang dong, ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo manusia yang karjá, memang sonde bisa. Ma kalo Tuhan Allah yang karjá, samua bisa jadi!&gt;&gt;<bt>He looked carefully at them, then He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;If humans are the ones who do/work it, it's surely not possible. But if God is the one who does/works it, all/everything can happen!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju Petrus kasi inga bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Botong su jalan kasi tenga botong pung harta samua, ko iko sang Bapa. Ma botong dapa apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus reminded saying, &lt;&lt;Father! We-exc have gone leaving all our wealth, in order to follow Father. But what do we get?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Parcaya sang Beta! Nanti kalo Tuhan Allah su bekin samua jadi baru, Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, dudu dalam hebat di korsi parenta bésar. Itu waktu, bosong yang iko sang Beta, ju iko dudu di atas 12 korsi parenta, ko jadi hakim kasi kotong pung 12 suku Isra'el!<bt>Dia replied saying, &lt;&lt;Believe Me! Later if/when God makes everything become new, I, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, will sit in amazingness/glory in a/the big ruling chair. At that time, you who follow Me, will also sit on 12 ruling chairs, in order to become judges for our-inc 12 Israel clans! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><note reference="19:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 25:31, Lukas 22:30</note><v n="29" />Orang yang jalan kasi tenga dia pung ruma, adi-kaka, mama-bapa, ana-ana, deng dia pung kabón, ko iko sang Beta, nanti dia tarima bale sampe 100 kali lipat. Ais kalo ini dunya kiamat, dia ju dapa idop deng Tuhan tarús-tarús.<bt>The person who goes leaving his/her house, elder-younger siblings, father-mother, children, and his/her garden/s, in order to follow Me, later s/he will receive in return up to 100 times increase. Then if/when this world ends, s/he will also get to live with the Lord continually-continually (=forever and ever).</bt><v n="30" />Jadi inga, é! Iko Tuhan Allah pung pikiran, banya orang yang bekin-bekin diri bésar, dong tu, andia orang yang paling kici. Ma orang yang anggap diri kici, dong tu, andia orang yang bésar, iko Tuhan pung pikiran.&gt;&gt;<bt>So remember, é! According to God's thinking, many people who makes themself big/important, they there, are a person who is the most small. But the person who considers him/her self small (=humble), they there, are a person who is big, according to the Lord's thinking.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="19:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 20:16, Lukas 13:30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Umpama so'al tukang garap kabón anggor<bt>Example/parable about workers in the vineyard</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="20" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus ajar bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta sama ke ini umpama: ada satu tuan kabón yang kaluar pagi-pagi jam anam, pi cari orang ko karjá di dia pung kabón anggor.<bt>After that, Yesus taught saying, &lt;&lt;God's ruling/authority is like this example: there was a garden owner/master who went out early at six in the morning, to find people to work in his grape garden.</bt><v n="2" />Dia dapa orang karjá, ju dong ba'akór ko karjá satu hari, deng dia pung sewa satu doi perak, iko harga biasa.<bt>He obtained workers, and they agreed to work one day with the rent/payment, one silver money, following normal price.</bt><note reference="20:2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;satu doi <span class="Italic">dinari</span>&gt;&gt;. Satu <span class="Italic">dinari</span> pung nilei, andia, satu orang karjá pung gaji satu hari anteru.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes, “one <span class="Italic">dinari</span> money”. The value of one <span class="Italic">dinari</span>, was a worker's wage for one full day.</bt></note>Satuju abis, ju dia suru dong pi karjá di dia pung kabón.<bt>After agreeing, then he ordered them to go work in that garden of his.</bt><v n="3" />Jam sambilan pagi, ju dia kaluar lai pi pasar. Di situ dia dapa lia barapa orang yang ada dudu tanganga bodo sa.<bt>At nine in the morning, then he went out again to the market. There he saw several people who were just sitting around lazily.</bt><v n="4" />Ju dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;We, bu dong! Bosong mau karjá di beta pung kabón, ko? Nanti beta bayar sang bosong iko yang pantas.&gt; Dengar bagitu, ju dong ia bae, ais dong pi karjá.<bt>The he told them saying, &lt;We, [+get attention] elder.brothers (= often used to address s.o. of lower status than you in a polite friendly somewhat respectful way)! Do you want to work in my garden [+tag question]? Later I will pay you according to what is appropriate.&gt; Hearing like that, then they agreed, and they went to work.</bt><v n="5" />Jam 12 tenga hari, deng jam tiga sore, itu tuan kabón kaluar ruma, ko pi cari orang karjá lai.<bt>At 12 oclock noon, and three in the afternoon, that garden master left home, to go find workers again.</bt><v n="6" />Su sore, kira-kira jam lima, ju itu tuan kabón kaluar lai. Dia lia pi-datang, te masi ada orang yang badiri-badiri kosong sa. Ais dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;Akurang ko bosong badiri kosong dari pagi sampe sore, deng sonde bekin apa-apa?&gt;<bt>When it was late afternoon, around five oclock, then that garden master went out again. He look all around to see there were still people who were just standing around empty (=doing nothing). Then he asked them saying, &lt;Why do you stand around empty from morning until late afternoon, and don't do anything?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Itu orang dong manyao bilang, &lt;Bapa, é! Sonde ada orang yang kasi botong karjá.&gt;<bt>Those people answered saying, &lt;Father! There is no one who gives us work.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais, itu tuan bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, na, bosong pi karjá di beta pung kabón su!&gt;<bt>Then that master said, &lt;If that's the case, then you-pl go work in my garden (imperative)!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sampe dia pung jam barenti karjá, ju itu tuan kabón pange dia pung mandor ko bilang, &lt;Pange orang karjá dong, ko bayar dong pung doi karjá satu-satu. Mulai dari orang yang maso tarahir sampe deng orang yang maso partama dong.&gt;<bt>When it was time to stop work, then that garden master called his manager and said, &lt;Call the workers in order to pay each of them their work money. Start from the people who enter last [going in order] until those people who entered first.&gt;</bt><note reference="20:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:13, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 24:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais, itu mandor pange itu orang dong yang karjá mulai dari jam lima sore. Dia kasi sang dong, satu-satu tarima satu doi perak.<bt>Then, that manager called those workers who worked starting from five oclock in the afternoon. He gave each one of them to receive one silver money/coin.</bt><v n="10" />Ais, itu mandor pange itu orang karjá laen dong, sampe deng orang yang karjá mulai dari jam anam pagi. Yang su karjá dari pagi pikir kata, tantu dong tarima lebe banya dari itu orang yang mulai karjá jam lima sore. Tau-tau te dong ju tarima satu doi perak.<bt>Then, that manager called those other workers, up to the people who worked started from six oclock in the morning. The ones who had worked since morning thought that, surely they would receive more than those people who started work at five in the afternoon. But in actual fact, they also received one silver money.</bt><v n="11" />Tarima bagitu ju, dong mangomek sang itu tuan kabón bilang,<bt>Receiving like that, then they grumbled to that garden master saying,</bt><v n="12" />&lt;Awe'! Tar bisa bagini, bos! Dong yang datang paling balakang, cuma karjá satu jam sa. Ma botong yang maso dari papagi hari ni, su karjá banting tulang satenga mati sampe karingat dong malele! Ma karmana ko bos bayar sang botong sama ke dong tu?&gt;<bt>&lt;Awe'! [+objection] It can't be like this, bos! Those who came the very last, only worked just one hour. But we here who entered from early in the morning, have worked to the bone until the sweat flowed down! But how is it that boss pays us the same as them there?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ju itu tuan kabón manyao sang satu dari dong bilang, &lt;Bu, é! Beta sonde panake sang bu. Tagal bu sandiri satuju karjá satu hari, deng dia pung sewa satu doi perak. Batúl, to? Jadi beta su bayar iko kotong pung janji, aa?<bt>Then that garden master replied to one of them saying, &lt;Elder.brother! I have not been unfair with elder.brother (=you). Because elder.brother yourself agreed to work one day, with the rent/payment one silver money. Right [+tag question]? So (consequently), I paid according to our-inc agreement, right?</bt><v n="14" />Ada lebe bae, bu tarima bu pung doi sewa ko pulang su. Kalo beta mau kasi orang yang maso karjá lebe lat dari bu, sama banya deng apa yang beta kasi sang bu, na, itu beta pung urusan.<bt>It would be better, elder.brother accepts elder.brother's rent/payment money and go home. If I want to give people who started working later than elder.brother the same amount that I give elder.brother, na, that is my business/arrangement. [NOTE to daughter translations: /doi sewa/ doesn't work for some cultural systems. Use /gaji/ or whatever is appropriate.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Tantu beta ni bebas pake beta pung doi iko beta pung suka. Karmana ko bu jengkel tagal beta pung hati bae?&gt;<bt>Surely I here am free to use my money according to my likes. How is that elder.brother is annoyed, because of my good liver (=kindness/generosity).&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Bagitu ju, waktu Tuhan Allah jadi Raja kasi orang dong, Dia balas kasi Dia pung orang dong iko Dia pung suka. Jadi orang yang datang tarahir, nanti dia tarima dia pung bagian sama ke orang yang datang partama. Deng orang yang datang partama, nanti dia tarima dia pung bagian sama ke orang yang datang tarahir.&gt;&gt;<bt>Like that also when God becomes King for people. He will reciprocate/reward people according to His liking/desire. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK ambiguity of ‘his desire’] So (consequently) a/the person who comes last (in a time/location sequence), s/he will receive his/her share the same as a/the person who comes first. And a person who comes first, s/he will receive his/her share the same as a person who comes last.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="20:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 19:30, Markus 10:31, Lukas 13:30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang yang katiga kali so'al Dia pung mati<bt>The Lord Yesus foretells the third time about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 10:32-34; Lukas 18:31-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais itu, ju Yesus dong mulai jalan pi Yerusalem. Di tenga jalan, Dia pange Dia pung ana bua ko dong bakumpul sandiri sa deng Dia. Ais itu, Dia kasi tau lai bilang,<bt>After that, then Yesus them began to walk to Yerusalem. In the middle of the road/way, He called His underlings to gather together alone with Him. After that, He told again saying,</bt><v n="18" />&lt;&lt;Bosong dengar, é! Kotong sakarang mau pi Yerusalem. Ma di sana dong jual buang sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, kasi pi di kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, deng guru agama dong. Ais dong putus hukuman mati sang Beta.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl listen! We-inc now want to go to Yerusalem. But there they will sell Me off (=betray), the Ideal/Prototypical Human, to the *chief priests and the religion teachers. Then they will decide the death punishment to Me.</bt><v n="19" />Ju dong sarakan sang Beta pi orang laen yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah. Ais dong omong bekin malu sang Beta. Dong firuk kasi ancor Beta pung badan. Ais, baru dong bunu bekin mati sang Beta di kayu palang. Memang Beta mati batúl. Ma dia pung lusa, Beta idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they turn Me over to other people who do not know God. Then they will speak making Me embarrased/ashamed. And they will whip destroying My body. And then they will kill Me on the crossed wood. Truly I will really die. But on the.day.after.the.next.day, I will live again.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yakobis dan Yohanis pung mama minta ko angka dia pung ana jadi orang bésar<bt>Yakobis and Yohanes' mama requests to that her children be lifted up to become big people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 10:35-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais itu, Sabadeus pung bini datang sang Yesus, sama-sama deng dia pung ana Yakobis deng Yohanis. Ju dia tikam lutut deng kasi hormat ko noki-noki sang Yesus.<bt>After that, Sabadius' wife came to Yesus, together with her children Yakobis and Yohanis. Then she knelt and gave respect in order to beg/nag/insist Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju Yesus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Mama ada mau parlú apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked her saying, &lt;&lt;What does mama need?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju itu mama kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, Bapa! Beta minta, kalo Bapa su dudu pegang parenta, na, Bapa angka sang beta pung ana dua ni, ko dong ju iko pegang parenta sama-sama deng Bapa. Beta minta ko Bapa kasi dudu satu di Bapa pung sablá kanan, deng satu di sablá kiri.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that mama told saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this, Father! I request, if/when Father already sits holding authority, na, Father lift up my two children here, so they also hold authority together with Father. I request that Father sits one on Father right side, and one on the left side.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar dia pung minta, ju Yesus kasi tau sang Yakobis deng Yohanis bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde mangarti apa yang bosong minta. Te Beta nanti dapa sangsara banya. Jadi karmana? Bosong kira bosong ju mampu pikol itu sangsara sama-sama deng Beta, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing her request, then Yesus told Yakobis and Yohanis saying, &lt;&lt;You don't understand what you ask. Cuz (elaboration) I later will get much suffering. So (consequently) how about it? Do you think you also are capable of shoulder carrying that suffering together with Me [+tag question]?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong dua manyao ena-ena sa bilang, &lt;&lt;Talalu bisa, Bapa, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>The two of them replied smugly saying, &lt;&lt;Too easy, Father, é!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais Dia manyao lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang, bosong ju nanti pikol itu sangsara sama ke Beta. Ma sapa yang nanti dudu di Beta pung kanan deng kiri, itu bukan Beta yang putus. Itu Tuhan Allah yang pung hak putus. Dia su putus memang, sapa-sapa yang dudu di itu tampa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He replied again saying, &lt;&lt;True, you also will later carry that suffering the same as Me. But who it is who later sits on My right and left, it is not Me who decides. It is God who has the right/authority to decide that. He has already decided beforehand, who it si who sits in those places.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Waktu sapulu ana bua yang laen su dengar dong dua pung minta bagitu, ju dong jengkel.<bt>When those ten other underlings heard what the two of them had asked like that, then they were upset.</bt><v n="25" />Ma Yesus pange ame sang dong samua, ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Bosong su tau, to? Orang-orang bésar yang pegang parenta biasa tendes dong pung rakyat, sampe dong sonde bisa bagarák. Deng kapala-kapala dari bangsa yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah, dong kasi parenta lebe-lebe, sampe dong pung rakyat sonde bisa angka kapala.<bt>But Yesus called them all, and He said, &lt;&lt;It's like this! You know, don't you? Big people who hold authority usually press.down/oppress their populace, until they cannot move. And the heads of nations who do not know God, they give excessive orders, until their populace cannot lift their heads.</bt><v n="26" />Ma bosong sonde bole bekin bagitu! Naa, sapa dari bosong yang mau jadi orang bésar, dia musti jadi sama ke jongos ko layani orang laen.<bt>But you-pl may not do like that! Naa, [+shift] whoever of you wants to become a big person, he must become like a servant/house.helper to serve other people.</bt><note reference="20:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:25-26</note><v n="27" />Deng sapa yang mau jadi kapala, dia musti bekin diri sama ke hamba.<bt>And whoever wants to become head, he must make himself like a slave.</bt><note reference="20:26-27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:11, Markus 9:35, Lukas 22:26</note><v n="28" />Dengar, é! Beta ju bagitu. Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, datang ko layani orang. Beta sonde datang ko orang layani sang Beta. Te Beta datang kasi Beta pung idop anteru-anteru, ko tabús ame banya orang dari dong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Listen! I am also like that. I, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, came to serve people. I did not come in order that people serve Me. Cuz (elaboration) I came to give My entire life, in order to *redeem many people from their wrongs.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang buta<bt>The Lord Yesus heals blind person/people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 10:46-52; Lukas 18:35-43)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais itu, Yesus dong jalan tarús. Waktu dong kaluar dari kota Yeriko, ada banya orang yang iko sang dong.<bt>After that, Yesus them walked on. When they came out of Yeriko city, there were many people who followed them.</bt><v n="30" />Di situ, ada dua orang buta yang dudu di pinggir jalan. Waktu dong dengar bilang, yang lewat tu, andia Yesus dari Nasaret, ju dong batarea karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos! Daud pung turunan, é! Botong su tunggu-tunggu lama sang Bos! Kasian sang botong dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>There, there were two blind people who sat on the side of the road. When they heard that the one who passed there, was Yesus from Nasaret, then they yelled loudly saying, &lt;&lt;Bos! Daud's descendant! We-inc have waited and waited so long for Bos! Have pity on us!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: “We-inc have been waiting so long for Father!” is implied in the title ‘Son of David’? Carson does a nice job of showing how Matthew treats this as a recurring book-level theme. It's pretty uncontroversial that the Jews understood this immediately to be a Messianic title. It's also fairly well demonstrated in our languages here that people don't know this unless they are taught it (and reminded of it). We don't do this at every occurrence, but do it here to hint at it, while trying to reflect something that could be shouted out. For us, the UNS response is king - regardless of what the RT (collective) says.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Dengar dong batarea bagitu, ju orang togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bosong dua jang baribut!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing them yelling like that, then people scolded saying, &lt;&lt;Heh! [+rebuke] You two don't be noisy!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong batarea lebe karás lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Daud pung turunan, é! Kasian sang botong doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they yelled even louder saying, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Daud's descendant! Have pity on us!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Waktu Yesus dengar bagitu, ju Dia barenti ko tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong mau Beta bekin apa kasi bosong?&gt;&gt;<bt>When He heard like that, then He stopped and asked them saying, &lt;&lt;What do you want Me to do for you?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos é! Tolong ko botong bisa dapa lia doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;Bos! Help us so we can see!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Dengar dong pung omong bagitu, ju Dia jato kasian sang dong. Ais Dia raba dong pung mata, ju dong lia memang. Ais itu, dong jalan iko sang Dia.<bt>Hearing their speaking like that, then He felt pity for them. Then He touched their eyes, and they saw straight away. After that, they walked following Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus maso kota Yerusalem sama ke Raja<bt>The Lord Yesus enters the city of Yerulsem as a King</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 11:1-11; Lukas 19:28-40; Yohanis 12:12-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="21" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus dong jalan tarús sampe di satu kampong nama Betfage, di gunung Saitun pung pinggir.<bt>After that, Yesus them walked on until a village named Betfage, on Saitun mountain's edge.</bt><note reference="21:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dong kasi nama &lt;Saitun&gt; di itu gunung, tagal di sana ada banya kabón pohon saitun. Dong biasa parés pohon saitun pung bua ko dapa dia pung minya. Itu gunung Saitun pung jao, kira-kira satu kilo dari kota Yerusalem.<bt>The gave the name &lt;Saitun&gt; to that mountain, because there there were many olive tree gardens, for them to press it's oil from that tree's fruit. That Saitun mountain's distance is approximately one kilometre from Yerusalem city.</bt></note>Itu kampong su deka-deka deng kota Yerusalem. Di situ dong barenti tahan. Ju Dia suru Dia pung ana bua dua orang ko pi lebe dolo.<bt>That village was near to Yerusalem city. There they stopped momentarily. Then He ordered two of his underlings to go on ahead.</bt><v n="2" />Dia suru sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dua pi di itu kampong sana. Kalo bosong maso, nanti bosong dapa lia binatang keledai mai deng dia pung ana satu ada ta'ika di situ. Bosong pi buka dong pung tali ko hela bawa datang kasi sang Beta.<bt>He commanded them saying, &lt;&lt;You two go to that village over there. If/When you enter, later you will see a female donkey animal and her child, are tied up there. You go open/untie their rope in order to pull bring [them] to Me.</bt><v n="3" />Ma kalo ada orang tanya sang bosong bilang, &lt;Akurang ko bosong hela bawa orang pung keledai?&gt; Naa, bosong manyao bilang, &lt;Bos ada mau pake. Kalo su pake abis, nanti Dia kirim pulang memang.&gt;<bt>But if someone asks you saying, &lt;Why are you pulling taking someone else's donkey?&gt; Naa, [+shift] you answer saying, &lt;&lt;Bos wants to use [it]. When [he] is finished using [it], later He will send [it] back right away.&gt; [EXEG: Does the Gk ‘he’ in the last clause refer to a) the Lord, or b) the owner of the donkey? English translations go in both directions. The Gk grammar slightly favours (a), and (a) also better reflects the parallel passages. TB goes with (a) here in Matthew, and our protocols say we follow the TB where 2 exegetical choices are equally supported.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Samua ni musti jadi, iko apa yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir su tulis memang bilang,<bt>All this must happen, following that which God's spokesperson has writen beforehand saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />&lt;We, bosong orang Yerusalem dong!<bt>&lt;We, [+get attention] you Yerusalem people!</bt><note reference="21:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Sion pung ana parampuan&gt;&gt;. Sion tu, andia Yerusalem pung nama laen. Jadi di sini Sakaria ada pake bahasa alus ko batarea kasi kota Yerusalem pung orang dong.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes, “daughter of Sion”. Sion is another name for Yerusalem. So (consequently), here Sakaria is using refined language to shout to the people of the city of Yerusalem.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mari ko lia sini doo!<bt>Come look here!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te bosong pung Raja ada datang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) your King is coming.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia datang deng randá hati.<bt>He comes with a low liver (=unpretentious/humble). [NOTE to daughter translations: careful for MTT noise from TB that uses /lemah lembut/ which skews focus on kind/gentle manner, rather than humble/low status.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia datang nae keledai ana.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>He comes on a donkey's offspring.&gt;&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK, you might have to say keledai muda in this, if /ana/ here is closer to newborn. In verse 2 it should be OK, cuz it's in relation to the mother there.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 9:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais ju itu ana bua pi, deng bekin iko samua, sama ke Yesus su pasán sang dong tu.<bt>Afterwards then those underlings went, and they did everything like Yesus had instructed them.</bt><v n="7" />Dong hela bawa itu keledai mai deng dia pung ana pi Yesus. Ais dong taro dong pung salimut di keledai pung balakang, ju Yesus nae di atas ko mau maso kota.<bt>They pulled brought that female donkey and her offspring to Yesus. Then they put their blanket/s (=word for Timorese men's traditional sarong), and He mounted on top in order to enter the city.</bt><v n="8" />Waktu dong mau maso pi dalam kota, ju banya orang ame dong pung salimut deng dong pung salendang, ko taro di jalan. Ada ju yang pi potong ame daon-daon palam<bt>When they were wanting to enter the city (=they had not yet got there), then many people took their blankets (=men's cloth) and their sashes (=women's cloth), in order to put them on the road. There were also those who went to cut palm leaves</bt><note reference="21:8" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Mateos pung tulisan asli bilang &lt;cabang dong&gt;. Ma kotong su tau dari Yohanis 12:13 bilang daon-daon palam.<bt>Matthew's original writing said &lt;branches&gt;. But we know from Yohanes 12:13 that it was <span class="Italic">palam </span>leaves.</bt></note>ko dong buka-buka di tenga jalan. Deng bagitu, dong bekin tanda bilang, dong sambut sang Dia sama ke orang bésar.<bt>in order for them to spread them out in the middle of the road. With that, they made a sign saying, they welcomed Him like a big person.</bt><v n="9" />Ju ada orang saparu pi bajalan lebe dolo di muka Yesus, deng ada yang iko dari balakang. Dong ba'eki rame-rame bilang,<bt>There were also some people who went walking ahead of Yesus, and there were those who followed from behind. They all yelled out enthusiastically saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Botong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt>&lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> We-exc praise and praise God!</bt><note reference="21:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dong pung bahasa Aram bilang <span class="Italic">&lt;Hosana&gt;</span>. Dia pung arti dolu-dolu bilang, &lt;dia kasi salamat orang&gt;. Waktu Tuhan Yesus masi idop di ini dunya, orang biasa pake itu kata dong, ko puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Their Aram language says <span class="Italic">&lt;Hosana&gt;.</span> Its very old meaning says, &lt;he saves people&gt;. When the Lord Yesus was still living on this earth, that word, they usually used to praise God.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Daud pung turunan su datang!<bt>Because Daud's descendant has come! [EXEG: Is ‘Hosanna’ addressing praise to God for Jesus, or praise to Jesus in this context? First issue, ‘hosanna’ shifted meaning over time (several hundred years) from an original meaning of ‘he saves’ to a later lexicalized sense of ‘praise God!’ (See CEG word sutdy on ‘hosana’.) Second issue, should the Gk dative preposition be taken as dative ‘to’ or benefactive ‘for’? The Gk case can have either reading. Note NLT, CEV, and TB2 all take the benefactive reading ‘for’, not the dative reading ‘to’ like NRSV. Note also that the context of the remainder of the quote also favours a benefactive reading.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Botong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt><span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> We-exc praise and praise God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Tuhan su utus datang ini Orang.<bt>Because the Lord has commissioned this Person to come.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Botong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt><span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> We-exc praise and praise God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Tuhan ada dudu parenta memang di langit yang paling tinggi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because the Lord really ruling, in the very highest sky!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="21:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Waktu Yesus maso Yerusalem deng rame-rame bagitu, ju isi kota samua kaluar ko batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Sapa yang datang ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus entered Yerusalem bustlingly/lively like that, then the all the contents of the city (=everyone) came to ask each.other saying, &lt;&lt;Awii [+amazement]! Who is this coming?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Orang banya manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ni, Tuhan Allah pung jubir. Dia pung nama Yesus, orang Nasaret, dari propinsi Galilea.&gt;&gt;<bt>The many people answered saying, &lt;&lt;He is God's spokesperson. His name is Yesus, he's a Nasaret person, from Galilea province.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus maso pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat ko bongkar buang pasar di situ<bt>The Lord Yesus enter into the Main Prayer House to demolish get rid of a market there</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 11:15-19; Lukas 19:45-48; Yohanis 2:13-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais Yesus dong jalan tarús, ju dong maso pi Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Di itu Ruma Sambayang pung kintal, orang su bekin jadi pasar, ko dong bajual burung pompa yang orang pake jadi korban buat sambayang. Lia bagitu, ju Yesus pi usir kasi kaluar sang dong. Dia banting kasi talempar meja-meja yang dong pake tukar doi, deng banting kasi tabale bangku-bangku yang dong pake bajual itu burung dong.<bt>Then Yesus them walked on, and they entered God's Main Prayer House. In that Prayer House's yard, people had made a market in order for them to sell dove/pidgin birds which people used as sacrifices for prayer/worship. Seeing like that, then Yesus went to expel kick them out. He flung making cast about tables which they used to change money, and flung turning upside down benches which they used to sell those birds.</bt><v n="13" />Ju Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan pung jubir su tulis bilang,<bt>Then He told them saying, &lt;&lt;The Lord's spokesperson has written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Beta kasi bangun ini Ruma,<bt>I build this House, [NOTE: ‘build’ here indicates primary and original purpose of having the house.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar orang bisa datang sambayang di sini.&gt;<bt>so that people can come pray/worship here.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tuhan pung maksud bagitu, ma bosong su bekin ini Ruma jadi parampok dong pung tampa bakumpul!&gt;&gt;<bt>The Lord's intent is like that, but you have made this House to become robbers gathering place!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="21:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 56:7, Yeremia 7:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais ju orang buta deng orang lumpu dong datang sang Yesus di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang tu. Ju Dia bekin bae sang dong samua.<bt>Afterwards then blind people and lame people came to Yesus in that Prayer House of God's. Then He healed them all.</bt><v n="15" />Di situ ada ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng guru agama dong. Waktu dong lia Yesus bekin tanda heran bagitu, ju dong jengkel. Lebe-lebe lai, waktu dong dengar itu ana-ana dong batarea rame-rame di Ruma Sambayang bilang,<bt>There there were also *chief priests and religion teachers. When they saw Yesus doing miracles like that, then they got upset/annoyed. Even more so when they heard those children yelling enthusiastically at the Prayer House saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Botong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt>&lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> We-inc praise and praise God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal raja Daud pung turunan su datang ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because descendant of raja Daud has now come!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais, itu bos-bos dong kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu dengar itu ana-ana dong pung omong? Itu sonde batúl tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, those bosses told Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! [+negative] Do you hear what those children are saying? It's not true/right!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Yesus manyao sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo, Beta ada dengar. Ko akurang? Bosong balóm parná baca di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi so'al ana-ana yang puji sang Tuhan Allah, ko? Te di situ ada tatulis bilang,<bt>But Yesus answered them saying, &lt;&lt;Yea, I hear. Why? Have you not yet ever read in the Bible about the children who praise God [+tag question]? Cuz (elaboration) there it is written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah su siap memang ana mea deng ana kici,<bt>&lt;God has prepared beforehand red children (=newborns) and small children,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong puji-puji sang Dia.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>so that they keep praising Him.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="21:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 8:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais ju Yesus dong kaluar kasi tenga itu kota, ko pi tidor di kampong Betania.<bt>Afterwards then Yesus (coll.) went out leaving behind that city, in order to go sleep in Betania village.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus parenta pohon satu ko jang babua lai<bt>The Lord Yesus commands a tree to no longer bear fruit</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 11:12-14, 20-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Dia pung beso papagi, Yesus dong jalan lai ko maso kambali pi kota Yerusalem. Ma di tenga jalan, Dia su rasa lapar.<bt>The next day early in the morning, Yesus them walked again in order to enter again to Yerusalem city. But in the middle of the road, He felt hungry.</bt><v n="19" />Dia dapa lia pohon satu di pinggir jalan yang orang biasa makan dia pung bua.<bt>He saw a tree on the edge of the road which people usually eat it's fruit.</bt><note reference="21:19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Indonesia pake kata &lt;pohon ara&gt; dari istila Yunani συκῆ <span class="Italic">(sukē).</span> Ma Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi kasi tunju satu pohon di sana yang orang biasa tanam, deng makan dia pung bua. Di Indonesia sablá matahari nae, orang sonde makan &lt;pohon ara&gt; pung bua. Jadi &lt;pohon ara&gt; di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi, sonde sama ke kotong pung pohon ara di sini.<bt>Indonesian uses the word &lt;ara tree&gt; from the Greek term <span class="Italic">συκῆ (sukē).</span> But the Bible designates a tree there which people usually plant, and eat its fruit. In eastern Indonesia, people do not eat &lt;ara tree's&gt; fruit. So &lt;ara tree&gt; in the Bible, is not the same as our-inc ara trees here.</bt></note>Jadi Dia pi deka-deka itu pohon, ko mau lia coba ada bua, ko sonde. Ma waktu Dia sampe di itu pohon, Dia sonde dapa lia bua satu ju, tagal itu pohon baru badaon sa. Ju Dia omong deng itu pohon bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal lu sonde kasi kaluar lu pung bua kasi sang Beta, andia ko lu sonde akan babua lai!&gt;&gt; Dia omong abis, ju itu pohon karíng memang.<bt>So He went close to that tree, to try and see if there was fruit, or not. But when He arrived at that tree, He did not see even one fruit, because that tree had just only leafed (=begun to grow leaves). then He spoke with that tree saying, &lt;&lt;Because you did not give out your fruit to Me, that is why you will not have fruit again!&gt;&gt; [When] He finished speaking, then that tree became dry right away. [EXEG: Matthew does not say anything about the season. Mark says “for it was not the season for figs.” So don't try to explain away Jesus' actions by saying “it was the fruit season” here. There is no textual or exegetical basis for doing so.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Dia pung ana bua dong lia bagitu, ju dong takuju. Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko takuju sa ini pohon karíng memang?&gt;&gt;<bt>His underlings saw like that, then they were surprised. They asked saying, &lt;&lt;How can it be that just all of a sudden this tree is dry straight away?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae, é! Kalo bosong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan, deng sonde hati bacabang sadiki ju, bosong bisa bekin sama ke yang Beta su bekin tu. Bosong ju bisa bekin lebe dari itu. Conto ke: bosong bisa parenta gunung satu ta'angka pi laut. Tantu Tuhan Allah kasi pinda itu gunung memang, asal bosong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Dia!<bt>Then He answered saying, &lt;&lt;Listen well! If you believe truly in the Lord, and don't doubt even a little bit, you can do the same as I did there. You can also do more than that. For example: you-pl could order a mountain to be picked up into the ocean. Surely God will move that mountain straight away, as.long as you truly believe in Him!</bt><note reference="21:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 17:20, 1 Korintus 13:2</note><v n="22" />Te samua hal yang bosong minta sang Tuhan Allah, nanti bosong tarima, asal bosong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) all things which you reqest of God, later you will receive, as long as you truly believe in Him.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bos-bos dong baso'al deng Tuhan Yesus pung hak<bt>The bosses query the Lord Yesus' right/authority</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 11:27-33; Lukas 20:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais Yesus dong jalan tarús. Sampe di Yerusalem, dong maso kambali lai pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal. Waktu Dia ajar orang so'al Tuhan Allah pung jalan idop, ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, deng tua-tua adat dong datang ko baso'al deng Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang suru lu datang bekin kaco di sini kamaren? Sapa yang kasi itu hak sang lu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Afterwards Yesus them walked on. Arriving at Yerusalem, they returned entered again to the yard of the Main Prayer House. While He taught people about God's life way, then the *chief priests, and traditional elders came to debate with Him saying, &lt;&lt;Who ordered you to come and make chaos here yesterday? Who gave that right/authority to you?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ma Dia tau dong ada cari jalan ko mau kasi jato sang Dia. Ais Dia balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ju mau tanya sang bosong. Bosong manyao sang Beta dolo, baru Beta manyao sang bosong.<bt>But He knew they were looking for a way to make Him fall. So He replied saying, &lt;&lt;I also want to ask you [something]. You answer Me first, then I will answer you.</bt><v n="25" />Beta mau tanya bagini: bosong samua kanál sang Yohanis, Tukang Sarani tu, to? Naa, sapa yang kasi hak sang dia ko sarani orang? Tuhan Allah ko, manusia?&gt;&gt;<bt>I want to ask like this: you all know Yohanis, that Habitual Baptizer, right? Naa, [+shift] who was it who ordered him to go baptize people? God or, humans?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dong bapikir pi-datang, deng barunding bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe'! Kotong su kaná hiki ni, ma! Te kalo kotong manyao bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah yang kasi hak&gt;, nanti Dia balas bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, akurang ko bosong sonde parcaya sang Yohanis?&gt;<bt>Then they thought going-coming (=all about it), and confered together saying, &lt;&lt;Oh no! We-inc have been trapped here [protest particle sort of like ugh!] Cuz (elaboration) if we answer saying &lt;It's God who gave the right/authority&gt;, later He will reply saying, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, why didn't you believe Yohanis?&gt;</bt><v n="26" />Ma kotong ju sonde bisa bilang, &lt;Manusia yang kasi hak&gt;, te nanti orang dong samua mangamok sang kotong. Tagal dong parcaya bilang, Yohanis tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir.&gt;&gt;<bt>But we also can't say, &lt;Humans [are the ones] who gave the right/authority&gt;, cuz (elaboration) later the people will all run amuck at us. Because they believe that Yohanis is God's spokesperson.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="27" />Andia ko dong manyao sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde tau.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why they answered Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;We don't know.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Kalo bagitu, Beta ju sonde parlú kasi tau sapa yang kasi hak sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Naa! If that's the case, I also don't need to tell you who gave the right/authority to Me [to do that yesterday].&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al satu bapa deng dia pung ana laki-laki dua orang<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about a father and his two sons</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus omong tarús deng itu bos-bos dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pikir karmana deng umpama ni? Ada satu bapa deng dia pung ana laki-laki dua orang. Dia parenta sang ana sulung bilang, &lt;Ana, é! Ini hari, na, lu pi karjá di kabón doo.&gt;<bt>Yesus continued speaking with those bosses saying, &lt;&lt;What do you think about this example? There was a father and his two male children. He ordered the first/oldest child saying, &lt;Son. Today, na, you go work in the garden.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma itu ana manyao bilang, &lt;Eeh! Beta sonde pi.&gt; Ma sonde lama ju dia manyasal, ais dia pi.<bt>But that child answered saying, ‘Eeh [+frustration/objection]! I won't go.’ But soon he felt regret, so/and he went.</bt><note reference="21:29-31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Indonesia TB1 su serong dari tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae di sini.<bt>The Indonesian language Bible TB1 deviates from the oldest and best Yunani writings here.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais ju itu bapa suru dia pung ana nomer dua bilang, &lt;Ana, é! Ini hari, na, lu pi karjá di kabón doo.&gt;<bt>And then that father ordered his number two child saying, ‘Child, today, na, you go work in the garden.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju itu ana manyao bilang, &lt;Bae bapa. Nanti beta pi&gt;. Ma tau-tau, te dia sonde pi.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then that child answered saying, ‘Ok father. I'll go’. But it turns out that he didn't go.” [EXEG: Most major Greek manuscripts (and the UBS and Majority texts) have what is given in the text above. However, a few reverse the answers and actions of the first/oldest and second/youngest sons throughout this section. Beginning here they say, “ '[I (will), master/sir/father],' but [he didn't go]. 30 Then (the man/father) went to the/his [second]/other/younger (son) (and) told (him DQto do) the same thing. And his son &lt;responding&gt; said (to him), 'I [don't want to], master/sir/father,' but [later he regretted (his answer) and went]. 31 (Now/So,) which of the two (sons) did/obeyed the will of (their) father?' They answered (Him/Jesus), 'The [last/second/younger] one.' Unfortunately, the TB1 follows this weak reading. The Kupang was correct, but somehow got changed just before printing, so the 2007 printed Kupang is INCORRECT, and there is a printed insert with the corrected text (relat—this is the only one). The footnote below also alerts people to this discrepency.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Carita ais bagitu, ju Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa, Beta mau tanya bagini: dari itu dua ana tu, yang mana yang bekin iko dia pung bapa pung parenta tu?&gt;&gt;<bt>After finishing telling the story like that then Yesus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;Naa, [+shift] I want to ask like this: From those two children there, which one did according to his father's command?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang partama!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they answered saying, &lt;&lt;That first one!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo. Ma dengar bae-bae, te Beta omong yang batúl. Orang yang bosong su cap orang tar laku-laku dong, sama ke ini tukang tagi bea, deng parampuan nakal, nanti dong maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang lebe dolo dari bosong. Te bosong cuma ia bae sang Tuhan sa, ma sonde bekin iko Dia pung mau.<bt>Then He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Yes (colloquial). But listen carefully, cuz (elaboration) I'm telling (you) the truth. People whom you have branded/stamped as worthless, like these tax collectors, and naughty women (whores/prostitutes), later they will enter becoming God's people ahead of you. Cuz (elaboration) you only yea ok God (= give verbal consent), but don't do according to His will.</bt><v n="32" />Dolu Yohanis tukang sarani su ajar sang bosong jalan karmana ko bosong bisa idop lurus. Ma bosong sonde mau parcaya sang dia. Padahal, waktu orang tar laku-laku dong dengar sang Yohanis, dong kasi tenga dong pung sala-sala, ko iko dia pung ajaran. Bosong ju su tau itu samua. Ma bosong sonde mau barenti dari bosong pung sala, ko iko Tuhan Allah pung mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>Previously Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer taught you, how you could live straight (=righteously). But you didn't want to believe him. However when worthless people heard Yohanis, they left behind their wrongs, to follow that teaching of his. You also already know all that. But you don't want to stop from your wrongs, to follow God's will.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="21:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 3:12, 7:29-30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al orang jahat yang garap kabón anggor<bt>The Lord Yesus give an example about evil people who share-cropped a grape garden</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:1-12; Lukas 20:9-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais itu, Yesus carita satu umpama lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu tuan tana yang pi buka kabón baru, ko mau tanam pohon anggor di dia pung tana sapo'ong. Ais dia bekin pagar kuliling. Deng dia bekin bak ko mau parés bua anggor pung aer. Ju dia kasi badiri satu tampa jaga yang tinggi. Ais dia kasi sewa itu kabón pi tukang garap, ko dong karjá bagi hasil deng dia. Tarús dia barangkat pi luar negrí.<bt>After that, Yesus storied one example more, sayimg. &lt;&lt;There was a land.owner who went to open/start a garden, in order to plant grape trees on his piece of land. Then he made a fence all around. And he made a tank in order to press the grape fruit's water/juice. Then he built a guarding place that was high. Then he rented that garden to land.workers, so they could work dividing the produce with him. Next he left to go overseas/to another country.</bt><note reference="21:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 5:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Sampe musim ketu bua anggor, ju itu tuan kabón suru dia pung ana bua dong pi di itu tukang garap, ko minta dia pung bagian.<bt>When the season for picking grape fruit arrived, then that garden master commanded his underlings to go to those land.workers, in order to request his share.</bt><v n="35" />Ma itu tukang garap dong sonde toe deng dia pung ana bua dong. Ada yang kaná pukul, ada yang kaná bunu, deng ada yang kaná lempar deng batu.<bt>But those land.workers didn't care/pay attention to his underlings. There were some which were beaten, there were some who were murdered, and some who had stones thrown at them.</bt><v n="36" />Ma itu tuan kabón suru lai dia pung ana bua satu rombongan yang lebe bésar dari yang partama tu. Ma itu tukang garap dong bekin jahat bagitu ju sang dong samua.<bt>But that garden master ordered/commissioned again a group of his underlings which was bigger than that first group. But those land.workers did evil like that also to them all.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Lama-lama ju, itu tuan kabón suru dia pung ana sandiri. Te dia pikir kata, &lt;Kalo beta kirim beta pung ana sandiri, pasti dong tarima bae-bae, deng dong dengar sang dia.&gt;<bt>Eventually then, that garden master ordered his own child. Cuz (elaboration) he thought saying, &lt;&lt;If I order my own child, surely they will accept [him] well, and they will listen to him.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ma waktu itu tukang garap dong lia sang itu ana, ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;We, bosong lia dolo! Te bapatua su kirim datang dia pung ana sandiri. Dia yang nanti tarima bapatua pung pusaka samua. Jadi mari ko kotong bunu sang dia su, ko biar kotong yang soa ini kabón.&gt;<bt>But when those land.workers saw that child, then they spoke to each other saying, &lt;We, [+get attention] you all look there! Cuz (elaboration) the old man has sent his own child. He is the one who will later receive all the old man's inheritance. So (consequently), let's murder him, so that we are the ones who own/take possession of this garden.&gt;</bt><v n="39" />Ju dong tangkap ame itu ana, ais hela buang pi luar kabón ko dong bunu sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they capture that child, then pulled threw him outside the garden to kill him.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Yesus carita abis, ju Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa, Beta mau tanya bagini: kalo itu tuan kabón kambali, kira-kira dia bekin karmana deng itu tukang garap dong?&gt;&gt;<bt>[When] Yesus finished narrating, He asked them saying, &lt;&lt;Naa, [+shift] I want to ask like this: if that garden master returns, what will he do with those land.workers?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais orang Yahudi pung bos-bos dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Pasti dia bunu bekin mati itu orang jahat samua. Ais itu, dia kasi sewa itu kabón kasi pi orang laen, yang nanti bagi hasil pas deng dia pung waktu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then bosses of the Yahudi people responded saying, &lt;&lt;Surely he would murder kill all those evil people. After that, he would rent that garden to other people, who later would share the results at the appropriate time/season.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Ais Yesus omong deng dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mangkali bosong sonde parná baca ame apa yang ada tatulis dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Then Yesus spoke with them saying, &lt;&lt;It appears you have never read what is written in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ada satu batu yang tukang batu dong tola buang,<bt>&lt;There was a stone which the stone.workers rejected threw out,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma sakarang itu batu su jadi ruma pung batu alas!<bt>but now that stone has become the house's main support stone!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan Allah sandiri yang pili ame, ju kasi dudu itu batu.<bt>God himself chose, and placed that stone.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko kotong lia dia pung bagus lai!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>This is why we-inc see its goodness is great!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="21:42" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ais Yesus sambung Dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jadi bosong pikir bae-bae, é. Dolu Tuhan pili kotong orang Yahudi ni, ko jadi Dia pung orang. Ma tagal bosong sonde mau toe sang Beta, nanti Tuhan pili orang laen. Te orang yang idop iko Dia pung mau sa yang bisa maso jadi Dia pung orang.<bt>Then Yesus talked on saying, &lt;&lt;So you think carefully, é. Previously the Lord chose us-inc Jewish people here, to become His people. But becaue you do not want to pay attention to Me, later God will choose other people. Cuz (elaboration) only the person who live following his will is the one who can enter to become His person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added ‘live’ to last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) added ‘live’ to last sentence</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />[Beta kasi tau lurus-lurus sa. Beta ni, andia itu batu alas tu. Orang yang jato kaná ini batu, nanti itu orang jadi ancor-ancor. Deng kalo itu batu jato kaná orang, nanti itu orang jadi uuk-uuk memang.]&gt;&gt;<bt>[I'm telling you straight (no hidden meaning). I here, am that support stone there! A person who falls hitting that stone, later that person will become completely destroyed. And if that stone falls on someone, later that person will become meal (=little bits like cornmeal) straight away.]&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="21:44" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu sonde muat ini ayat 44 ni.<bt>Some Yunani language writings don't carry/load this verse 44.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Waktu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, deng orang Farisi dong dengar Yesus pung carita, ju dong tau bilang, Dia ada ser sang dong. Dong parsís sama ke itu tukang garap kabón dong, deng itu tukang batu yang tola buang itu batu alas.<bt>When the *chief priests, and Farisi people heard Yesus' story, then they knew that He was targeting them. They were exactly like those garden land workers, and those stone.workers who rejected threw away that support stone.</bt><v n="46" />Jadi dong mara mau mati. Ais dong ator siasat ko mau tangkap sang Dia. Ma dong ada eleng sang orang banya yang anggap Yesus tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir. Andia ko dong sonde bisa bekin apa-apa sang Dia.<bt>So (consequently), they became very angry. So/then, they strategized in order to capture Him. But they were timid of the many people, because they considered Yesus, a spokesperson of God. That's why they could not do anything to Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al orang yang sonde mau datang di pesta kawin<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about people who do not want to come to a wedding feast</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 14:15-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="22" />
      <v n="1" />Ais Yesus omong lai deng dong pake umpama bilang,<bt>Then Yesus spoke again with them using an example saying,</bt><v n="2" />&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung pegang parenta tu, sama ke satu raja yang ada bekin pesta kawin kasi sang dia pung ana laki-laki.<bt>&lt;&lt;That holding.authority/way.of.ruling of God's is like a king who makes a wedding feast for his male child.</bt><v n="3" />Waktu pesta su siap, ju dia suru dia pung hamba ko pi kasi tau orang-orang yang kaná undang dong bilang, &lt;Mari, te acara su mau mulai.&gt; Ma itu orang dong sonde mau datang.<bt>When the feast is ready, then he orders his servant/s to go tell people who were invited saying, &lt;Come, cuz (elaboration) the program/ceremony is about to begin.&gt; But those people did not want to come.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais, itu hamba dong pulang ko lapor sang raja. Dengar bagitu ju, itu raja suru dia pung hamba yang laen dong bilang, &lt;Bosong pi kasi tau itu orang dong ko datang su, te pesta su siap. Beta su horo sapi, deng su masa ena-ena. Suru dong datang makan pesta, te samua su siap ni.&gt;<bt>Then that servant/s goes home and reports to the king. Hearing like that then, that king orders his other servants saying, &lt;You-pl go tell those people, to come, cuz (elaboration) the feast/party is ready. I have cut a cow (=what you say when you have a feast in Timor), and cooked delicious [stuff]. Order them to come eat the feast, cuz (elaboration) everything is ready here.&gt; [EXEG: the focus is on the activity of an event worthy of sacrificing cows; note the Gk is plural, so don't say “one cow”. Either make it plural, or make it activity focused.]</bt><v n="5" />Itu hamba dong pi kasi tau bagitu. Ma itu orang yang kaná undang dong sonde mau toe. Ada yang pi kabón, ada yang pi dong pung tampa karjá,<bt>Those servants went to tell like that. But those people who were invited did not want to know about it. Some went to the garden, some went to their work places,</bt><v n="6" />deng ada yang tangkap itu raja pung hamba dong, ko siksa sampe mati.<bt>and some captured those servants of the king, and they tortured them to death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu raja mara mau mati. Ais dia suru dia pung tantara dong ko pi bunu itu orang-orang yang su bunu dia pung hamba dong. Ais, itu tantara dong bakar itu kota sampe rata deng tana.<bt>Hearing like that, then that king was very angry. Then he ordered his army guys to go murder those people who had murdered his servants. Then those army guys burned that city flat to the ground.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais ju itu raja pange dia pung hamba yang laen dong deng kasi tau bilang, &lt;Pesta kawin su siap, ma orang-orang yang beta su undang tu, sonde pantas iko beta pung pesta.<bt>After that, that king called his other servants and told saying, &lt;&lt;The wedding feast is ready, but those people whom I invited, are not worthy to attend my feast.</bt><v n="9" />Sakarang bosong kaluar pi jalan rame dong, ko undang sapa sa yang bosong katumu di situ.&gt;<bt>Now you-pl go out onto the busy (=main) streets, and invites just whoever you meet there.&gt;</bt><v n="10" />Ais, itu hamba dong pi di jalan rame dong. Dong bawa datang banya orang yang dong katumu di situ, ko iko pesta kawin tu. Ada orang bae deng ada orang jahat yang datang bekin ponu itu tampa pesta.<bt>Then, those servants went to the budy streets. They brought back many people whom they met there to go to that wedding feast. There were good people and evil people who came making full that feast place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais, itu raja maso pi tampa pesta ko lia kuliling dia pung tamu dong. Ju dia dapa lia satu tamu yang sonde pake pakean pesta.<bt>Then, that king entered into the feast place and looked all around at his guests. Then he say a guest who was not wearing feast/party clothes.</bt><note reference="22:11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang yang pintar saparu bilang, ini raja ni su sadia pakean pesta kasi orang dong yang datang dari mana-mana. Ma ini satu orang ni, sonde mau pake itu pakean. Deng bagitu, dia bekin hina sang itu raja deng dia pung ana.<bt>Some knowledgable people (experts) say that this king provided feast/party clothes for the people who came from various places. But this one person didn't want to wear those clothes. In that way, he offended/insulted the king and his offspring.</bt></note><v n="12" />Ais itu raja tanya bilang, &lt;He, tamán! Akurang ko lu maso di sini sonde pake pakean pesta?&gt; Ma itu orang tanganga bodo sa.<bt>Then that king asked saying, &lt;He, [+attention, + light rebuke] friend, why did you enter here without wearing feast/party clothes?&gt; But that person was just agape and stupidly.speechless.</bt><v n="13" />Tarús itu raja parenta sang dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;Ika ini orang pung kaki deng tangan, ko angka buang sang dia pi luar. Biar ko dia manangis deng sangsara di tampa galáp sana.&gt;<bt>Next that king ordered his servants saying, &lt;Tie this person's feet and hands and pick him up throw him outside. Let him cry and suffer in the dark place over there.&gt;</bt><note reference="22:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 8:12, 25:30, Lukas 13:28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Bagitu ju, Tuhan Allah undang banya orang, ma Dia cuma pili sadiki sa ko jadi Dia pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Likewise, God also invites many people, but He only chooses just a few to become His people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong so'al bayar pajak kasi pamarenta<bt>The Lord Yesus talks about paying tax to the government</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:13-17; Lukas 20:20-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Dengar abis Yesus pung omong bagitu, ju orang Farisi dong ba'akór ko mau hiki deng tudu sang Dia.<bt>After hearing Yesus speaking like that, the Farisi people agreed with each other to try and trap and accuse/indict Him.</bt><v n="16" />Ais dong suru dong pung ana bua sama-sama deng orang dari Herodes pung partei politik, ko pi baso'al deng Yesus. Dong angka-angka nae sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Botong tau Bapa pung hati lurus. Bapa sonde tau putar-balek deng sonde pili muka. Bapa salalu ajar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata deng batúl.<bt>So they ordered their people together with people from Herodes' political party to go debate with Yesus. They lifted him up (=praised/flattered him) saying, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! We-exc know Father's liver is straight (=you are honest/just). Father doesn't twist-turn (=decieve) and doesn't choose faces (=discriminate). Father always teaches God's Words correctly. [NOTE: on ‘Herodians’, see CEV ftn and discussion in Morris.]</bt><v n="17" />Sakarang, botong mau tanya satu hal. Iko kotong pung atoran agama Yahudi, kira-kira kotong musti bayar pajak kasi pamarenta Roma pung raja bésar, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>Now we want to ask something. According to our-inc Jewish religious regulations, must we pay tax to the Roma goverment's big king, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ma Yesus su tau dong mau pancing sang Dia, ko Dia omong malawan pamarenta Roma. Ju Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dasar orang muka-balakang! Akurang ko bosong mau hiki sang Beta deng itu so'al?<bt>But Yesus already knew they were fishing/baiting/trying.to.trap Him, so that He would speak opposing the Roma government. Then He replied saying, &lt;&lt;[You are] fundamentally front-back people (=hypocrites)! Why are you trying to trap me with that problem/issue?</bt><v n="19" />Coba kasi lia sang Beta doi perak satu yang orang pake ko bayar pajak!&gt;&gt; Ju dong kasi tunju satu doi perak sang Dia.<bt>Show Me a silver money which people use to pay tax!&gt;&gt; Then they showed a silver money/coin to Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini sapa pung gambar ni? Deng ini sapa pung nama ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He asked them saying, &lt;&lt;This is whose picture here? And this is whose name here?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu keser, pamarenta Roma pung raja bésar tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;That's keser, that big king of the Roma government.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Kalo bagitu, bosong pi kasi sang pamarenta apa yang pamarenta pung hak. Deng kasi sang Tuhan Allah apa yang jadi Tuhan Allah pung hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told them saying, &lt;&lt;Well! If that's the case, you go give to the government that which the government has rights.to. And give to God that which God has rights.to.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar Dia manyao bagitu, ju dong samua taheran-heran, ko Dia bilang batúl na. Andia ko dong sonde bisa hiki sang Dia. Ju dong jalan kasi tenga sang Dia.<bt>Hearing Him answer like that, then they all were amazed, cuz (elaboration) He obviously spoke correctly. That's why they could not trap Him. Then they walked leaving Him. [NOTE (CEG): I assume /ko Dia omong batúl na./ is required from UNS response. Also implied by positive semantics of Gk ‘marvelled’. See also discussion in Morris, TN, and Carson.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar so'al orang mati idop kambali; deng orang bakawin di sorga, ko sonde?<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about dead people living again; and people marrying in heaven, or not?</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:18-27; Lukas 20:27-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Di situ ada orang dari partei Saduki ju. Orang dari ini partei Saduki ni ajar bilang, orang mati sonde idop kambali. Itu hari, dong ju cari jalan ko mau hiki sang Yesus. Andia ko dong datang baso'al deng Dia bilang,<bt>There there were also people from the Saduki party. People from this Saduki party here, taught that dead people do not live again. That day they also sought a way to trap Yesus. That's why they came to debate with Him saying,</bt><note reference="22:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 23:8</note><v n="24" />&lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Ba'i Musa su tulis kasi tenga sang kotong ini adat bilang: kalo ada satu laki-laki mati kasi tenga dia pung bini, ma sonde ada ana, na, itu laki-laki pung adi musti kawin ame itu janda, ko biar kasi turunan sang dia pung kaka yang su mati tu.<bt>&lt;&lt;Father Teacher! Gf/Ff Musa wrote leaving behind for us, this custom that says: if a man dies leaving his wife, but does not have a child, then that man's younger sibling must marry that widow, in order to give a descendant to that elder.sibling of his who is dead.</bt><note reference="22:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 25:5</note><v n="25" />Memang, dolu ba'i Musa ajar bagitu, ma sakarang botong ada mau tanya bagini: ada tuju laki-laki basodara. Yang partama kawin, ma dia mati, deng sonde kasi tenga ana. Ju dia pung adi yang iko sang dia, kawin bale itu janda.<bt>That's correct, previously Gf/Ff Musa taught like that, but now we-exc want to ask like this: there were seven male siblings. The first one married, but he died and did not leave a child. Then his younger sibling who followed him (=the next in line), married in return/response that widow.</bt><v n="26" />Sonde lama lai dia ju mati deng sonde ada ana. Bagitu ju deng adi yang nomer tiga; dia kawin deng itu janda, ma dia ju mati deng sonde kasi tenga ana. Bagitu tarús-tarús sampe adi bungsu ju mati.<bt>Not much longer he also died, and didn't have a child. Like that also with younger sibling number three; he married that widow, but he also died and did not leave behind a child. Like that over and over until the youngest younger sibling also died.</bt><v n="27" />Ais ju itu janda mati.<bt>Afterwards then, that widow died.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Naa! Sakarang botong mau tanya bagini: itu parampuan su parná kawin deng tuju laki-laki. Nanti kalo dunya kiamat, ais Tuhan kasi idop kambali orang mati dong, itu parampuan jadi sapa pung bini?&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Now we want to ask like this: that woman has married seven men. Later when the world ends, then the Lord makes the dead people live again, that woman will be whose wife?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong batanya bagitu, na, bosong su sala bésar ni! Te bosong sonde mangarti Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan pung isi. Deng bosong ju sonde mangarti Dia pung kuasa yang hebat!<bt>Then Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;If you-pl ask like that, na, you are really wrong here! Cuz (elaboration) you don't understand the contents of God's Writings. And yu also don't understand His power which is awesome!</bt><v n="30" />Yang batúl, bagini. Nanti, kalo Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali orang mati, dong ju sonde bakawin lai, sama ke Dia pung ana bua di sorga.<bt>What's correct, is like this. Later, when God makes dead people live again, they will also not marry anymore, the same as His underlings in heaven. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK carefully if this works in your lg. UNS's in Kupang respond correctly. But this is ambiguous. It can mean 1) unlike the angels who do marry, or 2) don't marry anymore like the angels don't marry. If unclear, add /...sorga ju sonde bakawin./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Deng Beta ju mau omong so'al orang mati bisa idop kambali, ko sonde. Dalam ba'i Musa pung tulisan ada itu carita so'al pohon kici yang tabakar ma sonde angus. Dari itu carita, kotong dapa tau bilang, orang mati bisa idop kambali. Te di situ Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang ba'i Musa bilang,<bt>And I also want to talk about whether dead people can live again, or not. In grandfather Musa' writing there is a the story of the small tree which was burning but did not burn up. From that story, we-inc know that dead people can live again. Cuz (elaboration) there God told Gf/Ff Musa saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="32" />&lt;Beta ni, lu pung ba'i-ba'i pung Tuhan Allah.<bt>&lt;I here am your grandfathers'/forefathers' God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, deng ba'i Yakob.<bt>That Gf/Ff Abraham, grandfather Isak, and grandfather Yakob.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dong samua sémba tarús sang Beta sampe sakarang.&gt;<bt>They all worship Me continually until now.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa! Kotong tau bilang, waktu Tuhan omong bagitu, itu ba'i dong su mati lama. Ma Tuhan Allah bilang Dia masi jadi tarús dong pung Tuhan. Andia ko kotong tau bilang, biar dong mati su lama, ma dong pung jiwa ada idop tarús. Jadi biar orang mati, ma dia idop kambali. Te cuma orang idop yang sémba sang Tuhan Allah, bukan orang mati, to?!&gt;&gt;<bt>So! We-inc know that when God spoke like that, those grandfathers had been dead a long time. But God said He was still continually being their Lord. That's why we-inc know that even though they have been dead a long time, nevertheless their souls continue to live. So even if people die, but they live again. Cuz (elaboration) only living people who worship God, not dead people, right?!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="22:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 3:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Dengar Yesus ajar bagitu, ju itu orang Saduki dong sonde bisa balas apa-apa lai. Ma itu orang banya dong ada taheran-heran deng ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ini Orang pung ajaran talalu hebat, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus teach like that, then those Saduki people could not reply anything else. But those many people were amazed and spoke to each other saying, &lt;&lt;Awii [+amazement]! This Person's teaching is really awesome, ó!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Is the 1st sentence an addition? No, it is driven by RL discourse. vs.23 Sadducees want to trip up Jesus; vs.24-28 elaborate trick question; vs.29-32 Jesus turns the tables on the Sadducees; vs.33 crowd is amazed; vs.34 (NRSV) “When the Pharisees heard that he had silenced the Sadducees...” When did this happen? It fits best in vs.33. Having to explicate these missing steps is common, and based both on researching the discourse, and UNS/MTT feedback.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar so'al parenta yang paling pantíng<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches about the command/order/s which are the most important</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:28-34; Lukas 10:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Waktu orang Farisi dong dengar bilang, Yesus su ontong sang itu orang Saduki dong, ju dong bakumpul rame-rame ko mau baso'al deng Dia.<bt>When the Farisi people heard that Yesus had surpassed/won.over those Saduki people, then they gathered enthusiastically to debate with Him.</bt><v n="35" />Dong pung ahli agama satu mau hiki coba sang Dia bilang,<bt>One of their religion experts tried to trap Him saying,</bt><v n="36" />&lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Beta mau tanya bagini: kotong pung adat pung atoran, deng agama pung parenta dong, talalu banya. Dari samua parenta yang datang dari ba'i Musa tu, yang mana yang paling pantíng?&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Father Teacher! I want to ask like this: our-inc tradition/custom's regulations, and religion's commandments, are very many. From all those commandments which come from Gf/Ff Musa, which one is the most important?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Parenta yang paling pantíng dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi tu bilang bagini:<bt>Then He replied saying, &lt;&lt;The commandment which is most important in the Scriptures, says like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah tu, bosong pung Allah.<bt>&lt;God is your-pl God <span class="Italic">(Allah)</span>.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jadi bosong musti sayang sang Dia <span class="Italic">lebe</span> dari samua.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must love Him <span class="Italic">more</span> than all.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Tagal itu, bosong musti salalu rindu sang Dia,<bt>Because of that, you must always yearn for Him,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rindu = love, perhaps implies physical"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">rindu = love, perhaps implies physical separation, but also implies a strong existing relationship that yearns.affectionately, always mindful</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">mangarti sang Dia,<bt>understand Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng karjá karás ko iko Dia pung mau.&gt;<bt>and work hard to follow His will.&gt;</bt><note reference="22:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Itu parenta tu, yang paling pantíng deng paling hebat!<bt>That command there, is the most important and most amazing/terrific/great!</bt><v n="39" />Deng ada parenta nomer dua yang bilang bagini:<bt>And the number two command says like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Lu musti sayang orang laen dong, sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;<bt>'You-s must love other people, the same as you love your own self.'</bt><note reference="22:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ini dua parenta ni, andia pohon dari ba'i Musa pung atoran deng Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong pung ajaran samua. Orang sonde mungkin iko parenta yang laen dong, kalo dia sonde iko lebe dolo ini dua parenta bésar ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>These two commandments here, are the tree/trunk (=root/basis) of all grandfather Musa's regulations and God's spokesperson's teachings. There is no way a person can follow the other commands, if he does not first follow these two big commands here.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: last sentence following Carson, CONNOT. UNSs could not get the point without the explication.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Musa pung atoran agama dong, deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">Musa pung atoran agama dong, deng Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong pung ajaran, dia pung pohon andia ini dua parenta ni.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:35-40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:25-28</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus tu, memang raja Daud pung turunan, ma Dia ju jadi raja Daud pung Bos<bt>Kristus is truly king Daud's descendant, but His also becomes/is king Daud's Bos</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:35-37; Lukas 20:41-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Waktu itu orang Farisi dong masi ada bakumpul di situ, ju Yesus so'al bale sang dong bilang,<bt>When those Farisi people were still gathered there, then Yesus debated with them in return saying,</bt><v n="42" />&lt;&lt;Dari dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah su janji kirim Kristus ko kasi salamat sang Dia pung orang dong. Naa, iko bosong pung pikiran, Kristus tu, sapa pung turunan?&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;From long ago God has promised to send Kristus to save His people. Naa, [+shift] according to your-pl thinking, that Kristus is whose descendant?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, raja Daud pung turunan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they answered saying, &lt;&lt;He is a descendant of king Daud.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, akurang ko Tuhan Allah pung Roh Barisi kasi tau sang raja Daud ko dia pange sang Kristus tu, &lt;Bos&gt;? Te Daud su tulis bilang,<bt>Yesus spoke further saying, &lt;&lt;If it's like that, na, why did God's Holy Spirit tell king Daud for him to call Kristus &lt;Bos&gt;? Cuz (elaboration) Daud wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="44" />&lt;Tuhan Allah su kasi tau sang beta pung bos bilang,<bt>&lt;God has told my bos saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Mari ko dudu di Beta pung sablá kanan, di tampa yang paling hormat ni.<bt>&lt;&lt;Come and sit at My right side, in the place of greatest respect/honour here.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Te nanti Beta bekin lu pung musu dong, sampe dong ta'alok sang lu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later I will make your enemies, to the point that they surrender to you.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="22:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Naa! Dari itu tulisan, kotong dapa tau bilang, raja Daud sandiri yang pange sang Kristus tu, &lt;Bos&gt;. Jadi, kalo orang bilang Kristus tu, cuma raja Daud pung turunan sa, itu balóm cukup! Tagal Dia ju jadi raja Daud pung Bos yang hak parenta sang dia na!&gt;&gt;<bt>So! From that writing, we-inc can know that it was king Daud himself who called the Kristus &lt;Bos&gt;. So (consequently), if people say that the Kristus is only just king Daud's descendant, that is not enough! Because He also was obviously king Daud's Bos who had say-so/ordering rights over him [+emphatic]!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Dengar Yesus pung omong bagitu, ju itu orang Farisi dong jadi tabodo-bodo sa, te sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa manyao sang Yesus. Andia ko mulai dari itu hari ju, dong su taku batanya-batanya deng dong sonde barani hiki coba sang Dia lai.<bt>Hearing Yesus' talking like that, then those Farisi people became just stupidly.speechless, cuz (elaboration) there was not a single person who could reply to Yesus. That's why starting from that day, they were afraid to question [Him] and they didn't dare try to trap Him anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi inga ko ati-ati sang guru agama deng orang Farisi dong<bt>The Lord Yesus reminds to be careful of the religion teachers and the Farisi people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:38-39; Lukas 11:43, 46; 20:45-46)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="23" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju Yesus ajar Dia pung ana bua dong, sama-sama deng itu orang banya yang ada iko sang dong.<bt>Afterwards then Yesus taught His underlings, together with those many people who were following them.</bt><v n="2" />Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu guru agama deng orang Farisi dong pegang hak ko ajar ba'i Musa pung atoran dong.<bt>He told saying, &lt;&lt;Those religion teachers and Farisi people have authority to teach grandfather Musa's regulations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pegang hak ko kasi tau Ba'i"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">pegang hak ko kasi tau Ba'i Musa pung atoran dong pung arti apa.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Tagal itu, bosong musti dengar sang dong deng iko dong pung ajaran ju. Ma jang iko apa yang dong bekin, tagal dong sonde bekin iko dong pung ajaran sandiri.<bt>Because of that, you-pl must listen/obey them and follow their teachings. But don't follow what they do, because they don't do according to their own teaching.</bt><v n="4" />Dong paksa orang ko pikol iko dong pung atoran agama yang barát. Ma dong sandiri sonde mau tolong orang dong ko iko itu atoran.<bt>They force people to shoulder.carry their religious regulations which are heavy. But they themselves don't want to help people to follow those regulations.</bt><v n="5" />Samua yang dong bekin, dong bekin ko biar orang puji-puji sang dong. Conto ke: ada satu barang yang ada isi Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata yang dong ika di dong pung kapala deng dong pung tangan. Ma dong bekin tamba bésar dong punya, ko biar orang angka-angka sang dong bilang, &lt;We! Dong tu, orang barisi, ó!&gt;<bt>Everything which they do, they do so that people will praise them. For example: there is a thing that contains God's Words which they tie/bind on their heads, and their arms. But they make theirs even bigger, so that people will lift them up (=praise) saying, &lt;We! They there are holy/clean people!&gt; [EXEG: The TB word for “tassles” (Arabic) isn't widely known. Trying to use an explanatory phrase skews the focus, and still comes out too vague. The existing structure clearly sets out the general pattern, followed by a specific example that is introduced as an example. So the point gets through without the details. Understranslated, but the teaching point is not lost.]</bt><note reference="23:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 6:1, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:8, Daftar Sensus 15:38</note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00274C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Orang Yahudi ika Tulisan Barisi di kapala<bt>A Yahudi person tying the Scripture on his head</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Kalo dong maso pi ruma sambayang, ko, dong iko pesta, dong salalu cari tampa dudu yang paling bagus, ko banya orang lia sang dong.<bt>If they enter the worship house, or they go to a feast/party, they always look for a sit which is the best, so many people can see them.</bt><v n="7" />Kalo dong pi pasar, dong ju gila hormat. Dong cari ko orang soya sang dong bilang, &lt;Salamat pagi, bapa guru yang terhormat.&gt;<bt>If they go to the market, they are also crazy for honor. They look for people to bow to them saying &lt;Good morning, Father Teacher who is honoured.&gt;</bt><v n="8" />Ma bosong jang iko dong pung cara tu! Orang sonde bole pange sang bosong bilang, &lt;bapa guru&gt;, tagal bosong pung Guru cuma satu sa. Deng bosong samua ni, basodara.<bt>But you-pl don't follow that way of theirs. People may not call you saying &lt;Father Teacher&gt;, because your Teacher is only just one. And you all here, are reciprocally siblings (= term used to imply same status).</bt><v n="9" />Jang angka-angka nae orang di dunya bilang, &lt;bapa&gt;, tagal bosong pung Bapa di sorga cuma satu sa.<bt>Don't lift.up/praise people in this world saying, &lt;&lt;father&gt;, because your Father in heaven is only just one.</bt><v n="10" />Orang ju sonde bole pange sang bosong bilang, &lt;bos&gt;, tagal bosong pung Bos yang hak parenta sang bosong cuma satu sa, andia Beta ni, yang Tuhan Allah su janji kirim dari dolu tu.<bt>People also may not call you saying &lt;bos&gt;, because your Bos who has say-so/ordering rights over you is only just one, that is Me here the one whom God had promised to send from long ago.</bt><v n="11" />Andia ko Beta bilang bosong sonde bole angka-angka diri sama ke itu orang yang gila hormat dong. Sapa dari bosong yang mau jadi orang bésar, dia musti jadi sama ke jongos ko layani orang laen.<bt>That's why I say you may not lift up yourselfs like those people who are crazy for honour. Whoever of you wants to become a big person, he must become the same as househelp to serve other people.</bt><note reference="23:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 20:26-27, Markus 9:35, 10:43-44, Lukas 22:26</note><v n="12" />Te orang yang angka-angka diri, nanti Tuhan kasi jato sang dia. Ma orang yang bekin diri sama ke orang kici, nanti Tuhan angka nae sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) a person who lift him/her self up, later the Lord will make him/her fall. But the person who make him/her self the same as a small person (=low status), later God will lift him/her up.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang bekin diri jadi orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">Orang yang bekin diri jadi orang nomer satu, nanti Tuhan Allah bekin dia sonde jadi doi lai. Ma orang yang lia dia pung diri sonde ada pung arti apa-apa, nanti Tuhan Allah bekin dia jadi orang nomer satu.</Message></Annotation><note reference="23:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 14:11, 18:14</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus togor bos-bos agama dong, tagal dong omong laen, bekin laen<bt>The Lord Yesus scolds the religious bosses, because they say one thing, and do another</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 12:40; Lukas 11:39-42, 44, 47-52; 20:47)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu, Yesus omong sambung bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh, bosong guru agama deng orang Farisi dong! Dasar bosong tu, orang muka-balakang! Nanti bosong dapa calaka, tagal bosong sonde mau parcaya sang Beta, andia itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji mau kirim datang ni. Deng lebe jahat lai, bosong palang ame orang yang datang mau maso dalam Tuhan pung parenta ko dong jang parcaya sang Beta.<bt>After that Yesus continued speaking saying, &lt;&lt;Heh, [+critical] you religion teachers and Farisi people! You-pl are hypocrites (front-back people)! Later you will get misfortune, because you do not want to believe Me, who is that Person whom God promised to send here. And what's even more evil, you obstruct people who want to come come to enter into God's rule/governing in order that they don't believe in Me. [EXEG: OV had bleached out figure of Kingdom. Now restored.] [Note: UNS suggestion to change this to 'in order that they don't need to believe in Me.' I think I prefer it as it is.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />[Heh, bosong guru agama deng orang Farisi dong! Dasar bosong tu, orang muka-balakang! Nanti bosong dapa calaka, tagal bosong maen putar-balek sang janda dong, ais rampas ame dong pung ruma. Ma di orang banya pung muka, bosong tutu bosong pung jahat tu, deng badiri sambayang lama-lama ko orang bilang bosong pung hati barisi. Ma nanti Tuhan Allah kasi hukum yang paling barát sang bosong.]<bt>[Heh, [+rebuke] you religion teachers and Farisi people! You are hypocrites! Later you will get misfortune, because you repeatedly twist-turn (=decieve) widows, then snatch away their house/s. But in front of many people, you cover over that evil of yours, and stand praying long-long so people say your livers are clean/holy. But later God will give a punishment which is very heavy to you.]</bt><note reference="23:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini ayat 14 sonde ada di tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua.<bt>This verse 14 isn't in the Yunani language writings which are the oldest.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Heh, bosong guru agama deng orang Farisi dong! Dasar bosong tu, orang muka-balakang! Nanti bosong dapa calaka, tagal bosong balayar pi mana-mana, deng nae-turun gunung, cuma mau cari satu orang sa, ko dia maso pi dalam bosong pung partei agama. Ma kalo dia su maso, na, bosong bekin dia pung idop jadi lebe jahat lai, sampe dia dapa hukum di naraka dua kali lebe barát dari bosong.<bt>Heh, [+rebuke] you religion teachers and Farisi people! You are hypocrites! Later you will get misfortune, because you sail all over the place and go up and down mountains only to just find one person, so that he will enter into your religious party. But when/if he has already entered, then you make his life become even more evil, to.the.point that he get a punishment in hell two times heavier than you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Weh! Bosong su jadi buta di hati, ma akurang ko bosong masi mau tunju jalan kasi orang laen lai? Nanti bosong dapa calaka tagal bosong ajar sambarang bilang, &lt;Kalo orang angka janji pake sumpa deng subu Ruma Sambayang Pusat, na, itu orang sonde ta'ika deng dia pung janji tu. Ma kalo dia angka janji pake sumpa deng subu barang mas yang ada dalam itu Ruma Sambayang, na, baru dia ta'ika deng dia pung janji tu.&gt;<bt>Huh! You have become blind in your livers (heartless, unfeeling), but why are you still showing the way for other people? Later you will get misfortune because you teach recklessly saying, &lt;If a person takes up a promise using an oath mentioning the Main Prayer House, then that person is not tied to that promise of his. But if he takes up a promise using an oath mentioning the gold things which are in that Temple, only then is he tied to that promise.&gt;</bt><v n="17" />Bosong ni orang bodo yang buta kanóp! Bosong kira Tuhan anggap barang mas lebe pantíng dari Dia pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat? Sonde! Te itu Ruma yang bekin itu barang jadi barisi!<bt>You here are stupid people who are blind knobs (=idiom, blind to the max)! Do you think the Lord considers gold things more important, that his Main Prayer House? No! Cuz (elaboration) that House is what makes those things become holy/clean!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Bosong ju ajar sambarang bilang, &lt;Kalo orang angka janji pake sumpa deng subu itu meja korban yang ada di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, na, itu orang sonde ta'ika deng dia pung janji tu. Ma kalo dia angka janji pake sumpa deng subu korban yang di atas itu meja, na, baru dia ta'ika deng dia pung janji tu.&gt;<bt>You also teach recklessly saying, &lt;If a person takes up a promise using an oath mentioning that sacrifice table which is in the Main Prayer House, then that person is not tied to that promise of his. But if he takes up a promise using an oath mentioning the sacrifice which is on top of that table, only then is he tied to that promise.&gt;</bt><v n="19" />Bosong ni, su buta batúl-batúl. Su tantu itu meja korban tu, lebe pantíng dari korban yang ada di itu meja pung atas. Te itu meja tu, yang bekin dong pung korban jadi barisi kasi Tuhan Allah.<bt>You here, are really-really blind. Of course that sacrifice table there, is more important that the sacrifice which is on top of that table. Cuz (elaboration) that table there is what makes their sacrifices be/become clean/holy/pure to God. [EXEG: OV went off in a funny direction. “makes it become clean” is reflecting the Gk.]</bt><v n="20" />Tagal itu, kalo orang sumpa deng subu meja korban, na, lebe bae subu itu meja, deng samua yang ada di itu meja pung atas ju.<bt>Because of that, if people oath mentioning the sacrifice table, it's better to mention that table and also everything which is on top of that table.</bt><v n="21" />Deng kalo orang sumpa deng subu Ruma Sambayang Pusat, na, lebe bae subu Ruma Sambayang sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah pung nama. Te Dia yang tenga di situ.<bt>And if people oath mentioning the Main Prayer House, it's better they mention the Prayer House together with God's name, cuz (elaboration) He is the one who lives there.</bt><v n="22" />Deng kalo orang sumpa deng subu sorga, na, itu tu, su sama ke dia subu Tuhan Allah pung korsi parenta sama-sama deng Dia pung nama, te Dia yang dudu pegang parenta di situ.<bt>And if people oath mentioning heaven, that is the same as his mentioning God's ruling chair together with His name, cuz (elaboration) He is the one who sits ruling there.</bt><note reference="23:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 66:1, Mateos 5:34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Heh, bosong guru agama deng orang Farisi dong! Dasar bosong tu, orang muka-balakang! Nanti bosong dapa calaka, tagal bosong talalu pintar itong ko kasi Tuhan satu bagian dari sapulu bagian. Bosong maen ba'itong samua-samua, sampe bosong pung bumbu-bumbu dari kabón, bosong ju itong mati. Conto ke bosong itong alus-alus bosong pung salasi, adas manis, deng jintan. Padahal bosong su lupa buang Tuhan Allah pung atoran yang paling pantíng dong! Te bosong sonde idop lurus. Bosong sonde sayang orang kasian dong. Deng bosong sonde idop tarús-tarús iko Tuhan pung mau. Lebe bae, bosong bekin iko itu samua dolo, baru bosong pi itong bosong pung bumbu-bumbu, yang bosong mau kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Heh, [+rebuke] you religion teachers and Farisi people! You are hypocrites! Later you will get misfortune, because you are too clever counting in order to give the Lord one part of ten. You repeatedly count everything-everything, including your spices from the garden, you also count down to the last detail. For example you count in finest detail your <span class="Italic">(salasi), </span>anise, and cumin. But in reality you have forgotten thrown away that most important regulation/s of God's! Cuz (elaboration) you don't live straight (=are not honest). You don't love poor people. And you don't continually follow the Lord's will. It's better you do all that first, before you go count your spices that you want to give the Lord.</bt><note reference="23:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 27:30</note><v n="24" />Bosong pung hati su buta, ma akurang ko bosong masi mau tunju jalan kasi orang laen lai? Bosong bekin atoran sampe alus-alus ko suru orang laen dong iko, ma Tuhan pung atoran yang paling pantíng tu, bosong sandiri sonde iko. Sama ke bosong pareksa alus-alus ko saring buang lalat kici dari bosong pung aer minum. Ma binatang bésar ke karbó, bosong kodo ame anteru-anteru!<bt>Your livers/insides are blind, but why are you still showing the way for other people? You make regulations in finest detail to order other people to follow, but that/those regulations of the Lord's which are most important, you yourselves don't follow. It's as if you inspect in great detail and filter out a small fly from your drinking water. But a big animal like a water.buffalo, you gulp it down whole! [NOTE: People around here often strain ants out of sugar, molasses, and nira.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Heh, bosong guru agama deng orang Farisi dong! Dasar bosong tu, orang muka-balakang! Nanti bosong dapa calaka, tagal bosong cuci ame bosong pung piring-mangko dong sampe mangkilat, ma itu cuma di bagian luar sa. Padahal dia pung dalam dadolek mati deng kotoran dari bosong pung parampok deng bosong pung balalas.<bt>Heh, [+rebuke] you religion teachers and Farisi people! You are hypocrites! Later you will get misfortune, because you wash your dishes cups until they are shiny white, but that is only just on the outside. But in reality the inside is very filthy with dirt from that stealing of yours and your greediness.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Weh! Orang Farisi buta dong! Cuci lebe dolo bosong pung piring mangko pung bagian dalam! Deng bagitu, dia pung bagian luar ju bisa jadi barisi!<bt>Weh! [+attention, + rebuke] Blind Farisi people! Wash first your dishes cups' inside part. In doing that the outside part can also become clean!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Heh, bosong guru agama deng orang Farisi dong! Dasar bosong tu, orang muka-balakang! Nanti bosong dapa calaka, tagal bosong ni sama ke kubur yang kaná cet puti. Orang dapa lia dia pung luar tu, talalu bagus. Ma dia pung dalam tu, ponu deng orang mati pung tulang, deng samua yang baboo puruk.<bt>Heh, [+rebuke] religion teachers and Farisi people! You are hypocrites! Later you will get misfortune, because you here are the same as a grave which has been painted white. People can see that outside part, is very good. But that inside part, is full of bones of dead people, and everything which smells rotten.</bt><note reference="23:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 23:3</note><v n="28" />Bosong ju sama! Bosong suka bekin diri tingka ke orang barisi. Dari luar orang lia bosong tu, sama ke orang yang hati lurus. Padahal bosong pung dalam hati tu, su ponu deng hal jahat. Te bosong omong laen bekin laen, deng lupa buang Tuhan Allah pung parenta dong.<bt>You are also like that! You like to make yourselves as if you are clean/holy people. From the outside people see you, the same as people who have straight livers. But in reality the inside of your liver there, is full of evil things. Cuz (elaboration) you say one thing, do another, and forget throw away God's commands.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Heh, bosong guru agama deng orang Farisi dong! Dasar bosong tu, orang muka-balakang! Nanti bosong dapa calaka! Bosong bekin kubur bésar-bésar kasi Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong, deng hias bagus-bagus orang bae dong pung kubur.<bt>Heh, [+rebuke] you religion teachers and Farisi people! You are hypocrites! Later you will get misfortune, because you make big grave/s for God's spokespersons, and fancily decorate good people's graves.</bt><v n="30" />Ma bosong bilang, &lt;Andekata botong idop satu jaman deng botong pung nene-moyang dong, tantu botong sonde iko-iko bunu Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong.&gt;<bt>But you say, &lt;Supposing we lived one time/age with our ancestors, surely we would not go along [with them] murdering God's spokespersons.&gt;</bt><v n="31" />Deng bagitu, bosong buka bosong pung kartu sandiri bilang, bosong tu, ju jahat sama ke bosong pung nene-moyang dong.<bt>In doing that, you show your cards yourselves (=reveal your motives), revealing that you there, are also evil the same as your ancestors.</bt><v n="32" />Jadi lebe bae, bosong bekin jahat bagitu sampe abis, iko bosong pung nene-moyang pung sala dong!<bt>So it's better you do evil like that until it's finished, following your ancestors wrongs!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Bosong ni batúl-batúl jahat sama ke ular baracon. Bosong kira Tuhan Allah sonde kasi hukum sang bosong? Jang harap! Tantu Dia lempar buang sang bosong pi dalam api naraka!<bt>You here are really evil the same as poisonous snakes. Do you think God won't punish you? Don't hope (=no such luck!)! Surely He will throw you away into hell fire!</bt><v n="34" />Dengar, é! Nanti Beta kirim kasi bosong Beta pung utusan dong, ko dong ajar deng kasi tunju sang bosong Tuhan pung jalan idop yang batúl. Ma nanti bosong bunu saparu, deng paku bekin mati saparu di kayu palang. Ada ju yang bosong firuk di dalam ruma-ruma sambayang, deng ada yang bosong siksa sampe dong balari dari satu kota pi kota laen.<bt>Listen, é! Later I will sent you My envoys, so they teach and show you the Lord's life path which is correct. But later you will kill some of them, and nail kill some of them on crossed sticks. There are also some you will whip/slap in the worship houses, and those you will torture until they run from one city to the next.</bt><v n="35" />Dolu-dolu bosong pung nene-moyang bunu sang Habel. Padahal dia tu, orang yang pung hati lurus. Bosong pung nene-moyang maen bunu tarús-tarús orang hati lurus dong dari satu turunan pi turunan laen. Sampe deng Sakaria, andia Barakia pung ana. Dong bunu sang dia di Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal deka deng meja korban. Tagal bosong iko bosong pung nene-moyang pung jahat tu, andia ko bosong musti tanggong itu orang hati lurus dong pung dara samua.<bt>Long ago your ancestors killed Habel. But in actual fact, he was a person whose liver is straight (=just). Your ancestors repeatedly murdered over and over straight/righteous people from one generation to the next generation. Until Sakaria, who was Barakia's child. They murdered him in the yard of the Main Worship House near the sacrifice table. Because you follow that evil of your ancestors, that's why you must carry all of those straight livered people's (=righteous people's) blood.</bt><v n="36" />Memang batúl! Te bosong yang ada sakarang ni, nanti kaná hukum, tagal ini hal-hal jahat dong yang bosong pung nene-moyang su bekin dari dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's true! Cuz (elaboration) you who are here now, later will be punished because of all those evil things which your ancestors did long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jato kasian sang orang Yerusalem dong<bt>Lord Yesus feels pity on Yerusalem people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 13:34-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />&lt;&lt;We, orang Yerusalem dong! Bosong yang maen bunu Tuhan Allah pung jubir dong, deng lempar bekin mati utusan yang mau datang tolong sang bosong. Beta maen buju sang bosong ulang kali ko datang sang Beta, sama ke ayam mai yang mau tutu ame dia pung ana dong di bawa dia pung sayap. Ma bosong sonde mau.<bt>&lt;&lt;We, [+get attention] people of Yerusalem! You-pl are the ones who repeatedly murders God's spokespersons, and throws [stones] killing envoys who want to come help you. I repeatedly try to persuade you over and over to come to Me, like a mother chicken who wants to cover over her children under her wings. But you don't want to.</bt><v n="38" />Tagal itu, Tuhan su sonde toe lai deng bosong pung ruma. Ais beso-lusa, te dia su kosong.<bt>Because of that, the Lord isn't concerned anymore about your-pl house. Then tomorrow and the next day (=near future), it will be empty.</bt><v n="39" />Dengar bae-bae, é! Te bosong sonde akan lia sang Beta lai, sampe dia pung waktu bosong mangaku bilang, &lt;Botong minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi berkat sang ini Orang, tagal Tuhan yang utus sang Dia.&gt; Bosong mangaku bagitu, baru bosong dapa lia sang Beta lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Listen well! Cuz (elaboration) you-pl won't see Me anymore, until the time when you acknowledge saying, &lt;We-exc request God to give blessing to this Person, because the Lord is the one who commissioned Him.&gt; You will acknowledge/confess like that [first], before you will see Me again.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung rubu<bt>The Lord Yesus tells ahead of time about the Main Prayer House's destruction</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 13:1-2; Lukas 21:5-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="24" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus mau jalan kasi tenga Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Waktu Dia kaluar, Dia pung ana bua dong datang kasi tunju itu Ruma Sambayang pung bagus.<bt>After that, Yesus wanted to go leaving the Main Prayer House. When He went out, His underlings came showing that Prayer House's beauty.</bt><v n="2" />Ma Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Ruma memang bagus! Ma dengar, é! Sonde lama lai, dong kasi rubu abis ini batu-batu samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>But He answered saying, &lt;&lt;This House is really beautiful! But listen, é! Not much longer (=soon), they will completely knock over all these stones.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau bilang, nanti Dia pung ana bua dong dapa sangsara<bt>The Lord Yesus tells that, later His underlings will get suffering</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 13:3-13; Lukas 21:7-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais Yesus jalan pi dudu di gunung Saitun. Ju Dia pung ana bua datang ko dong ba'omong sandiri deng Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Coba kasi tau ulang Bapa pung omong tadi tu. Kira-kira Bapa pung datang kambali tu, kapan? Deng dia pung tanda-tanda tu, kira-kira karmana? Karmana ju deng dunya pung kiamat?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus went to sit at Saitun mountain. Then His underlings came in order for them to converse alone with Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Please tell again that talking of Father's earlier. Approximately when will Father's (=your) return happen? And its signs, are approximately like what? How also with the end of the world?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Jaga diri bae-bae, ó! Ko bosong jang kaná tipu.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Watchout for yourselves really well! So you don't get decieved.</bt><v n="5" />Te nanti ada macam-macam orang yang datang puku dada bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Kristus, Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji dari dolu.&gt; Deng bagitu, dong tipu banya orang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later there will be all kinds of people who come beating their chest (=proudly) saying, &lt;I here, am Kristus, the Person whom God promised from long ago.&gt; In doing that, they will decieve many people.</bt><v n="6" />Kalo bosong lia orang baparáng, ko, bosong dengar kabar bilang, ada paráng di mana-mana, na, bosong sonde usa taku. Te hal macam bagitu tu, musti jadi. Ma hari kiamat balóm sampe.<bt>If you see people warring, or you hear new that there is war all over the place, na, you don't need to be afraid. Cuz (elaboration) thing such as those, must happen. But the end of the world has not yet arrived.</bt><v n="7" />Nanti satu suku baparáng lawan suku laen. Satu negara baparáng lawan negara laen. Ada tana goyang di mana-mana. Deng musim lapar ju hebat mati pung!<bt>Later one ethnic group will war opposing another ethnic group. One country will war opposing another country. There will be earthquakes all over the place. And also very severe hungry seasons (=famines)!</bt><v n="8" />Ma samua tu, baru tanda partama yang kasi tau bilang, hari kiamat pung waktu su deka-deka datang. Itu sama ke parampuan yang baru mulai rasa saki, tagal dia pung waktu barana su deka-deka datang.<bt>But all that, is just the first sign which tells that, the end of the world is near. That is the same as a woman who just begins to feel pain/sick, because her time for giving birth has come near.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Jadi bosong musti jaga diri bae-bae, é! Te nanti dong siksa deng bunu bekin mati sang bosong. Deng orang dari samua bangsa nanti binci mati sang bosong, tagal bosong iko sang Beta.<bt>So (consequently), you must watch yourselves well! Cuz (elaboration) later they will torture you, and murder kill you. And people from all nations will extremely hate you, because you follow Me.</bt><note reference="24:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:22</note><v n="10" />Itu waktu, banya orang bale balakang deng sonde mau parcaya sang Beta lai. Dong babinci, deng bajual satu deng satu.<bt>At that time, many people will turn their backs and not want to believe in Me anymore. They will hate each other, and sell (=betray) each other.</bt><v n="11" />Nanti ada tukang tipu bilang dong tu, Tuhan pung jubir. Deng banya orang parcaya sang dong.<bt>Later there will be habitual decievers who say they are the Lord's spokespersons. And many people will believe them.</bt><v n="12" />Nanti orang pung jahat dong tamba lama tamba banya, sampe orang su sonde basayang satu deng satu lai.<bt>Later people's evilness will increasingly get worse, until people do not love each other anymore.</bt><v n="13" />Ma orang yang batahan tarús sampe mati, pasti Tuhan Allah kasi salamat sang dia.<bt>But the person who endures continually until death, God will certainly save him/her.</bt><note reference="24:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:22</note><v n="14" />Te orang musti kasi tasiar Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae sampe di dunya pung huk-huk, ko biar samua orang bisa dapa tau Tuhan pung jalan idop yang batúl. Ais itu, baru hari kiamat datang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) people must go spread God's Good News, to the world's corners/far reaches, so that all people can know the Lord's live path which is true. After that, then the end of the world will come.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau bilang, satu orang jahat tukang bekin ancor nanti datang<bt>The Lord Yesus tells that an evil person a habitual destroyer, will come</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 13:14-23; Lukas 21:20-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Yesus omong tarús bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung jubir Daniel su tulis so'al satu orang yang jahat mati pung. Nanti dia datang maso pi badiri di tampa pamali di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Deng bagitu, dia bekin noju itu tampa. Andia ko Tuhan Allah bale balakang kasi tenga itu tampa. Naa! Kalo bosong su lia bagitu, ati-ati, ó! (Sapa yang baca ini tulisan ni, musti mangarti bae-bae!)<bt>Yesus continued speaking saying, &lt;&lt;God's spokesperson Daniel has written about a person who is very evil. Later he will come enter and go stand in the taboo place in God's Main Prayer House. In doing so, he will make that place repugnant. That's why God will turn his back and leave that place. So! If you see like that, becareful! (Whoever reads this writing here, must understand carefully!)</bt><note reference="24:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 9:27, 11:31, 12:11</note><v n="16" />Te itu jadi tanda bilang, hari-hari susa su ada di muka pintu. Kalo su lia bagitu, orang di propinsi Yudea bangun lari pi gunung suda.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that becomes a sign saying, suffering days are in front of the door. If/When [you] see like that, people in Yudea province must get up and run to the mountains.</bt><v n="17" />Kalo ada yang su kaluar dari ruma, jang pulang pi ame barang lai. Lari capát-capát su, ko biar jang kaná calaka.<bt>If there is a person who has gone out of the house, don't go home to get things anymore. Just run fast, to not get misfortune.</bt><v n="18" />Orang yang ada di kabón, jang kambali ko ame kaen panas lai. Lari tarús su!<bt>A person who is in the garden, don't go back to get warm cloth (=blanket) anymore. Run on!</bt><note reference="24:17-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 17:31</note><v n="19" />Yang paling kasian, andia parampuan yang ada dudu parú, deng mama-mama yang ada kasi susu ana mea. Te dong sonde bisa lari capát na.<bt>The ones who most to be pitied, are the women who are pregnant, and the mothers who are nursing red children (=newborns). Cuz (elaboration) obviously they can't run fast.</bt><v n="20" />Jadi lebe bae bosong sambayang ko minta itu calaka jang jato kaná deng musim ujan, ko, jato kaná deng hari barenti karjá.<bt>So (consequently) it's better you pray and request that that calamity doesn't happen during the rainy season, or happen on a day of stopping work.</bt><v n="21" />Te itu hari talalu susa mau mati! Mulai dari Tuhan Allah bekin ini dunya sampe sakarang, orang balóm parná lia susa bésar macam bagitu. Deng nanti orang ju sonde lia ulang lai susa macam bagitu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) those days will be exceedingly extremely difficult! Beginning from when God make this world until now, people have not yet seen difficulty/trouble as big as that. And later people also will not see again difficulty like that.</bt><note reference="24:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 12:1, Dunya Model Baru 7:14</note><v n="22" />Ma bosong ontong bésar, te Tuhan Allah kasi pende itu hari. Kalo sonde, na, sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa batahan idop. Ma tagal Tuhan Allah sayang Dia pung orang yang Dia su pili dong, andia ko Dia kasi pende itu hari-hari susa dong.<bt>But you are very fortunate, cuz (elaboration) God shortened those days. If not, there would not be even one person who could endure living. But because God loves His people whom He has chosen, that's why He shortened those difficult days.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Nanti kalo itu hari su sampe, bosong dengar orang bilang, &lt;Lia dolo! Kristus ada di sini!&gt; Deng orang laen bilang, &lt;Kristus ada di sana!&gt; Ma bosong jang parcaya, é!<bt>Later if those days have arrived, you will hear people saying, &lt;Look! Kristus is here!&gt; And other people saying, &lt;Kristus is there!&gt; But you don't believe it!</bt><v n="24" />Te nanti ada orang kaluar ko puku-puku dada bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Kristus!&gt; Deng yang laen lai bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Tuhan Allah pung jubir.&gt; Nanti dong bekin tanda heran macam-macam pake kuasa galáp ko putar-balek orang. Dong coba-coba ko Tuhan Allah pung orang dong ju kaná tipu!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later there will be people coming out beating their chests saying, &lt;&lt;I here, am Kristus!&gt; And yet others who say, &lt;I here, am God's spokesperson.&gt; later they do all kinds of miracles using powers of darkness in order to decieve people. They will try (on-going, or unsuccessfully) so God's people also get decieved! [EXEG: UNS worldview-driven responses assumed that miracles are always performed using God's power. ‘powers of darkness (always associated with evil, but broader than evil spirits)’. Some RLs will have to go more specific and say ‘evil spirits’. Support from AG and Morris.]</bt><v n="25" />Jadi bosong musti jaga diri bae-bae, é! Itu hari-hari susa dong balóm sampe, ma Beta su kasi inga memang sang bosong, ó!<bt>So you must watch yourselves carefully! Those difficult days have not yet arrived, but I have reminded you beforehand!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Kalo orang kasi tau sang bosong bilang, &lt;Kristus su ada di tana lapang sana, é!&gt; na, bosong jang pi sana. Deng kalo ada yang bilang, &lt;Kristus su ada di dalam ini ruma!&gt;, na, bosong jang parcaya deng dong pung putar-balek tu.<bt>If people tell you saying, ‘Kristus is at the open field over there!’, well you don't go there. And if there are those who say, ‘Kristus is in this house!’, well you don't believe that deceit of theirs.</bt><v n="27" />Te Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Nanti kalo Beta datang kambali di ini dunya, samua orang dapa lia sang Beta, sama ke orang lia kilat yang bacaya dari sablá matahari nae pi sablá matahari turun.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I here, am the Ideal/Prototypical Human. Later when i com back to this world, all people will see Me, just like people see lightning which shines from the east side to the west side.</bt><note reference="24:26-27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 17:23-24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Kalo Beta datang kambali, nanti bosong tau Beta ada di mana. Sama ke orang tau bilang, kalo ada burung tukang makan bangke bakumpul di satu tampa, na, di situ pasti ada bangke.&gt;&gt;<bt>If/When I come back, later you will know where I am. Just like people know that, if there are corpse-eating birds gathered in one place, then there is certainly a carcass/corpse there.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with your wording in Luke 17:37.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="burung makan bangke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">burung makan bangke</Message></Annotation><note reference="24:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 17:37</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau Dia pung datang kambali<bt>The Lord Yesus tells about His coming back</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 13:24-27; Lukas 21:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais Yesus sambung lai, ko kasi tau Dia pung ana bua bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo itu hari-hari susa dong su abis,<bt>Then Yesus connected/ continued again, to tell his underlings saying, &lt;&lt;If/when those difficult days are finished,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Nanti matahari jadi galáp,<bt>&lt;The sun will become dark,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bulan ju su sonde taráng lai.<bt>the moon also will no longer shine.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Bintang-bintang bajato dari langit,<bt>Stars will fall from the sky,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng samua kuasa di langit jadi harba-biruk.&gt;<bt>and all powers in the sky will become chaotic.&gt;</bt><note reference="24:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 13:10, 34:4, Yeskial 32:7, Yoel 2:10, 31, 3:15, Dunya Model Baru 6:12-13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais itu, ju samua orang dapa lia tanda di langit bilang, Manusia Tulen ada mau datang kambali. Lia bagitu ju, samua bangsa di dunya jadi taku sampe dong manangis. Te nanti Beta turun datang deng awan, baru dong lia Beta pung kuasa deng Beta pung hebat samua.<bt>After that then all people will see sign/s in the sky saying, the Ideal Human is going to/about to come back. Seeing like that, then all ethnic groups on earth will become afraid to the point that they cry. Cuz (elaboration) later [when] I will come down by/with a cloud, then they will see all My power and My amazingness. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><note reference="24:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13, Sakaria 12:10-14, Dunya Model Baru 1:7</note><v n="31" />Ais Beta pake bunyi tarompet yang karás ko parenta Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga pi kumpul samua orang yang Beta su pili ame dari dunya pung ujung-ujung, dari matahari nae sampe matahari turun; dari utara sampe salatan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I will use the loud sound of a trupet to command God's underlings from heaven, (to) go gather all the people whom I have chosen from the world's ends, from where the sun goes up (=east) to where the sun goes down (=west); from the north to the south.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hari-hari susa jadi tanda Tuhan Yesus pung datang [\s2]<bt>The difficult days are a sign of Lord Yesus' coming [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 13:28-31; Lukas 21:29-33)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />&lt;&lt;Beta ame conto ke pohon. Kalo dia pung daon mulai kuning, itu tanda bilang, musim panas su deka-deka datang.<bt>&lt;&lt;I take a sample/example like a tree. If/When it's leaves begin to yellow, that is sign that the hot season is almost come.</bt><v n="33" />Bagitu ju, kalo bosong su lia hari-hari susa datang, sama ke yang Beta su kasi tau tadi tu, itu tanda bilang, Beta su deka-deka datang.<bt>Like that also, when you see the difficult days come, like I told you earlier there, that is a sign saying I am almost coming. [EXEG: Gk ambiguous ‘he’ vs. ‘it’; we go with ‘He’ following NRSV and NLT, which flows on from the previous section.]</bt><v n="34" />Sakarang, dengar bae-bae! Dari samua orang yang idop sakarang ni, nanti ada yang balóm mati, te itu hari-hari susa dong su datang.<bt>Now, listen carefully! From all the people who live nowadays, later there will be those who have not yet died, when those difficult days have come.</bt><v n="35" />Biar langit deng bumi su ilang buang, ma Beta pung kata-kata ni batahan sonde abis-abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even if the sky and the earth disappear away, but these words of Mine with endure without ever stopping.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau bilang, Dia pung waktu datang tu, rahasia [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus tells that, that time of His coming is a secret [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 13:32-37; Lukas 17:26-30, 34-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />&lt;&lt;Sonde ada orang yang tau kapan Beta datang kambali. Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga, ju sonde tau. Beta sandiri, ju sonde tau. Cuma Beta pung Bapa sa yang tau.<bt>There is no person who know when I come again. God's underlings in heaven, also don't know. I myself, also don't know. Only just My Father who knows.</bt><v n="37" />Te Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Nanti kalo Beta datang kambali, itu sama ke dolu-dolu waktu Noh masi idop.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I here, am the Ideal/Prototypical Human. Later when I come again, that will be the same as long ago when Noh was still alive.</bt><note reference="24:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 6:5-8</note><v n="38" />Itu banjer bésar balóm datang, te orang dong makan-minum ena-ena, deng bakawin rame-rame sama ke biasa. Dong bekin bagitu tarús-tarús, sampe Noh maso pi dalam itu kapal bésar.<bt>That big flood had not yet come, and the people were eating drinking well, and busily marrying each other as normal. They did like that over and over until Noh entered into that big boat.</bt><v n="39" />Ma waktu banjer datang sapu bawa sang dong, baru dong pung mata tabuka, ko dong dapa tau apa yang su jadi tu. Bagitu ju deng Beta pung datang nanti.<bt>But when the flood came sweeping taking them, then their eyes were opened so they knew/understood what had happened there. My coming later will be like that also.</bt><note reference="24:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 7:6-24</note><v n="40" />Itu waktu, kalo dua orang ada karjá kabón, takuju sa, te Tuhan Allah angka bawa yang satu, ma yang laen Dia kasi tenga.<bt>At that time, if two people are working in the garden, suddenly, God will lift up take the one, but the other He will leave.</bt><v n="41" />Kalo dua parampuan ada tumbu padi, takuju sa, te Tuhan Allah angka bawa yang satu, ma yang laen Dia kasi tenga.<bt>If two women are pounding padi, suddenly, God will lift up take the one, but the other He will leave.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Tagal itu, bosong ju musti bajaga siang-malam, te bosong sonde tau kapan bosong pung Bos datang kambali.<bt>Because of that, you-pl must watch day-night, cuz (elaboration) you don't know when your Bos will come back.</bt><v n="43" />Pikir bae-bae, é! Kalo tuan ruma tau sabantar malam pancuri mau datang, su tantu dia bajaga tarús, ko biar pancuri jang maso dalam dia pung ruma.<bt>Think well, é! If a house master knows that later tonight a robber will come, surely he will watch the whole time, so that that robber doesn't come into his house.</bt><v n="44" />Tagal itu, bosong ju musti basiap-siap. Te Beta pung datang kambali tu, takuju-takuju sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that you must be ready/prepared. Cuz (elaboration) that coming back of Mine, will be sudden/unexpected.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="24:43-44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:39-40</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar bilang, tukang suru-suru musti iko bos pung mau tarús<bt>The Lord Yesus teaches that the servant must continually follow/obey the bos's will</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 12:41-48)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ais Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti jadi sama ke tukang suru-suru yang iko tarús-tarús dia pung bos pung mau. Te kalo bos mau jalan pi tampa jao, dia angka tukang suru-suru macam bagitu, ko urus dia pung isi ruma pung makan-minum samua.<bt>Then Yesus spoke further saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl must become like a servant who continually follows/obeys his bos's will. Cuz (elaboration) if the bos want to go to a faraway place, he lifts/appoints a servant like that, to manage all his household's food-drink.</bt><v n="46" />Kalo bos pulang deng dapa lia dia pung tukang suru-suru ada karjá bae-bae, pasti dia sanáng deng itu orang.<bt>If the bos comes home and sees his servant is working well, surely he is happy with that person.</bt><v n="47" />Parcaya sang Beta, te nanti itu bos kasi itu tukang suru-suru kuasa ko urus dia pung harta-milik samua.<bt>Believe Me, cuz (elaboration) later that bos will give that servant authority to manage all of his possessions.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ma kalo itu tukang suru-suru jahat, dia pasti omong dalam dia pung hati bilang,<bt>But if that servant is evil, surely he will speak in his liver saying,</bt><v n="49" />&lt;Bae su! Bos su jalan bagini, sapa pi tau kapan dia kambali, ó!&gt; Pikir bagitu ju, dia mulai papoko dia pung tamán orang karjá yang laen dong. Deng dia dudu makan-minum ena-ena sama-sama deng pamabok dong.<bt>&lt;Great, the bos has gone far away! Surely it's still a long time before he returns, ó.&gt; Thinking like that, then he begins to beat up the other servants. And he sits eating-drinking luxuriously together with drunkards.</bt><v n="50" />Ma sonde sangka-sangka, te takuju sa, dia pung bos pulang.<bt>But unexpectedly, suddenly, his bos comes home.</bt><v n="51" />Ju itu bos siksa ukur kuat sang dia, ais lempar buang sang dia pi luar, ko dia tenga sama-sama deng orang muka-balakang dong. Di itu tampa, dong samua manangis makarereu, tagal dong ada sangsara mati pung.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that bos tortures a heavy measurement to him, then throws him away outside, so he stays together with the hypocrites. In that place, they all cry wailing because they are suffering greatly.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al nona-nona yang tunggu ko sambut baroit laki-laki<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about young.girls who wait to greet a bridegroom</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="25" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju Yesus sambung Dia pung omong so'al Tuhan Allah pung parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti basiap-siap ko sambut Beta pung datang kambali, sama ke ini umpama ni. Bagini: satu kali, ada nona sapulu orang yang kaluar malam deng bawa dong pung lampu te'oek, ko pi sambut baroit laki-laki di dong pung tamán pung ruma.<bt>Afterwards then Yesus connected/continued his speaking about God's kingdom/rule saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl must be prepared to meet My coming back, the same as in this example here. Like this: one time, there were ten girls who went out at night bringing their <span class="Italic">te'oek</span> lamps, to go greet a bridegroom at their friend's house. [EXEG: figure of Kingdom restored in quote margin. Aspect of kingdom to be compared here: CONNOT, Crofts, France, TRT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) dia -- Dia in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) dia -- Dia in 1st sentence</Message></Annotation><note reference="25:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:35</note><v n="2" />Ma dari dong sapulu orang tu, ada lima yang bodo, deng lima yang pintar.<bt>But from those ten people there, there were five who were stupid, and five who were smart.</bt><v n="3" />Lima yang bodo lupa bawa minya lebe.<bt>The five who were stupid, forgot to bring extra oil.</bt><v n="4" />Ma lima yang pintar su bawa memang.<bt>But the five who were smart, had brought it beforehand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Sampe di itu ruma, itu baroit laki-laki balóm datang-datang ju. Lama-lama itu nona dong manganto kode, ju dong tatidor sonu.<bt>Arriving at that house, that bridegroom had not come yet (implies he was late or something). Eventually those girls monkey sleepy (=drowsy), and they fell soundly asleep.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tau-tau te dia pung tenga malam, ju dong dengar orang batarea bilang, &lt;Woi! Baroit su datang, ó! Mari kotong pi sambut sang dia su!&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Unexpectedly in the middle of the night, then they heard people yelling saying, &lt;Woi! [+should have known better] The bridegroom has come! Let's go greet/meet him!&gt;</bt><v n="7" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu nona dong bangun rame-rame. Ais dong pi siap-siap dong pung lampu te'oek.<bt>Hearing like that, then those girls got up busily. Then they prepared they te'oek lamps.</bt><v n="8" />Ma itu nona bodo dong omong deng dong pung tamán bilang, &lt;We, tamán dong! Tolong bagi minya sadiki kasi botong doo, te botong pung lampu su amper mati ni!&gt;<bt>But those stupid girls spoke to their friends saying, &lt;We, [+get attention] friends! Please divide/give a little oil to us, cuz (elaboration) our lamps are almost dead here!&gt;</bt><v n="9" />Ma itu nona yang pintar dong manyao bilang, &lt;Awe'! Jang mara, ma sonde bisa, ó. Te botong pung minya ni sonde cukup kasi kotong samua! Lebe bae bosong pi béli minya di kios sa.&gt;<bt>But those smart girls replied saying, &lt;Awe'! Don't get angry (=sorry) but can't do. Cuz (elaboration) our oil here is not enough for all of us! It's better if you just go buy oil at a stall/store.&gt;</bt><v n="10" />Ju dong pi béli minya. Ma waktu dong ada kaluar, itu baroit su sampe. Ais, itu nona yang pintar dong iko maso pi dalam tampa pesta, sama-sama deng baroit deng tamu samua. Dong samua maso di dalam ruma, ju orang tutu pintu.<bt>Then they went to buy oil. But when they were out, that bridegroom arrived. Then, those girls who were smart followed entering into the feast/party place, together with the bride(not specified male or female-implies both) and all the guests. They all entered into the house, then a person shut the door.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais, itu nona yang bodo dong ju datang. Dong batarea noki-noki bilang, &lt;Bos! Bos, é! Tolong buka pintu doo!&gt;<bt>Then those stupid girls also came. They yelled pleading saying, &lt;Bos! Bos, é! Please open the door!&gt;</bt><v n="12" />Ma dia manyao bilang, &lt;Weh, sonde bisa! Te beta sonde kanál sang bosong.&gt;<bt>But that father answered saying, &lt;Weh, [+objection] can't do. Cuz (elaboration) I don't know you!&gt;</bt><note reference="25:11-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 13:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tagal itu, bosong ju musti siap-siap ko bajaga tarús, te bosong ju sonde tau Beta pung datang kaná hari apa, ko jam barapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, you must be prepared and watch continually, cuz (elaboration) you also do not know what day or what hour is My coming.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al tukang suru-suru yang urus bos pung doi<bt>The Lord Yesus gives an example about the servant/slave/s who manage the bos' money</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 19:11-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais Yesus sambung satu umpama lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Beta su kasi tenga sang bosong, na, bosong musti karjá bae-bae kasi Beta, sama ke ini umpama ni. Bagini: ada satu bos mau pi tampa jao. Waktu dia su siap mau jalan, dia pange dia pung tukang suru-suru dong, ais dia parenta sang dong bilang, &lt;Bosong pake ini doi jadi modal. Nanti kalo beta pulang, bosong musti lapor sang beta, bosong su ontong barapa.&gt;<bt>Then Yesus added another example saying, &lt;&lt;If/When I have left you, you must work hard for Me, the same as this example here. Like.this: there was a bos wanting to go to a far place. When he was ready to go, he called his servant/slaves, then he ordered them saying, &lt;You use this money as (financial) capital. Later when I come home, you must report to me how much you have gained.&gt;</bt><v n="15" />Ais dia kasi dia pung tukang suru-suru partama, doi mas lima saku,<bt>Then he gave his first servant/slave five bags of money, [EXEG: See LN, BAGD, NRSV note for value. Follows NLT text.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added /mas/ and note"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) added /mas/ and note</Message></Annotation><note reference="25:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, lima τάλαντον (<span class="Italic">talanton</span>). Satu <span class="Italic">talanton </span>tu, sama ke satu tukang pung gaji 15 taon. Jadi lima <span class="Italic">talanton </span>tu, andia gaji 75 taon.<bt>The Yunani language here says, five τάλαντον (<span class="Italic">talanton</span>). One of those <span class="Italic">talanton, </span>is equal to a craftsman's wages for 15 years. So (consequently) five <span class="Italic">talanton, </span>is 75 years of wages.</bt></note>ko dia kasi babunga itu doi. Tarús dia kasi tukang suru-suru nomer dua, doi dua saku, deng tukang suru-suru nomer tiga, doi satu saku, iko dong satu-satu pung mampu. Ais ju dia barangkat pi jao.<bt>in order for him to make a yield/gain on that money. Next, he gave servant/slave number tow two sacks, and servant/slave number three one sack, according to each one's ability. Afterwards then he left to go far.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Tarima ame itu doi, ju itu tukang suru-suru partama kaluar memang ko pi badagang. Sonde lama, te dia su dapa ontong doi lima saku lai.<bt>Accepting that money, then that first servant/slave went our straight away to go trade. Not long, he had gained five sacks more of money.</bt><v n="17" />Bagitu ju deng tukang suru-suru nomer dua. Dia dapa ontong doi dua saku lai.<bt>Like that also with servant/slave number two. He gained two more sacks of money.</bt><v n="18" />Ma tukang suru-suru nomer tiga yang tarima doi satu saku tu, dia pi gali lobang di tana, ko sambunyi dia pung bos pung doi tu.<bt>But servant/slave number three who received that one sack of money, he went to dig a hole in the ground, to hide that money of his bos.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Lama-lama ju, baru itu bos datang. Ais dia kumpul dia pung tukang suru-suru ko mulai pareksa dia pung doi yang dong su urus tu.<bt>After a long time, that bos came. Then he gathered his servant/slaves to begin to examine his money which they had managed there.</bt><v n="20" />Itu tukang suru-suru partama maso deng sarakan doi sapulu saku, ju bilang, &lt;Ini bos pung doi. Tempo hari bos su kasi beta doi lima saku. Ma sakarang, beta su dapa ontong lima saku lai.&gt;<bt>That first servant/slave entered and handed over ten sacks of money saying, &lt;Here is bos' money. Before bos gave me five sacks of money. But now, I have gained five more sacks.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Dengar bagitu ju, itu bos sanáng. Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;Bagus! Lu ni, tukang suru-suru yang bae. Lu su karjá rajin, deng lu su iko tarús-tarús beta pung parenta, biar beta sonde ada di sini. Tagal lu su bisa urus hal kici bagini, nanti beta angka sang lu ko urus hal yang lebe bésar lai. Nanti beta bekin pesta ko kotong samua sanáng rame-rame.&gt;<bt>Hearing like that then, that bos was happy. He told saying, &lt;Great! You here are an servant/slave who is good. You have worked hard and you have followed continually my commands, even though I wasn't here. Because you can manage small things like this, later I will appoint you to manage things which are even bigger. Later I will make a feast so we-inc can all be happy festively.&gt; [EXEG: “small matters” here is understatement.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais, itu tukang suru-suru nomer dua datang sarakan sang dia pung bos doi ampa saku, deng bilang, &lt;Bos! Dolu bos sarakan kasi beta, doi dua saku. Lia sa, te beta su dapa ontong doi dua saku lai.&gt;<bt>Then, that number two servant/slave came and handed over his bos' four sacks of money and said, &lt;Bos! Previously bos (=you) handed me, two sacks of money. Now look, cuz (elaboration) I have gained two more sacks.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Itu bos ju sanáng. Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;Bagus! Lu ni, ju tukang suru-suru yang bae. Lu su karjá rajin, deng lu su iko tarús-tarús beta pung parenta, biar beta sonde ada di sini. Tagal lu su bisa urus hal kici bagini, nanti beta angka sang lu ko urus hal yang lebe bésar lai. Nanti beta bekin pesta ko kotong samua sanáng rame-rame.&gt;<bt>That bos was also happy. He told saying, &lt;Great! You here are an servant/slave who is good. You have worked hard and you have followed continually my commands, even though I wasn't here. Because you can manage small things like this, later I will appoint you to manage things which are even bigger. Later I will make a feast so we-inc can all be happy festively.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais, itu tukang suru-suru nomer tiga datang. Ju dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;Bos! Beta tau bos ni orang hati karás. Te bos ame apa yang orang laen bekin, deng ketu ame apa yang orang laen tanam.<bt>Then that number three servant/slave came. Then he told saying, &lt;Bos! I know bos (=you) here are a person with a hard liver. Cuz (elaboration) bos take that which other people do, and picks that which other people plant.</bt><v n="25" />Beta taku, jang sampe ini doi dong ilang buang, ais bos hukum sang beta. Andia ko beta sambunyi bae-bae sang dia. Ini bos! Ame pulang su, te bos pung doi satu saku ni ada aman-aman sa!&gt;<bt>I was afraid lest this money disappear, then bos would punish me. That's why I hid it carefully. Here it is bos! Take it back, cuz (elaboration) bos' one sack of money here is safe-safe (=safe and sound).&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dengar bagitu ju, itu bos masparak sang dia bilang, &lt;Lu ni tukang suru-suru jahat deng pamokol mati! Kalo lu su tau bilang, beta ame apa yang orang laen bekin, deng ketu ame apa yang orang laen tanam,<bt>Hearing like that then that bos got angry and he said, &lt;You here are a evil servant/slave and extremely lazy!~ If you know that I take that which other people do, and pick that which other people plant,</bt><v n="27" />akurang ko lu sonde pi simpan beta pung doi di bank sa? Ko biar beta pulang, na, beta bisa dapa dia pung bunga, biar sadiki, ju bae!&gt;<bt>why did you not just go save my money in the bank? So when I came home, I could get it's interest, even a little bit, would be good!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais, itu bos suru dia pung orang suru-suru laen bilang, &lt;Ame itu doi dari dia, ko sarakan kasi itu tukang suru-suru yang su dapa ontong doi lima saku tu.<bt>Then that bos ordered his other servant/slaves saying, &lt;Take that money from him, and give it to the servant/slave who gained those five sacks of money.</bt><v n="29" />Te orang yang urus bae-bae apa yang dia su pegang, nanti dia dapa tamba banya lai. Ma orang yang sonde mau urus apa yang dia su pegang tu, nanti dong ame itu samua dari dia.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) a person who manages well what s/he already holds, later s/he will get even more again. But a person who does not manage what s/he already has there, later they will take that all from him/her. [EXEG: CEV 'everything' as implication of 'even what he has'.]</bt><note reference="25:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 13:12, Markus 4:25, Lukas 8:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Tangkap ame ini tukang suru-suru yang sonde ada pung guna apa-apa ni. Hela raroso ko angka buang sang dia pi luar. Kasi tenga ko dia manangis makarereu deng sangsara di tampa galáp sana!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Capture this servant/slave who does not have any use here. Pull drag and pick him up throw him away outside. Leave him so he crys wailing and suffers in that dark place over there!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="25:14-30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 19:11-27, Mateos 8:12, 22:13, Lukas 13:28</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau so'al hari kiamat, waktu Dia mau putus samua orang pung parkara<bt>The Lord Yesus tells aboaut the end of the world when He will decide all people's cases/litigations</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais ju Yesus omong tarús bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, nanti turun datang kambali pake Beta pung Bapa pung kuasa yang hebat, sama-sama deng Dia pung ana bua dari sorga. Ais Beta dudu di atas Beta pung korsi parenta yang paling hebat, ko pareksa samua orang pung idop.<bt>Afterwards then Yesus spoke on saying, &lt;&lt;I, the Ideal/Prototypical Human here, later will come back down using My Father's power which is great, together with His underlings from heaven. Then I will sit on My ruling chair which is very great in order to examine all people's lives. [EXEG: Gk: glory here x2]</bt><note reference="25:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:27, 19:28</note><v n="32" />Nanti samua orang yang parná idop di dunya, datang mangada sang Beta. Ais Beta kasi pisa sang dong, sama ke gambala kasi pisa domba dari kambing, ko jadi dua kumpul.<bt>Later all the people who ever lived on earth, will come face Me. Then I will separate them, like a shepherd separates sheep from goats, to become two groups.</bt><v n="33" />Orang-orang yang idop iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, Beta taro di Beta pung sablá kanan. Ma yang sonde dong, Beta taro di sablá kiri.<bt>People who live according to God's will, I will put on My right side. But those others, I will put on the left side.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) changed do to live"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) changed do to live in 1st sentence</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Itu waktu, Beta pegang parenta sama ke Raja. Nanti Beta kasi tau sang itu orang yang ada di Beta pung sablá kanan bilang, &lt;Bosong ni yang tarima berkat dari Beta pung Bapa. Mari ko maso pi dalam Dia pung ruma yang Dia su siap memang dari mula-mula kasi sang bosong.<bt>At that time, I will rule/govern like a King. Later I will tell those people who are on My right side saying, &lt;You here are who will receive blessing from My Father. Come and enter into His house which He has prepared ahead of time from the very beginning for you.</bt><v n="35" />Beta undang sang bosong, tagal dolu waktu Beta lapar, bosong kasi Beta makan. Waktu Beta aus, bosong kasi Beta minum. Beta datang sama ke orang luar, ma bosong tarima sang Beta di bosong pung ruma.<bt>I invite you, because previously when I was hungry, you gave Me food. When I was thirsty, you gave Me drink. I came like an outsider, but you received Me in your homes.</bt><v n="36" />Beta sonde ada pung pakean, ma bosong kasi Beta pakean. Beta saki, ma bosong datang urus sang Beta. Beta di bui, ma bosong datang lia sang Beta.&gt;<bt>I did not have clothes, but you gave Me clothes. I was sick, but you came and took care of Me. I was in jail, but you came and saw Me.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Dengar bagitu, nanti itu orang hati lurus dong yang ada di Beta pung sablá kanan tu, manyao bale bilang, &lt;Tuhan, ini su karmana ni? Tuhan bilang, Tuhan lapar, ais botong kasi makan. Tuhan aus, ju botong kasi minum.<bt>Hearing like that, later those straight liver people on My right side will answer back saying, &lt;Lord, how is this? Lord says Lord was hungry, then we gave food. Lord was thirsty, then we gave drink.</bt><v n="38" />Tuhan sama ke orang luar, ju botong tarima maso di botong pung ruma. Tuhan sonde ada pung pakean, ais botong kasi.<bt>Lord was like an outsider, then we accepted into our homes. Lord did not have clothing, then we gave.</bt><v n="39" />Tuhan saki, ais botong pi urus. Tuhan di bui, ais botong pi tolong. Ma kapan botong bekin hal-hal bagitu?&gt;<bt>Lord was sick, then we went to take care. Lord was in jail, then we went to help. But when did we do all those things like that?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Nanti Beta manyao sang dong bilang, &lt;Parcaya sang Beta! Te waktu bosong bekin hal-hal bagitu kasi Beta pung orang dong, biar bekin kasi orang yang paling tar laku-laku ju, na, itu sama ke bosong su bekin kasi Beta ju!&gt;<bt>Later I will reply to them saying, &lt;Believe Me! Cuz (elaboration) when you did things like that to My people, even to people where that most insignificant, then itwas like/the same as you were doing it for Me!&gt; [EXEG: “my brothers” -NRSV members of my family, NLT my bro &amp; sis, CEV my people; “like, as if” see discussion in TH.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Tarús Beta kasi tau itu orang dong yang ada di Beta pung sablá kiri bilang, &lt;Heh, orang jahat dong! Tuhan Allah su kutuk sang bosong. Iskarobis dari sini! Nanti Beta suru orang pi lempar buang sang bosong pi dalam api naraka yang manyala sonde tau abis-abis. Te Tuhan Allah su sadia itu tampa sangsara kasi setan-setan deng dong pung bos bésar.<bt>Next I will tell those people on My left side saying, &lt;Heh, [+rebuke] evil people! God has cursed you. Get out of here! Later I will order people to throw you away into hell fire which burns with ever ending. Cuz (elaboration) God has prepared that suffering place there, for the evil spirit's and their big bos.</bt><v n="42" />Beta usir buang sang bosong, tagal waktu Beta lapar, bosong sonde kasi Beta makan. Waktu Beta aus, bosong sonde kasi Beta minum.<bt>I am expelling you because when I was hungry, you did not give Me food. When I was thristy, you did not give Me drink.</bt><v n="43" />Beta datang sama ke orang luar, ma bosong sonde tarima sang Beta di bosong pung ruma. Beta sonde ada pung pakean, ma bosong sonde kasi Beta pakean. Beta saki, ma bosong sonde datang urus sang Beta. Beta di bui, ma bosong sonde datang tolong sang Beta.&gt;<bt>I came like an outsider, but you did not accept Me into your house. I did not have clothes, but you did not give Me clothes. I was sick, but you did not come take care of Me. I was in jail, but you did not come help Me.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Dengar bagitu, nanti itu orang jahat dong manyao bilang, &lt;Tuhan, ini su karmana ni? Tuhan bilang Tuhan lapar, ma botong sonde kasi makan. Tuhan aus, ma botong sonde kasi minum. Tuhan sama ke orang luar, ma botong sonde tarima maso di botong pung ruma. Tuhan sonde ada pakean, ma botong sonde kasi. Tuhan ada saki, ma botong sonde pi urus. Tuhan di bui, ma botong sonde pi tolong. Ma kapan botong ada bekin sang Tuhan bagitu?&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, later those evil people will respond saying, &lt;Lord, how can this be? Lord says Lord was hungry, but we did not give food. Lord was thirsty, but we did not give drink. Lord was like an outsider, but we did not receive into our houses. Lord did have clothes, but we did not give. Lord was sick, but we did not go take care. Lord was in jail, but we did not go help. But when did we do like that to Lord?&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Nanti Beta manyao sang dong bilang, &lt;Parcaya sang Beta! Te waktu bosong sonde tolong orang tar laku-laku dong, na, itu su sama ke bosong sonde tolong sang Beta.&gt;<bt>Later I will reply to them saying, &lt;Believe Me! Cuz (elaboration) when you did not help the down and outers, that was the same as if you did not help Me.&gt;</bt><v n="46" />Ais, itu orang jahat dong dapa sangsara tarús-tarús sonde tau putus-putus. Ma itu orang yang hati lurus dong, dapa idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan sonde tau putus-putus.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those evil people will get suffering continually forever. But those people with straight livers they will live continually with the Lord forever.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="25:46" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 12:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Yahudi pung bos-bos cari akal ko mau bunu sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The Yahudi bosses look for a way to murder the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:1-2; Lukas 22:1-2; Yohanis 11:45-53)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="26" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu Yesus su ajar abis itu hal samua sang dong, ju Dia kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang,<bt>When Yesus had finsihed teaching all those things, then He told His underlings saying,</bt><v n="2" />&lt;&lt;Bosong su tau, nanti dua hari lai ada kotong pung hari bae, andia Pesta Paska. Itu waktu, nanti ada orang yang jual buang sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Ais dong paku bekin mati sang Beta di kayu palang.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You already know, later in two more days it is our-in good day (=holiday), that is, the Paska Feast. At that time, later there will be a person who sells Me off (=betray), this Ideal/Prototypical Human. Then they will nail kill Me on the crossed sticks.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="26:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:1-27</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Itu waktu, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat dong ada bakumpul di Kayafas pung ruma. Kayafas tu, andia kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar.<bt>On that day, the *chief priests and the traditional elders where gathered at Kayafas' house. That Kayafas, was the Jewish religion's big boss.</bt><v n="4" />Dong ada bacari akal ko mau tangkap sang Yesus deng diam-diam, ko dong bunu sang Dia.<bt>They were looking for a way to capture Yesus quietly, so they could murder Him.</bt><v n="5" />Ma dong ator siasat bilang, &lt;&lt;Tahan dolo! Kotong jang tangkap sang Dia capát-capát, tagal hari-hari bae su deka. Jang sampe orang banya yang suka sang Dia, bangun mangamok.&gt;&gt;<bt>But they strategized saying, &lt;&lt;Wait! We-inc shouldn't capture Him quickly, because the holidays are near. May it not be that many people who like Him, run.amok.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Satu parampuan po'a minya wangi yang mahal kasi sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>A woman pours fragrant oil which is expensive on the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:3-9; Yohanis 12:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Di kampong Betania, ada satu orang, nama Simon. Dolu orang noju sang dia, tagal dia kaná panyaki kusta. Ma sakarang dia su bae. Waktu itu hari bae dong balóm datang, ju Yesus dong ada pi makan di Simon pung ruma.<bt>In Betania village, there was a person named Simon. Previously people were abhorred by him (disgusted/grossed out/wanted to avoid), because he had leprosy illness, But now he was healed. When those holidays had not yet come, then Yesus them went to eat at Simon's house.</bt><v n="7" />Waktu dong makan, ju ada satu parampuan datang katumu sang Yesus. Dia ada pegang satu botol, bekin dari batu yang mahal.<bt>When they were eating, then a woman came to meet Yesus. She was holding a bottle, made from stone which was expensive.</bt><note reference="26:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu botol, dong bekin dari batu mahal yang orang bisa pahat. Alkitab Bahasa Yunani bilang itu botol dong bekin dari batu yang dia pung nama ἀλάβαστρος (<span class="Italic">&lt;alabastros&gt;</span>). Lia ju di Lukas 7:37-38.<bt>That bottle, they made from expensive stone that could be carved. The Yunani language Bible says that bottle they made out of a stone with its name <span class="Italic">&lt;alabastros&gt;</span>. Also see in Lukas 7:37-38.</bt></note>Itu botol pung isi minya wangi yang mahal mati pung. Ais, itu parampuan puku bekin pata itu botol pung tutu. Ju dia po'a kasi malele palán-palán itu minya di Yesus pung kapala, ko jadi tanda dia kasi hormat sang Yesus.<bt>That bottle's contents were fragrant oil which was expensive. Then, that woman hit breaking that bottle's cover. Then she poured making that oil drip slowly on Yesus' head, to be a sign she was giving honour to Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: Mark and John talk about the perfume being ‘pure’. Matthew does not.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma waktu Yesus pung ana bua dong lia itu parampuan bekin bagitu, ju dong mara, ko dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Jang buang parcuma itu minya wangi yang mahal mati pung!<bt>But when Yesus' underling saw that woman do that, then they got angry, and they spoke to each other saying, &lt;Hee! Don't needlessly throwing away that fragrant oil that is very expensive!</bt><v n="9" />Lebe bae dia jual itu minya sa! Ko biar dia pung doi, bagi kasi orang malarat dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>It's better she just sells that oil! To that its money can be divided out to the poor people!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ma Yesus tau dong pung pikiran tu, ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde usa bekin susa ini parampuan! Kasi tenga pi sang dia sa! Beta sanáng, tagal dia su po'a ini minya wangi di Beta pung badan.<bt>But Yesus know that thinking of theirs, and He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;You don't need to cause trouble for this woman! Just leave her alone! I am happy, because she has poured this fragrant oil on My body.</bt><v n="11" />Te orang malarat dong salalu ada di bosong pung teng-tenga. Ma sonde lama lai, te Beta ni su sonde ada sama-sama deng bosong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) poor people will always be among you. But not much longer and I here, will not be together with you.</bt><note reference="26:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 15:11</note><v n="12" />Deng ini parampuan po'a ini minya ni, dia su sadia Beta pung badan sama ke dia kasi rampe memang Beta pung mayat. Te Beta pung idop su sonde lama lai.<bt>With this woman pouring this oil here, she has prepared My body the same as if she was putting spices/flowers beforehand on My corpse. Cuz (elaboration) My life is not much longer.</bt><v n="13" />Inga bae-bae, ó! Di mana sa Tuhan Allah pung Carita Bae tasiar kuliling ini dunya, dong ju pasti carita ini parampuan pung bae, ko biar samua orang inga sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember well! Wherever God's Good News is spread around this world, they also were certainly telll this woman's goodness, so that all people remember her.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yudas ba'akór deng bos-bos agama Yahudi ko sarakan Tuhan Yesus pi dong pung tangan<bt>Yudas agrees with the Yahudi religious bosses to hand over the Lord Yesus to their hands</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:10-11; Lukas 22:3-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ada satu orang dari Yesus pung ana bua dua blas orang, nama Yudas Iskariot. Itu hari ju, dia kaluar pi cari kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, ko mau sarakan sang Yesus pi dong pung tangan.<bt>One of Yesus' twelve underlings, named Yudas Isakariot. That (same) day, he went out to go find the *chief priests, in order to turn Yesus over into their hands.</bt><v n="15" />Sampe di dong, ju dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa dong! Kalo beta bantu tangkap sang Yesus tu, na, bosong kasi beta apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Arriving at them, then he asked saying, &lt;&lt;Fathers! If I help capture that Yesus, then what will you give?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo lu mau jual buang sang Dia kasi botong, na, botong bayar.&gt;&gt; Ais dong itong ame tiga pulu doi perak ko sarakan pi Yudas.<bt>Then they replied saying, &lt;&lt;If you want to sell Him off to us, na, we will pay.&gt;&gt; Then they counted out thirty silver money to hand over to Yudas.</bt><note reference="26:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 11:12</note><v n="16" />Ais itu, Yudas kaluar, ju dia mulai cari akal ko mau sarakan sang Yesus pi di dong.<bt>After that, Yudas went out, and he begain to find a way to be able to hand over Yesus to them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus makan pesta Paska deng Dia pung ana bua dong<bt>The Lord Yesus eats Paska feast with His underlings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:12-21; Lukas 22:7-14, 21-23; Yohanis 13:21-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tiap taon, orang Yahudi dong ada hari-hari bae yang dia pung lama tuju hari. Dong subu itu hari bae bilang, &lt;Pesta Roti Sonde Pake Ragi&gt;.<bt>Every year, the Jewish people had holidays which lasted seven days. They called those holidays saying, &lt;The Feast of Bread Without Yeast&gt;.</bt><note reference="26:17" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu pesta bekin dong inga waktu orang Yahudi pung nene-moyang dong lari kaluar dari tana Masir. Itu waktu, dong angka kaki capát-capát. Andia ko sonde ada waktu cukup ko bekin reis dong pung roti bakál pake bibit roti. Baca <span class="Italic">Kaluar dari Masir</span> 12:6,15.<bt>That feast remembers when the Yahudi people's ancestors were fleeeing from the land of Masir. At that time, they left very quickly. That is why there was not enough time to raise their trailfood bread using bread seed (=yeast). Read <span class="Italic">Come out of Masir</span> 12:6,15.</bt></note>Waktu itu pesta su mau mulai, Yesus pung ana bua dong datang tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Ini malam kotong musti buka kotong pung hari-hari bae. Jadi Bapa mau ko botong pi horo domba, deng sadia tampa pesta Paska di mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>When that feast was about to begin, Yesus' underlings came asking Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Tonight we-inc must open/start our holidays. So (consequently), where does Father want us to go cut the sheep, and prepare the place for the Paska feast?&gt;&gt; [KT: several MTT teams reacted against “Trailfood Bread”, not just because it was so different from the Indo, but it also did not evoke focus on ‘yeast’ to them. July 2014.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong maso kota, nanti bosong katumu deng satu bapa. Kasi tau sang dia bilang bagini, &lt;Bu, é! Bapa Guru rasa su sonde lama lai Dia su mati. Ais Dia ada minta tampa di bu pung ruma, ko Dia pake bekin pesta Paska deng Dia pung ana bua dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He replied saying, &lt;&lt;You enter the city, and later you will met a father/man. Tell him saying like this, &lt;Elder.brother! Father Teacher feels He will die soon. (So) He is requesting a place in elder.brother's house, for Him to use to make the Paska feast with His underlings.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Carson points out that the phrase “My appointed time is near” was probably deliberately ambiguous. To the disciples and the house owner appearing to refer to the festivities, but to Jesus himself referring to the crucifixion. In Dhao (as in other daughter lgs), we can't just say “my time”. So it unfortunately has to go to “Father Teacher feels He will die soon (ALT:the time of His death is near), so....” which is consistent with the normal interpretation of “my time is near” throughout the gospels. KM fix is hard to render in daughter lgs because of /rasa/ “feels” which could alternately be rendered “says”.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dengar bagitu ju, Dia pung ana bua dong pi bekin iko Dia pung omong tu. Ais dong sadia makan pesta Paska di situ.<bt>Hearing like that, then His underlings went to do according to that speaking of His. Then they prepared for eating the Paska feast there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Waktu su malam ju, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua 12 orang dudu makan pesta.<bt>When it was night, then Yesus and His 12 underlings were sitting eating the feast.</bt><v n="21" />Waktu dong ada makan, ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dengar, é! Ada satu dari bosong, yang nanti jual buang sang Beta pi orang laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were eating, then He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;You listen! There is one of you, who later will sell Me off (=betray) to other people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong pung hati rasa tar enak. Tarús dong satu-satu tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu orang yang Bapa omong tu, bukan beta, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then their livers felt not good. Next each one asked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;That person whom Father was talking about there, it's not me, right?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang colo dia pung roti pi dalam ini mangko sama-sama deng Beta, dia tu yang nanti jual buang sang Beta.<bt>Then He replied saying, &lt;&lt;The person who dips his bread into this cup together with Me, it's he who will later sell Me away.</bt><note reference="26:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 41:10</note><v n="24" />Inga, é! Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, musti mati sama ke dong su tulis memang dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi. Ma ati-ati! Itu orang yang mau jual buang sang Beta tu, nanti dia pikol dia pung calaka! Ada lebe bae kalo dia pung mama sonde barana ame sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember, é! I, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, must die just like what they wrote ahead of time in God's writing. But be careful! That person who wants to sell Me off, later he will carry his misfortune. It's better if his mama didn't give birth to him!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais itu, Yudas ju iko tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Tantu itu orang yang Bapa omong tu, bukan beta, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yudas also went along with/participated in asking saying, &lt;Surely that perosn whom Father is speaking about there, it's not me, right?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang lu sandiri su bilang bagitu. Ko sapa lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Actually you yourself have said like that. Who else?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau bilang, itu roti deng aer anggor jadi tanda ko inga sang Dia [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus tells that that bread and grape water/juice/fluid become signs to remember Him [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:22-26; Lukas 22:14-20; 1 Korintus 11:23-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Waktu dong masi makan, ju Yesus angka ame roti satu balok, ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Dia bekin pica-pica itu roti, ju Dia sorong kasi sang Dia pung ana bua dong, deng kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini roti ni, Beta pung badan. Bosong ame ko makan su!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were still eating, then Yesus picked up a loaf of bread, and requested thank you from God. Then He broke up that bread, and He extended it to His underlings, and told saying, &lt;&lt;This bread here, is My body. You take [it] to eat!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais itu, Dia ame satu galás ponu deng aer anggor, ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais ju Dia sorong pi Dia pung ana bua dong, deng kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong samua ame ko minum.<bt>After that, He took a glass full of grape juice/fluid, and requested thank you to God. Then He extended it to His underlings, and told saying, &lt;&lt;You all take [it] and drink.</bt><v n="28" />Te ini aer anggor ni, Beta pung dara. Nanti Beta mati, Beta pung dara tatumpa ko kasi salamat orang banya dari dong pung sala-sala dong. Ini dara jadi bukti ko kasi inga bilang, apa yang Tuhan Allah su janji tu, memang sakarang ni su jadi. Naa, ame ko minum su!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) this grape juice/fluid here, is My blood. Later when I die, My blood will will tip over/spill out to save many people from their wrongs. This blood becomes evidence to remind that, that which God promised before, actually now it has happened. Naa, [+shift] take and drink!</bt><note reference="26:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 24:8, Yeremia 31:31-34</note><v n="29" />Ma dengar bae-bae! Mulai dari ini malam, Beta su sonde minum aer anggor lai. Nanti kalo Beta deng Beta pung Bapa su dudu pegang parenta di sorga, baru Beta minum lai deng bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But listen carefully! Starting from this night, I will not drink grape juice/fluid again. Later when I and My Father sits holding rule/governing in heaven, only then will I drink again with you.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais ju dong manyanyi satu lagu ko puji sang Tuhan Allah. Tarús, itu malam ju, dong kaluar pi gunung Saitun.<bt>After that, they sang a song to praise God. Next, that very night then they went out to Saitun mountain.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang bilang, Petrus nanti manyangkal sang Dia<bt>The Lord Yesus tell beforehand saying, Petrus later will deny Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:27-31; Lukas 22:31-34; Yohanis 13:36-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Waktu dong jalan tu, Yesus kasi tau Dia pung ana bua memang bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti sabantar malam ni, bosong samua lari kasi tenga sang Beta. Te dong su tulis memang dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>When they were walking there, Yesus told His underlings ahead of time saying, &lt;&lt;Later tonight, you all will run leaving Me. Cuz (elaboration) they have written ahead of time in the Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Nanti Tuhan Allah bekin mati gambala,<bt>‘God will kill the shepherd,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="strike the shepherd"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">strike the shepherd</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais dia pung domba dong lari batasiram.&gt;<bt>And his sheep will run scattered all over the place.’</bt><note reference="26:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 13:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Beta memang mati. Ma nanti kalo Beta su idop kambali, Beta pi tunggu bosong di propinsi Galilea sana.&gt;&gt;<bt>I will really die. But later when I live again, I will go wait for you yonder in Galilea province.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="26:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 28:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ma Petrus protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Biar orang laen dong samua lari kasi tenga Bapa, ma beta sonde akan!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus protested saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Even if all the other people run leaving Father, but I will never!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagitu ko, Pe'u? Parcaya sang Beta! Ini malam, ayam balóm kokore'o, te lu su omong tiga kali bilang, lu sonde kanál sang Beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Is that right, Pe'u? Believe Me! This night, the chicken will not yet crow, and you will have said three times that you do not know Me!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ma Petrus bakarás bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde, Bapa! Kalo Bapa mati, beta ju iko mati sama-sama. Te beta sonde akan lari kasi tenga sang Bapa!&gt;&gt; Petrus pung tamán laen dong ju satu-satu bilang bagitu.<bt>But Petrus strong opposed saying, &lt;&lt;No, Father! If Father dies, then I will follow dying together [with Father]. Cuz (elaboration) I will not run away abandoning Father!&gt;&gt; Each one of Petrus' other friends also said like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sambayang di kabón Getsemani<bt>The Lord Yesus prays in Getsemani garden</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:32-42; Lukas 22:39-46)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais Yesus dong jalan tarús pi gunung Saitun, sampe di satu kabón, nama <span class="Italic">Getsemani.</span><bt>Then Yesus them walked on to Saitun mountain, arriving at a garden, named <span class="Italic">Getsemani.</span></bt><note reference="26:36" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam bahasa Ibrani, &lt;Getsemani&gt; pung arti bilang, &lt;alat parés minya bua saitun&gt;.<bt>In the Ibrani language, &lt;Getsemani&gt; means &lt;instrument to press oil from saitun fruit&gt;.</bt></note>Di situ Dia kasi tau sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dudu tahan di sini doo, te Beta mau pi sambayang di sana.&gt;&gt;<bt>There He told His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;You sit a while here, cuz (elaboration) I want to pray over there.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="37" />Ma Dia pange bawa sang Petrus, Yakobis, deng Yohanis, ko dong tiga pi sama-sama deng Dia. Mulai dari itu waktu, ju Dia pung hati rasa susa deng sonde tanáng.<bt>But He called took Petrus, Yakobis, and Yohanis, so they three go together with Him. Starting from that time, then His liver felt troubled and not calm.</bt><v n="38" />Dong baru jalan sadiki, te Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung hati ada susa mau mati! Beta rasa tingka ke Beta su mau mati sa. Bosong dudu mete jaga deng Beta di sini dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>They had only walked a bit, cuz (elaboration) He told them saying, &lt;&lt;My liver is very distressed! I feel as if I am about to die. You sit and stay awake watch with Me here.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais Dia maju lebe jao sadiki, ju Dia tikam lutut ko sambayang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa manis! Kalo Bapa satuju, na, Beta sonde usa tanggong ini sangsara. Ma jang iko Beta pung mau; biar iko Bapa pung mau sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He went foreward a little bit further, and He knelt to pray saying, &lt;&lt;Sweet/dear Father! If Father agrees, na, I don't need to carry this suffering. But don't follow My will; allow it to just follow Father's will.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Sambayang abis, ju Dia kambali pi Dia pung ana bua tiga orang tu. Ma dong ada tidor sonu. Ais Dia kasi bangun sang dong, ju Dia omong deng Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;He, Pe'u! Kanapa ko bosong tidor? Beta di situ cuma sabantar sa, ma bosong sonde bisa mete jaga sadiki ju!<bt>After finished praying, then He returned to those three underlings of His. But they were sleeping soundly. The He woke them up, and He spoke with Petrus saying, &lt;&lt;He! [+light rebuke] Pete! Why are you-pl sleeping? I was there only just a little while, but you could not stay awake watching even a little bit!</bt><v n="41" />Goso bekin taráng bosong pung mata dolo. Ais bangun ko bajaga deng Beta! Te bosong pung hati memang mau bekin yang bae, cuma bosong pung badan sonde kuat. Jadi lebe bae bosong sambayang, ko kalo kaná coba'an, bosong bisa batahan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Rub and make your eyes clear. Then wake/get up to watch with Me! Cuz (elaboration) your livers really want to what is good, only your bodies are not strong. So (consequently) it's better you pray, so if you are affected by a temptation, you can endure.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Ais Dia pi sambayang lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Kalo Beta yang musti pikol ini sangsara, na, biar iko Bapa pung mau sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He went to pray again saying, &lt;&lt;Father! If I am the one who must shoulder carry this suffering, allow it to just follow Father's will.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="43" />Sambayang abis, ju Dia datang kambali di Dia pung ana bua tiga orang tu. Ma dong su tidor ulang lai, te dong pung mata talalu barát.<bt>After praying, then He came back to those three underlings of His. But they were sleeping again, cuz (elaboration) their eyes were heavy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ais Dia kasi tenga sang dong, ko pi sambayang satu kali lai. Dia minta ulang sang Bapa, ko jang kasi tenga Dia pikol itu sangsara, ma biar iko Bapa pung mau sa.<bt>Then He left them to go pray one more time. He requested again to the Father, to not leave Him to carry that suffering, but allow it to just follow the Father's will.</bt><v n="45" />Sambayang abis, ju Dia kambali ko kasi bangun sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong masi tidor tarús ni, ko? Bangun su! Te orang yang mau jual buang sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, su deka. Sakarang dong su mau tangkap sang Beta, ko sarakan pi orang jahat dong pung tangan.<bt>After praying, then He returned and woke up His underlings saying, &lt;&lt;You are still sleeping on here? Get/Wake up! Cuz (elaboration) the perosn who wants to sell Me off, this Ideal/Prototypical Human, is near. Now they already want to capture Me, to hand over to evil people's hands.</bt><v n="46" />Weh! Bangun su! Buka bosong pung mata ko lia coba pi sana dolo! Te itu orang yang jual buang sang Beta tu, su datang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Weh! [+attention, +rebuke] Get up! Open your eyes and look over there! Cuz (elaboration) those people who are selling Me off, have come.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang bésar dong kirim orang ko pi tangkap sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The big people send people to go capture the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:43-50; Lukas 22:47-53; Yohanis 18:3-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Waktu Yesus masi ba'omong bagitu, Yudas su datang deng orang bam-banya. Dong datang deng bawa kalewang kudung deng kayu kudung, ko mau tangkap sang Yesus. Dong bekin bagitu, iko parenta dari kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat dong.<bt>When Yesus was still conversing like that, Yudas had come with many people. They came bringing short swords and clubs, to capture Him. They did like that, following the command from cheif priests, and the traditional elders.</bt><v n="48" />Yudas su kasi sein memang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong lia bae-bae, é! Orang yang beta ciom tu, bosong tangkap ame sang Dia su! Te Dia tu, andia itu orang yang bosong cari!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yudas have given a code beforehand to them saying, &lt;&lt;You look well! The person whom I kiss, you capture Him! Cuz (elaboration) He is that person who you are looking for!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Waktu dong sampe di Yesus, ju Yudas langsung pi di Dia pung muka, ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Saloom, Bapa Guru!&gt;&gt; Ju Yudas paló-ciom sang Dia.<bt>When they arrived at Yesus, then Yudas immediately went to His face and said, &lt;&lt;Peace, Father Teacher!&gt;&gt; Then Yudas embraced-kissed Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ais Yesus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;He, Yudas! Lu pung datang ni, buat ini maksud, ko?&gt;&gt; Tarús, itu orang banya dong maju datang, ko mau tangkap sang Dia.<bt>Then Yesus asked him saying, &lt;&lt;He, [+light rebuke] Yudas! Your coming here, for this intent, [+tag question]? Next, those many people came forward, to capture Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT (like NLT): “go ahead and do what you have come for.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Ma tau-tau, te Yesus pung orang satu cabu ame dia pung parang, ko seruk bekin putus satu orang pung daon talinga. (Itu orang yang luka tu, andia kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung orang suru-suru.)<bt>But unexpectedly/in.actual.fact, one of Yesus' people pulled out his machete, and slashed severing a person's ear leaf. (That person who was wounded there, it was the servant of the big boss of the Jewish priests. [=*high priest]) [NOTE: RL context. Fishermen and farmers would have access to parangs, not kelewangs. The Gk term covers a wide range.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="52" />Lia bagitu, ju Yesus kasi tau sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi maso lu pung parang kambali pi dia pung tampa. Te orang yang idop deng maen kalewang, nanti dia ju mati kaná kalewang.<bt>Seeing like that, then Yesus told him saying, &lt;&lt;Put your machete back in its place. Cuz (elaboration) a person who lives (habitually) using swords, he will also die by a sword. [NOTE: (habitually) use a sword to try to deal with problems (like Peter just did).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="53" />Lu sonde tau, ko? Beta bisa minta Beta pung Bapa ko Dia kirim Dia pung ana bua puluan ribu<bt>Don't you know [+tag question]? I can request My Father to send tens of thousands</bt><note reference="26:53" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani bilang 12 <span class="Italic">legion</span>. Satu legion tantara Roma, kira-kira 6.000 orang.<bt>The Yunani language Bible says 12 <span class="Italic">legion</span>. One legion in the Roma army, is around 6,000 people.</bt></note>dari sorga, ko dong datang tolong sang Beta.<bt>of his underlings from heaven, to come help Me.</bt><v n="54" />Ma sonde usa. Kasi tenga sa, ko ini orang dong tangkap ame sang Beta. Te samua yang ada tatulis memang di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi so'al Beta tu, musti jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>But it's not necessary. Just allow it so these people capture Me. Cuz (elaboration) everything which is written beforehand in the Bible about Me there, must happen.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Ais Yesus omong sang itu banya orang yang datang tangkap sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong kira Beta ni, orang jahat, ko? Akurang ko bosong datang tangkap sang Beta deng bawa kalewang kudung deng kayu kudung? Padahal tiap hari Beta ajar sang bosong di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ma sonde ada satu orang ju yang bekin apa-apa sang Beta.<bt>Then Yesus spoke with those many people who came to capture Him saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! [+attention, +rebuke] Do you think I here am an evil person [+tag question]? Why do you come capture Me bringing swords and clubs? In actual fact every day I teach you in God's Main Prayer House, but there is not even one person who did anything to Me.</bt><note reference="26:55" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 19:47, 21:37</note><v n="56" />Ma biar sa! Mari, tangkap sang Beta su! Te ini samua su tatulis memang dari dolu di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>But just allow it! Come, capture Me! Cuz (elaboration) all of this is written beforehand from long ago in the Bible.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Lia bagitu ju, Yesus pung ana bua dong taku mau mati. Ju dong bangun lari kasi tenga sang Dia.<bt>Seeing like that, then Yesus' underlings were very afraid. They got up and ran leaving Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong bawa sang Tuhan Yesus pi orang yang putus parkara agama dong<bt>They bring the Lord Yesus to the people who decide religious disputes</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:53-65; Lukas 22:54-55, 63-71; Yohanis 18:13-14, 19-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Ais ju itu orang dong yang tangkap sang Yesus bawa sang Dia pi kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar, Kayafas, pung ruma, tagal orang bésar dong su bakumpul di situ. Andia, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, guru agama dong, deng tua-tua adat.<bt>Afterwards then those people who captured Yesus brought Him to the Yahudi religion's big boss, Kayafas', house, because the big (=important) people had already gathered there. That is, chief priests, the religion teachers, and the traditional elders. [EXEG: ‘chief priests’ from vs. 59]</bt><v n="58" />Waktu dong pegang bawa sang Dia tu, Petrus ju ada iko sambunyi-sambunyi dari balakang, sampe di itu bos bésar pung ruma. Petrus ju maso di kintal, ko iko dudu sama-sama deng orang-orang yang ada di situ. Te dia mau tau apa yang nanti jadi.<bt>When they were holding bringing Him, Petrus also was following hiding from behind, until that big boss' house. Petrus also entered the yard, to go along sitting together with people who were there. Cuz (elaboration) he wanted to know what would happen.</bt><v n="59" />Dalam itu ruma, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos ada berunding deng samua orang yang urus parkara agama. Dong samua cari bukti ko mau cari jalan ko putus hukuman mati kasi sang Yesus.<bt>In that house, the chief priests were conferring with all the people who handle religious disputes. They all were hunting for evidence to find a way to decide the death sentence for Yesus. [DISCOURSE: RL, generic here, specific (false witnesses) in 60)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="60" />Ma biar dong sorong saksi palsu yang banya ju, dong sonde dapa bukti apa-apa yang dong bisa pake. Ahirnya dong dapa saksi dua orang.<bt>But even though they put forward many false witnesses, they could not get any evidence they could use. Finally they got two witnesses. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><v n="61" />Itu dua orang basaksi bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong parná dengar ini Orang omong bilang, &lt;Nanti Beta kasi rubu Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ma dalam waktu tiga hari ju, Beta nanti kasi bangun ulang.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Those two people witnessed saying, &lt;&lt;We once heard this Person speak saying, &lt;Later I will knock over this Main Prayer House. But within three days, then I will build it again/rebuild it.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="26:61" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 2:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="62" />Ais, itu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar bangun badiri di muka samua orang yang dudu di situ. Ju dia tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu su dengar banya orang tudu sang Lu. Ma akurang ko Lu diam-diam sa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, that Jewish religion's big boss stood up in front of all the people who were sitting there. Then he asked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;You have heard many people accuse You. But why are You just quiet?&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="63" />Ma Yesus sonde manyao apa-apa. Ju itu bos bésar tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau tanya ni! Ma Lu musti manyao batúl-batúl sama ke Lu ada manyao kasi Tuhan Allah yang idop di sorga. Ada orang yang bilang, Lu ni, Kristus, Tuhan Allah pung Ana yang Dia su janji dari dolu tu. Batúl tu, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus did not reply anything. Then that big boss asked again saying, &lt;&lt;I want to ask this! But You must reply correctly as if You were replying to God who lives in heaven. There are people who say, You here, are Kristus, that Child of God's whom He promised from long ago. Is that right?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="64" />Ais ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl, sama ke pak omong tu. Ma inga, é! Te nanti bosong samua dapa lia Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Nanti Beta dudu di sorga di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan, ko pegang parenta sama-sama deng Dia yang paling kuasa. Ais itu, nanti Beta turun datang kambali deng awan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;It's true, the same as sir says there. But remember! Cuz (elaboration) later you all will see Me, this Ideal/Prototypical Human. Later I will sit in heaven at God's right side in order to hold authority together with Him who is most powerful. After that, later I will come back down with/by cloud.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="26:64" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="65" />Dengar Dia omong bagitu, ju itu bos bésar mara mau mati, sampe dia ru'i bekin tarobe dia pung baju panjang. Ais dia batarea kasi tau samua orang yang dudu di situ bilang, &lt;&lt;Woeh! Kotong sonde parlú saksi lai! Bosong su dengar deng bosong pung talinga sandiri, Dia pung omong, to! Dia su angka diri jadi Tuhan Allah pung Ana. Ini su hojat ni! Bosong samua su tau bilang, iko kotong pung atoran agama, kalo ada orang bekin diri sama deng Tuhan, na, itu orang musti mati!<bt>Hearing Him speaking like that, then that big boss was very angry, to the point that he yanked ripped his long robe. Then he yelled telling all the people who sat there saying, &lt;&lt;Woeh! [+enough already!] We-inc don't need anymore witnesses! You have heard with your very own ears, that speaking of His. He has lifted himself up to be God's Child. This is slander here! You all know that, according to our-inc religious regulations, if a person makes himself the same as God, then that person must die!</bt><v n="66" />Jadi sakarang, bosong mau putus bilang, apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) now, what do we want to decide?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong samua batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang memang sala batúl! Jadi Dia musti kaná hukum mati!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they all yelled saying, &lt;&lt;This person is really wrong! So (consequently), He must get the death penalty!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Avoid impression that Jews have authority to carry it out. Gk focuses on result, not Actor.]</bt><note reference="26:65-66" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 24:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="67" />Ais ada barapa orang maju ko sumbur luda sang Yesus. Ju dong papoko barmaen deng tampeleng sang Dia.<bt>Then several people came forward and spit at Jesus. And they pounded him over and over and slapped Him.</bt><note reference="26:67" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 50:6</note><v n="68" />Ais dong ejek sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu ni, Kristus, aa? Coba Lu rai doo! Sapa yang falungku sang Lu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they mocked Him saying, &lt;Weh! You here, are Kristus, right? Try and discern! Who is it who punched You there?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus omong tiga kali bilang, dia sonde kanál sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Petrus says three times, that he does not know the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 14:66-72; Lukas 22:56-62; Yohanis 18:15-18, 25-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="69" />Itu waktu, Petrus masi iko dudu di kintal. Ais ada budak parampuan satu datang omong deng dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tadi lu ju ada iko sama-sama deng Yesus, itu orang Nasaret, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Petrus was still sitting in the yard. Then a female slave came speaking with him saying, &lt;&lt;Earlier, you were following together with Yesus, that Nasaret person, right?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="70" />Ma dia manyangkal di muka orang banya tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Akurang ko lu tanya bagitu! Beta sonde kanál sang Dia, ma.&gt;&gt;<bt>But he denied it in front of those many people saying, &lt;&lt;No! Why are you asking like that! I don't know Him [protest particle].&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="71" />Ais Petrus kaluar ko pi badiri di muka pintu pagar.<bt>Then Petrus went out to go stand in front of the fence gate.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju ada satu parampuan laen yang lia sang dia di situ. Tarús dia kasi tau sang orang di situ dong bilang, &lt;&lt;We, tadi beta lia ini orang ada sama-sama deng Yesus, itu orang Nasaret tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then2 there was another woman who saw him there. Next, she told the people there saying, &lt;&lt;We, [+get attention] earlier I saw this person together with Yesus, that Nasaret person.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="72" />Ju Petrus protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu gila mangkali! Beta sonde kanál itu Orang, ma! Beta sumpa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus protested saying, &lt;&lt;You are crazy probably! I don't know that Person [protest]! I swear [it]!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Is ‘You must be crazy!’ an addition? The words, yes; the effect, no. I asked UNSs and MTTs, “If we took away this sentence, would it effect anything? Would anything be lost? Would it still read OK in context without it?” The UNSs and MTTs discussed this at length, and concluded it leaves the story kind of flat without it. As they see it, Peter simply ‘denies knowing’ Jesus in vs.70; protests more strongly in vs.72, and then swears a ‘death oath’ in vs.74 (calling on the name of the Lord, implied by the Gk lex choice [LN]), in which in the local worldview, the consequences of violating it are very risky. If this sentence is removed from vs.72, they say the sense of protest is lost. I asked is there an simpler word that could be substituted that has the same effect? They couldn't think of any. I asked if there are other ways of saying this. They said you could also say “You must be drunk!” “You must be confused!”. I asked which would be most likely to be said in this context? They were unanimous. As it is in the text. “You must be crazy!” From their discussion, I get the impression that this is an idiomatic way of registering protest, and the meaning of the word as ‘crazy’ is out of focus.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="73" />Sonde lama lai, orang laen dong yang ada di situ omong lai sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Lu jang putar-balek lai bilang, lu sonde sama-sama deng itu orang! Te botong dengar lu pung balogat tu, parsís sama ke orang Galilea!&gt;&gt;<bt>Not long again, other people who were there spoke again with him saying, &lt;&lt;Heh! [+rebuke] You don't twist-turn (decieve) again saying, you weren't together with that person! Cuz (elaboration) we hear that accent of yours, is exactly like Galilea people!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="74" />Ma dia mulai maki-maki, ju dia malawan bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Beta sumpa pake Tuhan Allah pung nama! Beta sonde kanál itu Orang!&gt;&gt; Pas dia omong bagitu, ju ayam kokore'o.<bt>But he began to curse, and he opposed saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! I swear by God's name/reputation! I don't know that Person!&gt;&gt; Exactly as he spoke like that, then the chicken crowed. [EXEG: curse/swear is explicit in Gk. Also the particular Gk lexical item for ‘swear’ here isn't the normal one, but invokes the wrath of a divine being if the oath is violated. In Kupang this is classed as a “sumpa mati” -extreme category of oath.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="75" />Dengar itu ayam pung kokore'o, ju Petrus inga ame Yesus pung bahasa tadi bilang, &lt;&lt;Ayam balóm kokore'o, te lu su omong tiga kali bilang, lu sonde kanál sang Beta.&gt;&gt; Inga ame bagitu ju, dia pi luar ko manangis maskakeduk.<bt>Hearing that chicken's crowing, then Petrus remembered Yesus language earlier saying, &lt;&lt;The chicken will not yet crow, and you will have said three times, that you do not know Me.&gt;&gt; Remembering like that, then he went outside to cry sobbing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong bawa Tuhan Yesus pi gubernor Pilatus<bt>They bring the Lord Yesus to gobernor Pilatus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 15:1; Lukas 23:1-2; Yohanis 18:28-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="27" />
      <v n="1" />Papagi sakali, samua orang yang urus parkara agama tu, basakongkol ko mau bekin mati sang Yesus.<bt>Very early in the morning, all those people who decide religious disputes, were in agreement to kill Yesus.</bt><v n="2" />Tagal itu, dong ika bawa sang Dia pi mangada sang gubernor Pilatus. Te dong mau ko gubernor hukum mati sang Dia.<bt>Because of that, they tied brought Him to face governor Pilatus. Cuz (elaboration) they wanted to the governor to give the death sentence to Him.</bt><note reference="27:2" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu waktu, orang Yahudi dong sonde ada pung hak ko hukum mati orang. Andia ko dong bawa Tuhan Yesus di pamarenta Roma.<bt>At that time, the Yahudi people did not have the right/authority to punish people with death. That is why they brought the Lord Yesus to the government of Roma.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yudas gantong diri, ju dia mati<bt>Yudas hangs himself, and he dies</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Utusan dong pung Carita 1:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Waktu Yudas tau bilang, Yesus su kaná hukuman mati, ju dia manyasal, tagal dia yang jual buang sang Yesus. Ais dia kambali pi kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, deng tua-tua adat, ko kasi pulang dong pung doi tiga pulu perak tu.<bt>When Yudas knew that, Yesus had gotten the death penalty, then he regretted, because he was the one who had sold off (=betrayed) Yesus. Then he returned to the chief priests and the traditional elders, to give back that thirty silver moneys of theirs.</bt><v n="4" />Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su bardosa ni, tagal beta su sarakan Orang yang sonde ada pung sala apa-apa ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>He told saying, &lt;&lt;I am sinful here, because I handed over the Person who does not have even any wrongs.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Botong sonde mau toe deng lu lai! Lu sandiri yang musti tanggong itu dosa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But they replied saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! We don't want to know/care about you anymore. You yourself are the one who has to be responsible for that sin.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="5" />Ais Yudas lempar buang itu doi pi dalam Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ju dia kaluar ko pi gantong diri sampe dia mati buang.<bt>Then Yudas threw away that money into the Main Prayer House. Then he went out to go hang himself until he died badly/completely.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos pi kumpul ame itu doi yang Yudas su lempar tu. Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong sonde bole kasi maso kambali ini doi pi dalam peti doi, tagal ini doi kotor.<bt>Then the chief priests went to gather up that money which Yudas had thrown there. They spoke with each other saying, &lt;&lt;We-inc can't put this money back in the money box, because this is dirty money. [NOTE: here just chief priests (probably the “elders” had no authority in this matter)]</bt><v n="7" />Jadi lebe bae kotong pi béli tana sapo'ong dari tukang bekin pareu. Kalo ada orang asing yang mati, deng sonde ada orang yang kanál sang dia, na, kotong bisa kubur sang dia di situ sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), it's better we go buy a piece of land from a pot maker. If there is a foreigner who dies, and there is now one who know him/her, then we can just bury him/her there.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="8" />Ais ju dong pake itu doi, ko pi béli itu tana. Andia ko sampe sakarang, orang subu itu tampa bilang, &lt;Tana Dara&gt;.<bt>Afterwards then they used that money, to go buy that land. That is why to this day, people call that land saying, &lt;Blood Land&gt;.</bt><note reference="27:3-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 1:18-19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Deng bagitu, dong iko apa yang Tuhan pung jubir Yeremia su omong memang bilang,<bt>With that,they followed what the Lord's spokesperson Yeremia has spoken ahead of time saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dong pake buang doi perak tiga pulu ko béli tana.<bt>&lt;&lt;They use up thirty silver moneys to buy land.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong pake itu doi, tagal itu doi tu, harga béli orang,<bt>They use that money, because that money there, is the price of buying a person,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">iko apa yang orang Isra'el dong su putus memang.<bt>according to what the Israel people have decided beforehand. [EXEG: Following the CEV. Matthew is being sloppy/free here. The whole Zachariah passage is actually in first person ‘I, me’, whereas Matthew handles it in the third person “the one having been valued” (AGNT), or “the one on whom a price had been set” (NRSV). Passives and “the one who” are extremely hard to handle in these languages, especially in combination, so a tight reflection of the words here is a bit of a lost cause. Using a simple third person pronoun ‘him’ seems to leave the passage lifeless and with unanswered questions, whereas framing it as we have at least gives a hint of what is going on. It seems a footnote would most likely add confusion, rather than enlightenment.] [NOTE to daughter translations: consider if you can make a phrasing with ‘him’ work, something like NIV or NLT.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Itu tana dong béli dari tukang bekin pareu,<bt>That land they bought from the pot maker,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta sang beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>following God's command to me.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="27:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 11:12-13; Yeremia 18:2-4, 19:1-11, 32:6-15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus mangada sang gubernor Pilatus<bt>The Lord Yesus fronts up to governor Pilatus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 15:2-5; Lukas 23:3-5; Yohanis 18:33-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Waktu itu orang dong ame bawa Yesus sampe di gubernor, ju dia so'al sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Lu ni, batúl-batúl orang Yahudi pung Raja, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>When those people brought Yesus to the governor, then he debated/questioned Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;How is it? Are you, really the Jewish people's King, [+tag question]?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo. Pak su omong batúl tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>He replied saying, &lt;&lt;Yes. Pak has spoken correctly there.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ma waktu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat dong tudu banya hal sang Yesus, Dia sonde manyao apa-apa ju.<bt>But when the chief priests and traditional elders accused Yesus of many things, He did not reply anything.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais gubernor tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu sonde dengar dong pung omong tu? Dong su kasi sala bam-banya sang Lu. Ma akurang ko Lu sonde balas ju?!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the governor asked to Him saying, &lt;&lt;Don't You hear that speaking of theirs? They are accusing you of many things. But why are You not responding?!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma Dia sonde manyao sadiki ju, sampe itu gubernor taheran-heran.<bt>But He didn't reply even a little bit, until the governor was amazed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gubernor Pilatus kasi jato hukum mati sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Governor Pilatus sends down a death sentence to the Lord Jesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 15:6-15; Lukas 23:13-25; Yohanis 18:39--19:16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tiap taon, kalo orang Yahudi dong bekin pesta Paska, orang banya dong biasa pili satu orang bui, ko gubernor kasi lapás sang dia.<bt>Each year, when the Jewish people had their Paska feast, many people usually chose a jail person, for the governor to free.</bt><v n="16" />Itu waktu, ada orang bui satu, nama Barabas.<bt>That time there was a jail person, named Barabas.</bt><note reference="27:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu tulis bilang, &lt;Yesus Barabas&gt;, deng saparu lai tulis bilang, &lt;Barabas&gt; sa.<bt>Some Yunani language writings write saying, ‘Yesus Barabas’, and some others write saying, ‘Barabas’.</bt></note>Samua orang su tau dia tu sapa, tagal dia talalu jahat.<bt>All the people knew who he was, because he was very evil.</bt><v n="17" />Itu hari ju, orang banya pi gubernor Pilatus ko minta dia kasi lapás satu orang bui sama ke biasa. Ju Pilatus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae! Ma beta kasi lapás sang sapa? Di sini ada Barabas, deng ada ju Yesus yang orang subu bilang, Kristus. Beta kasi lapás yang mana? Bosong pili sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>The day then many people went to governor Pilatus to request him to free a jail person the same as always. Then Pilatus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;Ok! But who do I free? Here there is Barabas, and there is also Yesus, whom people call Kristus. Which one should I free. You choose.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="18" />(Gubernor omong bagitu, te dia su tau kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos ame bawa sang Yesus kasi sang dia, tagal dong ada camburu deng jengkel mati sang Yesus.)<bt>(The governor spoke like that, cuz (elaboration) he knew the chief priests had brought Yesus to him, because they were terribly jealous and upset with Him.) [EXEG: Gk jealous, envy, (upset, annoyed) in context, See LN.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Waktu gubernor masi pareksa itu parkara, ju dia pung maitua kirim pasán kasi sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa, é! Ati-ati, ó, te Yesus ni Orang yang sonde ada pung sala apa-apa. Gara-gara Dia, andia ko tadi malam beta mimpi sonde bae. Sampe sakarang ju beta masi rasa tar enak sakali.&gt;&gt;<bt>When the governo was still examining the case, then his wife sent instructions to him saying, &lt;&lt;Father, é! (=appropriate term for a wife in this context) Be careful, cuz (elaboration) this Yesus is a Person who does not have any wrongs at all. All because of Him, that's why last night I dreamed not good. Even until now I still feel very uneasy.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="20" />Ma itu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng tua-tua adat dong tusu-tusu itu orang banya tu, ko dong minta gubernor kasi lapás sang Barabas, deng hukum mati sang Yesus.<bt>But those chief priests and traditional elders kept stirring up/inciting (poking) those many people, for them to request the governor to free Barabas, and give death sentence to Yesus.</bt><v n="21" />Ais dia tanya ulang lai sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dari ini dua orang ni, beta lapás yang mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he asked once again to them saying, &lt;&lt;From these two people here, which one do I free?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong samua manyao rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Barabas! Kasi lapás sang Barabas sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they all replied enthusiastically saying, &lt;&lt;Barabas! Just free Barabas!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, na, beta bekin karmana deng ini Yesus, yang orang subu bilang, Kristus?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he asked them saying, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, then what do I do with this Yesus, whom people refer to saying, Kristus?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong samua batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they all yelled enthusiatically saying, &lt;&lt;Just nail Him to death on the crossed wood!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais gubernor tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Dia pung sala apa? Beta su pareksa sang Dia, ma beta sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the governor asked again saying, &lt;&lt;So what is His wrong? I have examined Him, and I don't find any wrong of His!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong samua batarea lebe karás lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bekin mati sang Dia! Paku sang Dia di kayu palang suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they all yelled even louder again saying, &lt;&lt;Kill Him! Nail Him on the crossed wood!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Sonde lama ju, dia tau bilang, dia sonde bisa bekin apa-apa lai, te itu orang banya dong su mau mangamok. Andia ko dia ame aer ko cuci dia pung tangan di dong pung muka, deng kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sonde tanggong ini Orang pung mati! Biar bosong yang musti tanggong!&gt;&gt;<bt>Not long then he knew that he could not do anything more, cuz (elaboration) those many people were about to riot. That's why he took water to wash his hands in front of them, and told saying, &lt;&lt;I do not carry this Person's death! Just let it be you-pl who must carry/bear responsibility!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="27:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 21:6-9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ju itu orang banya dong batarea manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo, biar pi! Biar ko botong deng botong pung ana-cucu dong yang tanggong Dia pung dara tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those many people yelled in response saying, &lt;&lt;Yes, allow that! Allow that we and our children-grandchildren are the ones who are responsible for that blood of His!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dengar bagitu, ju dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Neu pi.&gt;&gt; Ju dia kasi lapás sang Barabas, iko dong pung mau. Ais dia parenta orang jaga dong, ko pi firuk sang Yesus pake cambuk.<bt>Hearing like that then he said, &lt;&lt;Alright.&gt;&gt; Then he freed Barabas, according to their will. Then he ordered guards, to go whip/strike Yesus using a whip.</bt><note reference="27:26" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tantara Roma dong pake cambuk yang bekin dari tali kulit binatang barapa urat. Ais dong ika tulang tajam, ko, tima tajam di tali pung ujung-ujung. Kalo firuk ulang-ulang pake itu cambuk, kulit dong takupas buang.<bt>The Roma soldiers used a whip that was made from several strips of skin/leather rope. Then they tied sharp bones or sharp lead on the ends of the ropes. If/when whipped over and over using that whip, skin can be peeled off/away.</bt></note>Firuk abis, ju tantara dong ame bawa sang Yesus, ko mau pi paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang.<bt>After whipping, then the army guys took Yesus, to go nail kill Him on the crossed wood.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tantara dong olok barmaen sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The soldiers ridule the Lord Yesus over and over</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 15:16-20; Yohanis 19:2-3)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais itu, tantara dong hela bawa sang Yesus pi dong pung benteng pung kintal bésar. Di situ, dong pange ame dong pung tamán satu batalyon.<bt>After that, the soldiers dragged took Yesus to their big yard. There, they called their friends from one batalion (+/- 750 people).</bt><note reference="27:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tantara dong pung tampa tu, dong subu dalam bahasa Latin bilang, <span class="Italic">praetorium.</span> Itu tantara dong pung tampa sandiri di kompleks ruma jabatan. Alkitab bahasa Yunani bilang dong pange bakumpul dong pung tamán satu <span class="Italic">speira</span>. Satu <span class="Italic">speira </span>tu, sama deng 600 tantara.<bt>That place of the soldiers, they called in the Latin language saying, <span class="Italic">praetorium</span>. It is the army's own place in the complex of the official house. The Yunani language Bible says they summoned their friends from one <span class="Italic">speira</span>. One speira, is the same as 600 soldiers.</bt></note><v n="28" />Ju dong buka buang Yesus pung pakean ais ganti kasi pake sang Dia satu baju panjang warna mera manyala.<bt>Then they stripped of Yesus' clothes and replaced (them) causing Him to wear a long scarlet robe. [EXEG: noise from Mark version (purple), vs. Matthew (scarlet). Interestingly the Indonesian TB2 and BIS both use purple (ungu) here. See discussion in TH, TRT. Morris notes “By getting a cloak of a color not quite that of royalty the soldiers were mocking Jesus’ claim to be a king.” In spite of a comment in CONNOT and TRT, there does not seem to be any support for the claim that “scarlet” symbolized the colour worn by royalty. Only purple carries this. Trying to say “scarlet was fairly close to purple which symbolized royalty” is overtranslation, and easy to stuff up the fine distinctions in translation. So “like kings usually wear” removed from the Matthew version. Because the two Indonesian translations say “purple” here, I've added a footnote. Even Calvin noted the differences.] [EXEG: fixed omission “they stripped of Jesus' clothes”. Note that in the Gk there is an element of force, but not tearing. TB “menanggalkan pakaian-Nya” is good. Later they cast lots to see who gets Jesus' seamless cloth.]</bt><note reference="27:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Mateos tulis bilang, baju panjang ni &lt;mera manyala&gt;. Markus tulis bilang, &lt;ungu&gt;.<bt>Mateos writes that this long robe was &lt;scarlet&gt;. Mark writes that is was &lt;purple&gt;.</bt></note><v n="29" />Ais dong ame pohon baduri pung takis ko mala'e bekin topi. Ju dong tendes itu topi baduri pi Yesus pung kapala, ko bekin maen-maen sama ke dong mau angka raja baru pake topi jabatan. Ais dong kasi Dia pegang kayu satu di Dia pung tangan kanan, sama ke tongkat parenta. Ju dong tikam lutut mangada sang Dia, deng dong ejek sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Hormat orang Yahudi pung Raja.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they took a thorn tree's branches and entwined them to make a hat. Then they pressed down that thorn hat on Yesus' head, to play around as if they were lifting/appointing a new king using an official hat. Then they had Him hold a stick in His right hand, like a ruling staff. Then they knelt in front of Him and they ridiculed Him saying, &lt;&lt;Honor to the Jewish people's King.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="30" />Ju dong buang luda sang Dia, deng ame itu tongkat dari Dia pung tangan, ko kadeluk barmaen Dia pung kapala.<bt>Then they spit at Him, and they took that staff from His hand, to hit him over and over on the head.</bt><v n="31" />Dong olok barmaen abis sang Dia, ju dong buka buang itu baju panjang. Tarús dong kasi pake ulang Dia pung pakean. Ais ju dong ame bawa sang Dia pi kaluar kota Yerusalem, ko mau pi paku sang Dia di kayu palang sampe mati.<bt>They finished playing ridiculing Him, then they took off that long robe. Next they put back on His clothes. Then they brought/took Him outside Yerusalem city, to go nail Him on the crossed wood until death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong paku sang Tuhan Yesus di kayu palang<bt>They nail the Lord Yesus on the crossed wood</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 15:21-32; Lukas 23:26-43; Yohanis 19:17-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Waktu dong ada hela bawa sang Yesus, di tenga jalan dong nae katumu satu orang kota Kirene yang baru mau maso kota Yerusalem. Dia pung nama Simon. Dong paksa sang dia ko pikol ganti Yesus pung kayu palang.<bt>When they were dragging bring Yesus there, in the middle of the road they (happened to) meet a person from Kirene city who was just entering the city. His name was Simon. They forced him to replace Yesus shoulder carrying his crossed wood. [EXEG: Gk makes it clear he is a Cyrenian (origins), not that he was just coming from there.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) recised, note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) recised, note added</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ais dong sampe di satu tampa, nama <span class="Italic">Golgota.</span> (Dalam bahasa Aram, dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Tampa tulang kapala.&gt;&gt;)<bt>Then they arrived at a place, named Golgota. (In the Aram language, it's meaning says, &lt;&lt;Head bone place.&gt;&gt;)</bt><v n="34" />Di situ dong mau kasi Yesus minum anggor yang su campor deng obat yang pait, ko biar Dia bisa tahan saki. Yesus rasa sadiki ma, ais Dia tola buang.<bt>There they want to give Him to drink wine which was mixed with medicine, so that He could endure pain. Yesus tasted a bit, but then He refused it. [EXEG: Because gall isn't known to reduce pain, some commentators think the term refers to a generic class of bitter medicines. See LN. NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pait"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">pait</Message></Annotation><note reference="27:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:22</note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00324C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Tuhan Yesus di kayu palang<bt>The Lord Yesus on the crossed wood</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais ju dong paku sang Dia di kayu palang. Ju tantara dong hela lot ko mau tau sapa yang dapa Dia pung pakean.<bt>And then they nailed Him on the crossed wood. Then the army guys drew lots to know who would get those clothes of His.</bt><note reference="27:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:19</note><v n="36" />Ais dong dudu jaga sang Dia di situ.<bt>Then they sat and guarded Him there.</bt><v n="37" />Dong ju tulis di satu papan bilang,<bt>They also wrote on a board saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line Centered" usfm="qc">&lt;&lt;INI YESUS, ORANG YAHUDI PUNG RAJA&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;THIS YESUS, [IS] THE JEWISH PEOPLE'S KING&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tarús dong paku itu papan di Dia pung atas kapala, ko kasi tau alasan kanapa ko dong hukum mati sang Dia.<bt>Next they nailed that board above His head, in order to tell the reason why they punished Him with death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Di situ, dong ju paku bekin mati dua orang parampok. Satu di Dia pung sablá kanan; satu di Dia pung sablá kiri.<bt>There they also nailed killing two robbers. One on His right side; one on His left side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Samua orang yang jalan lewat situ, lia sang Dia. Ju dong bekin babengko mulu ko olok sang Dia.<bt>All the people who walked by there, saw Him. And they twisted their mouths to mock embarrasing Him.</bt><note reference="27:39" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Yahudi pung biasa, andia, goyang dong pung kapala ko jadi tanda dong ada olok orang.<bt>Yahudi people had a custom to shake their heads as a sign that they were mocking someone.</bt></note><note reference="27:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:8, 109:25</note><v n="40" />Dong eki-eki sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi! Lu bilang Lu bisa kasi rubu Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ais kasi bangun ulang dalam tempo tiga hari, to? Kalo Lu batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana, na, coba Lu kasi lapás Lu pung diri ko turun dari itu kayu palang su.&gt;&gt;<bt>They yelled out at Him saying, &lt;&lt;Hoi! [+sceptical] You say You can knock over God's Main Prayer House, then build it again in the time of three days, right? If You are really God's Child, then You try and free Yourself in order to get down from that wood.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="27:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:61, Yohanis 2:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Bagitu ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, guru agama, deng tua-tua adat iko olok-olok sang Dia bilang,<bt>Like that also the *chief priests, teachers of religion, and the traditional elders ridiculed Him saying,</bt><v n="42" />&lt;&lt;Dia su kasi salamat orang laen, ma Dia sonde bisa kasi salamat Dia pung diri sandiri, ó. Dia bilang, Dia tu orang Isra'el pung Raja! Kalo bagitu, na, lebe bae Dia turun memang dari itu kayu palang. Kalo kotong lia bagitu, baru kotong parcaya sang Dia.<bt>&lt;&lt;He has saved other people, but He can save His own self. He said that, He was Israel people's King! If that's the case, na, it's better He gets down straight away from that wood. If we see like that, then we will believe Him.</bt><v n="43" />Kalo Dia batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana, biar ko<bt>If He is really God's Child, allow that</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dia baharap sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>&lt;He hopes in God</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jadi, kalo Tuhan suka sang Dia,<bt>So (consequently), if the Lord likes Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">biar ko Tuhan yang kasi salamat sang Dia.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>let it be the Lord who saves Him.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="27:43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Itu parampok dua orang tu, ju iko ba'olok sang Dia bagitu.<bt>Those two robbers, also went along mocking Him like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung mati<bt>The Lord Yesus' death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 15:33-41; Lukas 23:44-49; Yohanis 19:28-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ais itu, galáp gulita tutu ame itu tampa dari tenga hari sampe jam tiga sore.<bt>After that, pitch blackness covered over that place from mid day until three oclock in the afternoon.</bt><v n="46" />Pas jam tiga sore, ju Yesus batarea pake bahasa Aram bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Eli! Eli! Lema sabaktani?&gt;&gt;</span> (Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung Tuhan! Beta pung Allah, é! Akurang ko Bapa bale balakang kasi tenga sang Beta bagini?&gt;&gt;)<bt>Exactly at three in the afternoon, then Yesus yelled out using Aram language saying, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Eli! Eli! Lema sabaktani?&gt;&gt;</span> (It means &lt;&lt;My Lord! My God! Why has Father turned [his] back abandoning Me like this?&gt;&gt;) [NOTE to daughter translations: Aramaic form here different than in Mark.]</bt><note reference="27:46" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Ada barapa orang deka-deka di situ dengar Dia pung suara tu. Ju dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi! Bosong dengar dolo. Dia ada pange sang Elia, Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Several people near there heard that voice of His. Then they said, &lt;&lt;Hoi! [+sceptical] You-pl listen! His is calling Elia, that *spokesperson of God's from long ago!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="48" />Ais satu orang lari-lari pi ame lumut ko calóp maso pi dalam anggor asam. Ju dia tusu itu lumut deng ujung tongkat, tarús sorong pi Yesus pung bibir ko Dia isap.<bt>Then a person ran to get moss to dip into sour wine. The he stabbed that moss with the end of a staff/stick, next [he] extended it to Yesus' lips for Him to suck. [NOTE to daughter translations: if your lg has a word for sponge that people know, use it. Gk only has “put on stick”, so poked or tied both work.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="27:48" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ma ada orang laen lai yang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tunggu dolo ko kotong lia coba, Elia mau datang kasi salamat sang Dia, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>But there who other people who spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Let's wait and see if Elia comes to save Him, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ais Yesus batarea ulang lai deng suara karás, ju Dia mati.<bt>Then Yesus yelled once again with a loud voice, then He died. [EXEG: None of the Evangelists uses any of the usual ways of saying that Jesus died, and this may be part of the way they bring out the truth that there was something in his death that set it apart from all other deaths. There appears to be an element of voluntariness (cf. Chrysostom, Morris, TRT, etc.) Have you considered this? A: Yes. See CEV, TH, TRT. Complication around here is that the Muslims continue to promote the 2nd century heresy that Jesus didn't really die. Unfortunately the euphemism permits that argument to continue. There is no question in the commentaries or the early church fathers that the meaning here is that Jesus died. Note that we've actually preserved using a euphemism here, but moved it to vs.51. That way we make it clear what happened, but still reflect the style. In Kupang the rendering of the euphemism in vs. 51 allows a reading of either Jesus as agent or as experiencer, albeit the default reading would be the latter.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ada satu gorden bésar tagantong ko pele Tuhan Allah pung Kamar Paling Barisi. Parsís Yesus pung putus napas, ju itu gorden tarobe putus bagi dua, dari atas sampe bawa. Ju tana tagoyang, sampe batu bésar tabalá.<bt>In the Main Prayer House, there was a big curtain hanging in order to block God's Holy Room. Exactly at Yesus' stopping of breath (=death), then that curtain ripped severing in two, from the top to the bottom. Then the earth quaked, until big rocks split open.</bt><note reference="27:51" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 26:31-33</note><v n="52" />Kubur-kubur dong ju tabuka. Deng Tuhan Allah pung orang yang su mati, ada yang Dia kasi idop kambali.<bt>Graves also opened. And God's people who had died, there were some whom He made live again.</bt><v n="53" />Waktu Yesus su idop kambali, ju dong kaluar datang dari kuburan, ais maso pi Yerusalem. Banya orang dapa lia sang dong di situ.<bt>When Yesus had lived again, they came out of the graves, and then came into Yerusalem. Many people saw them there. [EXEG: After his res, they came out; order of events; CEV rendering of Gk participle complicates other passages; follow NRSV, NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong kaluar datang dari dong pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">Dong kaluar datang dari dong pung kubur-kubur. Ais waktu Yesus su idop kambali, dong maso pi Yerusalem. Di situ orang banya dapa lia sang dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Di Golgota, ada komandán deng dia pung ana bua yang jaga Yesus di kayu palang. Waktu dong lia bumi tagoyang, deng samua hal yang su jadi tu, ju dong taku mau mati. Dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ini Orang ni, memang batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana!&gt;&gt;<bt>At Golgota, there was an army commander and his underlings who guarded Yesus' crossed wood. When they saw the earth quake, and all the things which had happened there, then they became very afraid. They spoke to each other saying, &lt;&lt;Awii! [+impressed] This Person here, really truly was God's Child!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Di situ ju ada mama barapa orang, yang iko lia Dia pung mati dari jao. Dong su iko sang Dia dari Galilea, te dong yang layani sang Dia dari dolu.<bt>At that place also there were several women, who followed watching His death from far. The had followed Him from Galilea, cuz (elaboration) they had served Him from before. [NOTE to daughter translations: KM works for KM, but these women mentioned below may not all be married, so don't force ‘ina’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Dari itu mama dong, ada Maria dari kampong Magdala, Maria yang satu lai (andia Yakobis deng Yusuf pung mama), deng Sabadeus pung maitua (andia Yakobis deng Yohanis pung mama).<bt>From [among] those women there was Maria from Magdala village, another Maria (who was Yakobis and Yusuf's mama), and Sabadius' wife (that is, Yakobis and Yohanis' mother).</bt><note reference="27:55-56" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 8:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong kubur sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They bury the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 15:42-47; Lukas 23:50-56; Yohanis 19:38-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Di situ ada satu orang kaya dari kampong Arimatea, nama Yusuf. Dia su lama iko Yesus pung ajaran. Naa, Yesus pung mati tu, jato kaná deng hari Jumat. Dia pung beso kaná deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari sambayang. Andia ko waktu matahari mau tanggalám, ju Yusuf cari jalan ko mau kasi turun memang Yesus pung mayat dari itu kayu palang.<bt>There, there was a rich man from the village of Arimatea, named Yusuf. He had followed/obeyed Yesus' teaching/s for a long time. Naa, [+shift] Yesus' death was on a Friday. The next day was the Jewish people's prayer/worship day. That's why when the sun was about to go down, Yusuf was looking for a way to take down straight away Yesus' corpse from that *cross. [EXEG: vs.57-58; For timeframe, see NLT, and discussion in Carson &amp; Morris.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus pung mati tu, pas deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">Yesus pung mati tu, pas deng hari Jumat. Dia pung beso kaná deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari sambayang. Andia ko itu hari Jumat ju, ada satu orang cari jalan ko mau kasi turun memang Yesus pung mayat dari kayu palang tu. (Itu orang pung nama Yusuf. Dia tu, orang kaya dari kampong Arimatea yang su lama iko Yesus pung ajaran.)</Message></Annotation><v n="58" />Ais dia pi gubernor Pilatus, ko minta Yesus pung mayat. Ais gubernor parenta ko dong sarakan itu mayat sang Yusuf.<bt>So/then he went to governor Pilatus, to request Yesus' corpse. Then the governor ordered for them to hand over that corpse to him.</bt><v n="59" />Tarús Yusuf pi Golgota. Ju dia kasi turun Yesus pung mayat dari kayu palang tu. Ju dia bungkus bae-bae itu mayat deng kaen baru yang mahal.<bt>Then Yusuf went to Golgota. Then he took down Yesus' corpse from that crossed wood. Then he wrapped that corpse up well with new cloth that was expensive.</bt><v n="60" />Itu waktu, orang baru pahat abis satu lobang di gunung batu, ko sadia memang kubur kasi Yusuf deng dia pung kelu dong kalo dong mati. Jadi Yusuf dong koko kasi maso Yesus pung mayat ko pi taro dalam itu lobang. Tarús dong guling ame satu batu bésar, ko dong tutu bae-bae itu lobang. Ais itu, Yusuf dong pulang.<bt>At that time, people had just finished chiselling a hole in a rock mountain/hill, to prepare beforehand a grave for Yusuf and his family should they die. So (consequently), Yusuf them carried entered Yesus' corpse into that grave. Next, they rolled a big stone, to close/cover that hole well. After that, Yusuf (collective) went home.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />Itu waktu, Maria dari Magdala deng Maria yang laen tu, ju iko sampe di situ. Dong dudu-dudu mangada pi itu lobang.<bt>At that time, Maria from Magdala and that other Maria, also followed to that place. They kept just sitting facing that hole.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gubernor suru orang ko dong jaga di tampa kubur Tuhan Yesus pung mayat<bt>The governor tells people to guard the place where they placed the Lord Yesus' corpse</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="62" />Dia pung beso, kaná deng orang Yahudi pung hari barenti karjá. Ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos deng orang Farisi dong pi mangada sang gubernor.<bt>The next day, was the Jewish people's day of stopping work. Then the chief priests and Farisi people went to report to the governor.</bt><v n="63" />Dong kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak gub, botong inga waktu itu tukang tipu masi idop, dia ada parná bilang bagini: &lt;Beta memang mati, ma lewat tiga hari ju, Beta idop kambali.&gt;<bt>They told saying, &lt;&lt;Mr. governor [short form], we-exc remember when then habitual deciever was still alive, he once said like this: &lt;I will really die, but after three days, then I will live again.&gt;</bt><note reference="27:63" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:21, 17:23, 20:19, Markus 8:31, 9:31, 10:33-34, Lukas 9:22, 18:31-33</note><v n="64" />Tagal itu, pak tolong suru tantara dong ko jaga bae-bae itu kubur sampe dia pung tiga hari. Deng bagitu, Dia pung ana bua dong sonde bisa mancuri ame Dia pung mayat, ko tipu orang bilang, Dia su idop kambali. Te kalo dong tipu bagitu, itu su lebe jahat dari dong pung tipu dolo tu, waktu dong bilang Dia tu, andia Kristus.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, sir (=you) please order army guys to carefully guard that grave for three days. With that, His underlings won't be able to steal His corpse, to decieve people saying He has lived again. Cuz (elaboration) if they decieve like that, that's even more evil that their earlier deceptions, when they said He was Kristus.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="65" />Dengar bagitu, ju gubernor manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bae ju! Ma bosong ada pung orang jaga sandiri. Lebe bae pake sang dong sa, ko pi jaga bae-bae itu tampa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, then the governor replied saying, &lt;&lt;Ok! But you have your own guard people. It's better to just use them, to go carefully guard that place.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk. lit. “you have a guard”. Note Carson &amp; Morris have conflicting views on the interpretation of this verse (whose guard is it?); this has support from Carson, NLT, etc. TB goes the other way. But this way also makes better sense of 28:15. Carson-Matthew commentary (&amp; others focusing on the resurrection) discuss this extensively. A careful reading of 28:11-15 indicates: they reported to the chief priests, they were worried <span class="Italic">about the possibility</span> of Pilate's reaction, the chief priests said they would handle that if it occurred, they accepted payment from the chief priests. If they were Roman soldiers, then this passage is all wrong. Temple guards would report to the chief priests; Roman soldiers wouldn't normally. Commentators have noted the harsh penalties (death) afforded Roman soldiers who went to sleep or let prisoners escape. Roman soldiers would have been more likely to be worried about military discipline from their superiors (severe punishment or death), and less worried about political backlash and punishment from the governor. So I find Carson more convincing than Morris on this. GMIT ministers were involved in choosing to not follow the TB here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="66" />Ais dong pi di itu tampa, deng bawa dong pung orang jaga. Sampe di situ, dong segel mati itu batu di kubur pung pintu.<bt>Then they went to that place, and brought their guards. Arriving there, they completely sealed that grave's door.</bt><note reference="27:66" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ahli dong bilang, dong segel deng cara taro satu banáng di batu deng dinding lobang, pake lak kuliling itu batu.<bt>The experts say, they sealed by means of placing a thread on the rock and walls of the hole, using wax around that rock.</bt></note>Ju dong suru itu orang ko jaga tarús itu tampa, ko orang laen jang datang ame itu mayat.<bt>And they ordered that/those people to keep guarding that place, so that other people didn't come take that corpse.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cap lak = wax seal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">cap lak = wax seal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus idop kambali!<bt>The Lord Yesus lives again!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 16:1-10; Lukas 24:1-12; Yohanis 20:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="28" />
      <v n="1" />Ais hari Minggu papagi, ju Maria dari Magdala deng Maria yang laen tu, pi lia itu tampa kubur.<bt>Then early Sunday morning, Maria from Magdala and that other Maria went to see that burial place.</bt><v n="2" />Takuju sa, bumi tagoyang hebat. Tuhan Allah pung ana bua satu dari sorga turun datang, ju dia pi guling buang itu batu bésar yang ada tutu itu lobang. Ais ju dia dudu di itu batu pung atas.<bt>Suddenly there was a big earthquake. One of God's underlings from heaven came down, and he went rolling away that big stone which was closing that hole. Afterwards then he sat on that stone.</bt><v n="3" />Itu ana bua pung muka basinar sama ke kilat, deng dia pung pakean puti barisi.<bt>That underling's face shone like lightening, and his clothes were pure white.</bt><v n="4" />Itu orang jaga dong taku mau mati, sampe gamatar dingin, deng dong sonde bisa bagarak tingka ke orang mati.<bt>Those guards were terrified to the point that they trembled, and were unable to move like they were dead people. [EXEG: Both Carson &amp; Morris talk about “soldiers were made helpless” “paralysed”, others “incapacitated” which also fits the higher level context better than ‘pale’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng dong pung muka pucat tingka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">deng dong pung muka pucat tingka ke orang mati.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ju itu ana bua dari sorga tu, kasi tau sang itu mama dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde usa taku! Beta tau bosong datang cari sang Yesus, itu Orang yang dong paku bekin mati di kayu palang tu.<bt>Then that underling from heave told those women saying, &lt;&lt;You don't need to be afraid! I know you come to find Yesus, that Person whom they nailed killed on that crossed wood.</bt><v n="6" />Ma Dia su sonde ada di sini lai. Te Dia su idop kambali, sama ke Dia su omong memang tu. Mari maso ko lia sandiri itu tampa yang dong taro Dia pung mayat. Itu tampa su kosong!<bt>But He is not here anymore. Cuz (elaboration) he has lived again like he spoke about beforehand. Come in and see for yourselves that place where they put His corpse. That place is empty!</bt><v n="7" />Naa, sakarang bosong pulang capát-capát su! Pi kasi tau sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, Yesus su idop kambali. Dia su jalan lebe dolo pi Galilea. Dong musti pi katumu deng Dia di sana, sama ke dolu Dia su janji memang sang dong. Parcaya sa. Pulang su ko kasi tau apa yang beta omong ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, [+shift] now you must go home fast. Go tell his underlings saying, Yesus lives again. He ahs gone on ahead to Galilea. They must go meet Him there, like He previously promised ahead of time with them. Just believe. Go home and tell what I have spoken here!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ju itu mama dong lari kaluar kasi tenga itu tampa. Dong rasa taku, ma dong ju ada rasa sanáng. Dong pulang capát-capát ko lapor itu hal samua sang Dia pung ana bua dong.<bt>Then those women ran leaving that place. They felt afraid but they also felt happy. They went home quickly to report that all those things to His underlings.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma sampe di tenga jalan, takuju sa Yesus datang katumu sang dong. Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Saloom!&gt;&gt; Lia bagitu, ju dong datang deka-deka ko paló Dia pung kaki, deng sémba sang Dia.<bt>But in the middle of the road, unexpectedly Yesus came and met them. He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Peace!&gt;&gt; Seeing like that they came close to embrace his feet and worship Him.</bt><v n="10" />Ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang taku, é! Pi kasi tau Beta pung ana bua dong, ko dong pi tunggu sang Beta di Galilea.&gt;&gt;<bt>The He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Don't be afraid! Go tell My underlings for them to go wait for Me in Galilea.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: an earlier UNS check had the literal “see” saying it implied looking but not talking/meeting. I'm a bit sceptical, given the range of uses of “seeing” verbs in these lgs. But several UNSs suggested “meet” (which we have in vs.7). Then stylistically they don't like repetition in close proximity, and the RL preference is “wait for” rather than “see”. Most are in agreement that “see” here is not restricted to its primary sense. TRT see/meet. One sense of the Gk word includes ‘visit’ (LN).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang jaga dong pi lapor so'al apa yang su jadi di tampa kubur Tuhan Yesus pung mayat<bt>The guards go report about what happened at the place where they put the Lord Yesus' corpse</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Waktu itu mama dong masi di tenga jalan, ju itu orang jaga dong kambali pi kota. Dong pi lapor di kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, samua hal yang su jadi tu.<bt>When those women were still in the middle of the road (=halfway home), then those guards returned to the city. They went to report to the chief priests, all the things which had happened there.</bt><v n="12" />Ju itu bos-bos ator siasat deng tua-tua adat dong, ko tempel doi bam-banya di itu orang jaga dong, ko tutu dong pung mulu.<bt>Then those bosses strategised/plotted with the traditional elders, to stick/put/patch alot of money to close those guards mouths.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) fixed repeated phrase"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">*** (2009) fixed repeated phrase</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko tempel doi bam-banya, ko tutu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:38:52Z">ko tempel doi bam-banya, ko tutu itu orang jaga dong pung mulu.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Itu bos dong kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini. Kalo orang tanya, na, bosong musti manyao bilang, malam-malam bosong ada tidor sonu. Tau-tau, te Dia pung ana bua dong datang mancuri ame Dia pung mayat.<bt>Those bosses told saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this. If people/someone asks, na, you must reply saying, at night you were sleeping soundly. Apparently/ evidently His underlings came and stole away His corpse.</bt><v n="14" />Deng kalo pak gub dengar itu hal, na, bosong jang taku, te nanti botong yang ator sang bapatua.&gt;&gt;<bt>And if Mr governor hears this matter, then you don't worry, cuz (elaboration) later we'll be the ones who manage elderfather (=him).&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ju itu orang jaga dong ame itu doi. Dong bekin iko itu bos-bos dong pung mau. Andia ko sampe sakarang orang Yahudi dong masi parcaya itu carita putar-balek tu.<bt>Then those guards took that money. They did according to those bosses will. That's why until now Jewish people still believe that twisted/decietful story.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pi katumu deng Dia pung ana bua dong<bt>The Lord Yesus goes and shows his face to His underlings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Markus 16:14-18; Lukas 24:36-49; Yohanis 20:19-23; Utusan dong pung Carita 1:6-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Dengar abis itu mama-mama dong pung laporan, ju Yesus pung ana bua sablás orang tu, pi propinsi Galilea ko katumu deng Dia di satu gunung, iko Dia pung janji.<bt>After hearing those women's reports, then those eleven underlings of Jesus, went to Galilea province to meet with Him at a mountain, according to that promise of His.</bt><note reference="28:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:32, Markus 14:28</note><v n="17" />Waktu dong lia sang Dia di sana, ju dong sémba sang Dia. Biar bagitu, ma masi ada yang pung hati bacabang.<bt>When they saw Him there, then they worshiped Him. Even though it was like that, nevertheless there were still some who had forked livers (doubted).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ju Dia datang deka-deka sang dong, ais omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah su kasi Beta kuasa, ko Beta parenta samua yang ada di sorga, deng samua yang ada di dunya.<bt>Then He came close to them and spoke saying, &lt;&lt;God has given Me power, for Me to rule everything which is in heaven, and everything which is on earth.</bt><v n="19" />Jadi bosong pi mana-mana, na, bosong musti kasi tau samua suku-bangsa Beta pung Carita Bae. Bosong musti ajar bae-bae sang dong ko biar dong jadi Beta pung ana bua. Deng bosong musti sarani sang dong ko jadi tanda bilang, dong su ta'ika deng Bapa, deng Dia pung Ana, deng Dia pung Roh yang Barisi.<bt>So/consequently, wherever you go, na, you-pl must tell all people-nations My Good Story. You must teach them well so that they become My people. And you must baptise them as a sign saying they are tied together with Father, and His Child, and His Spirit who is Clean/Holy. [EXEG: “So (consequently), as you go wherever (=anywhere you go at anytime), you-pl must tell” Why this wording instead of “go everywhere”? A: Gk grammar. The imperative here is “make disciples”, supported by the participial clauses introduced by “baptizing” and “teaching”. The “go” verb is not imperative, but rather a participle. TH notes this over-all grammatical structure, but doesn't discuss the implications of it. The “go” as a participle, AGNT glosses “having gone”, Hendricks “as you are going”, and many other similar renderings such as “as you go” in the literature. The grammatical note in TW that this participle is “(imperative sense)” appears to be reading something into it from the traditional (KJV) rendering as an imperative, and is at odds with the more supportable grammatical note that this is a “passive deponent”. Morris more convincingly says the imperative reading on the participle “go” is by extension from sharing the imperative of the main verb “make disciples”. Morris also points out the main point of “going” is implying a contrast with “not going” (which is not an option). Discussing the above issue with the MTTs and UNSs, they say this 1) implies an assumption that you are or should be going, and 2) says that “making disciples” should be part and parcel of what you do as you are going. This seems to be what is intended by the Greek grammar.]</bt><note reference="28:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 1:8</note><v n="20" />Deng ajar sang dong ko bekin iko samua parenta yang Beta su kasi tau sang bosong. Inga, é! Beta ada tarús-tarús di bosong pung teng-tenga, sampe ini dunya kiamat.&gt;&gt;<bt>And teach them to do according to all the commands which I told you. Remember, é! I am continually in your midst, until the world ends.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>